        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>INTRODUCTION BY MRS FORSTER-NIETZSCHE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>HOW ZARATHUSTRA CAME INTO BEING.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Zarathustra” is my brother’s most personal work; it is the history of his most individual experiences, of his friendships, ideals, raptures, bitterest disappointments and sorrows. Above it all, however, there soars, transfiguring it, the image of his greatest hopes and remotest aims. My brother had the figure of Zarathustra in his mind from his very earliest youth: he once told me that even as a child he had dreamt of him. At different periods in his life, he would call this haunter of his dreams by different names; “but in the end,” he declares in a note on the subject, “I had to do a PERSIAN the honour of identifying him with this creature of my fancy. Persians were the first to take a broad and comprehensive view of history. Every series of evolutions, according to them, was presided over by a prophet; and every prophet had his ‘Hazar,’—his dynasty of a thousand years.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All Zarathustra’s views, as also his personality, were early conceptions of my brother’s mind. Whoever reads his posthumously published writings for the years 1869-82 with care, will constantly meet with passages suggestive of Zarathustra’s thoughts and doctrines. For instance, the ideal of the Superman is put forth quite clearly in all his writings during the years 1873-75; and in “We Philologists”, the following remarkable observations occur:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“How can one praise and glorify a nation as a whole?—Even among the Greeks, it was the INDIVIDUALS that counted.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The Greeks are interesting and extremely important because they reared such a vast number of great individuals. How was this possible? The question is one which ought to be studied.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I am interested only in the relations of a people to the rearing of the individual man, and among the Greeks the conditions were unusually favourable for the development of the individual; not by any means owing to the goodness of the people, but because of the struggles of their evil instincts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“WITH THE HELP OF FAVOURABLE MEASURES GREAT INDIVIDUALS MIGHT BE REARED WHO WOULD BE BOTH DIFFERENT FROM AND HIGHER THAN THOSE WHO HERETOFORE HAVE OWED THEIR EXISTENCE TO MERE CHANCE. Here we may still be hopeful: in the rearing of exceptional men.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The notion of rearing the Superman is only a new form of an ideal Nietzsche already had in his youth, that “THE OBJECT OF MANKIND SHOULD LIE IN ITS HIGHEST INDIVIDUALS” (or, as he writes in “Schopenhauer as Educator”: “Mankind ought constantly to be striving to produce great men—this and nothing else is its duty.”) But the ideals he most revered in those days are no longer held to be the highest types of men. No, around this future ideal of a coming humanity—the Superman—the poet spread the veil of becoming. Who can tell to what glorious heights man can still ascend? That is why, after having tested the worth of our noblest ideal—that of the Saviour, in the light of the new valuations, the poet cries with passionate emphasis in “Zarathustra”:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Never yet hath there been a Superman. Naked have I seen both of them, the greatest and the smallest man:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All-too-similar are they still to each other. Verily even the greatest found I—all-too-human!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The phrase “the rearing of the Superman,” has very often been misunderstood. By the word “rearing,” in this case, is meant the act of modifying by means of new and higher values—values which, as laws and guides of conduct and opinion, are now to rule over mankind. In general the doctrine of the Superman can only be understood correctly in conjunction with other ideas of the author’s, such as:—the Order of Rank, the Will to Power, and the Transvaluation of all Values. He assumes that Christianity, as a product of the resentment of the botched and the weak, has put in ban all that is beautiful, strong, proud, and powerful, in fact all the qualities resulting from strength, and that, in consequence, all forces which tend to promote or elevate life have been seriously undermined. Now, however, a new table of valuations must be placed over mankind—namely, that of the strong, mighty, and magnificent man, overflowing with life and elevated to his zenith—the Superman, who is now put before us with overpowering passion as the aim of our life, hope, and will. And just as the old system of valuing, which only extolled the qualities favourable to the weak, the suffering, and the oppressed, has succeeded in producing a weak, suffering, and “modern” race, so this new and reversed system of valuing ought to rear a healthy, strong, lively, and courageous type, which would be a glory to life itself. Stated briefly, the leading principle of this new system of valuing would be: “All that proceeds from power is good, all that springs from weakness is bad.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This type must not be regarded as a fanciful figure: it is not a nebulous hope which is to be realised at some indefinitely remote period, thousands of years hence; nor is it a new species (in the Darwinian sense) of which we can know nothing, and which it would therefore be somewhat absurd to strive after. But it is meant to be a possibility which men of the present could realise with all their spiritual and physical energies, provided they adopted the new values.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The author of “Zarathustra” never lost sight of that egregious example of a transvaluation of all values through Christianity, whereby the whole of the deified mode of life and thought of the Greeks, as well as strong Romedom, was almost annihilated or transvalued in a comparatively short time. Could not a rejuvenated Graeco-Roman system of valuing (once it had been refined and made more profound by the schooling which two thousand years of Christianity had provided) effect another such revolution within a calculable period of time, until that glorious type of manhood shall finally appear which is to be our new faith and hope, and in the creation of which Zarathustra exhorts us to participate?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In his private notes on the subject the author uses the expression “Superman” (always in the singular, by-the-bye), as signifying “the most thoroughly well-constituted type,” as opposed to “modern man”; above all, however, he designates Zarathustra himself as an example of the Superman. In “Ecco Homo” he is careful to enlighten us concerning the precursors and prerequisites to the advent of this highest type, in referring to a certain passage in the “Gay Science”:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“In order to understand this type, we must first be quite clear in regard to the leading physiological condition on which it depends: this condition is what I call GREAT HEALTHINESS. I know not how to express my meaning more plainly or more personally than I have done already in one of the last chapters (Aphorism 382) of the fifth book of the ‘Gaya Scienza’.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“We, the new, the nameless, the hard-to-understand,”—it says there,—“we firstlings of a yet untried future—we require for a new end also a new means, namely, a new healthiness, stronger, sharper, tougher, bolder and merrier than all healthiness hitherto. He whose soul longeth to experience the whole range of hitherto recognised values and desirabilities, and to circumnavigate all the coasts of this ideal ‘Mediterranean Sea’, who, from the adventures of his most personal experience, wants to know how it feels to be a conqueror, and discoverer of the ideal—as likewise how it is with the artist, the saint, the legislator, the sage, the scholar, the devotee, the prophet, and the godly non-conformist of the old style:—requires one thing above all for that purpose, GREAT HEALTHINESS—such healthiness as one not only possesses, but also constantly acquires and must acquire, because one unceasingly sacrifices it again, and must sacrifice it!—And now, after having been long on the way in this fashion, we Argonauts of the ideal, more courageous perhaps than prudent, and often enough shipwrecked and brought to grief, nevertheless dangerously healthy, always healthy again,—it would seem as if, in recompense for it all, that we have a still undiscovered country before us, the boundaries of which no one has yet seen, a beyond to all countries and corners of the ideal known hitherto, a world so over-rich in the beautiful, the strange, the questionable, the frightful, and the divine, that our curiosity as well as our thirst for possession thereof, have got out of hand—alas! that nothing will now any longer satisfy us!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“How could we still be content with THE MAN OF THE PRESENT DAY after such outlooks, and with such a craving in our conscience and consciousness? Sad enough; but it is unavoidable that we should look on the worthiest aims and hopes of the man of the present day with ill-concealed amusement, and perhaps should no longer look at them. Another ideal runs on before us, a strange, tempting ideal full of danger, to which we should not like to persuade any one, because we do not so readily acknowledge any one’s RIGHT THERETO: the ideal of a spirit who plays naively (that is to say involuntarily and from overflowing abundance and power) with everything that has hitherto been called holy, good, intangible, or divine; to whom the loftiest conception which the people have reasonably made their measure of value, would already practically imply danger, ruin, abasement, or at least relaxation, blindness, or temporary self-forgetfulness; the ideal of a humanly superhuman welfare and benevolence, which will often enough appear INHUMAN, for example, when put alongside of all past seriousness on earth, and alongside of all past solemnities in bearing, word, tone, look, morality, and pursuit, as their truest involuntary parody—and WITH which, nevertheless, perhaps THE GREAT SERIOUSNESS only commences, when the proper interrogative mark is set up, the fate of the soul changes, the hour-hand moves, and tragedy begins...”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Although the figure of Zarathustra and a large number of the leading thoughts in this work had appeared much earlier in the dreams and writings of the author, “Thus Spake Zarathustra” did not actually come into being until the month of August 1881 in Sils Maria; and it was the idea of the Eternal Recurrence of all things which finally induced my brother to set forth his new views in poetic language. In regard to his first conception of this idea, his autobiographical sketch, “Ecce Homo”, written in the autumn of 1888, contains the following passage:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The fundamental idea of my work—namely, the Eternal Recurrence of all things—this highest of all possible formulae of a Yea-saying philosophy, first occurred to me in August 1881. I made a note of the thought on a sheet of paper, with the postscript: 6,000 feet beyond men and time! That day I happened to be wandering through the woods alongside of the lake of Silvaplana, and I halted beside a huge, pyramidal and towering rock not far from Surlei. It was then that the thought struck me. Looking back now, I find that exactly two months previous to this inspiration, I had had an omen of its coming in the form of a sudden and decisive alteration in my tastes—more particularly in music. It would even be possible to consider all ‘Zarathustra’ as a musical composition. At all events, a very necessary condition in its production was a renaissance in myself of the art of hearing. In a small mountain resort (Recoaro) near Vicenza, where I spent the spring of 1881, I and my friend and Maestro, Peter Gast—also one who had been born again—discovered that the phoenix music that hovered over us, wore lighter and brighter plumes than it had done theretofore.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>During the month of August 1881 my brother resolved to reveal the teaching of the Eternal Recurrence, in dithyrambic and psalmodic form, through the mouth of Zarathustra. Among the notes of this period, we found a page on which is written the first definite plan of “Thus Spake Zarathustra”:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“MIDDAY AND ETERNITY.” “GUIDE-POSTS TO A NEW WAY OF LIVING.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beneath this is written:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Zarathustra born on lake Urmi; left his home in his thirtieth year, went into the province of Aria, and, during ten years of solitude in the mountains, composed the Zend-Avesta.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The sun of knowledge stands once more at midday; and the serpent of eternity lies coiled in its light—: It is YOUR time, ye midday brethren.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In that summer of 1881, my brother, after many years of steadily declining health, began at last to rally, and it is to this first gush of the recovery of his once splendid bodily condition that we owe not only “The Gay Science”, which in its mood may be regarded as a prelude to “Zarathustra”, but also “Zarathustra” itself. Just as he was beginning to recuperate his health, however, an unkind destiny brought him a number of most painful personal experiences. His friends caused him many disappointments, which were the more bitter to him, inasmuch as he regarded friendship as such a sacred institution; and for the first time in his life he realised the whole horror of that loneliness to which, perhaps, all greatness is condemned. But to be forsaken is something very different from deliberately choosing blessed loneliness. How he longed, in those days, for the ideal friend who would thoroughly understand him, to whom he would be able to say all, and whom he imagined he had found at various periods in his life from his earliest youth onwards. Now, however, that the way he had chosen grew ever more perilous and steep, he found nobody who could follow him: he therefore created a perfect friend for himself in the ideal form of a majestic philosopher, and made this creation the preacher of his gospel to the world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whether my brother would ever have written “Thus Spake Zarathustra” according to the first plan sketched in the summer of 1881, if he had not had the disappointments already referred to, is now an idle question; but perhaps where “Zarathustra” is concerned, we may also say with Master Eckhardt: “The fleetest beast to bear you to perfection is suffering.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brother writes as follows about the origin of the first part of “Zarathustra”:—“In the winter of 1882-83, I was living on the charming little Gulf of Rapallo, not far from Genoa, and between Chiavari and Cape Porto Fino. My health was not very good; the winter was cold and exceptionally rainy; and the small inn in which I lived was so close to the water that at night my sleep would be disturbed if the sea were high. These circumstances were surely the very reverse of favourable; and yet in spite of it all, and as if in demonstration of my belief that everything decisive comes to life in spite of every obstacle, it was precisely during this winter and in the midst of these unfavourable circumstances that my ‘Zarathustra’ originated. In the morning I used to start out in a southerly direction up the glorious road to Zoagli, which rises aloft through a forest of pines and gives one a view far out into the sea. In the afternoon, as often as my health permitted, I walked round the whole bay from Santa Margherita to beyond Porto Fino. This spot was all the more interesting to me, inasmuch as it was so dearly loved by the Emperor Frederick III. In the autumn of 1886 I chanced to be there again when he was revisiting this small, forgotten world of happiness for the last time. It was on these two roads that all ‘Zarathustra’ came to me, above all Zarathustra himself as a type;—I ought rather to say that it was on these walks that these ideas waylaid me.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The first part of “Zarathustra” was written in about ten days—that is to say, from the beginning to about the middle of February 1883. “The last lines were written precisely in the hallowed hour when Richard Wagner gave up the ghost in Venice.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the exception of the ten days occupied in composing the first part of this book, my brother often referred to this winter as the hardest and sickliest he had ever experienced. He did not, however, mean thereby that his former disorders were troubling him, but that he was suffering from a severe attack of influenza which he had caught in Santa Margherita, and which tormented him for several weeks after his arrival in Genoa. As a matter of fact, however, what he complained of most was his spiritual condition—that indescribable forsakenness—to which he gives such heartrending expression in “Zarathustra”. Even the reception which the first part met with at the hands of friends and acquaintances was extremely disheartening: for almost all those to whom he presented copies of the work misunderstood it. “I found no one ripe for many of my thoughts; the case of ‘Zarathustra’ proves that one can speak with the utmost clearness, and yet not be heard by any one.” My brother was very much discouraged by the feebleness of the response he was given, and as he was striving just then to give up the practice of taking hydrate of chloral—a drug he had begun to take while ill with influenza,—the following spring, spent in Rome, was a somewhat gloomy one for him. He writes about it as follows:—“I spent a melancholy spring in Rome, where I only just managed to live,—and this was no easy matter. This city, which is absolutely unsuited to the poet-author of ‘Zarathustra’, and for the choice of which I was not responsible, made me inordinately miserable. I tried to leave it. I wanted to go to Aquila—the opposite of Rome in every respect, and actually founded in a spirit of enmity towards that city (just as I also shall found a city some day), as a memento of an atheist and genuine enemy of the Church—a person very closely related to me,—the great Hohenstaufen, the Emperor Frederick II. But Fate lay behind it all: I had to return again to Rome. In the end I was obliged to be satisfied with the Piazza Barberini, after I had exerted myself in vain to find an anti-Christian quarter. I fear that on one occasion, to avoid bad smells as much as possible, I actually inquired at the Palazzo del Quirinale whether they could not provide a quiet room for a philosopher. In a chamber high above the Piazza just mentioned, from which one obtained a general view of Rome and could hear the fountains plashing far below, the loneliest of all songs was composed—‘The Night-Song’. About this time I was obsessed by an unspeakably sad melody, the refrain of which I recognised in the words, ‘dead through immortality.’”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We remained somewhat too long in Rome that spring, and what with the effect of the increasing heat and the discouraging circumstances already described, my brother resolved not to write any more, or in any case, not to proceed with “Zarathustra”, although I offered to relieve him of all trouble in connection with the proofs and the publisher. When, however, we returned to Switzerland towards the end of June, and he found himself once more in the familiar and exhilarating air of the mountains, all his joyous creative powers revived, and in a note to me announcing the dispatch of some manuscript, he wrote as follows: “I have engaged a place here for three months: forsooth, I am the greatest fool to allow my courage to be sapped from me by the climate of Italy. Now and again I am troubled by the thought: WHAT NEXT? My ‘future’ is the darkest thing in the world to me, but as there still remains a great deal for me to do, I suppose I ought rather to think of doing this than of my future, and leave the rest to THEE and the gods.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The second part of “Zarathustra” was written between the 26th of June and the 6th July. “This summer, finding myself once more in the sacred place where the first thought of ‘Zarathustra’ flashed across my mind, I conceived the second part. Ten days sufficed. Neither for the second, the first, nor the third part, have I required a day longer.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He often used to speak of the ecstatic mood in which he wrote “Zarathustra”; how in his walks over hill and dale the ideas would crowd into his mind, and how he would note them down hastily in a note-book from which he would transcribe them on his return, sometimes working till midnight. He says in a letter to me: “You can have no idea of the vehemence of such composition,” and in “Ecce Homo” (autumn 1888) he describes as follows with passionate enthusiasm the incomparable mood in which he created Zarathustra:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“—Has any one at the end of the nineteenth century any distinct notion of what poets of a stronger age understood by the word inspiration? If not, I will describe it. If one had the smallest vestige of superstition in one, it would hardly be possible to set aside completely the idea that one is the mere incarnation, mouthpiece or medium of an almighty power. The idea of revelation in the sense that something becomes suddenly visible and audible with indescribable certainty and accuracy, which profoundly convulses and upsets one—describes simply the matter of fact. One hears—one does not seek; one takes—one does not ask who gives: a thought suddenly flashes up like lightning, it comes with necessity, unhesitatingly—I have never had any choice in the matter. There is an ecstasy such that the immense strain of it is sometimes relaxed by a flood of tears, along with which one’s steps either rush or involuntarily lag, alternately. There is the feeling that one is completely out of hand, with the very distinct consciousness of an endless number of fine thrills and quiverings to the very toes;—there is a depth of happiness in which the painfullest and gloomiest do not operate as antitheses, but as conditioned, as demanded in the sense of necessary shades of colour in such an overflow of light. There is an instinct for rhythmic relations which embraces wide areas of forms (length, the need of a wide-embracing rhythm, is almost the measure of the force of an inspiration, a sort of counterpart to its pressure and tension). Everything happens quite involuntarily, as if in a tempestuous outburst of freedom, of absoluteness, of power and divinity. The involuntariness of the figures and similes is the most remarkable thing; one loses all perception of what constitutes the figure and what constitutes the simile; everything seems to present itself as the readiest, the correctest and the simplest means of expression. It actually seems, to use one of Zarathustra’s own phrases, as if all things came unto one, and would fain be similes: ‘Here do all things come caressingly to thy talk and flatter thee, for they want to ride upon thy back. On every simile dost thou here ride to every truth. Here fly open unto thee all being’s words and word-cabinets; here all being wanteth to become words, here all becoming wanteth to learn of thee how to talk.’ This is MY experience of inspiration. I do not doubt but that one would have to go back thousands of years in order to find some one who could say to me: It is mine also!—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the autumn of 1883 my brother left the Engadine for Germany and stayed there a few weeks. In the following winter, after wandering somewhat erratically through Stresa, Genoa, and Spezia, he landed in Nice, where the climate so happily promoted his creative powers that he wrote the third part of “Zarathustra”. “In the winter, beneath the halcyon sky of Nice, which then looked down upon me for the first time in my life, I found the third ‘Zarathustra’—and came to the end of my task; the whole having occupied me scarcely a year. Many hidden corners and heights in the landscapes round about Nice are hallowed to me by unforgettable moments. That decisive chapter entitled ‘Old and New Tables’ was composed in the very difficult ascent from the station to Eza—that wonderful Moorish village in the rocks. My most creative moments were always accompanied by unusual muscular activity. The body is inspired: let us waive the question of the ‘soul.’ I might often have been seen dancing in those days. Without a suggestion of fatigue I could then walk for seven or eight hours on end among the hills. I slept well and laughed well—I was perfectly robust and patient.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As we have seen, each of the three parts of “Zarathustra” was written, after a more or less short period of preparation, in about ten days. The composition of the fourth part alone was broken by occasional interruptions. The first notes relating to this part were written while he and I were staying together in Zurich in September 1884. In the following November, while staying at Mentone, he began to elaborate these notes, and after a long pause, finished the manuscript at Nice between the end of January and the middle of February 1885. My brother then called this part the fourth and last; but even before, and shortly after it had been privately printed, he wrote to me saying that he still intended writing a fifth and sixth part, and notes relating to these parts are now in my possession. This fourth part (the original MS. of which contains this note: “Only for my friends, not for the public”) is written in a particularly personal spirit, and those few to whom he presented a copy of it, he pledged to the strictest secrecy concerning its contents. He often thought of making this fourth part public also, but doubted whether he would ever be able to do so without considerably altering certain portions of it. At all events he resolved to distribute this manuscript production, of which only forty copies were printed, only among those who had proved themselves worthy of it, and it speaks eloquently of his utter loneliness and need of sympathy in those days, that he had occasion to present only seven copies of his book according to this resolution.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Already at the beginning of this history I hinted at the reasons which led my brother to select a Persian as the incarnation of his ideal of the majestic philosopher. His reasons, however, for choosing Zarathustra of all others to be his mouthpiece, he gives us in the following words:—“People have never asked me, as they should have done, what the name Zarathustra precisely means in my mouth, in the mouth of the first Immoralist; for what distinguishes that philosopher from all others in the past is the very fact that he was exactly the reverse of an immoralist. Zarathustra was the first to see in the struggle between good and evil the essential wheel in the working of things. The translation of morality into the metaphysical, as force, cause, end in itself, was HIS work. But the very question suggests its own answer. Zarathustra CREATED the most portentous error, MORALITY, consequently he should also be the first to PERCEIVE that error, not only because he has had longer and greater experience of the subject than any other thinker—all history is the experimental refutation of the theory of the so-called moral order of things:—the more important point is that Zarathustra was more truthful than any other thinker. In his teaching alone do we meet with truthfulness upheld as the highest virtue—i.e.: the reverse of the COWARDICE of the ‘idealist’ who flees from reality. Zarathustra had more courage in his body than any other thinker before or after him. To tell the truth and TO AIM STRAIGHT: that is the first Persian virtue. Am I understood?... The overcoming of morality through itself—through truthfulness, the overcoming of the moralist through his opposite—THROUGH ME—: that is what the name Zarathustra means in my mouth.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>ELIZABETH FORSTER-NIETZSCHE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche Archives,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Weimar, December 1905.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><br>\n<br>\n<a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>THUS SPAKE ZARATHUSTRA.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>FIRST PART. ZARATHUSTRA’S DISCOURSES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>ZARATHUSTRA’S PROLOGUE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>1.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra was thirty years old, he left his home and the lake of his home, and went into the mountains. There he enjoyed his spirit and solitude, and for ten years did not weary of it. But at last his heart changed,—and rising one morning with the rosy dawn, he went before the sun, and spake thus unto it:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou great star! What would be thy happiness if thou hadst not those for whom thou shinest!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For ten years hast thou climbed hither unto my cave: thou wouldst have wearied of thy light and of the journey, had it not been for me, mine eagle, and my serpent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But we awaited thee every morning, took from thee thine overflow and blessed thee for it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo! I am weary of my wisdom, like the bee that hath gathered too much honey; I need hands outstretched to take it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I would fain bestow and distribute, until the wise have once more become joyous in their folly, and the poor happy in their riches.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore must I descend into the deep: as thou doest in the evening, when thou goest behind the sea, and givest light also to the nether-world, thou exuberant star!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like thee must I GO DOWN, as men say, to whom I shall descend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Bless me, then, thou tranquil eye, that canst behold even the greatest happiness without envy!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Bless the cup that is about to overflow, that the water may flow golden out of it, and carry everywhere the reflection of thy bliss!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo! This cup is again going to empty itself, and Zarathustra is again going to be a man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus began Zarathustra’s down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra went down the mountain alone, no one meeting him. When he entered the forest, however, there suddenly stood before him an old man, who had left his holy cot to seek roots. And thus spake the old man to Zarathustra:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“No stranger to me is this wanderer: many years ago passed he by. Zarathustra he was called; but he hath altered.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then thou carriedst thine ashes into the mountains: wilt thou now carry thy fire into the valleys? Fearest thou not the incendiary’s doom?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, I recognise Zarathustra. Pure is his eye, and no loathing lurketh about his mouth. Goeth he not along like a dancer?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Altered is Zarathustra; a child hath Zarathustra become; an awakened one is Zarathustra: what wilt thou do in the land of the sleepers?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As in the sea hast thou lived in solitude, and it hath borne thee up. Alas, wilt thou now go ashore? Alas, wilt thou again drag thy body thyself?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra answered: “I love mankind.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why,” said the saint, “did I go into the forest and the desert? Was it not because I loved men far too well?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now I love God: men, I do not love. Man is a thing too imperfect for me. Love to man would be fatal to me.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra answered: “What spake I of love! I am bringing gifts unto men.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Give them nothing,” said the saint. “Take rather part of their load, and carry it along with them—that will be most agreeable unto them: if only it be agreeable unto thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If, however, thou wilt give unto them, give them no more than an alms, and let them also beg for it!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“No,” replied Zarathustra, “I give no alms. I am not poor enough for that.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The saint laughed at Zarathustra, and spake thus: “Then see to it that they accept thy treasures! They are distrustful of anchorites, and do not believe that we come with gifts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The fall of our footsteps ringeth too hollow through their streets. And just as at night, when they are in bed and hear a man abroad long before sunrise, so they ask themselves concerning us: Where goeth the thief?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Go not to men, but stay in the forest! Go rather to the animals! Why not be like me—a bear amongst bears, a bird amongst birds?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“And what doeth the saint in the forest?” asked Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The saint answered: “I make hymns and sing them; and in making hymns I laugh and weep and mumble: thus do I praise God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With singing, weeping, laughing, and mumbling do I praise the God who is my God. But what dost thou bring us as a gift?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had heard these words, he bowed to the saint and said: “What should I have to give thee! Let me rather hurry hence lest I take aught away from thee!”—And thus they parted from one another, the old man and Zarathustra, laughing like schoolboys.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra was alone, however, he said to his heart: “Could it be possible! This old saint in the forest hath not yet heard of it, that GOD IS DEAD!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra arrived at the nearest town which adjoineth the forest, he found many people assembled in the market-place; for it had been announced that a rope-dancer would give a performance. And Zarathustra spake thus unto the people:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I TEACH YOU THE SUPERMAN. Man is something that is to be surpassed. What have ye done to surpass man?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All beings hitherto have created something beyond themselves: and ye want to be the ebb of that great tide, and would rather go back to the beast than surpass man?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is the ape to man? A laughing-stock, a thing of shame. And just the same shall man be to the Superman: a laughing-stock, a thing of shame.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye have made your way from the worm to man, and much within you is still worm. Once were ye apes, and even yet man is more of an ape than any of the apes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even the wisest among you is only a disharmony and hybrid of plant and phantom. But do I bid you become phantoms or plants?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, I teach you the Superman!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The Superman is the meaning of the earth. Let your will say: The Superman SHALL BE the meaning of the earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I conjure you, my brethren, REMAIN TRUE TO THE EARTH, and believe not those who speak unto you of superearthly hopes! Poisoners are they, whether they know it or not.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Despisers of life are they, decaying ones and poisoned ones themselves, of whom the earth is weary: so away with them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once blasphemy against God was the greatest blasphemy; but God died, and therewith also those blasphemers. To blaspheme the earth is now the dreadfulest sin, and to rate the heart of the unknowable higher than the meaning of the earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once the soul looked contemptuously on the body, and then that contempt was the supreme thing:—the soul wished the body meagre, ghastly, and famished. Thus it thought to escape from the body and the earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, that soul was itself meagre, ghastly, and famished; and cruelty was the delight of that soul!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But ye, also, my brethren, tell me: What doth your body say about your soul? Is your soul not poverty and pollution and wretched self-complacency?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a polluted stream is man. One must be a sea, to receive a polluted stream without becoming impure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, I teach you the Superman: he is that sea; in him can your great contempt be submerged.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is the greatest thing ye can experience? It is the hour of great contempt. The hour in which even your happiness becometh loathsome unto you, and so also your reason and virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour when ye say: “What good is my happiness! It is poverty and pollution and wretched self-complacency. But my happiness should justify existence itself!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour when ye say: “What good is my reason! Doth it long for knowledge as the lion for his food? It is poverty and pollution and wretched self-complacency!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour when ye say: “What good is my virtue! As yet it hath not made me passionate. How weary I am of my good and my bad! It is all poverty and pollution and wretched self-complacency!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour when ye say: “What good is my justice! I do not see that I am fervour and fuel. The just, however, are fervour and fuel!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour when ye say: “What good is my pity! Is not pity the cross on which he is nailed who loveth man? But my pity is not a crucifixion.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have ye ever spoken thus? Have ye ever cried thus? Ah! would that I had heard you crying thus!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is not your sin—it is your self-satisfaction that crieth unto heaven; your very sparingness in sin crieth unto heaven!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where is the lightning to lick you with its tongue? Where is the frenzy with which ye should be inoculated?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, I teach you the Superman: he is that lightning, he is that frenzy!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had thus spoken, one of the people called out: “We have now heard enough of the rope-dancer; it is time now for us to see him!” And all the people laughed at Zarathustra. But the rope-dancer, who thought the words applied to him, began his performance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra, however, looked at the people and wondered. Then he spake thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man is a rope stretched between the animal and the Superman—a rope over an abyss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A dangerous crossing, a dangerous wayfaring, a dangerous looking-back, a dangerous trembling and halting.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is great in man is that he is a bridge and not a goal: what is lovable in man is that he is an OVER-GOING and a DOWN-GOING.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love those that know not how to live except as down-goers, for they are the over-goers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love the great despisers, because they are the great adorers, and arrows of longing for the other shore.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love those who do not first seek a reason beyond the stars for going down and being sacrifices, but sacrifice themselves to the earth, that the earth of the Superman may hereafter arrive.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who liveth in order to know, and seeketh to know in order that the Superman may hereafter live. Thus seeketh he his own down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who laboureth and inventeth, that he may build the house for the Superman, and prepare for him earth, animal, and plant: for thus seeketh he his own down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who loveth his virtue: for virtue is the will to down-going, and an arrow of longing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who reserveth no share of spirit for himself, but wanteth to be wholly the spirit of his virtue: thus walketh he as spirit over the bridge.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who maketh his virtue his inclination and destiny: thus, for the sake of his virtue, he is willing to live on, or live no more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who desireth not too many virtues. One virtue is more of a virtue than two, because it is more of a knot for one’s destiny to cling to.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him whose soul is lavish, who wanteth no thanks and doth not give back: for he always bestoweth, and desireth not to keep for himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who is ashamed when the dice fall in his favour, and who then asketh: “Am I a dishonest player?”—for he is willing to succumb.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who scattereth golden words in advance of his deeds, and always doeth more than he promiseth: for he seeketh his own down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who justifieth the future ones, and redeemeth the past ones: for he is willing to succumb through the present ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who chasteneth his God, because he loveth his God: for he must succumb through the wrath of his God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him whose soul is deep even in the wounding, and may succumb through a small matter: thus goeth he willingly over the bridge.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him whose soul is so overfull that he forgetteth himself, and all things are in him: thus all things become his down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love him who is of a free spirit and a free heart: thus is his head only the bowels of his heart; his heart, however, causeth his down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love all who are like heavy drops falling one by one out of the dark cloud that lowereth over man: they herald the coming of the lightning, and succumb as heralds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, I am a herald of the lightning, and a heavy drop out of the cloud: the lightning, however, is the SUPERMAN.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>5.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had spoken these words, he again looked at the people, and was silent. “There they stand,” said he to his heart; “there they laugh: they understand me not; I am not the mouth for these ears.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Must one first batter their ears, that they may learn to hear with their eyes? Must one clatter like kettledrums and penitential preachers? Or do they only believe the stammerer?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They have something whereof they are proud. What do they call it, that which maketh them proud? Culture, they call it; it distinguisheth them from the goatherds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They dislike, therefore, to hear of ‘contempt’ of themselves. So I will appeal to their pride.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I will speak unto them of the most contemptible thing: that, however, is THE LAST MAN!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thus spake Zarathustra unto the people:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is time for man to fix his goal. It is time for man to plant the germ of his highest hope.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still is his soil rich enough for it. But that soil will one day be poor and exhausted, and no lofty tree will any longer be able to grow thereon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas! there cometh the time when man will no longer launch the arrow of his longing beyond man—and the string of his bow will have unlearned to whizz!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I tell you: one must still have chaos in one, to give birth to a dancing star. I tell you: ye have still chaos in you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas! There cometh the time when man will no longer give birth to any star. Alas! There cometh the time of the most despicable man, who can no longer despise himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo! I show you THE LAST MAN.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What is love? What is creation? What is longing? What is a star?”—so asketh the last man and blinketh.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The earth hath then become small, and on it there hoppeth the last man who maketh everything small. His species is ineradicable like that of the ground-flea; the last man liveth longest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“We have discovered happiness”—say the last men, and blink thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They have left the regions where it is hard to live; for they need warmth. One still loveth one’s neighbour and rubbeth against him; for one needeth warmth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Turning ill and being distrustful, they consider sinful: they walk warily. He is a fool who still stumbleth over stones or men!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A little poison now and then: that maketh pleasant dreams. And much poison at last for a pleasant death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One still worketh, for work is a pastime. But one is careful lest the pastime should hurt one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One no longer becometh poor or rich; both are too burdensome. Who still wanteth to rule? Who still wanteth to obey? Both are too burdensome.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No shepherd, and one herd! Every one wanteth the same; every one is equal: he who hath other sentiments goeth voluntarily into the madhouse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Formerly all the world was insane,”—say the subtlest of them, and blink thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They are clever and know all that hath happened: so there is no end to their raillery. People still fall out, but are soon reconciled—otherwise it spoileth their stomachs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They have their little pleasures for the day, and their little pleasures for the night, but they have a regard for health.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“We have discovered happiness,”—say the last men, and blink thereby.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And here ended the first discourse of Zarathustra, which is also called “The Prologue”: for at this point the shouting and mirth of the multitude interrupted him. “Give us this last man, O Zarathustra,”—they called out—“make us into these last men! Then will we make thee a present of the Superman!” And all the people exulted and smacked their lips. Zarathustra, however, turned sad, and said to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“They understand me not: I am not the mouth for these ears.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too long, perhaps, have I lived in the mountains; too much have I hearkened unto the brooks and trees: now do I speak unto them as unto the goatherds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Calm is my soul, and clear, like the mountains in the morning. But they think me cold, and a mocker with terrible jests.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now do they look at me and laugh: and while they laugh they hate me too. There is ice in their laughter.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then, however, something happened which made every mouth mute and every eye fixed. In the meantime, of course, the rope-dancer had commenced his performance: he had come out at a little door, and was going along the rope which was stretched between two towers, so that it hung above the market-place and the people. When he was just midway across, the little door opened once more, and a gaudily-dressed fellow like a buffoon sprang out, and went rapidly after the first one. “Go on, halt-foot,” cried his frightful voice, “go on, lazy-bones, interloper, sallow-face!—lest I tickle thee with my heel! What dost thou here between the towers? In the tower is the place for thee, thou shouldst be locked up; to one better than thyself thou blockest the way!”—And with every word he came nearer and nearer the first one. When, however, he was but a step behind, there happened the frightful thing which made every mouth mute and every eye fixed—he uttered a yell like a devil, and jumped over the other who was in his way. The latter, however, when he thus saw his rival triumph, lost at the same time his head and his footing on the rope; he threw his pole away, and shot downwards faster than it, like an eddy of arms and legs, into the depth. The market-place and the people were like the sea when the storm cometh on: they all flew apart and in disorder, especially where the body was about to fall.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra, however, remained standing, and just beside him fell the body, badly injured and disfigured, but not yet dead. After a while consciousness returned to the shattered man, and he saw Zarathustra kneeling beside him. “What art thou doing there?” said he at last, “I knew long ago that the devil would trip me up. Now he draggeth me to hell: wilt thou prevent him?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“On mine honour, my friend,” answered Zarathustra, “there is nothing of all that whereof thou speakest: there is no devil and no hell. Thy soul will be dead even sooner than thy body: fear, therefore, nothing any more!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The man looked up distrustfully. “If thou speakest the truth,” said he, “I lose nothing when I lose my life. I am not much more than an animal which hath been taught to dance by blows and scanty fare.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Not at all,” said Zarathustra, “thou hast made danger thy calling; therein there is nothing contemptible. Now thou perishest by thy calling: therefore will I bury thee with mine own hands.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had said this the dying one did not reply further; but he moved his hand as if he sought the hand of Zarathustra in gratitude.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>7.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Meanwhile the evening came on, and the market-place veiled itself in gloom. Then the people dispersed, for even curiosity and terror become fatigued. Zarathustra, however, still sat beside the dead man on the ground, absorbed in thought: so he forgot the time. But at last it became night, and a cold wind blew upon the lonely one. Then arose Zarathustra and said to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a fine catch of fish hath Zarathustra made to-day! It is not a man he hath caught, but a corpse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sombre is human life, and as yet without meaning: a buffoon may be fateful to it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I want to teach men the sense of their existence, which is the Superman, the lightning out of the dark cloud—man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But still am I far from them, and my sense speaketh not unto their sense. To men I am still something between a fool and a corpse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gloomy is the night, gloomy are the ways of Zarathustra. Come, thou cold and stiff companion! I carry thee to the place where I shall bury thee with mine own hands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>8.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had said this to his heart, he put the corpse upon his shoulders and set out on his way. Yet had he not gone a hundred steps, when there stole a man up to him and whispered in his ear—and lo! he that spake was the buffoon from the tower. “Leave this town, O Zarathustra,” said he, “there are too many here who hate thee. The good and just hate thee, and call thee their enemy and despiser; the believers in the orthodox belief hate thee, and call thee a danger to the multitude. It was thy good fortune to be laughed at: and verily thou spakest like a buffoon. It was thy good fortune to associate with the dead dog; by so humiliating thyself thou hast saved thy life to-day. Depart, however, from this town,—or tomorrow I shall jump over thee, a living man over a dead one.” And when he had said this, the buffoon vanished; Zarathustra, however, went on through the dark streets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At the gate of the town the grave-diggers met him: they shone their torch on his face, and, recognising Zarathustra, they sorely derided him. “Zarathustra is carrying away the dead dog: a fine thing that Zarathustra hath turned a grave-digger! For our hands are too cleanly for that roast. Will Zarathustra steal the bite from the devil? Well then, good luck to the repast! If only the devil is not a better thief than Zarathustra!—he will steal them both, he will eat them both!” And they laughed among themselves, and put their heads together.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra made no answer thereto, but went on his way. When he had gone on for two hours, past forests and swamps, he had heard too much of the hungry howling of the wolves, and he himself became a-hungry. So he halted at a lonely house in which a light was burning.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Hunger attacketh me,” said Zarathustra, “like a robber. Among forests and swamps my hunger attacketh me, and late in the night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Strange humours hath my hunger. Often it cometh to me only after a repast, and all day it hath failed to come: where hath it been?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thereupon Zarathustra knocked at the door of the house. An old man appeared, who carried a light, and asked: “Who cometh unto me and my bad sleep?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“A living man and a dead one,” said Zarathustra. “Give me something to eat and drink, I forgot it during the day. He that feedeth the hungry refresheth his own soul, saith wisdom.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The old man withdrew, but came back immediately and offered Zarathustra bread and wine. “A bad country for the hungry,” said he; “that is why I live here. Animal and man come unto me, the anchorite. But bid thy companion eat and drink also, he is wearier than thou.” Zarathustra answered: “My companion is dead; I shall hardly be able to persuade him to eat.” “That doth not concern me,” said the old man sullenly; “he that knocketh at my door must take what I offer him. Eat, and fare ye well!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereafter Zarathustra again went on for two hours, trusting to the path and the light of the stars: for he was an experienced night-walker, and liked to look into the face of all that slept. When the morning dawned, however, Zarathustra found himself in a thick forest, and no path was any longer visible. He then put the dead man in a hollow tree at his head—for he wanted to protect him from the wolves—and laid himself down on the ground and moss. And immediately he fell asleep, tired in body, but with a tranquil soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>9.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Long slept Zarathustra; and not only the rosy dawn passed over his head, but also the morning. At last, however, his eyes opened, and amazedly he gazed into the forest and the stillness, amazedly he gazed into himself. Then he arose quickly, like a seafarer who all at once seeth the land; and he shouted for joy: for he saw a new truth. And he spake thus to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A light hath dawned upon me: I need companions—living ones; not dead companions and corpses, which I carry with me where I will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I need living companions, who will follow me because they want to follow themselves—and to the place where I will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A light hath dawned upon me. Not to the people is Zarathustra to speak, but to companions! Zarathustra shall not be the herd’s herdsman and hound!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To allure many from the herd—for that purpose have I come. The people and the herd must be angry with me: a robber shall Zarathustra be called by the herdsmen.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Herdsmen, I say, but they call themselves the good and just. Herdsmen, I say, but they call themselves the believers in the orthodox belief.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behold the good and just! Whom do they hate most? Him who breaketh up their tables of values, the breaker, the lawbreaker:—he, however, is the creator.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behold the believers of all beliefs! Whom do they hate most? Him who breaketh up their tables of values, the breaker, the law-breaker—he, however, is the creator.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Companions, the creator seeketh, not corpses—and not herds or believers either. Fellow-creators the creator seeketh—those who grave new values on new tables.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Companions, the creator seeketh, and fellow-reapers: for everything is ripe for the harvest with him. But he lacketh the hundred sickles: so he plucketh the ears of corn and is vexed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Companions, the creator seeketh, and such as know how to whet their sickles. Destroyers, will they be called, and despisers of good and evil. But they are the reapers and rejoicers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Fellow-creators, Zarathustra seeketh; fellow-reapers and fellow-rejoicers, Zarathustra seeketh: what hath he to do with herds and herdsmen and corpses!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thou, my first companion, rest in peace! Well have I buried thee in thy hollow tree; well have I hid thee from the wolves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I part from thee; the time hath arrived. ‘Twixt rosy dawn and rosy dawn there came unto me a new truth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am not to be a herdsman, I am not to be a grave-digger. Not any more will I discourse unto the people; for the last time have I spoken unto the dead.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the creators, the reapers, and the rejoicers will I associate: the rainbow will I show them, and all the stairs to the Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the lone-dwellers will I sing my song, and to the twain-dwellers; and unto him who hath still ears for the unheard, will I make the heart heavy with my happiness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I make for my goal, I follow my course; over the loitering and tardy will I leap. Thus let my on-going be their down-going!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>10.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This had Zarathustra said to his heart when the sun stood at noon-tide. Then he looked inquiringly aloft,—for he heard above him the sharp call of a bird. And behold! An eagle swept through the air in wide circles, and on it hung a serpent, not like a prey, but like a friend: for it kept itself coiled round the eagle’s neck.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“They are mine animals,” said Zarathustra, and rejoiced in his heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The proudest animal under the sun, and the wisest animal under the sun,—they have come out to reconnoitre.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They want to know whether Zarathustra still liveth. Verily, do I still live?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>More dangerous have I found it among men than among animals; in dangerous paths goeth Zarathustra. Let mine animals lead me!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had said this, he remembered the words of the saint in the forest. Then he sighed and spake thus to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Would that I were wiser! Would that I were wise from the very heart, like my serpent!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I am asking the impossible. Therefore do I ask my pride to go always with my wisdom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if my wisdom should some day forsake me:—alas! it loveth to fly away!—may my pride then fly with my folly!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus began Zarathustra’s down-going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>ZARATHUSTRA’S DISCOURSES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>I. THE THREE METAMORPHOSES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Three metamorphoses of the spirit do I designate to you: how the spirit becometh a camel, the camel a lion, and the lion at last a child.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many heavy things are there for the spirit, the strong load-bearing spirit in which reverence dwelleth: for the heavy and the heaviest longeth its strength.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is heavy? so asketh the load-bearing spirit; then kneeleth it down like the camel, and wanteth to be well laden.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is the heaviest thing, ye heroes? asketh the load-bearing spirit, that I may take it upon me and rejoice in my strength.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is it not this: To humiliate oneself in order to mortify one’s pride? To exhibit one’s folly in order to mock at one’s wisdom?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or is it this: To desert our cause when it celebrateth its triumph? To ascend high mountains to tempt the tempter?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or is it this: To feed on the acorns and grass of knowledge, and for the sake of truth to suffer hunger of soul?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or is it this: To be sick and dismiss comforters, and make friends of the deaf, who never hear thy requests?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or is it this: To go into foul water when it is the water of truth, and not disclaim cold frogs and hot toads?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or is it this: To love those who despise us, and give one’s hand to the phantom when it is going to frighten us?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All these heaviest things the load-bearing spirit taketh upon itself: and like the camel, which, when laden, hasteneth into the wilderness, so hasteneth the spirit into its wilderness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But in the loneliest wilderness happeneth the second metamorphosis: here the spirit becometh a lion; freedom will it capture, and lordship in its own wilderness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Its last Lord it here seeketh: hostile will it be to him, and to its last God; for victory will it struggle with the great dragon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is the great dragon which the spirit is no longer inclined to call Lord and God? “Thou-shalt,” is the great dragon called. But the spirit of the lion saith, “I will.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou-shalt,” lieth in its path, sparkling with gold—a scale-covered beast; and on every scale glittereth golden, “Thou shalt!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The values of a thousand years glitter on those scales, and thus speaketh the mightiest of all dragons: “All the values of things—glitter on me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All values have already been created, and all created values—do I represent. Verily, there shall be no ‘I will’ any more.” Thus speaketh the dragon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brethren, wherefore is there need of the lion in the spirit? Why sufficeth not the beast of burden, which renounceth and is reverent?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To create new values—that, even the lion cannot yet accomplish: but to create itself freedom for new creating—that can the might of the lion do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To create itself freedom, and give a holy Nay even unto duty: for that, my brethren, there is need of the lion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To assume the right to new values—that is the most formidable assumption for a load-bearing and reverent spirit. Verily, unto such a spirit it is preying, and the work of a beast of prey.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As its holiest, it once loved “Thou-shalt”: now is it forced to find illusion and arbitrariness even in the holiest things, that it may capture freedom from its love: the lion is needed for this capture.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But tell me, my brethren, what the child can do, which even the lion could not do? Why hath the preying lion still to become a child?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Innocence is the child, and forgetfulness, a new beginning, a game, a self-rolling wheel, a first movement, a holy Yea.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Aye, for the game of creating, my brethren, there is needed a holy Yea unto life: ITS OWN will, willeth now the spirit; HIS OWN world winneth the world’s outcast.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Three metamorphoses of the spirit have I designated to you: how the spirit became a camel, the camel a lion, and the lion at last a child.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra. And at that time he abode in the town which is called The Pied Cow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>II. THE ACADEMIC CHAIRS OF VIRTUE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>People commended unto Zarathustra a wise man, as one who could discourse well about sleep and virtue: greatly was he honoured and rewarded for it, and all the youths sat before his chair. To him went Zarathustra, and sat among the youths before his chair. And thus spake the wise man:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Respect and modesty in presence of sleep! That is the first thing! And to go out of the way of all who sleep badly and keep awake at night!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Modest is even the thief in presence of sleep: he always stealeth softly through the night. Immodest, however, is the night-watchman; immodestly he carrieth his horn.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No small art is it to sleep: it is necessary for that purpose to keep awake all day.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ten times a day must thou overcome thyself: that causeth wholesome weariness, and is poppy to the soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ten times must thou reconcile again with thyself; for overcoming is bitterness, and badly sleep the unreconciled.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ten truths must thou find during the day; otherwise wilt thou seek truth during the night, and thy soul will have been hungry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ten times must thou laugh during the day, and be cheerful; otherwise thy stomach, the father of affliction, will disturb thee in the night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Few people know it, but one must have all the virtues in order to sleep well. Shall I bear false witness? Shall I commit adultery?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Shall I covet my neighbour’s maidservant? All that would ill accord with good sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And even if one have all the virtues, there is still one thing needful: to send the virtues themselves to sleep at the right time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That they may not quarrel with one another, the good females! And about thee, thou unhappy one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Peace with God and thy neighbour: so desireth good sleep. And peace also with thy neighbour’s devil! Otherwise it will haunt thee in the night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Honour to the government, and obedience, and also to the crooked government! So desireth good sleep. How can I help it, if power like to walk on crooked legs?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who leadeth his sheep to the greenest pasture, shall always be for me the best shepherd: so doth it accord with good sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many honours I want not, nor great treasures: they excite the spleen. But it is bad sleeping without a good name and a little treasure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A small company is more welcome to me than a bad one: but they must come and go at the right time. So doth it accord with good sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well, also, do the poor in spirit please me: they promote sleep. Blessed are they, especially if one always give in to them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus passeth the day unto the virtuous. When night cometh, then take I good care not to summon sleep. It disliketh to be summoned—sleep, the lord of the virtues!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I think of what I have done and thought during the day. Thus ruminating, patient as a cow, I ask myself: What were thy ten overcomings?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And what were the ten reconciliations, and the ten truths, and the ten laughters with which my heart enjoyed itself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus pondering, and cradled by forty thoughts, it overtaketh me all at once—sleep, the unsummoned, the lord of the virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sleep tappeth on mine eye, and it turneth heavy. Sleep toucheth my mouth, and it remaineth open.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, on soft soles doth it come to me, the dearest of thieves, and stealeth from me my thoughts: stupid do I then stand, like this academic chair.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But not much longer do I then stand: I already lie.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra heard the wise man thus speak, he laughed in his heart: for thereby had a light dawned upon him. And thus spake he to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A fool seemeth this wise man with his forty thoughts: but I believe he knoweth well how to sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Happy even is he who liveth near this wise man! Such sleep is contagious—even through a thick wall it is contagious.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A magic resideth even in his academic chair. And not in vain did the youths sit before the preacher of virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His wisdom is to keep awake in order to sleep well. And verily, if life had no sense, and had I to choose nonsense, this would be the desirablest nonsense for me also.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now know I well what people sought formerly above all else when they sought teachers of virtue. Good sleep they sought for themselves, and poppy-head virtues to promote it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To all those belauded sages of the academic chairs, wisdom was sleep without dreams: they knew no higher significance of life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even at present, to be sure, there are some like this preacher of virtue, and not always so honourable: but their time is past. And not much longer do they stand: there they already lie.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Blessed are those drowsy ones: for they shall soon nod to sleep.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>III. BACKWORLDSMEN.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once on a time, Zarathustra also cast his fancy beyond man, like all backworldsmen. The work of a suffering and tortured God, did the world then seem to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The dream—and diction—of a God, did the world then seem to me; coloured vapours before the eyes of a divinely dissatisfied one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Good and evil, and joy and woe, and I and thou—coloured vapours did they seem to me before creative eyes. The creator wished to look away from himself,—thereupon he created the world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Intoxicating joy is it for the sufferer to look away from his suffering and forget himself. Intoxicating joy and self-forgetting, did the world once seem to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This world, the eternally imperfect, an eternal contradiction’s image and imperfect image—an intoxicating joy to its imperfect creator:—thus did the world once seem to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus, once on a time, did I also cast my fancy beyond man, like all backworldsmen. Beyond man, forsooth?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, ye brethren, that God whom I created was human work and human madness, like all the Gods!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A man was he, and only a poor fragment of a man and ego. Out of mine own ashes and glow it came unto me, that phantom. And verily, it came not unto me from the beyond!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What happened, my brethren? I surpassed myself, the suffering one; I carried mine own ashes to the mountain; a brighter flame I contrived for myself. And lo! Thereupon the phantom WITHDREW from me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To me the convalescent would it now be suffering and torment to believe in such phantoms: suffering would it now be to me, and humiliation. Thus speak I to backworldsmen.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Suffering was it, and impotence—that created all backworlds; and the short madness of happiness, which only the greatest sufferer experienceth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Weariness, which seeketh to get to the ultimate with one leap, with a death-leap; a poor ignorant weariness, unwilling even to will any longer: that created all Gods and backworlds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Believe me, my brethren! It was the body which despaired of the body—it groped with the fingers of the infatuated spirit at the ultimate walls.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Believe me, my brethren! It was the body which despaired of the earth—it heard the bowels of existence speaking unto it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And then it sought to get through the ultimate walls with its head—and not with its head only—into “the other world.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that “other world” is well concealed from man, that dehumanised, inhuman world, which is a celestial naught; and the bowels of existence do not speak unto man, except as man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, it is difficult to prove all being, and hard to make it speak. Tell me, ye brethren, is not the strangest of all things best proved?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, this ego, with its contradiction and perplexity, speaketh most uprightly of its being—this creating, willing, evaluing ego, which is the measure and value of things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this most upright existence, the ego—it speaketh of the body, and still implieth the body, even when it museth and raveth and fluttereth with broken wings.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Always more uprightly learneth it to speak, the ego; and the more it learneth, the more doth it find titles and honours for the body and the earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A new pride taught me mine ego, and that teach I unto men: no longer to thrust one’s head into the sand of celestial things, but to carry it freely, a terrestrial head, which giveth meaning to the earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A new will teach I unto men: to choose that path which man hath followed blindly, and to approve of it—and no longer to slink aside from it, like the sick and perishing!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The sick and perishing—it was they who despised the body and the earth, and invented the heavenly world, and the redeeming blood-drops; but even those sweet and sad poisons they borrowed from the body and the earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From their misery they sought escape, and the stars were too remote for them. Then they sighed: “O that there were heavenly paths by which to steal into another existence and into happiness!” Then they contrived for themselves their by-paths and bloody draughts!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beyond the sphere of their body and this earth they now fancied themselves transported, these ungrateful ones. But to what did they owe the convulsion and rapture of their transport? To their body and this earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gentle is Zarathustra to the sickly. Verily, he is not indignant at their modes of consolation and ingratitude. May they become convalescents and overcomers, and create higher bodies for themselves!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Neither is Zarathustra indignant at a convalescent who looketh tenderly on his delusions, and at midnight stealeth round the grave of his God; but sickness and a sick frame remain even in his tears.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many sickly ones have there always been among those who muse, and languish for God; violently they hate the discerning ones, and the latest of virtues, which is uprightness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Backward they always gaze toward dark ages: then, indeed, were delusion and faith something different. Raving of the reason was likeness to God, and doubt was sin.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too well do I know those godlike ones: they insist on being believed in, and that doubt is sin. Too well, also, do I know what they themselves most believe in.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, not in backworlds and redeeming blood-drops: but in the body do they also believe most; and their own body is for them the thing-in-itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it is a sickly thing to them, and gladly would they get out of their skin. Therefore hearken they to the preachers of death, and themselves preach backworlds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hearken rather, my brethren, to the voice of the healthy body; it is a more upright and pure voice.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>More uprightly and purely speaketh the healthy body, perfect and square-built; and it speaketh of the meaning of the earth.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>IV. THE DESPISERS OF THE BODY.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the despisers of the body will I speak my word. I wish them neither to learn afresh, nor teach anew, but only to bid farewell to their own bodies,—and thus be dumb.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Body am I, and soul”—so saith the child. And why should one not speak like children?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the awakened one, the knowing one, saith: “Body am I entirely, and nothing more; and soul is only the name of something in the body.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The body is a big sagacity, a plurality with one sense, a war and a peace, a flock and a shepherd.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An instrument of thy body is also thy little sagacity, my brother, which thou callest “spirit”—a little instrument and plaything of thy big sagacity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ego,” sayest thou, and art proud of that word. But the greater thing—in which thou art unwilling to believe—is thy body with its big sagacity; it saith not “ego,” but doeth it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What the sense feeleth, what the spirit discerneth, hath never its end in itself. But sense and spirit would fain persuade thee that they are the end of all things: so vain are they.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Instruments and playthings are sense and spirit: behind them there is still the Self. The Self seeketh with the eyes of the senses, it hearkeneth also with the ears of the spirit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ever hearkeneth the Self, and seeketh; it compareth, mastereth, conquereth, and destroyeth. It ruleth, and is also the ego’s ruler.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behind thy thoughts and feelings, my brother, there is a mighty lord, an unknown sage—it is called Self; it dwelleth in thy body, it is thy body.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is more sagacity in thy body than in thy best wisdom. And who then knoweth why thy body requireth just thy best wisdom?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thy Self laugheth at thine ego, and its proud prancings. “What are these prancings and flights of thought unto me?” it saith to itself. “A by-way to my purpose. I am the leading-string of the ego, and the prompter of its notions.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The Self saith unto the ego: “Feel pain!” And thereupon it suffereth, and thinketh how it may put an end thereto—and for that very purpose it IS MEANT to think.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The Self saith unto the ego: “Feel pleasure!” Thereupon it rejoiceth, and thinketh how it may ofttimes rejoice—and for that very purpose it IS MEANT to think.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the despisers of the body will I speak a word. That they despise is caused by their esteem. What is it that created esteeming and despising and worth and will?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The creating Self created for itself esteeming and despising, it created for itself joy and woe. The creating body created for itself spirit, as a hand to its will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even in your folly and despising ye each serve your Self, ye despisers of the body. I tell you, your very Self wanteth to die, and turneth away from life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No longer can your Self do that which it desireth most:—create beyond itself. That is what it desireth most; that is all its fervour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it is now too late to do so:—so your Self wisheth to succumb, ye despisers of the body.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To succumb—so wisheth your Self; and therefore have ye become despisers of the body. For ye can no longer create beyond yourselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And therefore are ye now angry with life and with the earth. And unconscious envy is in the sidelong look of your contempt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I go not your way, ye despisers of the body! Ye are no bridges for me to the Superman!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>V. JOYS AND PASSIONS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brother, when thou hast a virtue, and it is thine own virtue, thou hast it in common with no one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, thou wouldst call it by name and caress it; thou wouldst pull its ears and amuse thyself with it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And lo! Then hast thou its name in common with the people, and hast become one of the people and the herd with thy virtue!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better for thee to say: “Ineffable is it, and nameless, that which is pain and sweetness to my soul, and also the hunger of my bowels.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let thy virtue be too high for the familiarity of names, and if thou must speak of it, be not ashamed to stammer about it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus speak and stammer: “That is MY good, that do I love, thus doth it please me entirely, thus only do <i>I</i> desire the good.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not as the law of a God do I desire it, not as a human law or a human need do I desire it; it is not to be a guide-post for me to superearths and paradises.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An earthly virtue is it which I love: little prudence is therein, and the least everyday wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that bird built its nest beside me: therefore, I love and cherish it—now sitteth it beside me on its golden eggs.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus shouldst thou stammer, and praise thy virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once hadst thou passions and calledst them evil. But now hast thou only thy virtues: they grew out of thy passions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou implantedst thy highest aim into the heart of those passions: then became they thy virtues and joys.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And though thou wert of the race of the hot-tempered, or of the voluptuous, or of the fanatical, or the vindictive;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All thy passions in the end became virtues, and all thy devils angels.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once hadst thou wild dogs in thy cellar: but they changed at last into birds and charming songstresses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Out of thy poisons brewedst thou balsam for thyself; thy cow, affliction, milkedst thou—now drinketh thou the sweet milk of her udder.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And nothing evil groweth in thee any longer, unless it be the evil that groweth out of the conflict of thy virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brother, if thou be fortunate, then wilt thou have one virtue and no more: thus goest thou easier over the bridge.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Illustrious is it to have many virtues, but a hard lot; and many a one hath gone into the wilderness and killed himself, because he was weary of being the battle and battlefield of virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brother, are war and battle evil? Necessary, however, is the evil; necessary are the envy and the distrust and the back-biting among the virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo! how each of thy virtues is covetous of the highest place; it wanteth thy whole spirit to be ITS herald, it wanteth thy whole power, in wrath, hatred, and love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Jealous is every virtue of the others, and a dreadful thing is jealousy. Even virtues may succumb by jealousy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He whom the flame of jealousy encompasseth, turneth at last, like the scorpion, the poisoned sting against himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! my brother, hast thou never seen a virtue backbite and stab itself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man is something that hath to be surpassed: and therefore shalt thou love thy virtues,—for thou wilt succumb by them.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>VI. THE PALE CRIMINAL.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye do not mean to slay, ye judges and sacrificers, until the animal hath bowed its head? Lo! the pale criminal hath bowed his head: out of his eye speaketh the great contempt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Mine ego is something which is to be surpassed: mine ego is to me the great contempt of man”: so speaketh it out of that eye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When he judged himself—that was his supreme moment; let not the exalted one relapse again into his low estate!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is no salvation for him who thus suffereth from himself, unless it be speedy death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your slaying, ye judges, shall be pity, and not revenge; and in that ye slay, see to it that ye yourselves justify life!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is not enough that ye should reconcile with him whom ye slay. Let your sorrow be love to the Superman: thus will ye justify your own survival!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Enemy” shall ye say but not “villain,” “invalid” shall ye say but not “wretch,” “fool” shall ye say but not “sinner.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thou, red judge, if thou would say audibly all thou hast done in thought, then would every one cry: “Away with the nastiness and the virulent reptile!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But one thing is the thought, another thing is the deed, and another thing is the idea of the deed. The wheel of causality doth not roll between them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An idea made this pale man pale. Adequate was he for his deed when he did it, but the idea of it, he could not endure when it was done.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Evermore did he now see himself as the doer of one deed. Madness, I call this: the exception reversed itself to the rule in him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The streak of chalk bewitcheth the hen; the stroke he struck bewitched his weak reason. Madness AFTER the deed, I call this.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hearken, ye judges! There is another madness besides, and it is BEFORE the deed. Ah! ye have not gone deep enough into this soul!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus speaketh the red judge: “Why did this criminal commit murder? He meant to rob.” I tell you, however, that his soul wanted blood, not booty: he thirsted for the happiness of the knife!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But his weak reason understood not this madness, and it persuaded him. “What matter about blood!” it said; “wishest thou not, at least, to make booty thereby? Or take revenge?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he hearkened unto his weak reason: like lead lay its words upon him—thereupon he robbed when he murdered. He did not mean to be ashamed of his madness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now once more lieth the lead of his guilt upon him, and once more is his weak reason so benumbed, so paralysed, and so dull.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Could he only shake his head, then would his burden roll off; but who shaketh that head?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is this man? A mass of diseases that reach out into the world through the spirit; there they want to get their prey.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is this man? A coil of wild serpents that are seldom at peace among themselves—so they go forth apart and seek prey in the world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Look at that poor body! What it suffered and craved, the poor soul interpreted to itself—it interpreted it as murderous desire, and eagerness for the happiness of the knife.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Him who now turneth sick, the evil overtaketh which is now the evil: he seeketh to cause pain with that which causeth him pain. But there have been other ages, and another evil and good.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once was doubt evil, and the will to Self. Then the invalid became a heretic or sorcerer; as heretic or sorcerer he suffered, and sought to cause suffering.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But this will not enter your ears; it hurteth your good people, ye tell me. But what doth it matter to me about your good people!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many things in your good people cause me disgust, and verily, not their evil. I would that they had a madness by which they succumbed, like this pale criminal!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I would that their madness were called truth, or fidelity, or justice: but they have their virtue in order to live long, and in wretched self-complacency.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am a railing alongside the torrent; whoever is able to grasp me may grasp me! Your crutch, however, I am not.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>VII. READING AND WRITING.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Of all that is written, I love only what a person hath written with his blood. Write with blood, and thou wilt find that blood is spirit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is no easy task to understand unfamiliar blood; I hate the reading idlers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who knoweth the reader, doeth nothing more for the reader. Another century of readers—and spirit itself will stink.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every one being allowed to learn to read, ruineth in the long run not only writing but also thinking.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once spirit was God, then it became man, and now it even becometh populace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He that writeth in blood and proverbs doth not want to be read, but learnt by heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the mountains the shortest way is from peak to peak, but for that route thou must have long legs. Proverbs should be peaks, and those spoken to should be big and tall.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The atmosphere rare and pure, danger near and the spirit full of a joyful wickedness: thus are things well matched.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I want to have goblins about me, for I am courageous. The courage which scareth away ghosts, createth for itself goblins—it wanteth to laugh.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I no longer feel in common with you; the very cloud which I see beneath me, the blackness and heaviness at which I laugh—that is your thunder-cloud.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye look aloft when ye long for exaltation; and I look downward because I am exalted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Who among you can at the same time laugh and be exalted?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who climbeth on the highest mountains, laugheth at all tragic plays and tragic realities.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Courageous, unconcerned, scornful, coercive—so wisdom wisheth us; she is a woman, and ever loveth only a warrior.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye tell me, “Life is hard to bear.” But for what purpose should ye have your pride in the morning and your resignation in the evening?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Life is hard to bear: but do not affect to be so delicate! We are all of us fine sumpter asses and assesses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What have we in common with the rose-bud, which trembleth because a drop of dew hath formed upon it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is true we love life; not because we are wont to live, but because we are wont to love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is always some madness in love. But there is always, also, some method in madness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And to me also, who appreciate life, the butterflies, and soap-bubbles, and whatever is like them amongst us, seem most to enjoy happiness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To see these light, foolish, pretty, lively little sprites flit about—that moveth Zarathustra to tears and songs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I should only believe in a God that would know how to dance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I saw my devil, I found him serious, thorough, profound, solemn: he was the spirit of gravity—through him all things fall.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not by wrath, but by laughter, do we slay. Come, let us slay the spirit of gravity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I learned to walk; since then have I let myself run. I learned to fly; since then I do not need pushing in order to move from a spot.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now am I light, now do I fly; now do I see myself under myself. Now there danceth a God in me.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>VIII. THE TREE ON THE HILL.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra’s eye had perceived that a certain youth avoided him. And as he walked alone one evening over the hills surrounding the town called “The Pied Cow,” behold, there found he the youth sitting leaning against a tree, and gazing with wearied look into the valley. Zarathustra thereupon laid hold of the tree beside which the youth sat, and spake thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“If I wished to shake this tree with my hands, I should not be able to do so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the wind, which we see not, troubleth and bendeth it as it listeth. We are sorest bent and troubled by invisible hands.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereupon the youth arose disconcerted, and said: “I hear Zarathustra, and just now was I thinking of him!” Zarathustra answered:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why art thou frightened on that account?—But it is the same with man as with the tree.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The more he seeketh to rise into the height and light, the more vigorously do his roots struggle earthward, downward, into the dark and deep—into the evil.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Yea, into the evil!” cried the youth. “How is it possible that thou hast discovered my soul?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra smiled, and said: “Many a soul one will never discover, unless one first invent it.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Yea, into the evil!” cried the youth once more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou saidst the truth, Zarathustra. I trust myself no longer since I sought to rise into the height, and nobody trusteth me any longer; how doth that happen?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I change too quickly: my to-day refuteth my yesterday. I often overleap the steps when I clamber; for so doing, none of the steps pardons me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When aloft, I find myself always alone. No one speaketh unto me; the frost of solitude maketh me tremble. What do I seek on the height?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My contempt and my longing increase together; the higher I clamber, the more do I despise him who clambereth. What doth he seek on the height?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How ashamed I am of my clambering and stumbling! How I mock at my violent panting! How I hate him who flieth! How tired I am on the height!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here the youth was silent. And Zarathustra contemplated the tree beside which they stood, and spake thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“This tree standeth lonely here on the hills; it hath grown up high above man and beast.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if it wanted to speak, it would have none who could understand it: so high hath it grown.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now it waiteth and waiteth,—for what doth it wait? It dwelleth too close to the seat of the clouds; it waiteth perhaps for the first lightning?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had said this, the youth called out with violent gestures: “Yea, Zarathustra, thou speakest the truth. My destruction I longed for, when I desired to be on the height, and thou art the lightning for which I waited! Lo! what have I been since thou hast appeared amongst us? It is mine envy of thee that hath destroyed me!”—Thus spake the youth, and wept bitterly. Zarathustra, however, put his arm about him, and led the youth away with him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when they had walked a while together, Zarathustra began to speak thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It rendeth my heart. Better than thy words express it, thine eyes tell me all thy danger.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet thou art not free; thou still SEEKEST freedom. Too unslept hath thy seeking made thee, and too wakeful.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On the open height wouldst thou be; for the stars thirsteth thy soul. But thy bad impulses also thirst for freedom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thy wild dogs want liberty; they bark for joy in their cellar when thy spirit endeavoureth to open all prison doors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still art thou a prisoner—it seemeth to me—who deviseth liberty for himself: ah! sharp becometh the soul of such prisoners, but also deceitful and wicked.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To purify himself, is still necessary for the freedman of the spirit. Much of the prison and the mould still remaineth in him: pure hath his eye still to become.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, I know thy danger. But by my love and hope I conjure thee: cast not thy love and hope away!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Noble thou feelest thyself still, and noble others also feel thee still, though they bear thee a grudge and cast evil looks. Know this, that to everybody a noble one standeth in the way.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Also to the good, a noble one standeth in the way: and even when they call him a good man, they want thereby to put him aside.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The new, would the noble man create, and a new virtue. The old, wanteth the good man, and that the old should be conserved.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it is not the danger of the noble man to turn a good man, but lest he should become a blusterer, a scoffer, or a destroyer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! I have known noble ones who lost their highest hope. And then they disparaged all high hopes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then lived they shamelessly in temporary pleasures, and beyond the day had hardly an aim.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Spirit is also voluptuousness,”—said they. Then broke the wings of their spirit; and now it creepeth about, and defileth where it gnaweth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once they thought of becoming heroes; but sensualists are they now. A trouble and a terror is the hero to them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But by my love and hope I conjure thee: cast not away the hero in thy soul! Maintain holy thy highest hope!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>IX. THE PREACHERS OF DEATH.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are preachers of death: and the earth is full of those to whom desistance from life must be preached.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Full is the earth of the superfluous; marred is life by the many-too-many. May they be decoyed out of this life by the “life eternal”!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The yellow ones”: so are called the preachers of death, or “the black ones.” But I will show them unto you in other colours besides.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are the terrible ones who carry about in themselves the beast of prey, and have no choice except lusts or self-laceration. And even their lusts are self-laceration.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They have not yet become men, those terrible ones: may they preach desistance from life, and pass away themselves!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are the spiritually consumptive ones: hardly are they born when they begin to die, and long for doctrines of lassitude and renunciation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They would fain be dead, and we should approve of their wish! Let us beware of awakening those dead ones, and of damaging those living coffins!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They meet an invalid, or an old man, or a corpse—and immediately they say: “Life is refuted!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But they only are refuted, and their eye, which seeth only one aspect of existence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Shrouded in thick melancholy, and eager for the little casualties that bring death: thus do they wait, and clench their teeth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or else, they grasp at sweetmeats, and mock at their childishness thereby: they cling to their straw of life, and mock at their still clinging to it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Their wisdom speaketh thus: “A fool, he who remaineth alive; but so far are we fools! And that is the foolishest thing in life!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Life is only suffering”: so say others, and lie not. Then see to it that YE cease! See to it that the life ceaseth which is only suffering!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And let this be the teaching of your virtue: “Thou shalt slay thyself! Thou shalt steal away from thyself!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Lust is sin,”—so say some who preach death—“let us go apart and beget no children!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Giving birth is troublesome,”—say others—“why still give birth? One beareth only the unfortunate!” And they also are preachers of death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Pity is necessary,”—so saith a third party. “Take what I have! Take what I am! So much less doth life bind me!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Were they consistently pitiful, then would they make their neighbours sick of life. To be wicked—that would be their true goodness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But they want to be rid of life; what care they if they bind others still faster with their chains and gifts!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ye also, to whom life is rough labour and disquiet, are ye not very tired of life? Are ye not very ripe for the sermon of death?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All ye to whom rough labour is dear, and the rapid, new, and strange—ye put up with yourselves badly; your diligence is flight, and the will to self-forgetfulness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ye believed more in life, then would ye devote yourselves less to the momentary. But for waiting, ye have not enough of capacity in you—nor even for idling!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everywhere resoundeth the voices of those who preach death; and the earth is full of those to whom death hath to be preached.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or “life eternal”; it is all the same to me—if only they pass away quickly!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>X. WAR AND WARRIORS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>By our best enemies we do not want to be spared, nor by those either whom we love from the very heart. So let me tell you the truth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brethren in war! I love you from the very heart. I am, and was ever, your counterpart. And I am also your best enemy. So let me tell you the truth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I know the hatred and envy of your hearts. Ye are not great enough not to know of hatred and envy. Then be great enough not to be ashamed of them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if ye cannot be saints of knowledge, then, I pray you, be at least its warriors. They are the companions and forerunners of such saintship.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I see many soldiers; could I but see many warriors! “Uniform” one calleth what they wear; may it not be uniform what they therewith hide!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye shall be those whose eyes ever seek for an enemy—for YOUR enemy. And with some of you there is hatred at first sight.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your enemy shall ye seek; your war shall ye wage, and for the sake of your thoughts! And if your thoughts succumb, your uprightness shall still shout triumph thereby!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye shall love peace as a means to new wars—and the short peace more than the long.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>You I advise not to work, but to fight. You I advise not to peace, but to victory. Let your work be a fight, let your peace be a victory!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One can only be silent and sit peacefully when one hath arrow and bow; otherwise one prateth and quarrelleth. Let your peace be a victory!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye say it is the good cause which halloweth even war? I say unto you: it is the good war which halloweth every cause.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>War and courage have done more great things than charity. Not your sympathy, but your bravery hath hitherto saved the victims.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What is good?” ye ask. To be brave is good. Let the little girls say: “To be good is what is pretty, and at the same time touching.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They call you heartless: but your heart is true, and I love the bashfulness of your goodwill. Ye are ashamed of your flow, and others are ashamed of their ebb.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye are ugly? Well then, my brethren, take the sublime about you, the mantle of the ugly!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when your soul becometh great, then doth it become haughty, and in your sublimity there is wickedness. I know you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In wickedness the haughty man and the weakling meet. But they misunderstand one another. I know you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye shall only have enemies to be hated, but not enemies to be despised. Ye must be proud of your enemies; then, the successes of your enemies are also your successes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Resistance—that is the distinction of the slave. Let your distinction be obedience. Let your commanding itself be obeying!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the good warrior soundeth “thou shalt” pleasanter than “I will.” And all that is dear unto you, ye shall first have it commanded unto you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let your love to life be love to your highest hope; and let your highest hope be the highest thought of life!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your highest thought, however, ye shall have it commanded unto you by me—and it is this: man is something that is to be surpassed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So live your life of obedience and of war! What matter about long life! What warrior wisheth to be spared!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I spare you not, I love you from my very heart, my brethren in war!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XI. THE NEW IDOL.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Somewhere there are still peoples and herds, but not with us, my brethren: here there are states.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A state? What is that? Well! open now your ears unto me, for now will I say unto you my word concerning the death of peoples.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A state, is called the coldest of all cold monsters. Coldly lieth it also; and this lie creepeth from its mouth: “I, the state, am the people.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is a lie! Creators were they who created peoples, and hung a faith and a love over them: thus they served life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Destroyers, are they who lay snares for many, and call it the state: they hang a sword and a hundred cravings over them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where there is still a people, there the state is not understood, but hated as the evil eye, and as sin against laws and customs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This sign I give unto you: every people speaketh its language of good and evil: this its neighbour understandeth not. Its language hath it devised for itself in laws and customs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the state lieth in all languages of good and evil; and whatever it saith it lieth; and whatever it hath it hath stolen.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>False is everything in it; with stolen teeth it biteth, the biting one. False are even its bowels.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Confusion of language of good and evil; this sign I give unto you as the sign of the state. Verily, the will to death, indicateth this sign! Verily, it beckoneth unto the preachers of death!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many too many are born: for the superfluous ones was the state devised!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See just how it enticeth them to it, the many-too-many! How it swalloweth and cheweth and recheweth them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“On earth there is nothing greater than I: it is I who am the regulating finger of God”—thus roareth the monster. And not only the long-eared and short-sighted fall upon their knees!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! even in your ears, ye great souls, it whispereth its gloomy lies! Ah! it findeth out the rich hearts which willingly lavish themselves!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, it findeth you out too, ye conquerors of the old God! Weary ye became of the conflict, and now your weariness serveth the new idol!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Heroes and honourable ones, it would fain set up around it, the new idol! Gladly it basketh in the sunshine of good consciences,—the cold monster!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything will it give YOU, if YE worship it, the new idol: thus it purchaseth the lustre of your virtue, and the glance of your proud eyes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It seeketh to allure by means of you, the many-too-many! Yea, a hellish artifice hath here been devised, a death-horse jingling with the trappings of divine honours!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, a dying for many hath here been devised, which glorifieth itself as life: verily, a hearty service unto all preachers of death!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The state, I call it, where all are poison-drinkers, the good and the bad: the state, where all lose themselves, the good and the bad: the state, where the slow suicide of all—is called “life.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Just see these superfluous ones! They steal the works of the inventors and the treasures of the wise. Culture, they call their theft—and everything becometh sickness and trouble unto them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Just see these superfluous ones! Sick are they always; they vomit their bile and call it a newspaper. They devour one another, and cannot even digest themselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Just see these superfluous ones! Wealth they acquire and become poorer thereby. Power they seek for, and above all, the lever of power, much money—these impotent ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See them clamber, these nimble apes! They clamber over one another, and thus scuffle into the mud and the abyss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Towards the throne they all strive: it is their madness—as if happiness sat on the throne! Ofttimes sitteth filth on the throne.—and ofttimes also the throne on filth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Madmen they all seem to me, and clambering apes, and too eager. Badly smelleth their idol to me, the cold monster: badly they all smell to me, these idolaters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brethren, will ye suffocate in the fumes of their maws and appetites! Better break the windows and jump into the open air!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do go out of the way of the bad odour! Withdraw from the idolatry of the superfluous!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do go out of the way of the bad odour! Withdraw from the steam of these human sacrifices!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Open still remaineth the earth for great souls. Empty are still many sites for lone ones and twain ones, around which floateth the odour of tranquil seas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Open still remaineth a free life for great souls. Verily, he who possesseth little is so much the less possessed: blessed be moderate poverty!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There, where the state ceaseth—there only commenceth the man who is not superfluous: there commenceth the song of the necessary ones, the single and irreplaceable melody.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There, where the state CEASETH—pray look thither, my brethren! Do ye not see it, the rainbow and the bridges of the Superman?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XII. THE FLIES IN THE MARKET-PLACE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Flee, my friend, into thy solitude! I see thee deafened with the noise of the great men, and stung all over with the stings of the little ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Admirably do forest and rock know how to be silent with thee. Resemble again the tree which thou lovest, the broad-branched one—silently and attentively it o’erhangeth the sea.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where solitude endeth, there beginneth the market-place; and where the market-place beginneth, there beginneth also the noise of the great actors, and the buzzing of the poison-flies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the world even the best things are worthless without those who represent them: those representers, the people call great men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Little do the people understand what is great—that is to say, the creating agency. But they have a taste for all representers and actors of great things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Around the devisers of new values revolveth the world:—invisibly it revolveth. But around the actors revolve the people and the glory: such is the course of things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Spirit, hath the actor, but little conscience of the spirit. He believeth always in that wherewith he maketh believe most strongly—in HIMSELF!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Tomorrow he hath a new belief, and the day after, one still newer. Sharp perceptions hath he, like the people, and changeable humours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To upset—that meaneth with him to prove. To drive mad—that meaneth with him to convince. And blood is counted by him as the best of all arguments.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A truth which only glideth into fine ears, he calleth falsehood and trumpery. Verily, he believeth only in Gods that make a great noise in the world!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Full of clattering buffoons is the market-place,—and the people glory in their great men! These are for them the masters of the hour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the hour presseth them; so they press thee. And also from thee they want Yea or Nay. Alas! thou wouldst set thy chair betwixt For and Against?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On account of those absolute and impatient ones, be not jealous, thou lover of truth! Never yet did truth cling to the arm of an absolute one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On account of those abrupt ones, return into thy security: only in the market-place is one assailed by Yea? or Nay?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Slow is the experience of all deep fountains: long have they to wait until they know WHAT hath fallen into their depths.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away from the market-place and from fame taketh place all that is great: away from the market-place and from fame have ever dwelt the devisers of new values.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Flee, my friend, into thy solitude: I see thee stung all over by the poisonous flies. Flee thither, where a rough, strong breeze bloweth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Flee into thy solitude! Thou hast lived too closely to the small and the pitiable. Flee from their invisible vengeance! Towards thee they have nothing but vengeance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Raise no longer an arm against them! Innumerable are they, and it is not thy lot to be a fly-flap.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Innumerable are the small and pitiable ones; and of many a proud structure, rain-drops and weeds have been the ruin.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou art not stone; but already hast thou become hollow by the numerous drops. Thou wilt yet break and burst by the numerous drops.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Exhausted I see thee, by poisonous flies; bleeding I see thee, and torn at a hundred spots; and thy pride will not even upbraid.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Blood they would have from thee in all innocence; blood their bloodless souls crave for—and they sting, therefore, in all innocence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thou, profound one, thou sufferest too profoundly even from small wounds; and ere thou hadst recovered, the same poison-worm crawled over thy hand.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too proud art thou to kill these sweet-tooths. But take care lest it be thy fate to suffer all their poisonous injustice!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They buzz around thee also with their praise: obtrusiveness, is their praise. They want to be close to thy skin and thy blood.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They flatter thee, as one flattereth a God or devil; they whimper before thee, as before a God or devil. What doth it come to! Flatterers are they, and whimperers, and nothing more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Often, also, do they show themselves to thee as amiable ones. But that hath ever been the prudence of the cowardly. Yea! the cowardly are wise!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They think much about thee with their circumscribed souls—thou art always suspected by them! Whatever is much thought about is at last thought suspicious.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They punish thee for all thy virtues. They pardon thee in their inmost hearts only—for thine errors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Because thou art gentle and of upright character, thou sayest: “Blameless are they for their small existence.” But their circumscribed souls think: “Blamable is all great existence.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even when thou art gentle towards them, they still feel themselves despised by thee; and they repay thy beneficence with secret maleficence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thy silent pride is always counter to their taste; they rejoice if once thou be humble enough to be frivolous.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What we recognise in a man, we also irritate in him. Therefore be on your guard against the small ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In thy presence they feel themselves small, and their baseness gleameth and gloweth against thee in invisible vengeance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sawest thou not how often they became dumb when thou approachedst them, and how their energy left them like the smoke of an extinguishing fire?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, my friend, the bad conscience art thou of thy neighbours; for they are unworthy of thee. Therefore they hate thee, and would fain suck thy blood.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thy neighbours will always be poisonous flies; what is great in thee—that itself must make them more poisonous, and always more fly-like.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Flee, my friend, into thy solitude—and thither, where a rough strong breeze bloweth. It is not thy lot to be a fly-flap.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XIII. CHASTITY.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love the forest. It is bad to live in cities: there, there are too many of the lustful.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is it not better to fall into the hands of a murderer, than into the dreams of a lustful woman?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And just look at these men: their eye saith it—they know nothing better on earth than to lie with a woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Filth is at the bottom of their souls; and alas! if their filth hath still spirit in it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Would that ye were perfect—at least as animals! But to animals belongeth innocence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do I counsel you to slay your instincts? I counsel you to innocence in your instincts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do I counsel you to chastity? Chastity is a virtue with some, but with many almost a vice.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These are continent, to be sure: but doggish lust looketh enviously out of all that they do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even into the heights of their virtue and into their cold spirit doth this creature follow them, with its discord.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And how nicely can doggish lust beg for a piece of spirit, when a piece of flesh is denied it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye love tragedies and all that breaketh the heart? But I am distrustful of your doggish lust.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye have too cruel eyes, and ye look wantonly towards the sufferers. Hath not your lust just disguised itself and taken the name of fellow-suffering?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And also this parable give I unto you: Not a few who meant to cast out their devil, went thereby into the swine themselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To whom chastity is difficult, it is to be dissuaded: lest it become the road to hell—to filth and lust of soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do I speak of filthy things? That is not the worst thing for me to do.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not when the truth is filthy, but when it is shallow, doth the discerning one go unwillingly into its waters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, there are chaste ones from their very nature; they are gentler of heart, and laugh better and oftener than you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They laugh also at chastity, and ask: “What is chastity?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is chastity not folly? But the folly came unto us, and not we unto it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We offered that guest harbour and heart: now it dwelleth with us—let it stay as long as it will!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XIV. THE FRIEND.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“One, is always too many about me”—thinketh the anchorite. “Always once one—that maketh two in the long run!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I and me are always too earnestly in conversation: how could it be endured, if there were not a friend?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The friend of the anchorite is always the third one: the third one is the cork which preventeth the conversation of the two sinking into the depth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! there are too many depths for all anchorites. Therefore, do they long so much for a friend, and for his elevation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Our faith in others betrayeth wherein we would fain have faith in ourselves. Our longing for a friend is our betrayer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And often with our love we want merely to overleap envy. And often we attack and make ourselves enemies, to conceal that we are vulnerable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Be at least mine enemy!”—thus speaketh the true reverence, which doth not venture to solicit friendship.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If one would have a friend, then must one also be willing to wage war for him: and in order to wage war, one must be CAPABLE of being an enemy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One ought still to honour the enemy in one’s friend. Canst thou go nigh unto thy friend, and not go over to him?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In one’s friend one shall have one’s best enemy. Thou shalt be closest unto him with thy heart when thou withstandest him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou wouldst wear no raiment before thy friend? It is in honour of thy friend that thou showest thyself to him as thou art? But he wisheth thee to the devil on that account!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who maketh no secret of himself shocketh: so much reason have ye to fear nakedness! Aye, if ye were Gods, ye could then be ashamed of clothing!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou canst not adorn thyself fine enough for thy friend; for thou shalt be unto him an arrow and a longing for the Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sawest thou ever thy friend asleep—to know how he looketh? What is usually the countenance of thy friend? It is thine own countenance, in a coarse and imperfect mirror.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sawest thou ever thy friend asleep? Wert thou not dismayed at thy friend looking so? O my friend, man is something that hath to be surpassed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In divining and keeping silence shall the friend be a master: not everything must thou wish to see. Thy dream shall disclose unto thee what thy friend doeth when awake.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let thy pity be a divining: to know first if thy friend wanteth pity. Perhaps he loveth in thee the unmoved eye, and the look of eternity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let thy pity for thy friend be hid under a hard shell; thou shalt bite out a tooth upon it. Thus will it have delicacy and sweetness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou pure air and solitude and bread and medicine to thy friend? Many a one cannot loosen his own fetters, but is nevertheless his friend’s emancipator.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou a slave? Then thou canst not be a friend. Art thou a tyrant? Then thou canst not have friends.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Far too long hath there been a slave and a tyrant concealed in woman. On that account woman is not yet capable of friendship: she knoweth only love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In woman’s love there is injustice and blindness to all she doth not love. And even in woman’s conscious love, there is still always surprise and lightning and night, along with the light.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet woman is not capable of friendship: women are still cats, and birds. Or at the best, cows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet woman is not capable of friendship. But tell me, ye men, who of you are capable of friendship?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh! your poverty, ye men, and your sordidness of soul! As much as ye give to your friend, will I give even to my foe, and will not have become poorer thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is comradeship: may there be friendship!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XV. THE THOUSAND AND ONE GOALS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many lands saw Zarathustra, and many peoples: thus he discovered the good and bad of many peoples. No greater power did Zarathustra find on earth than good and bad.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No people could live without first valuing; if a people will maintain itself, however, it must not value as its neighbour valueth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Much that passed for good with one people was regarded with scorn and contempt by another: thus I found it. Much found I here called bad, which was there decked with purple honours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never did the one neighbour understand the other: ever did his soul marvel at his neighbour’s delusion and wickedness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A table of excellencies hangeth over every people. Lo! it is the table of their triumphs; lo! it is the voice of their Will to Power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is laudable, what they think hard; what is indispensable and hard they call good; and what relieveth in the direst distress, the unique and hardest of all,—they extol as holy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whatever maketh them rule and conquer and shine, to the dismay and envy of their neighbours, they regard as the high and foremost thing, the test and the meaning of all else.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, my brother, if thou knewest but a people’s need, its land, its sky, and its neighbour, then wouldst thou divine the law of its surmountings, and why it climbeth up that ladder to its hope.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Always shalt thou be the foremost and prominent above others: no one shall thy jealous soul love, except a friend”—that made the soul of a Greek thrill: thereby went he his way to greatness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“To speak truth, and be skilful with bow and arrow”—so seemed it alike pleasing and hard to the people from whom cometh my name—the name which is alike pleasing and hard to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“To honour father and mother, and from the root of the soul to do their will”—this table of surmounting hung another people over them, and became powerful and permanent thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“To have fidelity, and for the sake of fidelity to risk honour and blood, even in evil and dangerous courses”—teaching itself so, another people mastered itself, and thus mastering itself, became pregnant and heavy with great hopes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, men have given unto themselves all their good and bad. Verily, they took it not, they found it not, it came not unto them as a voice from heaven.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Values did man only assign to things in order to maintain himself—he created only the significance of things, a human significance! Therefore, calleth he himself “man,” that is, the valuator.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Valuing is creating: hear it, ye creating ones! Valuation itself is the treasure and jewel of the valued things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Through valuation only is there value; and without valuation the nut of existence would be hollow. Hear it, ye creating ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Change of values—that is, change of the creating ones. Always doth he destroy who hath to be a creator.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Creating ones were first of all peoples, and only in late times individuals; verily, the individual himself is still the latest creation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Peoples once hung over them tables of the good. Love which would rule and love which would obey, created for themselves such tables.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Older is the pleasure in the herd than the pleasure in the ego: and as long as the good conscience is for the herd, the bad conscience only saith: ego.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, the crafty ego, the loveless one, that seeketh its advantage in the advantage of many—it is not the origin of the herd, but its ruin.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Loving ones, was it always, and creating ones, that created good and bad. Fire of love gloweth in the names of all the virtues, and fire of wrath.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many lands saw Zarathustra, and many peoples: no greater power did Zarathustra find on earth than the creations of the loving ones—“good” and “bad” are they called.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a prodigy is this power of praising and blaming. Tell me, ye brethren, who will master it for me? Who will put a fetter upon the thousand necks of this animal?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A thousand goals have there been hitherto, for a thousand peoples have there been. Only the fetter for the thousand necks is still lacking; there is lacking the one goal. As yet humanity hath not a goal.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But pray tell me, my brethren, if the goal of humanity be still lacking, is there not also still lacking—humanity itself?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XVI. NEIGHBOUR-LOVE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye crowd around your neighbour, and have fine words for it. But I say unto you: your neighbour-love is your bad love of yourselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye flee unto your neighbour from yourselves, and would fain make a virtue thereof: but I fathom your “unselfishness.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The THOU is older than the <i>I</i>; the THOU hath been consecrated, but not yet the <i>I</i>: so man presseth nigh unto his neighbour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do I advise you to neighbour-love? Rather do I advise you to neighbour-flight and to furthest love!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Higher than love to your neighbour is love to the furthest and future ones; higher still than love to men, is love to things and phantoms.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The phantom that runneth on before thee, my brother, is fairer than thou; why dost thou not give unto it thy flesh and thy bones? But thou fearest, and runnest unto thy neighbour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye cannot endure it with yourselves, and do not love yourselves sufficiently: so ye seek to mislead your neighbour into love, and would fain gild yourselves with his error.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Would that ye could not endure it with any kind of near ones, or their neighbours; then would ye have to create your friend and his overflowing heart out of yourselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye call in a witness when ye want to speak well of yourselves; and when ye have misled him to think well of you, ye also think well of yourselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not only doth he lie, who speaketh contrary to his knowledge, but more so, he who speaketh contrary to his ignorance. And thus speak ye of yourselves in your intercourse, and belie your neighbour with yourselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus saith the fool: “Association with men spoileth the character, especially when one hath none.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The one goeth to his neighbour because he seeketh himself, and the other because he would fain lose himself. Your bad love to yourselves maketh solitude a prison to you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The furthest ones are they who pay for your love to the near ones; and when there are but five of you together, a sixth must always die.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love not your festivals either: too many actors found I there, and even the spectators often behaved like actors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not the neighbour do I teach you, but the friend. Let the friend be the festival of the earth to you, and a foretaste of the Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I teach you the friend and his overflowing heart. But one must know how to be a sponge, if one would be loved by overflowing hearts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I teach you the friend in whom the world standeth complete, a capsule of the good,—the creating friend, who hath always a complete world to bestow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And as the world unrolled itself for him, so rolleth it together again for him in rings, as the growth of good through evil, as the growth of purpose out of chance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let the future and the furthest be the motive of thy to-day; in thy friend shalt thou love the Superman as thy motive.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My brethren, I advise you not to neighbour-love—I advise you to furthest love!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XVII. THE WAY OF THE CREATING ONE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Wouldst thou go into isolation, my brother? Wouldst thou seek the way unto thyself? Tarry yet a little and hearken unto me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“He who seeketh may easily get lost himself. All isolation is wrong”: so say the herd. And long didst thou belong to the herd.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The voice of the herd will still echo in thee. And when thou sayest, “I have no longer a conscience in common with you,” then will it be a plaint and a pain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, that pain itself did the same conscience produce; and the last gleam of that conscience still gloweth on thine affliction.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thou wouldst go the way of thine affliction, which is the way unto thyself? Then show me thine authority and thy strength to do so!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou a new strength and a new authority? A first motion? A self-rolling wheel? Canst thou also compel stars to revolve around thee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas! there is so much lusting for loftiness! There are so many convulsions of the ambitions! Show me that thou art not a lusting and ambitious one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas! there are so many great thoughts that do nothing more than the bellows: they inflate, and make emptier than ever.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Free, dost thou call thyself? Thy ruling thought would I hear of, and not that thou hast escaped from a yoke.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou one ENTITLED to escape from a yoke? Many a one hath cast away his final worth when he hath cast away his servitude.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Free from what? What doth that matter to Zarathustra! Clearly, however, shall thine eye show unto me: free FOR WHAT?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Canst thou give unto thyself thy bad and thy good, and set up thy will as a law over thee? Canst thou be judge for thyself, and avenger of thy law?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Terrible is aloneness with the judge and avenger of one’s own law. Thus is a star projected into desert space, and into the icy breath of aloneness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To-day sufferest thou still from the multitude, thou individual; to-day hast thou still thy courage unabated, and thy hopes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But one day will the solitude weary thee; one day will thy pride yield, and thy courage quail. Thou wilt one day cry: “I am alone!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One day wilt thou see no longer thy loftiness, and see too closely thy lowliness; thy sublimity itself will frighten thee as a phantom. Thou wilt one day cry: “All is false!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are feelings which seek to slay the lonesome one; if they do not succeed, then must they themselves die! But art thou capable of it—to be a murderer?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hast thou ever known, my brother, the word “disdain”? And the anguish of thy justice in being just to those that disdain thee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou forcest many to think differently about thee; that, charge they heavily to thine account. Thou camest nigh unto them, and yet wentest past: for that they never forgive thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou goest beyond them: but the higher thou risest, the smaller doth the eye of envy see thee. Most of all, however, is the flying one hated.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“How could ye be just unto me!”—must thou say—“I choose your injustice as my allotted portion.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Injustice and filth cast they at the lonesome one: but, my brother, if thou wouldst be a star, thou must shine for them none the less on that account!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And be on thy guard against the good and just! They would fain crucify those who devise their own virtue—they hate the lonesome ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Be on thy guard, also, against holy simplicity! All is unholy to it that is not simple; fain, likewise, would it play with the fire—of the fagot and stake.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And be on thy guard, also, against the assaults of thy love! Too readily doth the recluse reach his hand to any one who meeteth him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To many a one mayest thou not give thy hand, but only thy paw; and I wish thy paw also to have claws.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the worst enemy thou canst meet, wilt thou thyself always be; thou waylayest thyself in caverns and forests.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou lonesome one, thou goest the way to thyself! And past thyself and thy seven devils leadeth thy way!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A heretic wilt thou be to thyself, and a wizard and a sooth-sayer, and a fool, and a doubter, and a reprobate, and a villain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ready must thou be to burn thyself in thine own flame; how couldst thou become new if thou have not first become ashes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou lonesome one, thou goest the way of the creating one: a God wilt thou create for thyself out of thy seven devils!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou lonesome one, thou goest the way of the loving one: thou lovest thyself, and on that account despisest thou thyself, as only the loving ones despise.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To create, desireth the loving one, because he despiseth! What knoweth he of love who hath not been obliged to despise just what he loved!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thy love, go into thine isolation, my brother, and with thy creating; and late only will justice limp after thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With my tears, go into thine isolation, my brother. I love him who seeketh to create beyond himself, and thus succumbeth.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XVIII. OLD AND YOUNG WOMEN.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why stealest thou along so furtively in the twilight, Zarathustra? And what hidest thou so carefully under thy mantle?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is it a treasure that hath been given thee? Or a child that hath been born thee? Or goest thou thyself on a thief’s errand, thou friend of the evil?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, my brother, said Zarathustra, it is a treasure that hath been given me: it is a little truth which I carry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it is naughty, like a young child; and if I hold not its mouth, it screameth too loudly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As I went on my way alone to-day, at the hour when the sun declineth, there met me an old woman, and she spake thus unto my soul:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Much hath Zarathustra spoken also to us women, but never spake he unto us concerning woman.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered her: “Concerning woman, one should only talk unto men.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Talk also unto me of woman,” said she; “I am old enough to forget it presently.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I obliged the old woman and spake thus unto her:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything in woman is a riddle, and everything in woman hath one solution—it is called pregnancy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man is for woman a means: the purpose is always the child. But what is woman for man?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Two different things wanteth the true man: danger and diversion. Therefore wanteth he woman, as the most dangerous plaything.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man shall be trained for war, and woman for the recreation of the warrior: all else is folly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too sweet fruits—these the warrior liketh not. Therefore liketh he woman;—bitter is even the sweetest woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better than man doth woman understand children, but man is more childish than woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the true man there is a child hidden: it wanteth to play. Up then, ye women, and discover the child in man!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A plaything let woman be, pure and fine like the precious stone, illumined with the virtues of a world not yet come.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let the beam of a star shine in your love! Let your hope say: “May I bear the Superman!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In your love let there be valour! With your love shall ye assail him who inspireth you with fear!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In your love be your honour! Little doth woman understand otherwise about honour. But let this be your honour: always to love more than ye are loved, and never be the second.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let man fear woman when she loveth: then maketh she every sacrifice, and everything else she regardeth as worthless.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let man fear woman when she hateth: for man in his innermost soul is merely evil; woman, however, is mean.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whom hateth woman most?—Thus spake the iron to the loadstone: “I hate thee most, because thou attractest, but art too weak to draw unto thee.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The happiness of man is, “I will.” The happiness of woman is, “He will.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Lo! now hath the world become perfect!”—thus thinketh every woman when she obeyeth with all her love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Obey, must the woman, and find a depth for her surface. Surface, is woman’s soul, a mobile, stormy film on shallow water.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man’s soul, however, is deep, its current gusheth in subterranean caverns: woman surmiseth its force, but comprehendeth it not.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then answered me the old woman: “Many fine things hath Zarathustra said, especially for those who are young enough for them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Strange! Zarathustra knoweth little about woman, and yet he is right about them! Doth this happen, because with women nothing is impossible?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now accept a little truth by way of thanks! I am old enough for it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Swaddle it up and hold its mouth: otherwise it will scream too loudly, the little truth.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Give me, woman, thy little truth!” said I. And thus spake the old woman:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou goest to women? Do not forget thy whip!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XIX. THE BITE OF THE ADDER.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One day had Zarathustra fallen asleep under a fig-tree, owing to the heat, with his arms over his face. And there came an adder and bit him in the neck, so that Zarathustra screamed with pain. When he had taken his arm from his face he looked at the serpent; and then did it recognise the eyes of Zarathustra, wriggled awkwardly, and tried to get away. “Not at all,” said Zarathustra, “as yet hast thou not received my thanks! Thou hast awakened me in time; my journey is yet long.” “Thy journey is short,” said the adder sadly; “my poison is fatal.” Zarathustra smiled. “When did ever a dragon die of a serpent’s poison?”—said he. “But take thy poison back! Thou art not rich enough to present it to me.” Then fell the adder again on his neck, and licked his wound.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra once told this to his disciples they asked him: “And what, O Zarathustra, is the moral of thy story?” And Zarathustra answered them thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The destroyer of morality, the good and just call me: my story is immoral.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When, however, ye have an enemy, then return him not good for evil: for that would abash him. But prove that he hath done something good to you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And rather be angry than abash any one! And when ye are cursed, it pleaseth me not that ye should then desire to bless. Rather curse a little also!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And should a great injustice befall you, then do quickly five small ones besides. Hideous to behold is he on whom injustice presseth alone.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did ye ever know this? Shared injustice is half justice. And he who can bear it, shall take the injustice upon himself!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A small revenge is humaner than no revenge at all. And if the punishment be not also a right and an honour to the transgressor, I do not like your punishing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nobler is it to own oneself in the wrong than to establish one’s right, especially if one be in the right. Only, one must be rich enough to do so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I do not like your cold justice; out of the eye of your judges there always glanceth the executioner and his cold steel.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Tell me: where find we justice, which is love with seeing eyes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Devise me, then, the love which not only beareth all punishment, but also all guilt!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Devise me, then, the justice which acquitteth every one except the judge!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And would ye hear this likewise? To him who seeketh to be just from the heart, even the lie becometh philanthropy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But how could I be just from the heart! How can I give every one his own! Let this be enough for me: I give unto every one mine own.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Finally, my brethren, guard against doing wrong to any anchorite. How could an anchorite forget! How could he requite!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like a deep well is an anchorite. Easy is it to throw in a stone: if it should sink to the bottom, however, tell me, who will bring it out again?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Guard against injuring the anchorite! If ye have done so, however, well then, kill him also!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XX. CHILD AND MARRIAGE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I have a question for thee alone, my brother: like a sounding-lead, cast I this question into thy soul, that I may know its depth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou art young, and desirest child and marriage. But I ask thee: Art thou a man ENTITLED to desire a child?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou the victorious one, the self-conqueror, the ruler of thy passions, the master of thy virtues? Thus do I ask thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or doth the animal speak in thy wish, and necessity? Or isolation? Or discord in thee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I would have thy victory and freedom long for a child. Living monuments shalt thou build to thy victory and emancipation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beyond thyself shalt thou build. But first of all must thou be built thyself, rectangular in body and soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not only onward shalt thou propagate thyself, but upward! For that purpose may the garden of marriage help thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A higher body shalt thou create, a first movement, a spontaneously rolling wheel—a creating one shalt thou create.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000000999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Marriage: so call I the will of the twain to create the one that is more than those who created it. The reverence for one another, as those exercising such a will, call I marriage.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let this be the significance and the truth of thy marriage. But that which the many-too-many call marriage, those superfluous ones—ah, what shall I call it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, the poverty of soul in the twain! Ah, the filth of soul in the twain! Ah, the pitiable self-complacency in the twain!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Marriage they call it all; and they say their marriages are made in heaven.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well, I do not like it, that heaven of the superfluous! No, I do not like them, those animals tangled in the heavenly toils!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Far from me also be the God who limpeth thither to bless what he hath not matched!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Laugh not at such marriages! What child hath not had reason to weep over its parents?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Worthy did this man seem, and ripe for the meaning of the earth: but when I saw his wife, the earth seemed to me a home for madcaps.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, I would that the earth shook with convulsions when a saint and a goose mate with one another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This one went forth in quest of truth as a hero, and at last got for himself a small decked-up lie: his marriage he calleth it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That one was reserved in intercourse and chose choicely. But one time he spoilt his company for all time: his marriage he calleth it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Another sought a handmaid with the virtues of an angel. But all at once he became the handmaid of a woman, and now would he need also to become an angel.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Careful, have I found all buyers, and all of them have astute eyes. But even the astutest of them buyeth his wife in a sack.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many short follies—that is called love by you. And your marriage putteth an end to many short follies, with one long stupidity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your love to woman, and woman’s love to man—ah, would that it were sympathy for suffering and veiled deities! But generally two animals alight on one another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But even your best love is only an enraptured simile and a painful ardour. It is a torch to light you to loftier paths.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beyond yourselves shall ye love some day! Then LEARN first of all to love. And on that account ye had to drink the bitter cup of your love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Bitterness is in the cup even of the best love: thus doth it cause longing for the Superman; thus doth it cause thirst in thee, the creating one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thirst in the creating one, arrow and longing for the Superman: tell me, my brother, is this thy will to marriage?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Holy call I such a will, and such a marriage.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXI. VOLUNTARY DEATH.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many die too late, and some die too early. Yet strange soundeth the precept: “Die at the right time!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Die at the right time: so teacheth Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, he who never liveth at the right time, how could he ever die at the right time? Would that he might never be born!—Thus do I advise the superfluous ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But even the superfluous ones make much ado about their death, and even the hollowest nut wanteth to be cracked.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every one regardeth dying as a great matter: but as yet death is not a festival. Not yet have people learned to inaugurate the finest festivals.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The consummating death I show unto you, which becometh a stimulus and promise to the living.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His death, dieth the consummating one triumphantly, surrounded by hoping and promising ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus should one learn to die; and there should be no festival at which such a dying one doth not consecrate the oaths of the living!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus to die is best; the next best, however, is to die in battle, and sacrifice a great soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But to the fighter equally hateful as to the victor, is your grinning death which stealeth nigh like a thief,—and yet cometh as master.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My death, praise I unto you, the voluntary death, which cometh unto me because <i>I</i> want it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when shall I want it?—He that hath a goal and an heir, wanteth death at the right time for the goal and the heir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And out of reverence for the goal and the heir, he will hang up no more withered wreaths in the sanctuary of life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, not the rope-makers will I resemble: they lengthen out their cord, and thereby go ever backward.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many a one, also, waxeth too old for his truths and triumphs; a toothless mouth hath no longer the right to every truth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whoever wanteth to have fame, must take leave of honour betimes, and practise the difficult art of—going at the right time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One must discontinue being feasted upon when one tasteth best: that is known by those who want to be long loved.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sour apples are there, no doubt, whose lot is to wait until the last day of autumn: and at the same time they become ripe, yellow, and shrivelled.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In some ageth the heart first, and in others the spirit. And some are hoary in youth, but the late young keep long young.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To many men life is a failure; a poison-worm gnaweth at their heart. Then let them see to it that their dying is all the more a success.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many never become sweet; they rot even in the summer. It is cowardice that holdeth them fast to their branches.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Far too many live, and far too long hang they on their branches. Would that a storm came and shook all this rottenness and worm-eatenness from the tree!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Would that there came preachers of SPEEDY death! Those would be the appropriate storms and agitators of the trees of life! But I hear only slow death preached, and patience with all that is “earthly.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! ye preach patience with what is earthly? This earthly is it that hath too much patience with you, ye blasphemers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, too early died that Hebrew whom the preachers of slow death honour: and to many hath it proved a calamity that he died too early.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet had he known only tears, and the melancholy of the Hebrews, together with the hatred of the good and just—the Hebrew Jesus: then was he seized with the longing for death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Had he but remained in the wilderness, and far from the good and just! Then, perhaps, would he have learned to live, and love the earth—and laughter also!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Believe it, my brethren! He died too early; he himself would have disavowed his doctrine had he attained to my age! Noble enough was he to disavow!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But he was still immature. Immaturely loveth the youth, and immaturely also hateth he man and earth. Confined and awkward are still his soul and the wings of his spirit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But in man there is more of the child than in the youth, and less of melancholy: better understandeth he about life and death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Free for death, and free in death; a holy Naysayer, when there is no longer time for Yea: thus understandeth he about death and life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That your dying may not be a reproach to man and the earth, my friends: that do I solicit from the honey of your soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In your dying shall your spirit and your virtue still shine like an evening after-glow around the earth: otherwise your dying hath been unsatisfactory.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus will I die myself, that ye friends may love the earth more for my sake; and earth will I again become, to have rest in her that bore me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a goal had Zarathustra; he threw his ball. Now be ye friends the heirs of my goal; to you throw I the golden ball.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Best of all, do I see you, my friends, throw the golden ball! And so tarry I still a little while on the earth—pardon me for it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXII. THE BESTOWING VIRTUE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had taken leave of the town to which his heart was attached, the name of which is “The Pied Cow,” there followed him many people who called themselves his disciples, and kept him company. Thus came they to a crossroad. Then Zarathustra told them that he now wanted to go alone; for he was fond of going alone. His disciples, however, presented him at his departure with a staff, on the golden handle of which a serpent twined round the sun. Zarathustra rejoiced on account of the staff, and supported himself thereon; then spake he thus to his disciples:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Tell me, pray: how came gold to the highest value? Because it is uncommon, and unprofiting, and beaming, and soft in lustre; it always bestoweth itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Only as image of the highest virtue came gold to the highest value. Goldlike, beameth the glance of the bestower. Gold-lustre maketh peace between moon and sun.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Uncommon is the highest virtue, and unprofiting, beaming is it, and soft of lustre: a bestowing virtue is the highest virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I divine you well, my disciples: ye strive like me for the bestowing virtue. What should ye have in common with cats and wolves?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is your thirst to become sacrifices and gifts yourselves: and therefore have ye the thirst to accumulate all riches in your soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Insatiably striveth your soul for treasures and jewels, because your virtue is insatiable in desiring to bestow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye constrain all things to flow towards you and into you, so that they shall flow back again out of your fountain as the gifts of your love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, an appropriator of all values must such bestowing love become; but healthy and holy, call I this selfishness.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Another selfishness is there, an all-too-poor and hungry kind, which would always steal—the selfishness of the sick, the sickly selfishness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the eye of the thief it looketh upon all that is lustrous; with the craving of hunger it measureth him who hath abundance; and ever doth it prowl round the tables of bestowers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sickness speaketh in such craving, and invisible degeneration; of a sickly body, speaketh the larcenous craving of this selfishness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Tell me, my brother, what do we think bad, and worst of all? Is it not DEGENERATION?—And we always suspect degeneration when the bestowing soul is lacking.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Upward goeth our course from genera on to super-genera. But a horror to us is the degenerating sense, which saith: “All for myself.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Upward soareth our sense: thus is it a simile of our body, a simile of an elevation. Such similes of elevations are the names of the virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus goeth the body through history, a becomer and fighter. And the spirit—what is it to the body? Its fights’ and victories’ herald, its companion and echo.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Similes, are all names of good and evil; they do not speak out, they only hint. A fool who seeketh knowledge from them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Give heed, my brethren, to every hour when your spirit would speak in similes: there is the origin of your virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Elevated is then your body, and raised up; with its delight, enraptureth it the spirit; so that it becometh creator, and valuer, and lover, and everything’s benefactor.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When your heart overfloweth broad and full like the river, a blessing and a danger to the lowlanders: there is the origin of your virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When ye are exalted above praise and blame, and your will would command all things, as a loving one’s will: there is the origin of your virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When ye despise pleasant things, and the effeminate couch, and cannot couch far enough from the effeminate: there is the origin of your virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When ye are willers of one will, and when that change of every need is needful to you: there is the origin of your virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a new good and evil is it! Verily, a new deep murmuring, and the voice of a new fountain!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Power is it, this new virtue; a ruling thought is it, and around it a subtle soul: a golden sun, with the serpent of knowledge around it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here paused Zarathustra awhile, and looked lovingly on his disciples. Then he continued to speak thus—and his voice had changed:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Remain true to the earth, my brethren, with the power of your virtue! Let your bestowing love and your knowledge be devoted to be the meaning of the earth! Thus do I pray and conjure you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let it not fly away from the earthly and beat against eternal walls with its wings! Ah, there hath always been so much flown-away virtue!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lead, like me, the flown-away virtue back to the earth—yea, back to body and life: that it may give to the earth its meaning, a human meaning!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A hundred times hitherto hath spirit as well as virtue flown away and blundered. Alas! in our body dwelleth still all this delusion and blundering: body and will hath it there become.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A hundred times hitherto hath spirit as well as virtue attempted and erred. Yea, an attempt hath man been. Alas, much ignorance and error hath become embodied in us!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not only the rationality of millenniums—also their madness, breaketh out in us. Dangerous is it to be an heir.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still fight we step by step with the giant Chance, and over all mankind hath hitherto ruled nonsense, the lack-of-sense.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let your spirit and your virtue be devoted to the sense of the earth, my brethren: let the value of everything be determined anew by you! Therefore shall ye be fighters! Therefore shall ye be creators!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Intelligently doth the body purify itself; attempting with intelligence it exalteth itself; to the discerners all impulses sanctify themselves; to the exalted the soul becometh joyful.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Physician, heal thyself: then wilt thou also heal thy patient. Let it be his best cure to see with his eyes him who maketh himself whole.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A thousand paths are there which have never yet been trodden; a thousand salubrities and hidden islands of life. Unexhausted and undiscovered is still man and man’s world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Awake and hearken, ye lonesome ones! From the future come winds with stealthy pinions, and to fine ears good tidings are proclaimed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye lonesome ones of to-day, ye seceding ones, ye shall one day be a people: out of you who have chosen yourselves, shall a chosen people arise:—and out of it the Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a place of healing shall the earth become! And already is a new odour diffused around it, a salvation-bringing odour—and a new hope!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had spoken these words, he paused, like one who had not said his last word; and long did he balance the staff doubtfully in his hand. At last he spake thus—and his voice had changed:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I now go alone, my disciples! Ye also now go away, and alone! So will I have it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I advise you: depart from me, and guard yourselves against Zarathustra! And better still: be ashamed of him! Perhaps he hath deceived you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The man of knowledge must be able not only to love his enemies, but also to hate his friends.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One requiteth a teacher badly if one remain merely a scholar. And why will ye not pluck at my wreath?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye venerate me; but what if your veneration should some day collapse? Take heed lest a statue crush you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye say, ye believe in Zarathustra? But of what account is Zarathustra! Ye are my believers: but of what account are all believers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye had not yet sought yourselves: then did ye find me. So do all believers; therefore all belief is of so little account.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now do I bid you lose me and find yourselves; and only when ye have all denied me, will I return unto you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, with other eyes, my brethren, shall I then seek my lost ones; with another love shall I then love you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And once again shall ye have become friends unto me, and children of one hope: then will I be with you for the third time, to celebrate the great noontide with you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And it is the great noontide, when man is in the middle of his course between animal and Superman, and celebrateth his advance to the evening as his highest hope: for it is the advance to a new morning.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At such time will the down-goer bless himself, that he should be an over-goer; and the sun of his knowledge will be at noontide.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“DEAD ARE ALL THE GODS: NOW DO WE DESIRE THE SUPERMAN TO LIVE.”—Let this be our final will at the great noontide!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>THUS SPAKE ZARATHUSTRA. SECOND PART.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>“—and only when ye have all denied me, will I return unto you.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, with other eyes, my brethren, shall I then seek my lost ones; with another love shall I then love you.”—ZARATHUSTRA, I., “The Bestowing Virtue.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXIII. THE CHILD WITH THE MIRROR.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>After this Zarathustra returned again into the mountains to the solitude of his cave, and withdrew himself from men, waiting like a sower who hath scattered his seed. His soul, however, became impatient and full of longing for those whom he loved: because he had still much to give them. For this is hardest of all: to close the open hand out of love, and keep modest as a giver.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus passed with the lonesome one months and years; his wisdom meanwhile increased, and caused him pain by its abundance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One morning, however, he awoke ere the rosy dawn, and having meditated long on his couch, at last spake thus to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why did I startle in my dream, so that I awoke? Did not a child come to me, carrying a mirror?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra”—said the child unto me—“look at thyself in the mirror!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But when I looked into the mirror, I shrieked, and my heart throbbed: for not myself did I see therein, but a devil’s grimace and derision.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, all too well do I understand the dream’s portent and monition: my DOCTRINE is in danger; tares want to be called wheat!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mine enemies have grown powerful and have disfigured the likeness of my doctrine, so that my dearest ones have to blush for the gifts that I gave them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lost are my friends; the hour hath come for me to seek my lost ones!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With these words Zarathustra started up, not however like a person in anguish seeking relief, but rather like a seer and a singer whom the spirit inspireth. With amazement did his eagle and serpent gaze upon him: for a coming bliss overspread his countenance like the rosy dawn.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What hath happened unto me, mine animals?—said Zarathustra. Am I not transformed? Hath not bliss come unto me like a whirlwind?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Foolish is my happiness, and foolish things will it speak: it is still too young—so have patience with it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Wounded am I by my happiness: all sufferers shall be physicians unto me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To my friends can I again go down, and also to mine enemies! Zarathustra can again speak and bestow, and show his best love to his loved ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My impatient love overfloweth in streams,—down towards sunrise and sunset. Out of silent mountains and storms of affliction, rusheth my soul into the valleys.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too long have I longed and looked into the distance. Too long hath solitude possessed me: thus have I unlearned to keep silence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Utterance have I become altogether, and the brawling of a brook from high rocks: downward into the valleys will I hurl my speech.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And let the stream of my love sweep into unfrequented channels! How should a stream not finally find its way to the sea!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Forsooth, there is a lake in me, sequestered and self-sufficing; but the stream of my love beareth this along with it, down—to the sea!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>New paths do I tread, a new speech cometh unto me; tired have I become— like all creators—of the old tongues. No longer will my spirit walk on worn-out soles.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too slowly runneth all speaking for me:—into thy chariot, O storm, do I leap! And even thee will I whip with my spite!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like a cry and an huzza will I traverse wide seas, till I find the Happy Isles where my friends sojourn;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And mine enemies amongst them! How I now love every one unto whom I may but speak! Even mine enemies pertain to my bliss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I want to mount my wildest horse, then doth my spear always help me up best: it is my foot’s ever ready servant:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The spear which I hurl at mine enemies! How grateful am I to mine enemies that I may at last hurl it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too great hath been the tension of my cloud: ‘twixt laughters of lightnings will I cast hail-showers into the depths.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Violently will my breast then heave; violently will it blow its storm over the mountains: thus cometh its assuagement.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, like a storm cometh my happiness, and my freedom! But mine enemies shall think that THE EVIL ONE roareth over their heads.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, ye also, my friends, will be alarmed by my wild wisdom; and perhaps ye will flee therefrom, along with mine enemies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, that I knew how to lure you back with shepherds’ flutes! Ah, that my lioness wisdom would learn to roar softly! And much have we already learned with one another!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My wild wisdom became pregnant on the lonesome mountains; on the rough stones did she bear the youngest of her young.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now runneth she foolishly in the arid wilderness, and seeketh and seeketh the soft sward—mine old, wild wisdom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On the soft sward of your hearts, my friends!—on your love, would she fain couch her dearest one!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXIV. IN THE HAPPY ISLES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The figs fall from the trees, they are good and sweet; and in falling the red skins of them break. A north wind am I to ripe figs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus, like figs, do these doctrines fall for you, my friends: imbibe now their juice and their sweet substance! It is autumn all around, and clear sky, and afternoon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, what fullness is around us! And out of the midst of superabundance, it is delightful to look out upon distant seas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once did people say God, when they looked out upon distant seas; now, however, have I taught you to say, Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God is a conjecture: but I do not wish your conjecturing to reach beyond your creating will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Could ye CREATE a God?—Then, I pray you, be silent about all Gods! But ye could well create the Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not perhaps ye yourselves, my brethren! But into fathers and forefathers of the Superman could ye transform yourselves: and let that be your best creating!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God is a conjecture: but I should like your conjecturing restricted to the conceivable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Could ye CONCEIVE a God?—But let this mean Will to Truth unto you, that everything be transformed into the humanly conceivable, the humanly visible, the humanly sensible! Your own discernment shall ye follow out to the end!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And what ye have called the world shall but be created by you: your reason, your likeness, your will, your love, shall it itself become! And verily, for your bliss, ye discerning ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And how would ye endure life without that hope, ye discerning ones? Neither in the inconceivable could ye have been born, nor in the irrational.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that I may reveal my heart entirely unto you, my friends: IF there were gods, how could I endure it to be no God! THEREFORE there are no Gods.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, I have drawn the conclusion; now, however, doth it draw me.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God is a conjecture: but who could drink all the bitterness of this conjecture without dying? Shall his faith be taken from the creating one, and from the eagle his flights into eagle-heights?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God is a thought—it maketh all the straight crooked, and all that standeth reel. What? Time would be gone, and all the perishable would be but a lie?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To think this is giddiness and vertigo to human limbs, and even vomiting to the stomach: verily, the reeling sickness do I call it, to conjecture such a thing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Evil do I call it and misanthropic: all that teaching about the one, and the plenum, and the unmoved, and the sufficient, and the imperishable!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All the imperishable—that’s but a simile, and the poets lie too much.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But of time and of becoming shall the best similes speak: a praise shall they be, and a justification of all perishableness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Creating—that is the great salvation from suffering, and life’s alleviation. But for the creator to appear, suffering itself is needed, and much transformation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, much bitter dying must there be in your life, ye creators! Thus are ye advocates and justifiers of all perishableness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the creator himself to be the new-born child, he must also be willing to be the child-bearer, and endure the pangs of the child-bearer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, through a hundred souls went I my way, and through a hundred cradles and birth-throes. Many a farewell have I taken; I know the heart-breaking last hours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But so willeth it my creating Will, my fate. Or, to tell you it more candidly: just such a fate—willeth my Will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All FEELING suffereth in me, and is in prison: but my WILLING ever cometh to me as mine emancipator and comforter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Willing emancipateth: that is the true doctrine of will and emancipation—so teacheth you Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No longer willing, and no longer valuing, and no longer creating! Ah, that that great debility may ever be far from me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And also in discerning do I feel only my will’s procreating and evolving delight; and if there be innocence in my knowledge, it is because there is will to procreation in it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away from God and Gods did this will allure me; what would there be to create if there were—Gods!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But to man doth it ever impel me anew, my fervent creative will; thus impelleth it the hammer to the stone.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, ye men, within the stone slumbereth an image for me, the image of my visions! Ah, that it should slumber in the hardest, ugliest stone!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now rageth my hammer ruthlessly against its prison. From the stone fly the fragments: what’s that to me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I will complete it: for a shadow came unto me—the stillest and lightest of all things once came unto me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The beauty of the Superman came unto me as a shadow. Ah, my brethren! Of what account now are—the Gods to me!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXV. THE PITIFUL.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My friends, there hath arisen a satire on your friend: “Behold Zarathustra! Walketh he not amongst us as if amongst animals?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it is better said in this wise: “The discerning one walketh amongst men AS amongst animals.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man himself is to the discerning one: the animal with red cheeks.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How hath that happened unto him? Is it not because he hath had to be ashamed too oft?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my friends! Thus speaketh the discerning one: shame, shame, shame—that is the history of man!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And on that account doth the noble one enjoin upon himself not to abash: bashfulness doth he enjoin on himself in presence of all sufferers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I like them not, the merciful ones, whose bliss is in their pity: too destitute are they of bashfulness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If I must be pitiful, I dislike to be called so; and if I be so, it is preferably at a distance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Preferably also do I shroud my head, and flee, before being recognised: and thus do I bid you do, my friends!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>May my destiny ever lead unafflicted ones like you across my path, and those with whom I MAY have hope and repast and honey in common!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I have done this and that for the afflicted: but something better did I always seem to do when I had learned to enjoy myself better.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Since humanity came into being, man hath enjoyed himself too little: that alone, my brethren, is our original sin!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when we learn better to enjoy ourselves, then do we unlearn best to give pain unto others, and to contrive pain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore do I wash the hand that hath helped the sufferer; therefore do I wipe also my soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For in seeing the sufferer suffering—thereof was I ashamed on account of his shame; and in helping him, sorely did I wound his pride.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Great obligations do not make grateful, but revengeful; and when a small kindness is not forgotten, it becometh a gnawing worm.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Be shy in accepting! Distinguish by accepting!”—thus do I advise those who have naught to bestow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I, however, am a bestower: willingly do I bestow as friend to friends. Strangers, however, and the poor, may pluck for themselves the fruit from my tree: thus doth it cause less shame.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beggars, however, one should entirely do away with! Verily, it annoyeth one to give unto them, and it annoyeth one not to give unto them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And likewise sinners and bad consciences! Believe me, my friends: the sting of conscience teacheth one to sting.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The worst things, however, are the petty thoughts. Verily, better to have done evilly than to have thought pettily!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, ye say: “The delight in petty evils spareth one many a great evil deed.” But here one should not wish to be sparing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like a boil is the evil deed: it itcheth and irritateth and breaketh forth—it speaketh honourably.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Behold, I am disease,” saith the evil deed: that is its honourableness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But like infection is the petty thought: it creepeth and hideth, and wanteth to be nowhere—until the whole body is decayed and withered by the petty infection.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To him however, who is possessed of a devil, I would whisper this word in the ear: “Better for thee to rear up thy devil! Even for thee there is still a path to greatness!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, my brethren! One knoweth a little too much about every one! And many a one becometh transparent to us, but still we can by no means penetrate him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is difficult to live among men because silence is so difficult.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And not to him who is offensive to us are we most unfair, but to him who doth not concern us at all.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If, however, thou hast a suffering friend, then be a resting-place for his suffering; like a hard bed, however, a camp-bed: thus wilt thou serve him best.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if a friend doeth thee wrong, then say: “I forgive thee what thou hast done unto me; that thou hast done it unto THYSELF, however—how could I forgive that!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus speaketh all great love: it surpasseth even forgiveness and pity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One should hold fast one’s heart; for when one letteth it go, how quickly doth one’s head run away!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, where in the world have there been greater follies than with the pitiful? And what in the world hath caused more suffering than the follies of the pitiful?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Woe unto all loving ones who have not an elevation which is above their pity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the devil unto me, once on a time: “Even God hath his hell: it is his love for man.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And lately, did I hear him say these words: “God is dead: of his pity for man hath God died.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So be ye warned against pity: FROM THENCE there yet cometh unto men a heavy cloud! Verily, I understand weather-signs!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But attend also to this word: All great love is above all its pity: for it seeketh—to create what is loved!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Myself do I offer unto my love, AND MY NEIGHBOUR AS MYSELF”—such is the language of all creators.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All creators, however, are hard.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXVI. THE PRIESTS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And one day Zarathustra made a sign to his disciples, and spake these words unto them:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Here are priests: but although they are mine enemies, pass them quietly and with sleeping swords!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even among them there are heroes; many of them have suffered too much—: so they want to make others suffer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Bad enemies are they: nothing is more revengeful than their meekness. And readily doth he soil himself who toucheth them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But my blood is related to theirs; and I want withal to see my blood honoured in theirs.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when they had passed, a pain attacked Zarathustra; but not long had he struggled with the pain, when he began to speak thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It moveth my heart for those priests. They also go against my taste; but that is the smallest matter unto me, since I am among men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I suffer and have suffered with them: prisoners are they unto me, and stigmatised ones. He whom they call Saviour put them in fetters:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In fetters of false values and fatuous words! Oh, that some one would save them from their Saviour!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On an isle they once thought they had landed, when the sea tossed them about; but behold, it was a slumbering monster!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>False values and fatuous words: these are the worst monsters for mortals—long slumbereth and waiteth the fate that is in them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But at last it cometh and awaketh and devoureth and engulfeth whatever hath built tabernacles upon it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, just look at those tabernacles which those priests have built themselves! Churches, they call their sweet-smelling caves!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, that falsified light, that mustified air! Where the soul—may not fly aloft to its height!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But so enjoineth their belief: “On your knees, up the stair, ye sinners!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, rather would I see a shameless one than the distorted eyes of their shame and devotion!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Who created for themselves such caves and penitence-stairs? Was it not those who sought to conceal themselves, and were ashamed under the clear sky?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And only when the clear sky looketh again through ruined roofs, and down upon grass and red poppies on ruined walls—will I again turn my heart to the seats of this God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They called God that which opposed and afflicted them: and verily, there was much hero-spirit in their worship!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And they knew not how to love their God otherwise than by nailing men to the cross!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As corpses they thought to live; in black draped they their corpses; even in their talk do I still feel the evil flavour of charnel-houses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he who liveth nigh unto them liveth nigh unto black pools, wherein the toad singeth his song with sweet gravity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better songs would they have to sing, for me to believe in their Saviour: more like saved ones would his disciples have to appear unto me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Naked, would I like to see them: for beauty alone should preach penitence. But whom would that disguised affliction convince!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, their Saviours themselves came not from freedom and freedom’s seventh heaven! Verily, they themselves never trod the carpets of knowledge!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Of defects did the spirit of those Saviours consist; but into every defect had they put their illusion, their stop-gap, which they called God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In their pity was their spirit drowned; and when they swelled and o’erswelled with pity, there always floated to the surface a great folly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Eagerly and with shouts drove they their flock over their foot-bridge; as if there were but one foot-bridge to the future! Verily, those shepherds also were still of the flock!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Small spirits and spacious souls had those shepherds: but, my brethren, what small domains have even the most spacious souls hitherto been!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Characters of blood did they write on the way they went, and their folly taught that truth is proved by blood.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But blood is the very worst witness to truth; blood tainteth the purest teaching, and turneth it into delusion and hatred of heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when a person goeth through fire for his teaching—what doth that prove! It is more, verily, when out of one’s own burning cometh one’s own teaching!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sultry heart and cold head; where these meet, there ariseth the blusterer, the “Saviour.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Greater ones, verily, have there been, and higher-born ones, than those whom the people call Saviours, those rapturous blusterers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And by still greater ones than any of the Saviours must ye be saved, my brethren, if ye would find the way to freedom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet hath there been a Superman. Naked have I seen both of them, the greatest man and the smallest man:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All-too-similar are they still to each other. Verily, even the greatest found I—all-too-human!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXVII. THE VIRTUOUS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thunder and heavenly fireworks must one speak to indolent and somnolent senses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But beauty’s voice speaketh gently: it appealeth only to the most awakened souls.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gently vibrated and laughed unto me to-day my buckler; it was beauty’s holy laughing and thrilling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At you, ye virtuous ones, laughed my beauty to-day. And thus came its voice unto me: “They want—to be paid besides!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye want to be paid besides, ye virtuous ones! Ye want reward for virtue, and heaven for earth, and eternity for your to-day?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now ye upbraid me for teaching that there is no reward-giver, nor paymaster? And verily, I do not even teach that virtue is its own reward.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! this is my sorrow: into the basis of things have reward and punishment been insinuated—and now even into the basis of your souls, ye virtuous ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But like the snout of the boar shall my word grub up the basis of your souls; a ploughshare will I be called by you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All the secrets of your heart shall be brought to light; and when ye lie in the sun, grubbed up and broken, then will also your falsehood be separated from your truth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For this is your truth: ye are TOO PURE for the filth of the words: vengeance, punishment, recompense, retribution.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye love your virtue as a mother loveth her child; but when did one hear of a mother wanting to be paid for her love?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is your dearest Self, your virtue. The ring’s thirst is in you: to reach itself again struggleth every ring, and turneth itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And like the star that goeth out, so is every work of your virtue: ever is its light on its way and travelling—and when will it cease to be on its way?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus is the light of your virtue still on its way, even when its work is done. Be it forgotten and dead, still its ray of light liveth and travelleth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That your virtue is your Self, and not an outward thing, a skin, or a cloak: that is the truth from the basis of your souls, ye virtuous ones!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But sure enough there are those to whom virtue meaneth writhing under the lash: and ye have hearkened too much unto their crying!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And others are there who call virtue the slothfulness of their vices; and when once their hatred and jealousy relax the limbs, their “justice” becometh lively and rubbeth its sleepy eyes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And others are there who are drawn downwards: their devils draw them. But the more they sink, the more ardently gloweth their eye, and the longing for their God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! their crying also hath reached your ears, ye virtuous ones: “What I am NOT, that, that is God to me, and virtue!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And others are there who go along heavily and creakingly, like carts taking stones downhill: they talk much of dignity and virtue—their drag they call virtue!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And others are there who are like eight-day clocks when wound up; they tick, and want people to call ticking—virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, in those have I mine amusement: wherever I find such clocks I shall wind them up with my mockery, and they shall even whirr thereby!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And others are proud of their modicum of righteousness, and for the sake of it do violence to all things: so that the world is drowned in their unrighteousness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! how ineptly cometh the word “virtue” out of their mouth! And when they say: “I am just,” it always soundeth like: “I am just—revenged!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With their virtues they want to scratch out the eyes of their enemies; and they elevate themselves only that they may lower others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And again there are those who sit in their swamp, and speak thus from among the bulrushes: “Virtue—that is to sit quietly in the swamp.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We bite no one, and go out of the way of him who would bite; and in all matters we have the opinion that is given us.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And again there are those who love attitudes, and think that virtue is a sort of attitude.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Their knees continually adore, and their hands are eulogies of virtue, but their heart knoweth naught thereof.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And again there are those who regard it as virtue to say: “Virtue is necessary”; but after all they believe only that policemen are necessary.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many a one who cannot see men’s loftiness, calleth it virtue to see their baseness far too well: thus calleth he his evil eye virtue.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And some want to be edified and raised up, and call it virtue: and others want to be cast down,—and likewise call it virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thus do almost all think that they participate in virtue; and at least every one claimeth to be an authority on “good” and “evil.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But Zarathustra came not to say unto all those liars and fools: “What do YE know of virtue! What COULD ye know of virtue!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that ye, my friends, might become weary of the old words which ye have learned from the fools and liars:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That ye might become weary of the words “reward,” “retribution,” “punishment,” “righteous vengeance.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That ye might become weary of saying: “That an action is good is because it is unselfish.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! my friends! That YOUR very Self be in your action, as the mother is in the child: let that be YOUR formula of virtue!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I have taken from you a hundred formulae and your virtue’s favourite playthings; and now ye upbraid me, as children upbraid.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They played by the sea—then came there a wave and swept their playthings into the deep: and now do they cry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the same wave shall bring them new playthings, and spread before them new speckled shells!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus will they be comforted; and like them shall ye also, my friends, have your comforting—and new speckled shells!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXVIII. THE RABBLE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Life is a well of delight; but where the rabble also drink, there all fountains are poisoned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To everything cleanly am I well disposed; but I hate to see the grinning mouths and the thirst of the unclean.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They cast their eye down into the fountain: and now glanceth up to me their odious smile out of the fountain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The holy water have they poisoned with their lustfulness; and when they called their filthy dreams delight, then poisoned they also the words.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Indignant becometh the flame when they put their damp hearts to the fire; the spirit itself bubbleth and smoketh when the rabble approach the fire.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mawkish and over-mellow becometh the fruit in their hands: unsteady, and withered at the top, doth their look make the fruit-tree.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many a one who hath turned away from life, hath only turned away from the rabble: he hated to share with them fountain, flame, and fruit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many a one who hath gone into the wilderness and suffered thirst with beasts of prey, disliked only to sit at the cistern with filthy camel-drivers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many a one who hath come along as a destroyer, and as a hailstorm to all cornfields, wanted merely to put his foot into the jaws of the rabble, and thus stop their throat.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And it is not the mouthful which hath most choked me, to know that life itself requireth enmity and death and torture-crosses:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I asked once, and suffocated almost with my question: What? is the rabble also NECESSARY for life?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Are poisoned fountains necessary, and stinking fires, and filthy dreams, and maggots in the bread of life?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not my hatred, but my loathing, gnawed hungrily at my life! Ah, ofttimes became I weary of spirit, when I found even the rabble spiritual!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And on the rulers turned I my back, when I saw what they now call ruling: to traffic and bargain for power—with the rabble!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Amongst peoples of a strange language did I dwell, with stopped ears: so that the language of their trafficking might remain strange unto me, and their bargaining for power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And holding my nose, I went morosely through all yesterdays and to-days: verily, badly smell all yesterdays and to-days of the scribbling rabble!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like a cripple become deaf, and blind, and dumb—thus have I lived long; that I might not live with the power-rabble, the scribe-rabble, and the pleasure-rabble.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Toilsomely did my spirit mount stairs, and cautiously; alms of delight were its refreshment; on the staff did life creep along with the blind one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What hath happened unto me? How have I freed myself from loathing? Who hath rejuvenated mine eye? How have I flown to the height where no rabble any longer sit at the wells?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did my loathing itself create for me wings and fountain-divining powers? Verily, to the loftiest height had I to fly, to find again the well of delight!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, I have found it, my brethren! Here on the loftiest height bubbleth up for me the well of delight! And there is a life at whose waters none of the rabble drink with me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Almost too violently dost thou flow for me, thou fountain of delight! And often emptiest thou the goblet again, in wanting to fill it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And yet must I learn to approach thee more modestly: far too violently doth my heart still flow towards thee:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My heart on which my summer burneth, my short, hot, melancholy, over-happy summer: how my summer heart longeth for thy coolness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Past, the lingering distress of my spring! Past, the wickedness of my snowflakes in June! Summer have I become entirely, and summer-noontide!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A summer on the loftiest height, with cold fountains and blissful stillness: oh, come, my friends, that the stillness may become more blissful!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For this is OUR height and our home: too high and steep do we here dwell for all uncleanly ones and their thirst.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Cast but your pure eyes into the well of my delight, my friends! How could it become turbid thereby! It shall laugh back to you with ITS purity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On the tree of the future build we our nest; eagles shall bring us lone ones food in their beaks!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, no food of which the impure could be fellow-partakers! Fire, would they think they devoured, and burn their mouths!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, no abodes do we here keep ready for the impure! An ice-cave to their bodies would our happiness be, and to their spirits!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And as strong winds will we live above them, neighbours to the eagles, neighbours to the snow, neighbours to the sun: thus live the strong winds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And like a wind will I one day blow amongst them, and with my spirit, take the breath from their spirit: thus willeth my future.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a strong wind is Zarathustra to all low places; and this counsel counselleth he to his enemies, and to whatever spitteth and speweth: “Take care not to spit AGAINST the wind!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXIX. THE TARANTULAS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo, this is the tarantula’s den! Wouldst thou see the tarantula itself? Here hangeth its web: touch this, so that it may tremble.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There cometh the tarantula willingly: Welcome, tarantula! Black on thy back is thy triangle and symbol; and I know also what is in thy soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Revenge is in thy soul: wherever thou bitest, there ariseth black scab; with revenge, thy poison maketh the soul giddy!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus do I speak unto you in parable, ye who make the soul giddy, ye preachers of EQUALITY! Tarantulas are ye unto me, and secretly revengeful ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I will soon bring your hiding-places to the light: therefore do I laugh in your face my laughter of the height.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore do I tear at your web, that your rage may lure you out of your den of lies, and that your revenge may leap forth from behind your word “justice.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Because, FOR MAN TO BE REDEEMED FROM REVENGE—that is for me the bridge to the highest hope, and a rainbow after long storms.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Otherwise, however, would the tarantulas have it. “Let it be very justice for the world to become full of the storms of our vengeance”—thus do they talk to one another.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Vengeance will we use, and insult, against all who are not like us”—thus do the tarantula-hearts pledge themselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“And ‘Will to Equality’—that itself shall henceforth be the name of virtue; and against all that hath power will we raise an outcry!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye preachers of equality, the tyrant-frenzy of impotence crieth thus in you for “equality”: your most secret tyrant-longings disguise themselves thus in virtue-words!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Fretted conceit and suppressed envy—perhaps your fathers’ conceit and envy: in you break they forth as flame and frenzy of vengeance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What the father hath hid cometh out in the son; and oft have I found in the son the father’s revealed secret.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Inspired ones they resemble: but it is not the heart that inspireth them—but vengeance. And when they become subtle and cold, it is not spirit, but envy, that maketh them so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Their jealousy leadeth them also into thinkers’ paths; and this is the sign of their jealousy—they always go too far: so that their fatigue hath at last to go to sleep on the snow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In all their lamentations soundeth vengeance, in all their eulogies is maleficence; and being judge seemeth to them bliss.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thus do I counsel you, my friends: distrust all in whom the impulse to punish is powerful!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They are people of bad race and lineage; out of their countenances peer the hangman and the sleuth-hound.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Distrust all those who talk much of their justice! Verily, in their souls not only honey is lacking.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when they call themselves “the good and just,” forget not, that for them to be Pharisees, nothing is lacking but—power!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My friends, I will not be mixed up and confounded with others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are those who preach my doctrine of life, and are at the same time preachers of equality, and tarantulas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That they speak in favour of life, though they sit in their den, these poison-spiders, and withdrawn from life—is because they would thereby do injury.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To those would they thereby do injury who have power at present: for with those the preaching of death is still most at home.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Were it otherwise, then would the tarantulas teach otherwise: and they themselves were formerly the best world-maligners and heretic-burners.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With these preachers of equality will I not be mixed up and confounded. For thus speaketh justice UNTO ME: “Men are not equal.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And neither shall they become so! What would be my love to the Superman, if I spake otherwise?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On a thousand bridges and piers shall they throng to the future, and always shall there be more war and inequality among them: thus doth my great love make me speak!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Inventors of figures and phantoms shall they be in their hostilities; and with those figures and phantoms shall they yet fight with each other the supreme fight!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Good and evil, and rich and poor, and high and low, and all names of values: weapons shall they be, and sounding signs, that life must again and again surpass itself!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Aloft will it build itself with columns and stairs—life itself: into remote distances would it gaze, and out towards blissful beauties— THEREFORE doth it require elevation!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And because it requireth elevation, therefore doth it require steps, and variance of steps and climbers! To rise striveth life, and in rising to surpass itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And just behold, my friends! Here where the tarantula’s den is, riseth aloft an ancient temple’s ruins—just behold it with enlightened eyes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, he who here towered aloft his thoughts in stone, knew as well as the wisest ones about the secret of life!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That there is struggle and inequality even in beauty, and war for power and supremacy: that doth he here teach us in the plainest parable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How divinely do vault and arch here contrast in the struggle: how with light and shade they strive against each other, the divinely striving ones.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus, steadfast and beautiful, let us also be enemies, my friends! Divinely will we strive AGAINST one another!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas! There hath the tarantula bit me myself, mine old enemy! Divinely steadfast and beautiful, it hath bit me on the finger!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Punishment must there be, and justice”—so thinketh it: “not gratuitously shall he here sing songs in honour of enmity!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, it hath revenged itself! And alas! now will it make my soul also dizzy with revenge!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That I may NOT turn dizzy, however, bind me fast, my friends, to this pillar! Rather will I be a pillar-saint than a whirl of vengeance!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, no cyclone or whirlwind is Zarathustra: and if he be a dancer, he is not at all a tarantula-dancer!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXX. THE FAMOUS WISE ONES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The people have ye served and the people’s superstition—NOT the truth!—all ye famous wise ones! And just on that account did they pay you reverence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And on that account also did they tolerate your unbelief, because it was a pleasantry and a by-path for the people. Thus doth the master give free scope to his slaves, and even enjoyeth their presumptuousness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But he who is hated by the people, as the wolf by the dogs—is the free spirit, the enemy of fetters, the non-adorer, the dweller in the woods.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To hunt him out of his lair—that was always called “sense of right” by the people: on him do they still hound their sharpest-toothed dogs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“For there the truth is, where the people are! Woe, woe to the seeking ones!”—thus hath it echoed through all time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your people would ye justify in their reverence: that called ye “Will to Truth,” ye famous wise ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And your heart hath always said to itself: “From the people have I come: from thence came to me also the voice of God.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Stiff-necked and artful, like the ass, have ye always been, as the advocates of the people.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many a powerful one who wanted to run well with the people, hath harnessed in front of his horses—a donkey, a famous wise man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now, ye famous wise ones, I would have you finally throw off entirely the skin of the lion!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The skin of the beast of prey, the speckled skin, and the dishevelled locks of the investigator, the searcher, and the conqueror!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! for me to learn to believe in your “conscientiousness,” ye would first have to break your venerating will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Conscientious—so call I him who goeth into God-forsaken wildernesses, and hath broken his venerating heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the yellow sands and burnt by the sun, he doubtless peereth thirstily at the isles rich in fountains, where life reposeth under shady trees.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But his thirst doth not persuade him to become like those comfortable ones: for where there are oases, there are also idols.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hungry, fierce, lonesome, God-forsaken: so doth the lion-will wish itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Free from the happiness of slaves, redeemed from Deities and adorations, fearless and fear-inspiring, grand and lonesome: so is the will of the conscientious.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the wilderness have ever dwelt the conscientious, the free spirits, as lords of the wilderness; but in the cities dwell the well-foddered, famous wise ones—the draught-beasts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For, always, do they draw, as asses—the PEOPLE’S carts!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not that I on that account upbraid them: but serving ones do they remain, and harnessed ones, even though they glitter in golden harness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And often have they been good servants and worthy of their hire. For thus saith virtue: “If thou must be a servant, seek him unto whom thy service is most useful!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The spirit and virtue of thy master shall advance by thou being his servant: thus wilt thou thyself advance with his spirit and virtue!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, ye famous wise ones, ye servants of the people! Ye yourselves have advanced with the people’s spirit and virtue—and the people by you! To your honour do I say it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the people ye remain for me, even with your virtues, the people with purblind eyes—the people who know not what SPIRIT is!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Spirit is life which itself cutteth into life: by its own torture doth it increase its own knowledge,—did ye know that before?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And the spirit’s happiness is this: to be anointed and consecrated with tears as a sacrificial victim,—did ye know that before?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And the blindness of the blind one, and his seeking and groping, shall yet testify to the power of the sun into which he hath gazed,—did ye know that before?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And with mountains shall the discerning one learn to BUILD! It is a small thing for the spirit to remove mountains,—did ye know that before?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye know only the sparks of the spirit: but ye do not see the anvil which it is, and the cruelty of its hammer!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, ye know not the spirit’s pride! But still less could ye endure the spirit’s humility, should it ever want to speak!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And never yet could ye cast your spirit into a pit of snow: ye are not hot enough for that! Thus are ye unaware, also, of the delight of its coldness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In all respects, however, ye make too familiar with the spirit; and out of wisdom have ye often made an almshouse and a hospital for bad poets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye are not eagles: thus have ye never experienced the happiness of the alarm of the spirit. And he who is not a bird should not camp above abysses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye seem to me lukewarm ones: but coldly floweth all deep knowledge. Ice-cold are the innermost wells of the spirit: a refreshment to hot hands and handlers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Respectable do ye there stand, and stiff, and with straight backs, ye famous wise ones!—no strong wind or will impelleth you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have ye ne’er seen a sail crossing the sea, rounded and inflated, and trembling with the violence of the wind?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like the sail trembling with the violence of the spirit, doth my wisdom cross the sea—my wild wisdom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But ye servants of the people, ye famous wise ones—how COULD ye go with me!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXI. THE NIGHT-SONG.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Tis night: now do all gushing fountains speak louder. And my soul also is a gushing fountain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Tis night: now only do all songs of the loving ones awake. And my soul also is the song of a loving one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Something unappeased, unappeasable, is within me; it longeth to find expression. A craving for love is within me, which speaketh itself the language of love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Light am I: ah, that I were night! But it is my lonesomeness to be begirt with light!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, that I were dark and nightly! How would I suck at the breasts of light!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And you yourselves would I bless, ye twinkling starlets and glow-worms aloft!—and would rejoice in the gifts of your light.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I live in mine own light, I drink again into myself the flames that break forth from me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I know not the happiness of the receiver; and oft have I dreamt that stealing must be more blessed than receiving.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is my poverty that my hand never ceaseth bestowing; it is mine envy that I see waiting eyes and the brightened nights of longing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, the misery of all bestowers! Oh, the darkening of my sun! Oh, the craving to crave! Oh, the violent hunger in satiety!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They take from me: but do I yet touch their soul? There is a gap ‘twixt giving and receiving; and the smallest gap hath finally to be bridged over.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A hunger ariseth out of my beauty: I should like to injure those I illumine; I should like to rob those I have gifted:—thus do I hunger for wickedness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Withdrawing my hand when another hand already stretcheth out to it; hesitating like the cascade, which hesitateth even in its leap:—thus do I hunger for wickedness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such revenge doth mine abundance think of: such mischief welleth out of my lonesomeness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My happiness in bestowing died in bestowing; my virtue became weary of itself by its abundance!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who ever bestoweth is in danger of losing his shame; to him who ever dispenseth, the hand and heart become callous by very dispensing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mine eye no longer overfloweth for the shame of suppliants; my hand hath become too hard for the trembling of filled hands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whence have gone the tears of mine eye, and the down of my heart? Oh, the lonesomeness of all bestowers! Oh, the silence of all shining ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many suns circle in desert space: to all that is dark do they speak with their light—but to me they are silent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, this is the hostility of light to the shining one: unpityingly doth it pursue its course.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unfair to the shining one in its innermost heart, cold to the suns:—thus travelleth every sun.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like a storm do the suns pursue their courses: that is their travelling. Their inexorable will do they follow: that is their coldness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, ye only is it, ye dark, nightly ones, that extract warmth from the shining ones! Oh, ye only drink milk and refreshment from the light’s udders!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, there is ice around me; my hand burneth with the iciness! Ah, there is thirst in me; it panteth after your thirst!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Tis night: alas, that I have to be light! And thirst for the nightly! And lonesomeness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Tis night: now doth my longing break forth in me as a fountain,—for speech do I long.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Tis night: now do all gushing fountains speak louder. And my soul also is a gushing fountain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Tis night: now do all songs of loving ones awake. And my soul also is the song of a loving one.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sang Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXII. THE DANCE-SONG.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One evening went Zarathustra and his disciples through the forest; and when he sought for a well, lo, he lighted upon a green meadow peacefully surrounded with trees and bushes, where maidens were dancing together. As soon as the maidens recognised Zarathustra, they ceased dancing; Zarathustra, however, approached them with friendly mien and spake these words:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Cease not your dancing, ye lovely maidens! No game-spoiler hath come to you with evil eye, no enemy of maidens.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God’s advocate am I with the devil: he, however, is the spirit of gravity. How could I, ye light-footed ones, be hostile to divine dances? Or to maidens’ feet with fine ankles?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, I am a forest, and a night of dark trees: but he who is not afraid of my darkness, will find banks full of roses under my cypresses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And even the little God may he find, who is dearest to maidens: beside the well lieth he quietly, with closed eyes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, in broad daylight did he fall asleep, the sluggard! Had he perhaps chased butterflies too much?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Upbraid me not, ye beautiful dancers, when I chasten the little God somewhat! He will cry, certainly, and weep—but he is laughable even when weeping!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And with tears in his eyes shall he ask you for a dance; and I myself will sing a song to his dance:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A dance-song and satire on the spirit of gravity my supremest, powerfulest devil, who is said to be “lord of the world.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this is the song that Zarathustra sang when Cupid and the maidens danced together:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Of late did I gaze into thine eye, O Life! And into the unfathomable did I there seem to sink.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thou pulledst me out with a golden angle; derisively didst thou laugh when I called thee unfathomable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Such is the language of all fish,” saidst thou; “what THEY do not fathom is unfathomable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But changeable am I only, and wild, and altogether a woman, and no virtuous one:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Though I be called by you men the ‘profound one,’ or the ‘faithful one,’ ‘the eternal one,’ ‘the mysterious one.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But ye men endow us always with your own virtues—alas, ye virtuous ones!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did she laugh, the unbelievable one; but never do I believe her and her laughter, when she speaketh evil of herself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I talked face to face with my wild Wisdom, she said to me angrily: “Thou willest, thou cravest, thou lovest; on that account alone dost thou PRAISE Life!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then had I almost answered indignantly and told the truth to the angry one; and one cannot answer more indignantly than when one “telleth the truth” to one’s Wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For thus do things stand with us three. In my heart do I love only Life—and verily, most when I hate her!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that I am fond of Wisdom, and often too fond, is because she remindeth me very strongly of Life!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>She hath her eye, her laugh, and even her golden angle-rod: am I responsible for it that both are so alike?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when once Life asked me: “Who is she then, this Wisdom?”—then said I eagerly: “Ah, yes! Wisdom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One thirsteth for her and is not satisfied, one looketh through veils, one graspeth through nets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is she beautiful? What do I know! But the oldest carps are still lured by her.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Changeable is she, and wayward; often have I seen her bite her lip, and pass the comb against the grain of her hair.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Perhaps she is wicked and false, and altogether a woman; but when she speaketh ill of herself, just then doth she seduce most.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When I had said this unto Life, then laughed she maliciously, and shut her eyes. “Of whom dost thou speak?” said she. “Perhaps of me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if thou wert right—is it proper to say THAT in such wise to my face! But now, pray, speak also of thy Wisdom!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, and now hast thou again opened thine eyes, O beloved Life! And into the unfathomable have I again seemed to sink.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sang Zarathustra. But when the dance was over and the maidens had departed, he became sad.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The sun hath been long set,” said he at last, “the meadow is damp, and from the forest cometh coolness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An unknown presence is about me, and gazeth thoughtfully. What! Thou livest still, Zarathustra?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why? Wherefore? Whereby? Whither? Where? How? Is it not folly still to live?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, my friends; the evening is it which thus interrogateth in me. Forgive me my sadness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Evening hath come on: forgive me that evening hath come on!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sang Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXIII. THE GRAVE-SONG.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Yonder is the grave-island, the silent isle; yonder also are the graves of my youth. Thither will I carry an evergreen wreath of life.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Resolving thus in my heart, did I sail o’er the sea.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, ye sights and scenes of my youth! Oh, all ye gleams of love, ye divine fleeting gleams! How could ye perish so soon for me! I think of you to-day as my dead ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From you, my dearest dead ones, cometh unto me a sweet savour, heart-opening and melting. Verily, it convulseth and openeth the heart of the lone seafarer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still am I the richest and most to be envied—I, the lonesomest one! For I HAVE POSSESSED you, and ye possess me still. Tell me: to whom hath there ever fallen such rosy apples from the tree as have fallen unto me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still am I your love’s heir and heritage, blooming to your memory with many-hued, wild-growing virtues, O ye dearest ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, we were made to remain nigh unto each other, ye kindly strange marvels; and not like timid birds did ye come to me and my longing—nay, but as trusting ones to a trusting one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, made for faithfulness, like me, and for fond eternities, must I now name you by your faithlessness, ye divine glances and fleeting gleams: no other name have I yet learnt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, too early did ye die for me, ye fugitives. Yet did ye not flee from me, nor did I flee from you: innocent are we to each other in our faithlessness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To kill ME, did they strangle you, ye singing birds of my hopes! Yea, at you, ye dearest ones, did malice ever shoot its arrows—to hit my heart!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And they hit it! Because ye were always my dearest, my possession and my possessedness: ON THAT ACCOUNT had ye to die young, and far too early!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At my most vulnerable point did they shoot the arrow—namely, at you, whose skin is like down—or more like the smile that dieth at a glance!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But this word will I say unto mine enemies: What is all manslaughter in comparison with what ye have done unto me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Worse evil did ye do unto me than all manslaughter; the irretrievable did ye take from me:—thus do I speak unto you, mine enemies!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Slew ye not my youth’s visions and dearest marvels! My playmates took ye from me, the blessed spirits! To their memory do I deposit this wreath and this curse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This curse upon you, mine enemies! Have ye not made mine eternal short, as a tone dieth away in a cold night! Scarcely, as the twinkle of divine eyes, did it come to me—as a fleeting gleam!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake once in a happy hour my purity: “Divine shall everything be unto me.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then did ye haunt me with foul phantoms; ah, whither hath that happy hour now fled!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“All days shall be holy unto me”—so spake once the wisdom of my youth: verily, the language of a joyous wisdom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But then did ye enemies steal my nights, and sold them to sleepless torture: ah, whither hath that joyous wisdom now fled?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once did I long for happy auspices: then did ye lead an owl-monster across my path, an adverse sign. Ah, whither did my tender longing then flee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All loathing did I once vow to renounce: then did ye change my nigh ones and nearest ones into ulcerations. Ah, whither did my noblest vow then flee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As a blind one did I once walk in blessed ways: then did ye cast filth on the blind one’s course: and now is he disgusted with the old footpath.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I performed my hardest task, and celebrated the triumph of my victories, then did ye make those who loved me call out that I then grieved them most.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, it was always your doing: ye embittered to me my best honey, and the diligence of my best bees.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To my charity have ye ever sent the most impudent beggars; around my sympathy have ye ever crowded the incurably shameless. Thus have ye wounded the faith of my virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I offered my holiest as a sacrifice, immediately did your “piety” put its fatter gifts beside it: so that my holiest suffocated in the fumes of your fat.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And once did I want to dance as I had never yet danced: beyond all heavens did I want to dance. Then did ye seduce my favourite minstrel.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now hath he struck up an awful, melancholy air; alas, he tooted as a mournful horn to mine ear!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Murderous minstrel, instrument of evil, most innocent instrument! Already did I stand prepared for the best dance: then didst thou slay my rapture with thy tones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Only in the dance do I know how to speak the parable of the highest things:—and now hath my grandest parable remained unspoken in my limbs!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unspoken and unrealised hath my highest hope remained! And there have perished for me all the visions and consolations of my youth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How did I ever bear it? How did I survive and surmount such wounds? How did my soul rise again out of those sepulchres?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, something invulnerable, unburiable is with me, something that would rend rocks asunder: it is called MY WILL. Silently doth it proceed, and unchanged throughout the years.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Its course will it go upon my feet, mine old Will; hard of heart is its nature and invulnerable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Invulnerable am I only in my heel. Ever livest thou there, and art like thyself, thou most patient one! Ever hast thou burst all shackles of the tomb!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In thee still liveth also the unrealisedness of my youth; and as life and youth sittest thou here hopeful on the yellow ruins of graves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, thou art still for me the demolisher of all graves: Hail to thee, my Will! And only where there are graves are there resurrections.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sang Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXIV. SELF-SURPASSING.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Will to Truth” do ye call it, ye wisest ones, that which impelleth you and maketh you ardent?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Will for the thinkableness of all being: thus do <i>I</i> call your will!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All being would ye MAKE thinkable: for ye doubt with good reason whether it be already thinkable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it shall accommodate and bend itself to you! So willeth your will. Smooth shall it become and subject to the spirit, as its mirror and reflection.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That is your entire will, ye wisest ones, as a Will to Power; and even when ye speak of good and evil, and of estimates of value.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye would still create a world before which ye can bow the knee: such is your ultimate hope and ecstasy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The ignorant, to be sure, the people—they are like a river on which a boat floateth along: and in the boat sit the estimates of value, solemn and disguised.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your will and your valuations have ye put on the river of becoming; it betrayeth unto me an old Will to Power, what is believed by the people as good and evil.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It was ye, ye wisest ones, who put such guests in this boat, and gave them pomp and proud names—ye and your ruling Will!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Onward the river now carrieth your boat: it MUST carry it. A small matter if the rough wave foameth and angrily resisteth its keel!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is not the river that is your danger and the end of your good and evil, ye wisest ones: but that Will itself, the Will to Power—the unexhausted, procreating life-will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that ye may understand my gospel of good and evil, for that purpose will I tell you my gospel of life, and of the nature of all living things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The living thing did I follow; I walked in the broadest and narrowest paths to learn its nature.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With a hundred-faced mirror did I catch its glance when its mouth was shut, so that its eye might speak unto me. And its eye spake unto me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But wherever I found living things, there heard I also the language of obedience. All living things are obeying things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this heard I secondly: Whatever cannot obey itself, is commanded. Such is the nature of living things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, however, is the third thing which I heard—namely, that commanding is more difficult than obeying. And not only because the commander beareth the burden of all obeyers, and because this burden readily crusheth him:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An attempt and a risk seemed all commanding unto me; and whenever it commandeth, the living thing risketh itself thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, even when it commandeth itself, then also must it atone for its commanding. Of its own law must it become the judge and avenger and victim.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How doth this happen! so did I ask myself. What persuadeth the living thing to obey, and command, and even be obedient in commanding?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hearken now unto my word, ye wisest ones! Test it seriously, whether I have crept into the heart of life itself, and into the roots of its heart!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Wherever I found a living thing, there found I Will to Power; and even in the will of the servant found I the will to be master.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That to the stronger the weaker shall serve—thereto persuadeth he his will who would be master over a still weaker one. That delight alone he is unwilling to forego.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And as the lesser surrendereth himself to the greater that he may have delight and power over the least of all, so doth even the greatest surrender himself, and staketh—life, for the sake of power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is the surrender of the greatest to run risk and danger, and play dice for death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And where there is sacrifice and service and love-glances, there also is the will to be master. By by-ways doth the weaker then slink into the fortress, and into the heart of the mightier one—and there stealeth power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this secret spake Life herself unto me. “Behold,” said she, “I am that WHICH MUST EVER SURPASS ITSELF.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, ye call it will to procreation, or impulse towards a goal, towards the higher, remoter, more manifold: but all that is one and the same secret.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Rather would I succumb than disown this one thing; and verily, where there is succumbing and leaf-falling, lo, there doth Life sacrifice itself—for power!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That I have to be struggle, and becoming, and purpose, and cross-purpose—ah, he who divineth my will, divineth well also on what CROOKED paths it hath to tread!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whatever I create, and however much I love it,—soon must I be adverse to it, and to my love: so willeth my will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And even thou, discerning one, art only a path and footstep of my will: verily, my Will to Power walketh even on the feet of thy Will to Truth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He certainly did not hit the truth who shot at it the formula: ‘Will to existence’: that will—doth not exist!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For what is not, cannot will; that, however, which is in existence—how could it still strive for existence!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Only where there is life, is there also will: not, however, Will to Life, but—so teach I thee—Will to Power!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Much is reckoned higher than life itself by the living one; but out of the very reckoning speaketh—the Will to Power!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did Life once teach me: and thereby, ye wisest ones, do I solve you the riddle of your hearts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I say unto you: good and evil which would be everlasting—it doth not exist! Of its own accord must it ever surpass itself anew.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With your values and formulae of good and evil, ye exercise power, ye valuing ones: and that is your secret love, and the sparkling, trembling, and overflowing of your souls.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But a stronger power groweth out of your values, and a new surpassing: by it breaketh egg and egg-shell.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he who hath to be a creator in good and evil—verily, he hath first to be a destroyer, and break values in pieces.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus doth the greatest evil pertain to the greatest good: that, however, is the creating good.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let us SPEAK thereof, ye wisest ones, even though it be bad. To be silent is worse; all suppressed truths become poisonous.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And let everything break up which—can break up by our truths! Many a house is still to be built!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXV. THE SUBLIME ONES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Calm is the bottom of my sea: who would guess that it hideth droll monsters!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unmoved is my depth: but it sparkleth with swimming enigmas and laughters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A sublime one saw I to-day, a solemn one, a penitent of the spirit: Oh, how my soul laughed at his ugliness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With upraised breast, and like those who draw in their breath: thus did he stand, the sublime one, and in silence:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O’erhung with ugly truths, the spoil of his hunting, and rich in torn raiment; many thorns also hung on him—but I saw no rose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not yet had he learned laughing and beauty. Gloomy did this hunter return from the forest of knowledge.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From the fight with wild beasts returned he home: but even yet a wild beast gazeth out of his seriousness—an unconquered wild beast!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As a tiger doth he ever stand, on the point of springing; but I do not like those strained souls; ungracious is my taste towards all those self-engrossed ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ye tell me, friends, that there is to be no dispute about taste and tasting? But all life is a dispute about taste and tasting!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Taste: that is weight at the same time, and scales and weigher; and alas for every living thing that would live without dispute about weight and scales and weigher!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Should he become weary of his sublimeness, this sublime one, then only will his beauty begin—and then only will I taste him and find him savoury.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And only when he turneth away from himself will he o’erleap his own shadow—and verily! into HIS sun.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Far too long did he sit in the shade; the cheeks of the penitent of the spirit became pale; he almost starved on his expectations.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Contempt is still in his eye, and loathing hideth in his mouth. To be sure, he now resteth, but he hath not yet taken rest in the sunshine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As the ox ought he to do; and his happiness should smell of the earth, and not of contempt for the earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As a white ox would I like to see him, which, snorting and lowing, walketh before the plough-share: and his lowing should also laud all that is earthly!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Dark is still his countenance; the shadow of his hand danceth upon it. O’ershadowed is still the sense of his eye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His deed itself is still the shadow upon him: his doing obscureth the doer. Not yet hath he overcome his deed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, I love in him the shoulders of the ox: but now do I want to see also the eye of the angel.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Also his hero-will hath he still to unlearn: an exalted one shall he be, and not only a sublime one:—the ether itself should raise him, the will-less one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He hath subdued monsters, he hath solved enigmas. But he should also redeem his monsters and enigmas; into heavenly children should he transform them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet hath his knowledge not learned to smile, and to be without jealousy; as yet hath his gushing passion not become calm in beauty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, not in satiety shall his longing cease and disappear, but in beauty! Gracefulness belongeth to the munificence of the magnanimous.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His arm across his head: thus should the hero repose; thus should he also surmount his repose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But precisely to the hero is BEAUTY the hardest thing of all. Unattainable is beauty by all ardent wills.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A little more, a little less: precisely this is much here, it is the most here.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To stand with relaxed muscles and with unharnessed will: that is the hardest for all of you, ye sublime ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When power becometh gracious and descendeth into the visible—I call such condescension, beauty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And from no one do I want beauty so much as from thee, thou powerful one: let thy goodness be thy last self-conquest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All evil do I accredit to thee: therefore do I desire of thee the good.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I have often laughed at the weaklings, who think themselves good because they have crippled paws!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The virtue of the pillar shalt thou strive after: more beautiful doth it ever become, and more graceful—but internally harder and more sustaining—the higher it riseth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, thou sublime one, one day shalt thou also be beautiful, and hold up the mirror to thine own beauty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then will thy soul thrill with divine desires; and there will be adoration even in thy vanity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For this is the secret of the soul: when the hero hath abandoned it, then only approacheth it in dreams—the superhero.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXVI. THE LAND OF CULTURE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>Too far did I fly into the future: a horror seized upon me.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I looked around me, lo! there time was my sole contemporary.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then did I fly backwards, homewards—and always faster. Thus did I come unto you, ye present-day men, and into the land of culture.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the first time brought I an eye to see you, and good desire: verily, with longing in my heart did I come.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But how did it turn out with me? Although so alarmed—I had yet to laugh! Never did mine eye see anything so motley-coloured!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I laughed and laughed, while my foot still trembled, and my heart as well. “Here forsooth, is the home of all the paintpots,”—said I.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With fifty patches painted on faces and limbs—so sat ye there to mine astonishment, ye present-day men!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And with fifty mirrors around you, which flattered your play of colours, and repeated it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, ye could wear no better masks, ye present-day men, than your own faces! Who could—RECOGNISE you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Written all over with the characters of the past, and these characters also pencilled over with new characters—thus have ye concealed yourselves well from all decipherers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And though one be a trier of the reins, who still believeth that ye have reins! Out of colours ye seem to be baked, and out of glued scraps.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All times and peoples gaze divers-coloured out of your veils; all customs and beliefs speak divers-coloured out of your gestures.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who would strip you of veils and wrappers, and paints and gestures, would just have enough left to scare the crows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I myself am the scared crow that once saw you naked, and without paint; and I flew away when the skeleton ogled at me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Rather would I be a day-labourer in the nether-world, and among the shades of the by-gone!—Fatter and fuller than ye, are forsooth the nether-worldlings!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, yea this, is bitterness to my bowels, that I can neither endure you naked nor clothed, ye present-day men!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All that is unhomelike in the future, and whatever maketh strayed birds shiver, is verily more homelike and familiar than your “reality.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For thus speak ye: “Real are we wholly, and without faith and superstition”: thus do ye plume yourselves—alas! even without plumes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Indeed, how would ye be ABLE to believe, ye divers-coloured ones!—ye who are pictures of all that hath ever been believed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Perambulating refutations are ye, of belief itself, and a dislocation of all thought. UNTRUSTWORTHY ONES: thus do <i>I</i> call you, ye real ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All periods prate against one another in your spirits; and the dreams and pratings of all periods were even realer than your awakeness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unfruitful are ye: THEREFORE do ye lack belief. But he who had to create, had always his presaging dreams and astral premonitions—and believed in believing!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Half-open doors are ye, at which grave-diggers wait. And this is YOUR reality: “Everything deserveth to perish.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas, how ye stand there before me, ye unfruitful ones; how lean your ribs! And many of you surely have had knowledge thereof.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many a one hath said: “There hath surely a God filched something from me secretly whilst I slept? Verily, enough to make a girl for himself therefrom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Amazing is the poverty of my ribs!” thus hath spoken many a present-day man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, ye are laughable unto me, ye present-day men! And especially when ye marvel at yourselves!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And woe unto me if I could not laugh at your marvelling, and had to swallow all that is repugnant in your platters!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As it is, however, I will make lighter of you, since I have to carry <i>what is heavy;</i> and what matter if beetles and May-bugs also alight on my load!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, it shall not on that account become heavier to me! And not from you, ye present-day men, shall my great weariness arise.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, whither shall I now ascend with my longing! From all mountains do I look out for fatherlands and motherlands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But a home have I found nowhere: unsettled am I in all cities, and decamping at all gates.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alien to me, and a mockery, are the present-day men, to whom of late my heart impelled me; and exiled am I from fatherlands and motherlands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus do I love only my CHILDREN’S LAND, the undiscovered in the remotest sea: for it do I bid my sails search and search.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unto my children will I make amends for being the child of my fathers: and unto all the future—for THIS present-day!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXVII. IMMACULATE PERCEPTION.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When yester-eve the moon arose, then did I fancy it about to bear a sun: so broad and teeming did it lie on the horizon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it was a liar with its pregnancy; and sooner will I believe in the man in the moon than in the woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, little of a man is he also, that timid night-reveller. Verily, with a bad conscience doth he stalk over the roofs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For he is covetous and jealous, the monk in the moon; covetous of the earth, and all the joys of lovers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nay, I like him not, that tom-cat on the roofs! Hateful unto me are all that slink around half-closed windows!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Piously and silently doth he stalk along on the star-carpets:—but I like no light-treading human feet, on which not even a spur jingleth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every honest one’s step speaketh; the cat however, stealeth along over the ground. Lo! cat-like doth the moon come along, and dishonestly.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This parable speak I unto you sentimental dissemblers, unto you, the “pure discerners!” You do <i>I</i> call—covetous ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Also ye love the earth, and the earthly: I have divined you well!—but shame is in your love, and a bad conscience—ye are like the moon!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To despise the earthly hath your spirit been persuaded, but not your bowels: these, however, are the strongest in you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now is your spirit ashamed to be at the service of your bowels, and goeth by-ways and lying ways to escape its own shame.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“That would be the highest thing for me”—so saith your lying spirit unto itself—“to gaze upon life without desire, and not like the dog, with hanging-out tongue:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be happy in gazing: with dead will, free from the grip and greed of selfishness—cold and ashy-grey all over, but with intoxicated moon-eyes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That would be the dearest thing to me”—thus doth the seduced one seduce himself,—“to love the earth as the moon loveth it, and with the eye only to feel its beauty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this do I call IMMACULATE perception of all things: to want nothing else from them, but to be allowed to lie before them as a mirror with a hundred facets.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, ye sentimental dissemblers, ye covetous ones! Ye lack innocence in your desire: and now do ye defame desiring on that account!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, not as creators, as procreators, or as jubilators do ye love the earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where is innocence? Where there is will to procreation. And he who seeketh to create beyond himself, hath for me the purest will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where is beauty? Where I MUST WILL with my whole Will; where I will love and perish, that an image may not remain merely an image.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Loving and perishing: these have rhymed from eternity. Will to love: that is to be ready also for death. Thus do I speak unto you cowards!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But now doth your emasculated ogling profess to be “contemplation!” And that which can be examined with cowardly eyes is to be christened “beautiful!” Oh, ye violators of noble names!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it shall be your curse, ye immaculate ones, ye pure discerners, that ye shall never bring forth, even though ye lie broad and teeming on the horizon!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, ye fill your mouth with noble words: and we are to believe that your heart overfloweth, ye cozeners?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But MY words are poor, contemptible, stammering words: gladly do I pick up what falleth from the table at your repasts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yet still can I say therewith the truth—to dissemblers! Yea, my fish-bones, shells, and prickly leaves shall—tickle the noses of dissemblers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Bad air is always about you and your repasts: your lascivious thoughts, your lies, and secrets are indeed in the air!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Dare only to believe in yourselves—in yourselves and in your inward parts! He who doth not believe in himself always lieth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A God’s mask have ye hung in front of you, ye “pure ones”: into a God’s mask hath your execrable coiling snake crawled.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily ye deceive, ye “contemplative ones!” Even Zarathustra was once the dupe of your godlike exterior; he did not divine the serpent’s coil with which it was stuffed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A God’s soul, I once thought I saw playing in your games, ye pure discerners! No better arts did I once dream of than your arts!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Serpents’ filth and evil odour, the distance concealed from me: and that a lizard’s craft prowled thereabouts lasciviously.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I came NIGH unto you: then came to me the day,—and now cometh it to you,—at an end is the moon’s love affair!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See there! Surprised and pale doth it stand—before the rosy dawn!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For already she cometh, the glowing one,—HER love to the earth cometh! Innocence and creative desire, is all solar love!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See there, how she cometh impatiently over the sea! Do ye not feel the thirst and the hot breath of her love?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At the sea would she suck, and drink its depths to her height: now riseth the desire of the sea with its thousand breasts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Kissed and sucked WOULD it be by the thirst of the sun; vapour WOULD it become, and height, and path of light, and light itself!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, like the sun do I love life, and all deep seas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this meaneth TO ME knowledge: all that is deep shall ascend—to my height!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXVIII. SCHOLARS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When I lay asleep, then did a sheep eat at the ivy-wreath on my head,—it ate, and said thereby: “Zarathustra is no longer a scholar.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It said this, and went away clumsily and proudly. A child told it to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I like to lie here where the children play, beside the ruined wall, among thistles and red poppies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A scholar am I still to the children, and also to the thistles and red poppies. Innocent are they, even in their wickedness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But to the sheep I am no longer a scholar: so willeth my lot—blessings upon it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For this is the truth: I have departed from the house of the scholars, and the door have I also slammed behind me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too long did my soul sit hungry at their table: not like them have I got the knack of investigating, as the knack of nut-cracking.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Freedom do I love, and the air over fresh soil; rather would I sleep on ox-skins than on their honours and dignities.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am too hot and scorched with mine own thought: often is it ready to take away my breath. Then have I to go into the open air, and away from all dusty rooms.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But they sit cool in the cool shade: they want in everything to be merely spectators, and they avoid sitting where the sun burneth on the steps.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like those who stand in the street and gape at the passers-by: thus do they also wait, and gape at the thoughts which others have thought.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Should one lay hold of them, then do they raise a dust like flour-sacks, and involuntarily: but who would divine that their dust came from corn, and from the yellow delight of the summer fields?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When they give themselves out as wise, then do their petty sayings and truths chill me: in their wisdom there is often an odour as if it came from the swamp; and verily, I have even heard the frog croak in it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Clever are they—they have dexterous fingers: what doth MY simplicity pretend to beside their multiplicity! All threading and knitting and weaving do their fingers understand: thus do they make the hose of the spirit!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Good clockworks are they: only be careful to wind them up properly! Then do they indicate the hour without mistake, and make a modest noise thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like millstones do they work, and like pestles: throw only seed-corn unto them!—they know well how to grind corn small, and make white dust out of it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They keep a sharp eye on one another, and do not trust each other the best. Ingenious in little artifices, they wait for those whose knowledge walketh on lame feet,—like spiders do they wait.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I saw them always prepare their poison with precaution; and always did they put glass gloves on their fingers in doing so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They also know how to play with false dice; and so eagerly did I find them playing, that they perspired thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We are alien to each other, and their virtues are even more repugnant to my taste than their falsehoods and false dice.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I lived with them, then did I live above them. Therefore did they take a dislike to me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They want to hear nothing of any one walking above their heads; and so they put wood and earth and rubbish betwixt me and their heads.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did they deafen the sound of my tread: and least have I hitherto been heard by the most learned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All mankind’s faults and weaknesses did they put betwixt themselves and me:—they call it “false ceiling” in their houses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But nevertheless I walk with my thoughts ABOVE their heads; and even should I walk on mine own errors, still would I be above them and their heads.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For men are NOT equal: so speaketh justice. And what I will, THEY may not will!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XXXIX. POETS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Since I have known the body better”—said Zarathustra to one of his disciples—“the spirit hath only been to me symbolically spirit; and all the ‘imperishable’—that is also but a simile.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“So have I heard thee say once before,” answered the disciple, “and then thou addedst: ‘But the poets lie too much.’ Why didst thou say that the poets lie too much?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why?” said Zarathustra. “Thou askest why? I do not belong to those who may be asked after their Why.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is my experience but of yesterday? It is long ago that I experienced the reasons for mine opinions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Should I not have to be a cask of memory, if I also wanted to have my reasons with me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is already too much for me even to retain mine opinions; and many a bird flieth away.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And sometimes, also, do I find a fugitive creature in my dovecote, which is alien to me, and trembleth when I lay my hand upon it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But what did Zarathustra once say unto thee? That the poets lie too much?—But Zarathustra also is a poet.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Believest thou that he there spake the truth? Why dost thou believe it?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The disciple answered: “I believe in Zarathustra.” But Zarathustra shook his head and smiled.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Belief doth not sanctify me, said he, least of all the belief in myself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But granting that some one did say in all seriousness that the poets lie too much: he was right—WE do lie too much.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We also know too little, and are bad learners: so we are obliged to lie.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And which of us poets hath not adulterated his wine? Many a poisonous hotchpotch hath evolved in our cellars: many an indescribable thing hath there been done.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And because we know little, therefore are we pleased from the heart with the poor in spirit, especially when they are young women!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And even of those things are we desirous, which old women tell one another in the evening. This do we call the eternally feminine in us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And as if there were a special secret access to knowledge, which CHOKETH UP for those who learn anything, so do we believe in the people and in their “wisdom.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, however, do all poets believe: that whoever pricketh up his ears when lying in the grass or on lonely slopes, learneth something of the things that are betwixt heaven and earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if there come unto them tender emotions, then do the poets always think that nature herself is in love with them:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And that she stealeth to their ear to whisper secrets into it, and amorous flatteries: of this do they plume and pride themselves, before all mortals!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, there are so many things betwixt heaven and earth of which only the poets have dreamed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And especially ABOVE the heavens: for all Gods are poet-symbolisations, poet-sophistications!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, ever are we drawn aloft—that is, to the realm of the clouds: on these do we set our gaudy puppets, and then call them Gods and Supermen:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Are not they light enough for those chairs!—all these Gods and Supermen?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, how I am weary of all the inadequate that is insisted on as actual! Ah, how I am weary of the poets!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra so spake, his disciple resented it, but was silent. And Zarathustra also was silent; and his eye directed itself inwardly, as if it gazed into the far distance. At last he sighed and drew breath.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am of to-day and heretofore, said he thereupon; but something is in me that is of the morrow, and the day following, and the hereafter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I became weary of the poets, of the old and of the new: superficial are they all unto me, and shallow seas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They did not think sufficiently into the depth; therefore their feeling did not reach to the bottom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Some sensation of voluptuousness and some sensation of tedium: these have as yet been their best contemplation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ghost-breathing and ghost-whisking, seemeth to me all the jingle-jangling of their harps; what have they known hitherto of the fervour of tones!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They are also not pure enough for me: they all muddle their water that it may seem deep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And fain would they thereby prove themselves reconcilers: but mediaries and mixers are they unto me, and half-and-half, and impure!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, I cast indeed my net into their sea, and meant to catch good fish; but always did I draw up the head of some ancient God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did the sea give a stone to the hungry one. And they themselves may well originate from the sea.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Certainly, one findeth pearls in them: thereby they are the more like hard molluscs. And instead of a soul, I have often found in them salt slime.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They have learned from the sea also its vanity: is not the sea the peacock of peacocks?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even before the ugliest of all buffaloes doth it spread out its tail; never doth it tire of its lace-fan of silver and silk.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Disdainfully doth the buffalo glance thereat, nigh to the sand with its soul, nigher still to the thicket, nighest, however, to the swamp.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is beauty and sea and peacock-splendour to it! This parable I speak unto the poets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, their spirit itself is the peacock of peacocks, and a sea of vanity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Spectators, seeketh the spirit of the poet—should they even be buffaloes!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But of this spirit became I weary; and I see the time coming when it will become weary of itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, changed have I seen the poets, and their glance turned towards themselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Penitents of the spirit have I seen appearing; they grew out of the poets.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XL. GREAT EVENTS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is an isle in the sea—not far from the Happy Isles of Zarathustra—on which a volcano ever smoketh; of which isle the people, and especially the old women amongst them, say that it is placed as a rock before the gate of the nether-world; but that through the volcano itself the narrow way leadeth downwards which conducteth to this gate.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now about the time that Zarathustra sojourned on the Happy Isles, it happened that a ship anchored at the isle on which standeth the smoking mountain, and the crew went ashore to shoot rabbits. About the noontide hour, however, when the captain and his men were together again, they saw suddenly a man coming towards them through the air, and a voice said distinctly: “It is time! It is the highest time!” But when the figure was nearest to them (it flew past quickly, however, like a shadow, in the direction of the volcano), then did they recognise with the greatest surprise that it was Zarathustra; for they had all seen him before except the captain himself, and they loved him as the people love: in such wise that love and awe were combined in equal degree.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Behold!” said the old helmsman, “there goeth Zarathustra to hell!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>About the same time that these sailors landed on the fire-isle, there was a rumour that Zarathustra had disappeared; and when his friends were asked about it, they said that he had gone on board a ship by night, without saying whither he was going.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus there arose some uneasiness. After three days, however, there came the story of the ship’s crew in addition to this uneasiness—and then did all the people say that the devil had taken Zarathustra. His disciples laughed, sure enough, at this talk; and one of them said even: “Sooner would I believe that Zarathustra hath taken the devil.” But at the bottom of their hearts they were all full of anxiety and longing: so their joy was great when on the fifth day Zarathustra appeared amongst them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this is the account of Zarathustra’s interview with the fire-dog:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The earth, said he, hath a skin; and this skin hath diseases. One of these diseases, for example, is called “man.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And another of these diseases is called “the fire-dog”: concerning HIM men have greatly deceived themselves, and let themselves be deceived.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To fathom this mystery did I go o’er the sea; and I have seen the truth naked, verily! barefooted up to the neck.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now do I know how it is concerning the fire-dog; and likewise concerning all the spouting and subversive devils, of which not only old women are afraid.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Up with thee, fire-dog, out of thy depth!” cried I, “and confess how deep that depth is! Whence cometh that which thou snortest up?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou drinkest copiously at the sea: that doth thine embittered eloquence betray! In sooth, for a dog of the depth, thou takest thy nourishment too much from the surface!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At the most, I regard thee as the ventriloquist of the earth: and ever, when I have heard subversive and spouting devils speak, I have found them like thee: embittered, mendacious, and shallow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye understand how to roar and obscure with ashes! Ye are the best braggarts, and have sufficiently learned the art of making dregs boil.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where ye are, there must always be dregs at hand, and much that is spongy, hollow, and compressed: it wanteth to have freedom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Freedom’ ye all roar most eagerly: but I have unlearned the belief in ‘great events,’ when there is much roaring and smoke about them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And believe me, friend Hullabaloo! The greatest events—are not our noisiest, but our stillest hours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not around the inventors of new noise, but around the inventors of new values, doth the world revolve; INAUDIBLY it revolveth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And just own to it! Little had ever taken place when thy noise and smoke passed away. What, if a city did become a mummy, and a statue lay in the mud!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this do I say also to the o’erthrowers of statues: It is certainly the greatest folly to throw salt into the sea, and statues into the mud.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the mud of your contempt lay the statue: but it is just its law, that out of contempt, its life and living beauty grow again!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With diviner features doth it now arise, seducing by its suffering; and verily! it will yet thank you for o’erthrowing it, ye subverters!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This counsel, however, do I counsel to kings and churches, and to all that is weak with age or virtue—let yourselves be o’erthrown! That ye may again come to life, and that virtue—may come to you!—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake I before the fire-dog: then did he interrupt me sullenly, and asked: “Church? What is that?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Church?” answered I, “that is a kind of state, and indeed the most mendacious. But remain quiet, thou dissembling dog! Thou surely knowest thine own species best!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like thyself the state is a dissembling dog; like thee doth it like to speak with smoke and roaring—to make believe, like thee, that it speaketh out of the heart of things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For it seeketh by all means to be the most important creature on earth, the state; and people think it so.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When I had said this, the fire-dog acted as if mad with envy. “What!” cried he, “the most important creature on earth? And people think it so?” And so much vapour and terrible voices came out of his throat, that I thought he would choke with vexation and envy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At last he became calmer and his panting subsided; as soon, however, as he was quiet, I said laughingly:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou art angry, fire-dog: so I am in the right about thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And that I may also maintain the right, hear the story of another fire-dog; he speaketh actually out of the heart of the earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gold doth his breath exhale, and golden rain: so doth his heart desire. What are ashes and smoke and hot dregs to him!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Laughter flitteth from him like a variegated cloud; adverse is he to thy gargling and spewing and grips in the bowels!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The gold, however, and the laughter—these doth he take out of the heart of the earth: for, that thou mayst know it,—THE HEART OF THE EARTH IS OF GOLD.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the fire-dog heard this, he could no longer endure to listen to me. Abashed did he draw in his tail, said “bow-wow!” in a cowed voice, and crept down into his cave.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus told Zarathustra. His disciples, however, hardly listened to him: so great was their eagerness to tell him about the sailors, the rabbits, and the flying man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What am I to think of it!” said Zarathustra. “Am I indeed a ghost?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it may have been my shadow. Ye have surely heard something of the Wanderer and his Shadow?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One thing, however, is certain: I must keep a tighter hold of it; otherwise it will spoil my reputation.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And once more Zarathustra shook his head and wondered. “What am I to think of it!” said he once more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why did the ghost cry: ‘It is time! It is the highest time!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>For what</i> is it then—the highest time?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLI. THE SOOTHSAYER.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“-And I saw a great sadness come over mankind. The best turned weary of their works.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A doctrine appeared, a faith ran beside it: ‘All is empty, all is alike, all hath been!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And from all hills there re-echoed: ‘All is empty, all is alike, all hath been!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure we have harvested: but why have all our fruits become rotten and brown? What was it fell last night from the evil moon?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In vain was all our labour, poison hath our wine become, the evil eye hath singed yellow our fields and hearts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Arid have we all become; and fire falling upon us, then do we turn dust like ashes:—yea, the fire itself have we made aweary.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All our fountains have dried up, even the sea hath receded. All the ground trieth to gape, but the depth will not swallow!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Alas! where is there still a sea in which one could be drowned?’ so soundeth our plaint—across shallow swamps.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, even for dying have we become too weary; now do we keep awake and live on—in sepulchres.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did Zarathustra hear a soothsayer speak; and the foreboding touched his heart and transformed him. Sorrowfully did he go about and wearily; and he became like unto those of whom the soothsayer had spoken.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, said he unto his disciples, a little while, and there cometh the long twilight. Alas, how shall I preserve my light through it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That it may not smother in this sorrowfulness! To remoter worlds shall it be a light, and also to remotest nights!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did Zarathustra go about grieved in his heart, and for three days he did not take any meat or drink: he had no rest, and lost his speech. At last it came to pass that he fell into a deep sleep. His disciples, however, sat around him in long night-watches, and waited anxiously to see if he would awake, and speak again, and recover from his affliction.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this is the discourse that Zarathustra spake when he awoke; his voice, however, came unto his disciples as from afar:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hear, I pray you, the dream that I dreamed, my friends, and help me to divine its meaning!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A riddle is it still unto me, this dream; the meaning is hidden in it and encaged, and doth not yet fly above it on free pinions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All life had I renounced, so I dreamed. Night-watchman and grave-guardian had I become, aloft, in the lone mountain-fortress of Death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There did I guard his coffins: full stood the musty vaults of those trophies of victory. Out of glass coffins did vanquished life gaze upon me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The odour of dust-covered eternities did I breathe: sultry and dust-covered lay my soul. And who could have aired his soul there!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Brightness of midnight was ever around me; lonesomeness cowered beside her; and as a third, death-rattle stillness, the worst of my female friends.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Keys did I carry, the rustiest of all keys; and I knew how to open with them the most creaking of all gates.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like a bitterly angry croaking ran the sound through the long corridors when the leaves of the gate opened: ungraciously did this bird cry, unwillingly was it awakened.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But more frightful even, and more heart-strangling was it, when it again became silent and still all around, and I alone sat in that malignant silence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did time pass with me, and slip by, if time there still was: what do I know thereof! But at last there happened that which awoke me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thrice did there peal peals at the gate like thunders, thrice did the vaults resound and howl again: then did I go to the gate.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alpa! cried I, who carrieth his ashes unto the mountain? Alpa! Alpa! who carrieth his ashes unto the mountain?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I pressed the key, and pulled at the gate, and exerted myself. But not a finger’s-breadth was it yet open:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then did a roaring wind tear the folds apart: whistling, whizzing, and piercing, it threw unto me a black coffin.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And in the roaring, and whistling, and whizzing the coffin burst up, and spouted out a thousand peals of laughter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And a thousand caricatures of children, angels, owls, fools, and child-sized butterflies laughed and mocked, and roared at me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Fearfully was I terrified thereby: it prostrated me. And I cried with horror as I ne’er cried before.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But mine own crying awoke me:—and I came to myself.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did Zarathustra relate his dream, and then was silent: for as yet he knew not the interpretation thereof. But the disciple whom he loved most arose quickly, seized Zarathustra’s hand, and said:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thy life itself interpreteth unto us this dream, O Zarathustra!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou not thyself the wind with shrill whistling, which bursteth open the gates of the fortress of Death?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou not thyself the coffin full of many-hued malices and angel-caricatures of life?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, like a thousand peals of children’s laughter cometh Zarathustra into all sepulchres, laughing at those night-watchmen and grave-guardians, and whoever else rattleth with sinister keys.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thy laughter wilt thou frighten and prostrate them: fainting and recovering will demonstrate thy power over them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when the long twilight cometh and the mortal weariness, even then wilt thou not disappear from our firmament, thou advocate of life!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>New stars hast thou made us see, and new nocturnal glories: verily, laughter itself hast thou spread out over us like a many-hued canopy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now will children’s laughter ever from coffins flow; now will a strong wind ever come victoriously unto all mortal weariness: of this thou art thyself the pledge and the prophet!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, THEY THEMSELVES DIDST THOU DREAM, thine enemies: that was thy sorest dream.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But as thou awokest from them and camest to thyself, so shall they awaken from themselves—and come unto thee!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the disciple; and all the others then thronged around Zarathustra, grasped him by the hands, and tried to persuade him to leave his bed and his sadness, and return unto them. Zarathustra, however, sat upright on his couch, with an absent look. Like one returning from long foreign sojourn did he look on his disciples, and examined their features; but still he knew them not. When, however, they raised him, and set him upon his feet, behold, all on a sudden his eye changed; he understood everything that had happened, stroked his beard, and said with a strong voice:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Well! this hath just its time; but see to it, my disciples, that we have a good repast; and without delay! Thus do I mean to make amends for bad dreams!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The soothsayer, however, shall eat and drink at my side: and verily, I will yet show him a sea in which he can drown himself!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra. Then did he gaze long into the face of the disciple who had been the dream-interpreter, and shook his head.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLII. REDEMPTION.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra went one day over the great bridge, then did the cripples and beggars surround him, and a hunchback spake thus unto him:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Behold, Zarathustra! Even the people learn from thee, and acquire faith in thy teaching: but for them to believe fully in thee, one thing is still needful—thou must first of all convince us cripples! Here hast thou now a fine selection, and verily, an opportunity with more than one forelock! The blind canst thou heal, and make the lame run; and from him who hath too much behind, couldst thou well, also, take away a little;—that, I think, would be the right method to make the cripples believe in Zarathustra!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra, however, answered thus unto him who so spake: When one taketh his hump from the hunchback, then doth one take from him his spirit—so do the people teach. And when one giveth the blind man eyes, then doth he see too many bad things on the earth: so that he curseth him who healed him. He, however, who maketh the lame man run, inflicteth upon him the greatest injury; for hardly can he run, when his vices run away with him—so do the people teach concerning cripples. And why should not Zarathustra also learn from the people, when the people learn from Zarathustra?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is, however, the smallest thing unto me since I have been amongst men, to see one person lacking an eye, another an ear, and a third a leg, and that others have lost the tongue, or the nose, or the head.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I see and have seen worse things, and divers things so hideous, that I should neither like to speak of all matters, nor even keep silent about some of them: namely, men who lack everything, except that they have too much of one thing—men who are nothing more than a big eye, or a big mouth, or a big belly, or something else big,—reversed cripples, I call such men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I came out of my solitude, and for the first time passed over this bridge, then I could not trust mine eyes, but looked again and again, and said at last: “That is an ear! An ear as big as a man!” I looked still more attentively—and actually there did move under the ear something that was pitiably small and poor and slim. And in truth this immense ear was perched on a small thin stalk—the stalk, however, was a man! A person putting a glass to his eyes, could even recognise further a small envious countenance, and also that a bloated soullet dangled at the stalk. The people told me, however, that the big ear was not only a man, but a great man, a genius. But I never believed in the people when they spake of great men—and I hold to my belief that it was a reversed cripple, who had too little of everything, and too much of one thing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had spoken thus unto the hunchback, and unto those of whom the hunchback was the mouthpiece and advocate, then did he turn to his disciples in profound dejection, and said:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, my friends, I walk amongst men as amongst the fragments and limbs of human beings!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is the terrible thing to mine eye, that I find man broken up, and scattered about, as on a battle- and butcher-ground.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when mine eye fleeth from the present to the bygone, it findeth ever the same: fragments and limbs and fearful chances—but no men!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The present and the bygone upon earth—ah! my friends—that is MY most unbearable trouble; and I should not know how to live, if I were not a seer of what is to come.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A seer, a purposer, a creator, a future itself, and a bridge to the future—and alas! also as it were a cripple on this bridge: all that is Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ye also asked yourselves often: “Who is Zarathustra to us? What shall he be called by us?” And like me, did ye give yourselves questions for answers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is he a promiser? Or a fulfiller? A conqueror? Or an inheritor? A harvest? Or a ploughshare? A physician? Or a healed one?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is he a poet? Or a genuine one? An emancipator? Or a subjugator? A good one? Or an evil one?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I walk amongst men as the fragments of the future: that future which I contemplate.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And it is all my poetisation and aspiration to compose and collect into unity what is fragment and riddle and fearful chance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And how could I endure to be a man, if man were not also the composer, and riddle-reader, and redeemer of chance!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To redeem what is past, and to transform every “It was” into “Thus would I have it!”—that only do I call redemption!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Will—so is the emancipator and joy-bringer called: thus have I taught you, my friends! But now learn this likewise: the Will itself is still a prisoner.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Willing emancipateth: but what is that called which still putteth the emancipator in chains?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“It was”: thus is the Will’s teeth-gnashing and lonesomest tribulation called. Impotent towards what hath been done—it is a malicious spectator of all that is past.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not backward can the Will will; that it cannot break time and time’s desire—that is the Will’s lonesomest tribulation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Willing emancipateth: what doth Willing itself devise in order to get free from its tribulation and mock at its prison?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, a fool becometh every prisoner! Foolishly delivereth itself also the imprisoned Will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That time doth not run backward—that is its animosity: “That which was”: so is the stone which it cannot roll called.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thus doth it roll stones out of animosity and ill-humour, and taketh revenge on whatever doth not, like it, feel rage and ill-humour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did the Will, the emancipator, become a torturer; and on all that is capable of suffering it taketh revenge, because it cannot go backward.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, yea, this alone is REVENGE itself: the Will’s antipathy to time, and its “It was.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, a great folly dwelleth in our Will; and it became a curse unto all humanity, that this folly acquired spirit!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THE SPIRIT OF REVENGE: my friends, that hath hitherto been man’s best contemplation; and where there was suffering, it was claimed there was always penalty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Penalty,” so calleth itself revenge. With a lying word it feigneth a good conscience.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And because in the willer himself there is suffering, because he cannot will backwards—thus was Willing itself, and all life, claimed—to be penalty!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And then did cloud after cloud roll over the spirit, until at last madness preached: “Everything perisheth, therefore everything deserveth to perish!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“And this itself is justice, the law of time—that he must devour his children:” thus did madness preach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Morally are things ordered according to justice and penalty. Oh, where is there deliverance from the flux of things and from the ‘existence’ of penalty?” Thus did madness preach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Can there be deliverance when there is eternal justice? Alas, unrollable is the stone, ‘It was’: eternal must also be all penalties!” Thus did madness preach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“No deed can be annihilated: how could it be undone by the penalty! This, this is what is eternal in the ‘existence’ of penalty, that existence also must be eternally recurring deed and guilt!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unless the Will should at last deliver itself, and Willing become non-Willing—:” but ye know, my brethren, this fabulous song of madness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away from those fabulous songs did I lead you when I taught you: “The Will is a creator.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All “It was” is a fragment, a riddle, a fearful chance—until the creating Will saith thereto: “But thus would I have it.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Until the creating Will saith thereto: “But thus do I will it! Thus shall I will it!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But did it ever speak thus? And when doth this take place? Hath the Will been unharnessed from its own folly?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hath the Will become its own deliverer and joy-bringer? Hath it unlearned the spirit of revenge and all teeth-gnashing?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And who hath taught it reconciliation with time, and something higher than all reconciliation?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Something higher than all reconciliation must the Will will which is the Will to Power—: but how doth that take place? Who hath taught it also to will backwards?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—But at this point in his discourse it chanced that Zarathustra suddenly paused, and looked like a person in the greatest alarm. With terror in his eyes did he gaze on his disciples; his glances pierced as with arrows their thoughts and arrear-thoughts. But after a brief space he again laughed, and said soothedly:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“It is difficult to live amongst men, because silence is so difficult— especially for a babbler.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra. The hunchback, however, had listened to the conversation and had covered his face during the time; but when he heard Zarathustra laugh, he looked up with curiosity, and said slowly:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“But why doth Zarathustra speak otherwise unto us than unto his disciples?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra answered: “What is there to be wondered at! With hunchbacks one may well speak in a hunchbacked way!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Very good,” said the hunchback; “and with pupils one may well tell tales out of school.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But why doth Zarathustra speak otherwise unto his pupils—than unto himself?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLIII. MANLY PRUDENCE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>Not the height, it is the declivity that is terrible!</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The declivity, where the gaze shooteth DOWNWARDS, and the hand graspeth UPWARDS. There doth the heart become giddy through its double will.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, friends, do ye divine also my heart’s double will?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, this is MY declivity and my danger, that my gaze shooteth towards the summit, and my hand would fain clutch and lean—on the depth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To man clingeth my will; with chains do I bind myself to man, because I am pulled upwards to the Superman: for thither doth mine other will tend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And THEREFORE do I live blindly among men, as if I knew them not: that my hand may not entirely lose belief in firmness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I know not you men: this gloom and consolation is often spread around me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I sit at the gateway for every rogue, and ask: Who wisheth to deceive me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is my first manly prudence, that I allow myself to be deceived, so as not to be on my guard against deceivers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, if I were on my guard against man, how could man be an anchor to my ball! Too easily would I be pulled upwards and away!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This providence is over my fate, that I have to be without foresight.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he who would not languish amongst men, must learn to drink out of all glasses; and he who would keep clean amongst men, must know how to wash himself even with dirty water.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thus spake I often to myself for consolation: “Courage! Cheer up! old heart! An unhappiness hath failed to befall thee: enjoy that as thy—happiness!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, however, is mine other manly prudence: I am more forbearing to the VAIN than to the proud.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is not wounded vanity the mother of all tragedies? Where, however, pride is wounded, there there groweth up something better than pride.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That life may be fair to behold, its game must be well played; for that purpose, however, it needeth good actors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Good actors have I found all the vain ones: they play, and wish people to be fond of beholding them—all their spirit is in this wish.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They represent themselves, they invent themselves; in their neighbourhood I like to look upon life—it cureth of melancholy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore am I forbearing to the vain, because they are the physicians of my melancholy, and keep me attached to man as to a drama.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And further, who conceiveth the full depth of the modesty of the vain man! I am favourable to him, and sympathetic on account of his modesty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From you would he learn his belief in himself; he feedeth upon your glances, he eateth praise out of your hands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your lies doth he even believe when you lie favourably about him: for in its depths sigheth his heart: “What am <i>I</i>?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if that be the true virtue which is unconscious of itself—well, the vain man is unconscious of his modesty!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000001999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is, however, my third manly prudence: I am not put out of conceit with the WICKED by your timorousness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am happy to see the marvels the warm sun hatcheth: tigers and palms and rattle-snakes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Also amongst men there is a beautiful brood of the warm sun, and much that is marvellous in the wicked.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In truth, as your wisest did not seem to me so very wise, so found I also human wickedness below the fame of it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And oft did I ask with a shake of the head: Why still rattle, ye rattle-snakes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, there is still a future even for evil! And the warmest south is still undiscovered by man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How many things are now called the worst wickedness, which are only twelve feet broad and three months long! Some day, however, will greater dragons come into the world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For that the Superman may not lack his dragon, the superdragon that is worthy of him, there must still much warm sun glow on moist virgin forests!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Out of your wild cats must tigers have evolved, and out of your poison-toads, crocodiles: for the good hunter shall have a good hunt!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, ye good and just! In you there is much to be laughed at, and especially your fear of what hath hitherto been called “the devil!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So alien are ye in your souls to what is great, that to you the Superman would be FRIGHTFUL in his goodness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ye wise and knowing ones, ye would flee from the solar-glow of the wisdom in which the Superman joyfully batheth his nakedness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye highest men who have come within my ken! this is my doubt of you, and my secret laughter: I suspect ye would call my Superman—a devil!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, I became tired of those highest and best ones: from their “height” did I long to be up, out, and away to the Superman!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A horror came over me when I saw those best ones naked: then there grew for me the pinions to soar away into distant futures.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Into more distant futures, into more southern souths than ever artist dreamed of: thither, where Gods are ashamed of all clothes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But disguised do I want to see YOU, ye neighbours and fellowmen, and well-attired and vain and estimable, as “the good and just;”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And disguised will I myself sit amongst you—that I may MISTAKE you and myself: for that is my last manly prudence.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLIV. THE STILLEST HOUR.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What hath happened unto me, my friends? Ye see me troubled, driven forth, unwillingly obedient, ready to go—alas, to go away from YOU!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea, once more must Zarathustra retire to his solitude: but unjoyously this time doth the bear go back to his cave!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What hath happened unto me? Who ordereth this?—Ah, mine angry mistress wisheth it so; she spake unto me. Have I ever named her name to you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yesterday towards evening there spake unto me MY STILLEST HOUR: that is the name of my terrible mistress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thus did it happen—for everything must I tell you, that your heart may not harden against the suddenly departing one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do ye know the terror of him who falleth asleep?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the very toes he is terrified, because the ground giveth way under him, and the dream beginneth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This do I speak unto you in parable. Yesterday at the stillest hour did the ground give way under me: the dream began.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour-hand moved on, the timepiece of my life drew breath—never did I hear such stillness around me, so that my heart was terrified.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there spoken unto me without voice: “THOU KNOWEST IT, ZARATHUSTRA?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I cried in terror at this whispering, and the blood left my face: but I was silent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there once more spoken unto me without voice: “Thou knowest it, Zarathustra, but thou dost not speak it!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And at last I answered, like one defiant: “Yea, I know it, but I will not speak it!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “Thou WILT not, Zarathustra? Is this true? Conceal thyself not behind thy defiance!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I wept and trembled like a child, and said: “Ah, I would indeed, but how can I do it! Exempt me only from this! It is beyond my power!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “What matter about thyself, Zarathustra! Speak thy word, and succumb!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered: “Ah, is it MY word? Who am <i>I</i>? I await the worthier one; I am not worthy even to succumb by it.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “What matter about thyself? Thou art not yet humble enough for me. Humility hath the hardest skin.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered: “What hath not the skin of my humility endured! At the foot of my height do I dwell: how high are my summits, no one hath yet told me. But well do I know my valleys.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “O Zarathustra, he who hath to remove mountains removeth also valleys and plains.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered: “As yet hath my word not removed mountains, and what I have spoken hath not reached man. I went, indeed, unto men, but not yet have I attained unto them.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “What knowest thou THEREOF! The dew falleth on the grass when the night is most silent.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered: “They mocked me when I found and walked in mine own path; and certainly did my feet then tremble.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thus did they speak unto me: Thou forgottest the path before, now dost thou also forget how to walk!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “What matter about their mockery! Thou art one who hast unlearned to obey: now shalt thou command!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Knowest thou not who is most needed by all? He who commandeth great things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To execute great things is difficult: but the more difficult task is to command great things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is thy most unpardonable obstinacy: thou hast the power, and thou wilt not rule.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered: “I lack the lion’s voice for all commanding.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me as a whispering: “It is the stillest words which bring the storm. Thoughts that come with doves’ footsteps guide the world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, thou shalt go as a shadow of that which is to come: thus wilt thou command, and in commanding go foremost.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I answered: “I am ashamed.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was there again spoken unto me without voice: “Thou must yet become a child, and be without shame.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The pride of youth is still upon thee; late hast thou become young: but he who would become a child must surmount even his youth.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I considered a long while, and trembled. At last, however, did I say what I had said at first. “I will not.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then did a laughing take place all around me. Alas, how that laughing lacerated my bowels and cut into my heart!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And there was spoken unto me for the last time: “O Zarathustra, thy fruits are ripe, but thou art not ripe for thy fruits!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So must thou go again into solitude: for thou shalt yet become mellow.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And again was there a laughing, and it fled: then did it become still around me, as with a double stillness. I lay, however, on the ground, and the sweat flowed from my limbs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Now have ye heard all, and why I have to return into my solitude. Nothing have I kept hidden from you, my friends.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But even this have ye heard from me, WHO is still the most reserved of men—and will be so!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, my friends! I should have something more to say unto you! I should have something more to give unto you! Why do I not give it? Am I then a niggard?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When, however, Zarathustra had spoken these words, the violence of his pain, and a sense of the nearness of his departure from his friends came over him, so that he wept aloud; and no one knew how to console him. In the night, however, he went away alone and left his friends.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>THIRD PART.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ye look aloft when ye long for exaltation, and I look downward because I am exalted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Who among you can at the same time laugh and be exalted?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“He who climbeth on the highest mountains, laugheth at all tragic plays and tragic realities.”—ZARATHUSTRA, I., “Reading and Writing.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLV. THE WANDERER.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then, when it was about midnight, Zarathustra went his way over the ridge of the isle, that he might arrive early in the morning at the other coast; because there he meant to embark. For there was a good roadstead there, in which foreign ships also liked to anchor: those ships took many people with them, who wished to cross over from the Happy Isles. So when Zarathustra thus ascended the mountain, he thought on the way of his many solitary wanderings from youth onwards, and how many mountains and ridges and summits he had already climbed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am a wanderer and mountain-climber, said he to his heart, I love not the plains, and it seemeth I cannot long sit still.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whatever may still overtake me as fate and experience—a wandering will be therein, and a mountain-climbing: in the end one experienceth only oneself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The time is now past when accidents could befall me; and what COULD now fall to my lot which would not already be mine own!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It returneth only, it cometh home to me at last—mine own Self, and such of it as hath been long abroad, and scattered among things and accidents.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And one thing more do I know: I stand now before my last summit, and before that which hath been longest reserved for me. Ah, my hardest path must I ascend! Ah, I have begun my lonesomest wandering!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He, however, who is of my nature doth not avoid such an hour: the hour that saith unto him: Now only dost thou go the way to thy greatness! Summit and abyss—these are now comprised together!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou goest the way to thy greatness: now hath it become thy last refuge, what was hitherto thy last danger!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou goest the way to thy greatness: it must now be thy best courage that there is no longer any path behind thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou goest the way to thy greatness: here shall no one steal after thee! Thy foot itself hath effaced the path behind thee, and over it standeth written: Impossibility.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if all ladders henceforth fail thee, then must thou learn to mount upon thine own head: how couldst thou mount upward otherwise?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Upon thine own head, and beyond thine own heart! Now must the gentlest in thee become the hardest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who hath always much-indulged himself, sickeneth at last by his much-indulgence. Praises on what maketh hardy! I do not praise the land where butter and honey—flow!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To learn TO LOOK AWAY FROM oneself, is necessary in order to see MANY THINGS:—this hardiness is needed by every mountain-climber.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He, however, who is obtrusive with his eyes as a discerner, how can he ever see more of anything than its foreground!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thou, O Zarathustra, wouldst view the ground of everything, and its background: thus must thou mount even above thyself—up, upwards, until thou hast even thy stars UNDER thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yea! To look down upon myself, and even upon my stars: that only would I call my SUMMIT, that hath remained for me as my LAST summit!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra to himself while ascending, comforting his heart with harsh maxims: for he was sore at heart as he had never been before. And when he had reached the top of the mountain-ridge, behold, there lay the other sea spread out before him: and he stood still and was long silent. The night, however, was cold at this height, and clear and starry.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I recognise my destiny, said he at last, sadly. Well! I am ready. Now hath my last lonesomeness begun.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, this sombre, sad sea, below me! Ah, this sombre nocturnal vexation! Ah, fate and sea! To you must I now GO DOWN!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Before my highest mountain do I stand, and before my longest wandering: therefore must I first go deeper down than I ever ascended:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Deeper down into pain than I ever ascended, even into its darkest flood! So willeth my fate. Well! I am ready.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whence come the highest mountains? so did I once ask. Then did I learn that they come out of the sea.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That testimony is inscribed on their stones, and on the walls of their summits. Out of the deepest must the highest come to its height.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra on the ridge of the mountain where it was cold: when, however, he came into the vicinity of the sea, and at last stood alone amongst the cliffs, then had he become weary on his way, and eagerer than ever before.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything as yet sleepeth, said he; even the sea sleepeth. Drowsily and strangely doth its eye gaze upon me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it breatheth warmly—I feel it. And I feel also that it dreameth. It tosseth about dreamily on hard pillows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hark! Hark! How it groaneth with evil recollections! Or evil expectations?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, I am sad along with thee, thou dusky monster, and angry with myself even for thy sake.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, that my hand hath not strength enough! Gladly, indeed, would I free thee from evil dreams!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And while Zarathustra thus spake, he laughed at himself with melancholy and bitterness. What! Zarathustra, said he, wilt thou even sing consolation to the sea?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, thou amiable fool, Zarathustra, thou too-blindly confiding one! But thus hast thou ever been: ever hast thou approached confidently all that is terrible.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every monster wouldst thou caress. A whiff of warm breath, a little soft tuft on its paw—: and immediately wert thou ready to love and lure it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>LOVE is the danger of the lonesomest one, love to anything, IF IT ONLY LIVE! Laughable, verily, is my folly and my modesty in love!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and laughed thereby a second time. Then, however, he thought of his abandoned friends—and as if he had done them a wrong with his thoughts, he upbraided himself because of his thoughts. And forthwith it came to pass that the laugher wept—with anger and longing wept Zarathustra bitterly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLVI. THE VISION AND THE ENIGMA.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When it got abroad among the sailors that Zarathustra was on board the ship—for a man who came from the Happy Isles had gone on board along with him,—there was great curiosity and expectation. But Zarathustra kept silent for two days, and was cold and deaf with sadness; so that he neither answered looks nor questions. On the evening of the second day, however, he again opened his ears, though he still kept silent: for there were many curious and dangerous things to be heard on board the ship, which came from afar, and was to go still further. Zarathustra, however, was fond of all those who make distant voyages, and dislike to live without danger. And behold! when listening, his own tongue was at last loosened, and the ice of his heart broke. Then did he begin to speak thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To you, the daring venturers and adventurers, and whoever hath embarked with cunning sails upon frightful seas,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To you the enigma-intoxicated, the twilight-enjoyers, whose souls are allured by flutes to every treacherous gulf:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For ye dislike to grope at a thread with cowardly hand; and where ye can DIVINE, there do ye hate to CALCULATE—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To you only do I tell the enigma that I SAW—the vision of the lonesomest one.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gloomily walked I lately in corpse-coloured twilight—gloomily and sternly, with compressed lips. Not only one sun had set for me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A path which ascended daringly among boulders, an evil, lonesome path, which neither herb nor shrub any longer cheered, a mountain-path, crunched under the daring of my foot.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mutely marching over the scornful clinking of pebbles, trampling the stone that let it slip: thus did my foot force its way upwards.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Upwards:—in spite of the spirit that drew it downwards, towards the abyss, the spirit of gravity, my devil and arch-enemy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Upwards:—although it sat upon me, half-dwarf, half-mole; paralysed, paralysing; dripping lead in mine ear, and thoughts like drops of lead into my brain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” it whispered scornfully, syllable by syllable, “thou stone of wisdom! Thou threwest thyself high, but every thrown stone must—fall!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, thou stone of wisdom, thou sling-stone, thou star-destroyer! Thyself threwest thou so high,—but every thrown stone—must fall!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Condemned of thyself, and to thine own stoning: O Zarathustra, far indeed threwest thou thy stone—but upon THYSELF will it recoil!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then was the dwarf silent; and it lasted long. The silence, however, oppressed me; and to be thus in pairs, one is verily lonesomer than when alone!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I ascended, I ascended, I dreamt, I thought,—but everything oppressed me. A sick one did I resemble, whom bad torture wearieth, and a worse dream reawakeneth out of his first sleep.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But there is something in me which I call courage: it hath hitherto slain for me every dejection. This courage at last bade me stand still and say: “Dwarf! Thou! Or I!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For courage is the best slayer,—courage which ATTACKETH: for in every attack there is sound of triumph.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man, however, is the most courageous animal: thereby hath he overcome every animal. With sound of triumph hath he overcome every pain; human pain, however, is the sorest pain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Courage slayeth also giddiness at abysses: and where doth man not stand at abysses! Is not seeing itself—seeing abysses?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Courage is the best slayer: courage slayeth also fellow-suffering. Fellow-suffering, however, is the deepest abyss: as deeply as man looketh into life, so deeply also doth he look into suffering.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Courage, however, is the best slayer, courage which attacketh: it slayeth even death itself; for it saith: “WAS THAT life? Well! Once more!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In such speech, however, there is much sound of triumph. He who hath ears to hear, let him hear.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Halt, dwarf!” said I. “Either I—or thou! I, however, am the stronger of the two:—thou knowest not mine abysmal thought! IT—couldst thou not endure!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then happened that which made me lighter: for the dwarf sprang from my shoulder, the prying sprite! And it squatted on a stone in front of me. There was however a gateway just where we halted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Look at this gateway! Dwarf!” I continued, “it hath two faces. Two roads come together here: these hath no one yet gone to the end of.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This long lane backwards: it continueth for an eternity. And that long lane forward—that is another eternity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They are antithetical to one another, these roads; they directly abut on one another:—and it is here, at this gateway, that they come together. The name of the gateway is inscribed above: ‘This Moment.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But should one follow them further—and ever further and further on, thinkest thou, dwarf, that these roads would be eternally antithetical?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Everything straight lieth,” murmured the dwarf, contemptuously. “All truth is crooked; time itself is a circle.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou spirit of gravity!” said I wrathfully, “do not take it too lightly! Or I shall let thee squat where thou squattest, Haltfoot,—and I carried thee HIGH!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Observe,” continued I, “This Moment! From the gateway, This Moment, there runneth a long eternal lane BACKWARDS: behind us lieth an eternity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Must not whatever CAN run its course of all things, have already run along that lane? Must not whatever CAN happen of all things have already happened, resulted, and gone by?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if everything have already existed, what thinkest thou, dwarf, of This Moment? Must not this gateway also—have already existed?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And are not all things closely bound together in such wise that This Moment draweth all coming things after it? CONSEQUENTLY—itself also?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For whatever CAN run its course of all things, also in this long lane OUTWARD—MUST it once more run!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this slow spider which creepeth in the moonlight, and this moonlight itself, and thou and I in this gateway whispering together, whispering of eternal things—must we not all have already existed?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And must we not return and run in that other lane out before us, that long weird lane—must we not eternally return?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did I speak, and always more softly: for I was afraid of mine own thoughts, and arrear-thoughts. Then, suddenly did I hear a dog HOWL near me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Had I ever heard a dog howl thus? My thoughts ran back. Yes! When I was a child, in my most distant childhood:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Then did I hear a dog howl thus. And saw it also, with hair bristling, its head upwards, trembling in the stillest midnight, when even dogs believe in ghosts:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—So that it excited my commiseration. For just then went the full moon, silent as death, over the house; just then did it stand still, a glowing globe—at rest on the flat roof, as if on some one’s property:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereby had the dog been terrified: for dogs believe in thieves and ghosts. And when I again heard such howling, then did it excite my commiseration once more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where was now the dwarf? And the gateway? And the spider? And all the whispering? Had I dreamt? Had I awakened? ‘Twixt rugged rocks did I suddenly stand alone, dreary in the dreariest moonlight.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>BUT THERE LAY A MAN! And there! The dog leaping, bristling, whining—now did it see me coming—then did it howl again, then did it CRY:—had I ever heard a dog cry so for help?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, what I saw, the like had I never seen. A young shepherd did I see, writhing, choking, quivering, with distorted countenance, and with a heavy black serpent hanging out of his mouth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Had I ever seen so much loathing and pale horror on one countenance? He had perhaps gone to sleep? Then had the serpent crawled into his throat—there had it bitten itself fast.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My hand pulled at the serpent, and pulled:—in vain! I failed to pull the serpent out of his throat. Then there cried out of me: “Bite! Bite!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Its head off! Bite!”—so cried it out of me; my horror, my hatred, my loathing, my pity, all my good and my bad cried with one voice out of me.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye daring ones around me! Ye venturers and adventurers, and whoever of you have embarked with cunning sails on unexplored seas! Ye enigma-enjoyers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Solve unto me the enigma that I then beheld, interpret unto me the vision of the lonesomest one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For it was a vision and a foresight:—WHAT did I then behold in parable? And WHO is it that must come some day?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>WHO is the shepherd into whose throat the serpent thus crawled? WHO is the man into whose throat all the heaviest and blackest will thus crawl?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The shepherd however bit as my cry had admonished him; he bit with a strong bite! Far away did he spit the head of the serpent—: and sprang up.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No longer shepherd, no longer man—a transfigured being, a light-surrounded being, that LAUGHED! Never on earth laughed a man as HE laughed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, I heard a laughter which was no human laughter,—and now gnaweth a thirst at me, a longing that is never allayed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My longing for that laughter gnaweth at me: oh, how can I still endure to live! And how could I endure to die at present!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLVII. INVOLUNTARY BLISS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With such enigmas and bitterness in his heart did Zarathustra sail o’er the sea. When, however, he was four day-journeys from the Happy Isles and from his friends, then had he surmounted all his pain—: triumphantly and with firm foot did he again accept his fate. And then talked Zarathustra in this wise to his exulting conscience:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alone am I again, and like to be so, alone with the pure heaven, and the open sea; and again is the afternoon around me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On an afternoon did I find my friends for the first time; on an afternoon, also, did I find them a second time:—at the hour when all light becometh stiller.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For whatever happiness is still on its way ‘twixt heaven and earth, now seeketh for lodging a luminous soul: WITH HAPPINESS hath all light now become stiller.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O afternoon of my life! Once did my happiness also descend to the valley that it might seek a lodging: then did it find those open hospitable souls.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O afternoon of my life! What did I not surrender that I might have one thing: this living plantation of my thoughts, and this dawn of my highest hope!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Companions did the creating one once seek, and children of HIS hope: and lo, it turned out that he could not find them, except he himself should first create them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus am I in the midst of my work, to my children going, and from them returning: for the sake of his children must Zarathustra perfect himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For in one’s heart one loveth only one’s child and one’s work; and where there is great love to oneself, then is it the sign of pregnancy: so have I found it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still are my children verdant in their first spring, standing nigh one another, and shaken in common by the winds, the trees of my garden and of my best soil.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, where such trees stand beside one another, there ARE Happy Isles!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But one day will I take them up, and put each by itself alone: that it may learn lonesomeness and defiance and prudence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gnarled and crooked and with flexible hardness shall it then stand by the sea, a living lighthouse of unconquerable life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Yonder where the storms rush down into the sea, and the snout of the mountain drinketh water, shall each on a time have his day and night watches, for HIS testing and recognition.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Recognised and tested shall each be, to see if he be of my type and lineage:—if he be master of a long will, silent even when he speaketh, and giving in such wise that he TAKETH in giving:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—So that he may one day become my companion, a fellow-creator and fellow-enjoyer with Zarathustra:—such a one as writeth my will on my tables, for the fuller perfection of all things.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And for his sake and for those like him, must I perfect MYSELF: therefore do I now avoid my happiness, and present myself to every misfortune—for MY final testing and recognition.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, it were time that I went away; and the wanderer’s shadow and the longest tedium and the stillest hour—have all said unto me: “It is the highest time!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The word blew to me through the keyhole and said “Come!” The door sprang subtlely open unto me, and said “Go!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I lay enchained to my love for my children: desire spread this snare for me—the desire for love—that I should become the prey of my children, and lose myself in them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Desiring—that is now for me to have lost myself. I POSSESS YOU, MY CHILDREN! In this possessing shall everything be assurance and nothing desire.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But brooding lay the sun of my love upon me, in his own juice stewed Zarathustra,—then did shadows and doubts fly past me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For frost and winter I now longed: “Oh, that frost and winter would again make me crack and crunch!” sighed I:—then arose icy mist out of me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My past burst its tomb, many pains buried alive woke up—: fully slept had they merely, concealed in corpse-clothes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So called everything unto me in signs: “It is time!” But I—heard not, until at last mine abyss moved, and my thought bit me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, abysmal thought, which art MY thought! When shall I find strength to hear thee burrowing, and no longer tremble?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To my very throat throbbeth my heart when I hear thee burrowing! Thy muteness even is like to strangle me, thou abysmal mute one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet have I never ventured to call thee UP; it hath been enough that I—have carried thee about with me! As yet have I not been strong enough for my final lion-wantonness and playfulness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sufficiently formidable unto me hath thy weight ever been: but one day shall I yet find the strength and the lion’s voice which will call thee up!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When I shall have surmounted myself therein, then will I surmount myself also in that which is greater; and a VICTORY shall be the seal of my perfection!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Meanwhile do I sail along on uncertain seas; chance flattereth me, smooth-tongued chance; forward and backward do I gaze—, still see I no end.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As yet hath the hour of my final struggle not come to me—or doth it come to me perhaps just now? Verily, with insidious beauty do sea and life gaze upon me round about:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O afternoon of my life! O happiness before eventide! O haven upon high seas! O peace in uncertainty! How I distrust all of you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, distrustful am I of your insidious beauty! Like the lover am I, who distrusteth too sleek smiling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As he pusheth the best-beloved before him—tender even in severity, the jealous one—, so do I push this blissful hour before me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away with thee, thou blissful hour! With thee hath there come to me an involuntary bliss! Ready for my severest pain do I here stand:—at the wrong time hast thou come!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away with thee, thou blissful hour! Rather harbour there—with my children! Hasten! and bless them before eventide with MY happiness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There, already approacheth eventide: the sun sinketh. Away—my happiness!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra. And he waited for his misfortune the whole night; but he waited in vain. The night remained clear and calm, and happiness itself came nigher and nigher unto him. Towards morning, however, Zarathustra laughed to his heart, and said mockingly: “Happiness runneth after me. That is because I do not run after women. Happiness, however, is a woman.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLVIII. BEFORE SUNRISE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O heaven above me, thou pure, thou deep heaven! Thou abyss of light! Gazing on thee, I tremble with divine desires.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Up to thy height to toss myself—that is MY depth! In thy purity to hide myself—that is MINE innocence!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The God veileth his beauty: thus hidest thou thy stars. Thou speakest not: THUS proclaimest thou thy wisdom unto me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mute o’er the raging sea hast thou risen for me to-day; thy love and thy modesty make a revelation unto my raging soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In that thou camest unto me beautiful, veiled in thy beauty, in that thou spakest unto me mutely, obvious in thy wisdom:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I fail to divine all the modesty of thy soul! BEFORE the sun didst thou come unto me—the lonesomest one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We have been friends from the beginning: to us are grief, gruesomeness, and ground common; even the sun is common to us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We do not speak to each other, because we know too much—: we keep silent to each other, we smile our knowledge to each other.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou not the light of my fire? Hast thou not the sister-soul of mine insight?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Together did we learn everything; together did we learn to ascend beyond ourselves to ourselves, and to smile uncloudedly:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Uncloudedly to smile down out of luminous eyes and out of miles of distance, when under us constraint and purpose and guilt steam like rain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And wandered I alone, for WHAT did my soul hunger by night and in labyrinthine paths? And climbed I mountains, WHOM did I ever seek, if not thee, upon mountains?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And all my wandering and mountain-climbing: a necessity was it merely, and a makeshift of the unhandy one:—to FLY only, wanteth mine entire will, to fly into THEE!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And what have I hated more than passing clouds, and whatever tainteth thee? And mine own hatred have I even hated, because it tainted thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The passing clouds I detest—those stealthy cats of prey: they take from thee and me what is common to us—the vast unbounded Yea- and Amen-saying.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These mediators and mixers we detest—the passing clouds: those half-and-half ones, that have neither learned to bless nor to curse from the heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Rather will I sit in a tub under a closed heaven, rather will I sit in the abyss without heaven, than see thee, thou luminous heaven, tainted with passing clouds!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And oft have I longed to pin them fast with the jagged gold-wires of lightning, that I might, like the thunder, beat the drum upon their kettle-bellies:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—An angry drummer, because they rob me of thy Yea and Amen!—thou heaven above me, thou pure, thou luminous heaven! Thou abyss of light!—because they rob thee of MY Yea and Amen.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For rather will I have noise and thunders and tempest-blasts, than this discreet, doubting cat-repose; and also amongst men do I hate most of all the soft-treaders, and half-and-half ones, and the doubting, hesitating, passing clouds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And “he who cannot bless shall LEARN to curse!”—this clear teaching dropt unto me from the clear heaven; this star standeth in my heaven even in dark nights.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I, however, am a blesser and a Yea-sayer, if thou be but around me, thou pure, thou luminous heaven! Thou abyss of light!—into all abysses do I then carry my beneficent Yea-saying.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A blesser have I become and a Yea-sayer: and therefore strove I long and was a striver, that I might one day get my hands free for blessing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, however, is my blessing: to stand above everything as its own heaven, its round roof, its azure bell and eternal security: and blessed is he who thus blesseth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For all things are baptized at the font of eternity, and beyond good and evil; good and evil themselves, however, are but fugitive shadows and damp afflictions and passing clouds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, it is a blessing and not a blasphemy when I teach that “above all things there standeth the heaven of chance, the heaven of innocence, the heaven of hazard, the heaven of wantonness.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Of Hazard”—that is the oldest nobility in the world; that gave I back to all things; I emancipated them from bondage under purpose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This freedom and celestial serenity did I put like an azure bell above all things, when I taught that over them and through them, no “eternal Will”—willeth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This wantonness and folly did I put in place of that Will, when I taught that “In everything there is one thing impossible—rationality!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A LITTLE reason, to be sure, a germ of wisdom scattered from star to star—this leaven is mixed in all things: for the sake of folly, wisdom is mixed in all things!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A little wisdom is indeed possible; but this blessed security have I found in all things, that they prefer—<i>to dance</i> on the feet of chance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O heaven above me! thou pure, thou lofty heaven! This is now thy purity unto me, that there is no eternal reason-spider and reason-cobweb:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That thou art to me a dancing-floor for divine chances, that thou art to me a table of the Gods, for divine dice and dice-players!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thou blushest? Have I spoken unspeakable things? Have I abused, when I meant to bless thee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or is it the shame of being two of us that maketh thee blush!—Dost thou bid me go and be silent, because now—DAY cometh?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The world is deep:—and deeper than e’er the day could read. Not everything may be uttered in presence of day. But day cometh: so let us part!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O heaven above me, thou modest one! thou glowing one! O thou, my happiness before sunrise! The day cometh: so let us part!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>XLIX. THE BEDWARFING VIRTUE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra was again on the continent, he did not go straightway to his mountains and his cave, but made many wanderings and questionings, and ascertained this and that; so that he said of himself jestingly: “Lo, a river that floweth back unto its source in many windings!” For he wanted to learn what had taken place AMONG MEN during the interval: whether they had become greater or smaller. And once, when he saw a row of new houses, he marvelled, and said:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What do these houses mean? Verily, no great soul put them up as its simile!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did perhaps a silly child take them out of its toy-box? Would that another child put them again into the box!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And these rooms and chambers—can MEN go out and in there? They seem to be made for silk dolls; or for dainty-eaters, who perhaps let others eat with them.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And Zarathustra stood still and meditated. At last he said sorrowfully: “There hath EVERYTHING become smaller!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everywhere do I see lower doorways: he who is of MY type can still go therethrough, but—he must stoop!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, when shall I arrive again at my home, where I shall no longer have to stoop—shall no longer have to stoop BEFORE THE SMALL ONES!”—And Zarathustra sighed, and gazed into the distance.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The same day, however, he gave his discourse on the bedwarfing virtue.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I pass through this people and keep mine eyes open: they do not forgive me for not envying their virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They bite at me, because I say unto them that for small people, small virtues are necessary—and because it is hard for me to understand that small people are NECESSARY!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here am I still like a cock in a strange farm-yard, at which even the hens peck: but on that account I am not unfriendly to the hens.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am courteous towards them, as towards all small annoyances; to be prickly towards what is small, seemeth to me wisdom for hedgehogs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They all speak of me when they sit around their fire in the evening—they speak of me, but no one thinketh—of me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is the new stillness which I have experienced: their noise around me spreadeth a mantle over my thoughts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They shout to one another: “What is this gloomy cloud about to do to us? Let us see that it doth not bring a plague upon us!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And recently did a woman seize upon her child that was coming unto me: “Take the children away,” cried she, “such eyes scorch children’s souls.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They cough when I speak: they think coughing an objection to strong winds—they divine nothing of the boisterousness of my happiness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“We have not yet time for Zarathustra”—so they object; but what matter about a time that “hath no time” for Zarathustra?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if they should altogether praise me, how could I go to sleep on THEIR praise? A girdle of spines is their praise unto me: it scratcheth me even when I take it off.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this also did I learn among them: the praiser doeth as if he gave back; in truth, however, he wanteth more to be given him!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ask my foot if their lauding and luring strains please it! Verily, to such measure and ticktack, it liketh neither to dance nor to stand still.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To small virtues would they fain lure and laud me; to the ticktack of small happiness would they fain persuade my foot.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I pass through this people and keep mine eyes open; they have become SMALLER, and ever become smaller:—THE REASON THEREOF IS THEIR DOCTRINE OF HAPPINESS AND VIRTUE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For they are moderate also in virtue,—because they want comfort. With comfort, however, moderate virtue only is compatible.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure, they also learn in their way to stride on and stride forward: that, I call their HOBBLING.—Thereby they become a hindrance to all who are in haste.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many of them go forward, and look backwards thereby, with stiffened necks: those do I like to run up against.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Foot and eye shall not lie, nor give the lie to each other. But there is much lying among small people.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Some of them WILL, but most of them are WILLED. Some of them are genuine, but most of them are bad actors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are actors without knowing it amongst them, and actors without intending it—, the genuine ones are always rare, especially the genuine actors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Of man there is little here: therefore do their women masculinise themselves. For only he who is man enough, will—SAVE THE WOMAN in woman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And this hypocrisy found I worst amongst them, that even those who command feign the virtues of those who serve.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I serve, thou servest, we serve”—so chanteth here even the hypocrisy of the rulers—and alas! if the first lord be ONLY the first servant!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, even upon their hypocrisy did mine eyes’ curiosity alight; and well did I divine all their fly-happiness, and their buzzing around sunny window-panes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So much kindness, so much weakness do I see. So much justice and pity, so much weakness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Round, fair, and considerate are they to one another, as grains of sand are round, fair, and considerate to grains of sand.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Modestly to embrace a small happiness—that do they call “submission”! and at the same time they peer modestly after a new small happiness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In their hearts they want simply one thing most of all: that no one hurt them. Thus do they anticipate every one’s wishes and do well unto every one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That, however, is COWARDICE, though it be called “virtue.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when they chance to speak harshly, those small people, then do <i>I</i> hear therein only their hoarseness—every draught of air maketh them hoarse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Shrewd indeed are they, their virtues have shrewd fingers. But they lack fists: their fingers do not know how to creep behind fists.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Virtue for them is what maketh modest and tame: therewith have they made the wolf a dog, and man himself man’s best domestic animal.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“We set our chair in the MIDST”—so saith their smirking unto me—“and as far from dying gladiators as from satisfied swine.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That, however, is—MEDIOCRITY, though it be called moderation.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I pass through this people and let fall many words: but they know neither how to take nor how to retain them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They wonder why I came not to revile venery and vice; and verily, I came not to warn against pickpockets either!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They wonder why I am not ready to abet and whet their wisdom: as if they had not yet enough of wiseacres, whose voices grate on mine ear like slate-pencils!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I call out: “Curse all the cowardly devils in you, that would fain whimper and fold the hands and adore”—then do they shout: “Zarathustra is godless.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And especially do their teachers of submission shout this;—but precisely in their ears do I love to cry: “Yea! I AM Zarathustra, the godless!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Those teachers of submission! Wherever there is aught puny, or sickly, or scabby, there do they creep like lice; and only my disgust preventeth me from cracking them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! This is my sermon for THEIR ears: I am Zarathustra the godless, who saith: “Who is more godless than I, that I may enjoy his teaching?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am Zarathustra the godless: where do I find mine equal? And all those are mine equals who give unto themselves their Will, and divest themselves of all submission.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am Zarathustra the godless! I cook every chance in MY pot. And only when it hath been quite cooked do I welcome it as MY food.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, many a chance came imperiously unto me: but still more imperiously did my WILL speak unto it,—then did it lie imploringly upon its knees—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Imploring that it might find home and heart with me, and saying flatteringly: “See, O Zarathustra, how friend only cometh unto friend!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But why talk I, when no one hath MINE ears! And so will I shout it out unto all the winds:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye ever become smaller, ye small people! Ye crumble away, ye comfortable ones! Ye will yet perish—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—By your many small virtues, by your many small omissions, and by your many small submissions!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too tender, too yielding: so is your soil! But for a tree to become GREAT, it seeketh to twine hard roots around hard rocks!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Also what ye omit weaveth at the web of all the human future; even your naught is a cobweb, and a spider that liveth on the blood of the future.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when ye take, then is it like stealing, ye small virtuous ones; but even among knaves HONOUR saith that “one shall only steal when one cannot rob.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“It giveth itself”—that is also a doctrine of submission. But I say unto you, ye comfortable ones, that IT TAKETH TO ITSELF, and will ever take more and more from you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, that ye would renounce all HALF-willing, and would decide for idleness as ye decide for action!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, that ye understood my word: “Do ever what ye will—but first be such as CAN WILL.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Love ever your neighbour as yourselves—but first be such as LOVE THEMSELVES—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Such as love with great love, such as love with great contempt!” Thus speaketh Zarathustra the godless.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But why talk I, when no one hath MINE ears! It is still an hour too early for me here.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mine own forerunner am I among this people, mine own cockcrow in dark lanes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But THEIR hour cometh! And there cometh also mine! Hourly do they become smaller, poorer, unfruitfuller,—poor herbs! poor earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And SOON shall they stand before me like dry grass and prairie, and verily, weary of themselves—and panting for FIRE, more than for water!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O blessed hour of the lightning! O mystery before noontide!—Running fires will I one day make of them, and heralds with flaming tongues:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Herald shall they one day with flaming tongues: It cometh, it is nigh, THE GREAT NOONTIDE!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>L. ON THE OLIVE-MOUNT.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Winter, a bad guest, sitteth with me at home; blue are my hands with his friendly hand-shaking.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I honour him, that bad guest, but gladly leave him alone. Gladly do I run away from him; and when one runneth WELL, then one escapeth him!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With warm feet and warm thoughts do I run where the wind is calm—to the sunny corner of mine olive-mount.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There do I laugh at my stern guest, and am still fond of him; because he cleareth my house of flies, and quieteth many little noises.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For he suffereth it not if a gnat wanteth to buzz, or even two of them; also the lanes maketh he lonesome, so that the moonlight is afraid there at night.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A hard guest is he,—but I honour him, and do not worship, like the tenderlings, the pot-bellied fire-idol.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better even a little teeth-chattering than idol-adoration!—so willeth my nature. And especially have I a grudge against all ardent, steaming, steamy fire-idols.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Him whom I love, I love better in winter than in summer; better do I now mock at mine enemies, and more heartily, when winter sitteth in my house.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Heartily, verily, even when I CREEP into bed—: there, still laugheth and wantoneth my hidden happiness; even my deceptive dream laugheth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I, a—creeper? Never in my life did I creep before the powerful; and if ever I lied, then did I lie out of love. Therefore am I glad even in my winter-bed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A poor bed warmeth me more than a rich one, for I am jealous of my poverty. And in winter she is most faithful unto me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With a wickedness do I begin every day: I mock at the winter with a cold bath: on that account grumbleth my stern house-mate.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Also do I like to tickle him with a wax-taper, that he may finally let the heavens emerge from ashy-grey twilight.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For especially wicked am I in the morning: at the early hour when the pail rattleth at the well, and horses neigh warmly in grey lanes:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Impatiently do I then wait, that the clear sky may finally dawn for me, the snow-bearded winter-sky, the hoary one, the white-head,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The winter-sky, the silent winter-sky, which often stifleth even its sun!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did I perhaps learn from it the long clear silence? Or did it learn it from me? Or hath each of us devised it himself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Of all good things the origin is a thousandfold,—all good roguish things spring into existence for joy: how could they always do so—for once only!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A good roguish thing is also the long silence, and to look, like the winter-sky, out of a clear, round-eyed countenance:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Like it to stifle one’s sun, and one’s inflexible solar will: verily, this art and this winter-roguishness have I learnt WELL!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My best-loved wickedness and art is it, that my silence hath learned not to betray itself by silence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Clattering with diction and dice, I outwit the solemn assistants: all those stern watchers, shall my will and purpose elude.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That no one might see down into my depth and into mine ultimate will—for that purpose did I devise the long clear silence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many a shrewd one did I find: he veiled his countenance and made his water muddy, that no one might see therethrough and thereunder.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But precisely unto him came the shrewder distrusters and nut-crackers: precisely from him did they fish his best-concealed fish!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the clear, the honest, the transparent—these are for me the wisest silent ones: in them, so PROFOUND is the depth that even the clearest water doth not—betray it.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou snow-bearded, silent, winter-sky, thou round-eyed whitehead above me! Oh, thou heavenly simile of my soul and its wantonness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And MUST I not conceal myself like one who hath swallowed gold—lest my soul should be ripped up?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>MUST I not wear stilts, that they may OVERLOOK my long legs—all those enviers and injurers around me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Those dingy, fire-warmed, used-up, green-tinted, ill-natured souls—how COULD their envy endure my happiness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus do I show them only the ice and winter of my peaks—and NOT that my mountain windeth all the solar girdles around it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They hear only the whistling of my winter-storms: and know NOT that I also travel over warm seas, like longing, heavy, hot south-winds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They commiserate also my accidents and chances:—but MY word saith: “Suffer the chance to come unto me: innocent is it as a little child!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How COULD they endure my happiness, if I did not put around it accidents, and winter-privations, and bear-skin caps, and enmantling snowflakes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—If I did not myself commiserate their PITY, the pity of those enviers and injurers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—If I did not myself sigh before them, and chatter with cold, and patiently LET myself be swathed in their pity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is the wise waggish-will and good-will of my soul, that it CONCEALETH NOT its winters and glacial storms; it concealeth not its chilblains either.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To one man, lonesomeness is the flight of the sick one; to another, it is the flight FROM the sick ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let them HEAR me chattering and sighing with winter-cold, all those poor squinting knaves around me! With such sighing and chattering do I flee from their heated rooms.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let them sympathise with me and sigh with me on account of my chilblains: “At the ice of knowledge will he yet FREEZE TO DEATH!”—so they mourn.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Meanwhile do I run with warm feet hither and thither on mine olive-mount: in the sunny corner of mine olive-mount do I sing, and mock at all pity.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sang Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LI. ON PASSING-BY.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus slowly wandering through many peoples and divers cities, did Zarathustra return by round-about roads to his mountains and his cave. And behold, thereby came he unawares also to the gate of the GREAT CITY. Here, however, a foaming fool, with extended hands, sprang forward to him and stood in his way. It was the same fool whom the people called “the ape of Zarathustra:” for he had learned from him something of the expression and modulation of language, and perhaps liked also to borrow from the store of his wisdom. And the fool talked thus to Zarathustra:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, here is the great city: here hast thou nothing to seek and everything to lose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why wouldst thou wade through this mire? Have pity upon thy foot! Spit rather on the gate of the city, and—turn back!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here is the hell for anchorites’ thoughts: here are great thoughts seethed alive and boiled small.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here do all great sentiments decay: here may only rattle-boned sensations rattle!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Smellest thou not already the shambles and cookshops of the spirit? Steameth not this city with the fumes of slaughtered spirit?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Seest thou not the souls hanging like limp dirty rags?—And they make newspapers also out of these rags!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hearest thou not how spirit hath here become a verbal game? Loathsome verbal swill doth it vomit forth!—And they make newspapers also out of this verbal swill.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They hound one another, and know not whither! They inflame one another, and know not why! They tinkle with their pinchbeck, they jingle with their gold.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They are cold, and seek warmth from distilled waters: they are inflamed, and seek coolness from frozen spirits; they are all sick and sore through public opinion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All lusts and vices are here at home; but here there are also the virtuous; there is much appointable appointed virtue:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Much appointable virtue with scribe-fingers, and hardy sitting-flesh and waiting-flesh, blessed with small breast-stars, and padded, haunchless daughters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is here also much piety, and much faithful spittle-licking and spittle-backing, before the God of Hosts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“From on high,” drippeth the star, and the gracious spittle; for the high, longeth every starless bosom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The moon hath its court, and the court hath its moon-calves: unto all, however, that cometh from the court do the mendicant people pray, and all appointable mendicant virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I serve, thou servest, we serve”—so prayeth all appointable virtue to the prince: that the merited star may at last stick on the slender breast!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the moon still revolveth around all that is earthly: so revolveth also the prince around what is earthliest of all—that, however, is the gold of the shopman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The God of the Hosts of war is not the God of the golden bar; the prince proposeth, but the shopman—disposeth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>By all that is luminous and strong and good in thee, O Zarathustra! Spit on this city of shopmen and return back!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here floweth all blood putridly and tepidly and frothily through all veins: spit on the great city, which is the great slum where all the scum frotheth together!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Spit on the city of compressed souls and slender breasts, of pointed eyes and sticky fingers—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—On the city of the obtrusive, the brazen-faced, the pen-demagogues and tongue-demagogues, the overheated ambitious:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where everything maimed, ill-famed, lustful, untrustful, over-mellow, sickly-yellow and seditious, festereth pernicious:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Spit on the great city and turn back!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here, however, did Zarathustra interrupt the foaming fool, and shut his mouth.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Stop this at once! called out Zarathustra, long have thy speech and thy species disgusted me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why didst thou live so long by the swamp, that thou thyself hadst to become a frog and a toad?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Floweth there not a tainted, frothy, swamp-blood in thine own veins, when thou hast thus learned to croak and revile?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why wentest thou not into the forest? Or why didst thou not till the ground? Is the sea not full of green islands?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I despise thy contempt; and when thou warnedst me—why didst thou not warn thyself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Out of love alone shall my contempt and my warning bird take wing; but not out of the swamp!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They call thee mine ape, thou foaming fool: but I call thee my grunting-pig,—by thy grunting, thou spoilest even my praise of folly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What was it that first made thee grunt? Because no one sufficiently FLATTERED thee:—therefore didst thou seat thyself beside this filth, that thou mightest have cause for much grunting,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That thou mightest have cause for much VENGEANCE! For vengeance, thou vain fool, is all thy foaming; I have divined thee well!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thy fools’-word injureth ME, even when thou art right! And even if Zarathustra’s word WERE a hundred times justified, thou wouldst ever—DO wrong with my word!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra. Then did he look on the great city and sighed, and was long silent. At last he spake thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I loathe also this great city, and not only this fool. Here and there— there is nothing to better, nothing to worsen.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Woe to this great city!—And I would that I already saw the pillar of fire in which it will be consumed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For such pillars of fire must precede the great noontide. But this hath its time and its own fate.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This precept, however, give I unto thee, in parting, thou fool: Where one can no longer love, there should one—PASS BY!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and passed by the fool and the great city.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LII. THE APOSTATES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, lieth everything already withered and grey which but lately stood green and many-hued on this meadow! And how much honey of hope did I carry hence into my beehives!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Those young hearts have already all become old—and not old even! only weary, ordinary, comfortable:—they declare it: “We have again become pious.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Of late did I see them run forth at early morn with valorous steps: but the feet of their knowledge became weary, and now do they malign even their morning valour!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, many of them once lifted their legs like the dancer; to them winked the laughter of my wisdom:—then did they bethink themselves. Just now have I seen them bent down—to creep to the cross.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Around light and liberty did they once flutter like gnats and young poets. A little older, a little colder: and already are they mystifiers, and mumblers and mollycoddles.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did perhaps their hearts despond, because lonesomeness had swallowed me like a whale? Did their ear perhaps hearken yearningly-long for me IN VAIN, and for my trumpet-notes and herald-calls?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ah! Ever are there but few of those whose hearts have persistent courage and exuberance; and in such remaineth also the spirit patient. The rest, however, are COWARDLY.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The rest: these are always the great majority, the common-place, the superfluous, the far-too many—those all are cowardly!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Him who is of my type, will also the experiences of my type meet on the way: so that his first companions must be corpses and buffoons.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His second companions, however—they will call themselves his BELIEVERS,—will be a living host, with much love, much folly, much unbearded veneration.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To those believers shall he who is of my type among men not bind his heart; in those spring-times and many-hued meadows shall he not believe, who knoweth the fickly faint-hearted human species!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>COULD they do otherwise, then would they also WILL otherwise. The half-and-half spoil every whole. That leaves become withered,—what is there to lament about that!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let them go and fall away, O Zarathustra, and do not lament! Better even to blow amongst them with rustling winds,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Blow amongst those leaves, O Zarathustra, that everything WITHERED may run away from thee the faster!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“We have again become pious”—so do those apostates confess; and some of them are still too pusillanimous thus to confess.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unto them I look into the eye,—before them I say it unto their face and unto the blush on their cheeks: Ye are those who again PRAY!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is however a shame to pray! Not for all, but for thee, and me, and whoever hath his conscience in his head. For THEE it is a shame to pray!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou knowest it well: the faint-hearted devil in thee, which would fain fold its arms, and place its hands in its bosom, and take it easier:—this faint-hearted devil persuadeth thee that “there IS a God!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THEREBY, however, dost thou belong to the light-dreading type, to whom light never permitteth repose: now must thou daily thrust thy head deeper into obscurity and vapour!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, thou choosest the hour well: for just now do the nocturnal birds again fly abroad. The hour hath come for all light-dreading people, the vesper hour and leisure hour, when they do not—“take leisure.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I hear it and smell it: it hath come—their hour for hunt and procession, not indeed for a wild hunt, but for a tame, lame, snuffling, soft-treaders’, soft-prayers’ hunt,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For a hunt after susceptible simpletons: all mouse-traps for the heart have again been set! And whenever I lift a curtain, a night-moth rusheth out of it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did it perhaps squat there along with another night-moth? For everywhere do I smell small concealed communities; and wherever there are closets there are new devotees therein, and the atmosphere of devotees.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They sit for long evenings beside one another, and say: “Let us again become like little children and say, ‘good God!’”—ruined in mouths and stomachs by the pious confectioners.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or they look for long evenings at a crafty, lurking cross-spider, that preacheth prudence to the spiders themselves, and teacheth that “under crosses it is good for cobweb-spinning!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or they sit all day at swamps with angle-rods, and on that account think themselves PROFOUND; but whoever fisheth where there are no fish, I do not even call him superficial!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or they learn in godly-gay style to play the harp with a hymn-poet, who would fain harp himself into the heart of young girls:—for he hath tired of old girls and their praises.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or they learn to shudder with a learned semi-madcap, who waiteth in darkened rooms for spirits to come to him—and the spirit runneth away entirely!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or they listen to an old roving howl- and growl-piper, who hath learnt from the sad winds the sadness of sounds; now pipeth he as the wind, and preacheth sadness in sad strains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And some of them have even become night-watchmen: they know now how to blow horns, and go about at night and awaken old things which have long fallen asleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Five words about old things did I hear yester-night at the garden-wall: they came from such old, sorrowful, arid night-watchmen.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“For a father he careth not sufficiently for his children: human fathers do this better!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“He is too old! He now careth no more for his children,”—answered the other night-watchman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“HATH he then children? No one can prove it unless he himself prove it! I have long wished that he would for once prove it thoroughly.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Prove? As if HE had ever proved anything! Proving is difficult to him; he layeth great stress on one’s BELIEVING him.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ay! Ay! Belief saveth him; belief in him. That is the way with old people! So it is with us also!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thus spake to each other the two old night-watchmen and light-scarers, and tooted thereupon sorrowfully on their horns: so did it happen yester-night at the garden-wall.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To me, however, did the heart writhe with laughter, and was like to break; it knew not where to go, and sunk into the midriff.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, it will be my death yet—to choke with laughter when I see asses drunken, and hear night-watchmen thus doubt about God.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hath the time not LONG since passed for all such doubts? Who may nowadays awaken such old slumbering, light-shunning things!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the old Deities hath it long since come to an end:—and verily, a good joyful Deity-end had they!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They did not “begloom” themselves to death—that do people fabricate! On the contrary, they—LAUGHED themselves to death once on a time!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That took place when the unGodliest utterance came from a God himself—the utterance: “There is but one God! Thou shalt have no other Gods before me!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—An old grim-beard of a God, a jealous one, forgot himself in such wise:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And all the Gods then laughed, and shook upon their thrones, and exclaimed: “Is it not just divinity that there are Gods, but no God?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He that hath an ear let him hear.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus talked Zarathustra in the city he loved, which is surnamed “The Pied Cow.” For from here he had but two days to travel to reach once more his cave and his animals; his soul, however, rejoiced unceasingly on account of the nighness of his return home.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LIII. THE RETURN HOME.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O lonesomeness! My HOME, lonesomeness! Too long have I lived wildly in wild remoteness, to return to thee without tears!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now threaten me with the finger as mothers threaten; now smile upon me as mothers smile; now say just: “Who was it that like a whirlwind once rushed away from me?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Who when departing called out: ‘Too long have I sat with lonesomeness; there have I unlearned silence!’ THAT hast thou learned now—surely?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, everything do I know; and that thou wert MORE FORSAKEN amongst the many, thou unique one, than thou ever wert with me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One thing is forsakenness, another matter is lonesomeness: THAT hast thou now learned! And that amongst men thou wilt ever be wild and strange:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Wild and strange even when they love thee: for above all they want to be TREATED INDULGENTLY!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here, however, art thou at home and house with thyself; here canst thou utter everything, and unbosom all motives; nothing is here ashamed of concealed, congealed feelings.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here do all things come caressingly to thy talk and flatter thee: for they want to ride upon thy back. On every simile dost thou here ride to every truth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Uprightly and openly mayest thou here talk to all things: and verily, it soundeth as praise in their ears, for one to talk to all things—directly!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Another matter, however, is forsakenness. For, dost thou remember, O Zarathustra? When thy bird screamed overhead, when thou stoodest in the forest, irresolute, ignorant where to go, beside a corpse:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When thou spakest: ‘Let mine animals lead me! More dangerous have I found it among men than among animals:’—THAT was forsakenness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And dost thou remember, O Zarathustra? When thou sattest in thine isle, a well of wine giving and granting amongst empty buckets, bestowing and distributing amongst the thirsty:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Until at last thou alone sattest thirsty amongst the drunken ones, and wailedst nightly: ‘Is taking not more blessed than giving? And stealing yet more blessed than taking?’—THAT was forsakenness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And dost thou remember, O Zarathustra? When thy stillest hour came and drove thee forth from thyself, when with wicked whispering it said: ‘Speak and succumb!’—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When it disgusted thee with all thy waiting and silence, and discouraged thy humble courage: THAT was forsakenness!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O lonesomeness! My home, lonesomeness! How blessedly and tenderly speaketh thy voice unto me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We do not question each other, we do not complain to each other; we go together openly through open doors.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For all is open with thee and clear; and even the hours run here on lighter feet. For in the dark, time weigheth heavier upon one than in the light.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here fly open unto me all being’s words and word-cabinets: here all being wanteth to become words, here all becoming wanteth to learn of me how to talk.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Down there, however—all talking is in vain! There, forgetting and passing-by are the best wisdom: THAT have I learned now!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who would understand everything in man must handle everything. But for that I have too clean hands.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I do not like even to inhale their breath; alas! that I have lived so long among their noise and bad breaths!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O blessed stillness around me! O pure odours around me! How from a deep breast this stillness fetcheth pure breath! How it hearkeneth, this blessed stillness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But down there—there speaketh everything, there is everything misheard. If one announce one’s wisdom with bells, the shopmen in the market-place will out-jingle it with pennies!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything among them talketh; no one knoweth any longer how to understand. Everything falleth into the water; nothing falleth any longer into deep wells.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything among them talketh, nothing succeedeth any longer and accomplisheth itself. Everything cackleth, but who will still sit quietly on the nest and hatch eggs?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything among them talketh, everything is out-talked. And that which yesterday was still too hard for time itself and its tooth, hangeth to-day, outchamped and outchewed, from the mouths of the men of to-day.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything among them talketh, everything is betrayed. And what was once called the secret and secrecy of profound souls, belongeth to-day to the street-trumpeters and other butterflies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O human hubbub, thou wonderful thing! Thou noise in dark streets! Now art thou again behind me:—my greatest danger lieth behind me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In indulging and pitying lay ever my greatest danger; and all human hubbub wisheth to be indulged and tolerated.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With suppressed truths, with fool’s hand and befooled heart, and rich in petty lies of pity:—thus have I ever lived among men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Disguised did I sit amongst them, ready to misjudge MYSELF that I might endure THEM, and willingly saying to myself: “Thou fool, thou dost not know men!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One unlearneth men when one liveth amongst them: there is too much foreground in all men—what can far-seeing, far-longing eyes do THERE!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And, fool that I was, when they misjudged me, I indulged them on that account more than myself, being habitually hard on myself, and often even taking revenge on myself for the indulgence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Stung all over by poisonous flies, and hollowed like the stone by many drops of wickedness: thus did I sit among them, and still said to myself: “Innocent is everything petty of its pettiness!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Especially did I find those who call themselves “the good,” the most poisonous flies; they sting in all innocence, they lie in all innocence; how COULD they—be just towards me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who liveth amongst the good—pity teacheth him to lie. Pity maketh stifling air for all free souls. For the stupidity of the good is unfathomable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To conceal myself and my riches—THAT did I learn down there: for every one did I still find poor in spirit. It was the lie of my pity, that I knew in every one,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That I saw and scented in every one, what was ENOUGH of spirit for him, and what was TOO MUCH!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Their stiff wise men: I call them wise, not stiff—thus did I learn to slur over words.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The grave-diggers dig for themselves diseases. Under old rubbish rest bad vapours. One should not stir up the marsh. One should live on mountains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With blessed nostrils do I again breathe mountain-freedom. Freed at last is my nose from the smell of all human hubbub!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With sharp breezes tickled, as with sparkling wine, SNEEZETH my soul— sneezeth, and shouteth self-congratulatingly: “Health to thee!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LIV. THE THREE EVIL THINGS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In my dream, in my last morning-dream, I stood to-day on a promontory— beyond the world; I held a pair of scales, and WEIGHED the world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas, that the rosy dawn came too early to me: she glowed me awake, the jealous one! Jealous is she always of the glows of my morning-dream.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Measurable by him who hath time, weighable by a good weigher, attainable by strong pinions, divinable by divine nut-crackers: thus did my dream find the world:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My dream, a bold sailor, half-ship, half-hurricane, silent as the butterfly, impatient as the falcon: how had it the patience and leisure to-day for world-weighing!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did my wisdom perhaps speak secretly to it, my laughing, wide-awake day-wisdom, which mocketh at all “infinite worlds”? For it saith: “Where force is, there becometh NUMBER the master: it hath more force.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How confidently did my dream contemplate this finite world, not new-fangledly, not old-fangledly, not timidly, not entreatingly:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As if a big round apple presented itself to my hand, a ripe golden apple, with a coolly-soft, velvety skin:—thus did the world present itself unto me:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As if a tree nodded unto me, a broad-branched, strong-willed tree, curved as a recline and a foot-stool for weary travellers: thus did the world stand on my promontory:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As if delicate hands carried a casket towards me—a casket open for the delectation of modest adoring eyes: thus did the world present itself before me to-day:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Not riddle enough to scare human love from it, not solution enough to put to sleep human wisdom:—a humanly good thing was the world to me to-day, of which such bad things are said!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How I thank my morning-dream that I thus at to-day’s dawn, weighed the world! As a humanly good thing did it come unto me, this dream and heart-comforter!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And that I may do the like by day, and imitate and copy its best, now will I put the three worst things on the scales, and weigh them humanly well.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who taught to bless taught also to curse: what are the three best cursed things in the world? These will I put on the scales.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>VOLUPTUOUSNESS, PASSION FOR POWER, and SELFISHNESS: these three things have hitherto been best cursed, and have been in worst and falsest repute—these three things will I weigh humanly well.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! Here is my promontory, and there is the sea—IT rolleth hither unto me, shaggily and fawningly, the old, faithful, hundred-headed dog-monster that I love!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! Here will I hold the scales over the weltering sea: and also a witness do I choose to look on—thee, the anchorite-tree, thee, the strong-odoured, broad-arched tree that I love!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On what bridge goeth the now to the hereafter? By what constraint doth the high stoop to the low? And what enjoineth even the highest still—to grow upwards?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now stand the scales poised and at rest: three heavy questions have I thrown in; three heavy answers carrieth the other scale.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Voluptuousness: unto all hair-shirted despisers of the body, a sting and stake; and, cursed as “the world,” by all backworldsmen: for it mocketh and befooleth all erring, misinferring teachers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Voluptuousness: to the rabble, the slow fire at which it is burnt; to all wormy wood, to all stinking rags, the prepared heat and stew furnace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Voluptuousness: to free hearts, a thing innocent and free, the garden-happiness of the earth, all the future’s thanks-overflow to the present.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Voluptuousness: only to the withered a sweet poison; to the lion-willed, however, the great cordial, and the reverently saved wine of wines.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Voluptuousness: the great symbolic happiness of a higher happiness and highest hope. For to many is marriage promised, and more than marriage,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—To many that are more unknown to each other than man and woman:—and who hath fully understood HOW UNKNOWN to each other are man and woman!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Voluptuousness:—but I will have hedges around my thoughts, and even around my words, lest swine and libertine should break into my gardens!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: the glowing scourge of the hardest of the heart-hard; the cruel torture reserved for the cruellest themselves; the gloomy flame of living pyres.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: the wicked gadfly which is mounted on the vainest peoples; the scorner of all uncertain virtue; which rideth on every horse and on every pride.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: the earthquake which breaketh and upbreaketh all that is rotten and hollow; the rolling, rumbling, punitive demolisher of whited sepulchres; the flashing interrogative-sign beside premature answers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: before whose glance man creepeth and croucheth and drudgeth, and becometh lower than the serpent and the swine:—until at last great contempt crieth out of him—,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: the terrible teacher of great contempt, which preacheth to their face to cities and empires: “Away with thee!”—until a voice crieth out of themselves: “Away with ME!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: which, however, mounteth alluringly even to the pure and lonesome, and up to self-satisfied elevations, glowing like a love that painteth purple felicities alluringly on earthly heavens.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Passion for power: but who would call it PASSION, when the height longeth to stoop for power! Verily, nothing sick or diseased is there in such longing and descending!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That the lonesome height may not for ever remain lonesome and self-sufficing; that the mountains may come to the valleys and the winds of the heights to the plains:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, who could find the right prenomen and honouring name for such longing! “Bestowing virtue”—thus did Zarathustra once name the unnamable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And then it happened also,—and verily, it happened for the first time!—that his word blessed SELFISHNESS, the wholesome, healthy selfishness, that springeth from the powerful soul:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—From the powerful soul, to which the high body appertaineth, the handsome, triumphing, refreshing body, around which everything becometh a mirror:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The pliant, persuasive body, the dancer, whose symbol and epitome is the self-enjoying soul. Of such bodies and souls the self-enjoyment calleth itself “virtue.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With its words of good and bad doth such self-enjoyment shelter itself as with sacred groves; with the names of its happiness doth it banish from itself everything contemptible.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away from itself doth it banish everything cowardly; it saith: “Bad—THAT IS cowardly!” Contemptible seem to it the ever-solicitous, the sighing, the complaining, and whoever pick up the most trifling advantage.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It despiseth also all bitter-sweet wisdom: for verily, there is also wisdom that bloometh in the dark, a night-shade wisdom, which ever sigheth: “All is vain!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Shy distrust is regarded by it as base, and every one who wanteth oaths instead of looks and hands: also all over-distrustful wisdom,—for such is the mode of cowardly souls.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Baser still it regardeth the obsequious, doggish one, who immediately lieth on his back, the submissive one; and there is also wisdom that is submissive, and doggish, and pious, and obsequious.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hateful to it altogether, and a loathing, is he who will never defend himself, he who swalloweth down poisonous spittle and bad looks, the all-too-patient one, the all-endurer, the all-satisfied one: for that is the mode of slaves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whether they be servile before Gods and divine spurnings, or before men and stupid human opinions: at ALL kinds of slaves doth it spit, this blessed selfishness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Bad: thus doth it call all that is spirit-broken, and sordidly-servile—constrained, blinking eyes, depressed hearts, and the false submissive style, which kisseth with broad cowardly lips.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And spurious wisdom: so doth it call all the wit that slaves, and hoary-headed and weary ones affect; and especially all the cunning, spurious-witted, curious-witted foolishness of priests!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The spurious wise, however, all the priests, the world-weary, and those whose souls are of feminine and servile nature—oh, how hath their game all along abused selfishness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And precisely THAT was to be virtue and was to be called virtue—to abuse selfishness! And “selfless”—so did they wish themselves with good reason, all those world-weary cowards and cross-spiders!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But to all those cometh now the day, the change, the sword of judgment, THE GREAT NOONTIDE: then shall many things be revealed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he who proclaimeth the EGO wholesome and holy, and selfishness blessed, verily, he, the prognosticator, speaketh also what he knoweth: “BEHOLD, IT COMETH, IT IS NIGH, THE GREAT NOONTIDE!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LV. THE SPIRIT OF GRAVITY.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My mouthpiece—is of the people: too coarsely and cordially do I talk for Angora rabbits. And still stranger soundeth my word unto all ink-fish and pen-foxes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My hand—is a fool’s hand: woe unto all tables and walls, and whatever hath room for fool’s sketching, fool’s scrawling!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My foot—is a horse-foot; therewith do I trample and trot over stick and stone, in the fields up and down, and am bedevilled with delight in all fast racing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My stomach—is surely an eagle’s stomach? For it preferreth lamb’s flesh. Certainly it is a bird’s stomach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nourished with innocent things, and with few, ready and impatient to fly, to fly away—that is now my nature: why should there not be something of bird-nature therein!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And especially that I am hostile to the spirit of gravity, that is bird-nature:—verily, deadly hostile, supremely hostile, originally hostile! Oh, whither hath my hostility not flown and misflown!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereof could I sing a song—and WILL sing it: though I be alone in an empty house, and must sing it to mine own ears.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Other singers are there, to be sure, to whom only the full house maketh the voice soft, the hand eloquent, the eye expressive, the heart wakeful:—those do I not resemble.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who one day teacheth men to fly will have shifted all landmarks; to him will all landmarks themselves fly into the air; the earth will he christen anew—as “the light body.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The ostrich runneth faster than the fastest horse, but it also thrusteth its head heavily into the heavy earth: thus is it with the man who cannot yet fly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Heavy unto him are earth and life, and so WILLETH the spirit of gravity! But he who would become light, and be a bird, must love himself:—thus do <i>I</i> teach.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not, to be sure, with the love of the sick and infected, for with them stinketh even self-love!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One must learn to love oneself—thus do I teach—with a wholesome and healthy love: that one may endure to be with oneself, and not go roving about.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such roving about christeneth itself “brotherly love”; with these words hath there hitherto been the best lying and dissembling, and especially by those who have been burdensome to every one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, it is no commandment for to-day and to-morrow to LEARN to love oneself. Rather is it of all arts the finest, subtlest, last and patientest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For to its possessor is all possession well concealed, and of all treasure-pits one’s own is last excavated—so causeth the spirit of gravity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Almost in the cradle are we apportioned with heavy words and worths: “good” and “evil”—so calleth itself this dowry. For the sake of it we are forgiven for living.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And therefore suffereth one little children to come unto one, to forbid them betimes to love themselves—so causeth the spirit of gravity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And we—we bear loyally what is apportioned unto us, on hard shoulders, over rugged mountains! And when we sweat, then do people say to us: “Yea, life is hard to bear!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But man himself only is hard to bear! The reason thereof is that he carrieth too many extraneous things on his shoulders. Like the camel kneeleth he down, and letteth himself be well laden.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Especially the strong load-bearing man in whom reverence resideth. Too many EXTRANEOUS heavy words and worths loadeth he upon himself—then seemeth life to him a desert!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily! Many a thing also that is OUR OWN is hard to bear! And many internal things in man are like the oyster—repulsive and slippery and hard to grasp;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So that an elegant shell, with elegant adornment, must plead for them. But this art also must one learn: to HAVE a shell, and a fine appearance, and sagacious blindness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Again, it deceiveth about many things in man, that many a shell is poor and pitiable, and too much of a shell. Much concealed goodness and power is never dreamt of; the choicest dainties find no tasters!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Women know that, the choicest of them: a little fatter a little leaner— oh, how much fate is in so little!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man is difficult to discover, and unto himself most difficult of all; often lieth the spirit concerning the soul. So causeth the spirit of gravity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He, however, hath discovered himself who saith: This is MY good and evil: therewith hath he silenced the mole and the dwarf, who say: “Good for all, evil for all.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, neither do I like those who call everything good, and this world the best of all. Those do I call the all-satisfied.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All-satisfiedness, which knoweth how to taste everything,—that is not the best taste! I honour the refractory, fastidious tongues and stomachs, which have learned to say “I” and “Yea” and “Nay.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To chew and digest everything, however—that is the genuine swine-nature! Ever to say YE-A—that hath only the ass learnt, and those like it!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Deep yellow and hot red—so wanteth MY taste—it mixeth blood with all colours. He, however, who whitewasheth his house, betrayeth unto me a whitewashed soul.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With mummies, some fall in love; others with phantoms: both alike hostile to all flesh and blood—oh, how repugnant are both to my taste! For I love blood.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And there will I not reside and abide where every one spitteth and speweth: that is now MY taste,—rather would I live amongst thieves and perjurers. Nobody carrieth gold in his mouth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Still more repugnant unto me, however, are all lickspittles; and the most repugnant animal of man that I found, did I christen “parasite”: it would not love, and would yet live by love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unhappy do I call all those who have only one choice: either to become evil beasts, or evil beast-tamers. Amongst such would I not build my tabernacle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unhappy do I also call those who have ever to WAIT,—they are repugnant to my taste—all the toll-gatherers and traders, and kings, and other landkeepers and shopkeepers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, I learned waiting also, and thoroughly so,—but only waiting for MYSELF. And above all did I learn standing and walking and running and leaping and climbing and dancing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This however is my teaching: he who wisheth one day to fly, must first learn standing and walking and running and climbing and dancing:—one doth not fly into flying!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With rope-ladders learned I to reach many a window, with nimble legs did I climb high masts: to sit on high masts of perception seemed to me no small bliss;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—To flicker like small flames on high masts: a small light, certainly, but a great comfort to cast-away sailors and ship-wrecked ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>By divers ways and wendings did I arrive at my truth; not by one ladder did I mount to the height where mine eye roveth into my remoteness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And unwillingly only did I ask my way—that was always counter to my taste! Rather did I question and test the ways themselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A testing and a questioning hath been all my travelling:—and verily, one must also LEARN to answer such questioning! That, however,—is my taste:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Neither a good nor a bad taste, but MY taste, of which I have no longer either shame or secrecy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“This—is now MY way,—where is yours?” Thus did I answer those who asked me “the way.” For THE way—it doth not exist!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LVI. OLD AND NEW TABLES.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here do I sit and wait, old broken tables around me and also new half-written tables. When cometh mine hour?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The hour of my descent, of my down-going: for once more will I go unto men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For that hour do I now wait: for first must the signs come unto me that it is MINE hour—namely, the laughing lion with the flock of doves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Meanwhile do I talk to myself as one who hath time. No one telleth me anything new, so I tell myself mine own story.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When I came unto men, then found I them resting on an old infatuation: all of them thought they had long known what was good and bad for men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An old wearisome business seemed to them all discourse about virtue; and he who wished to sleep well spake of “good” and “bad” ere retiring to rest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This somnolence did I disturb when I taught that NO ONE YET KNOWETH what is good and bad:—unless it be the creating one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—It is he, however, who createth man’s goal, and giveth to the earth its meaning and its future: he only EFFECTETH it THAT aught is good or bad.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I bade them upset their old academic chairs, and wherever that old infatuation had sat; I bade them laugh at their great moralists, their saints, their poets, and their Saviours.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At their gloomy sages did I bid them laugh, and whoever had sat admonishing as a black scarecrow on the tree of life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On their great grave-highway did I seat myself, and even beside the carrion and vultures—and I laughed at all their bygone and its mellow decaying glory.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, like penitential preachers and fools did I cry wrath and shame on all their greatness and smallness. Oh, that their best is so very small! Oh, that their worst is so very small! Thus did I laugh.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus did my wise longing, born in the mountains, cry and laugh in me; a wild wisdom, verily!—my great pinion-rustling longing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And oft did it carry me off and up and away and in the midst of laughter; then flew I quivering like an arrow with sun-intoxicated rapture:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Out into distant futures, which no dream hath yet seen, into warmer souths than ever sculptor conceived,—where gods in their dancing are ashamed of all clothes:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(That I may speak in parables and halt and stammer like the poets: and verily I am ashamed that I have still to be a poet!)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where all becoming seemed to me dancing of Gods, and wantoning of Gods, and the world unloosed and unbridled and fleeing back to itself:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As an eternal self-fleeing and re-seeking of one another of many Gods, as the blessed self-contradicting, recommuning, and refraternising with one another of many Gods:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where all time seemed to me a blessed mockery of moments, where necessity was freedom itself, which played happily with the goad of freedom:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where I also found again mine old devil and arch-enemy, the spirit of gravity, and all that it created: constraint, law, necessity and consequence and purpose and will and good and evil:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For must there not be that which is danced OVER, danced beyond? Must there not, for the sake of the nimble, the nimblest,—be moles and clumsy dwarfs?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There was it also where I picked up from the path the word “Superman,” and that man is something that must be surpassed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That man is a bridge and not a goal—rejoicing over his noontides and evenings, as advances to new rosy dawns:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The Zarathustra word of the great noontide, and whatever else I have hung up over men like purple evening-afterglows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, also new stars did I make them see, along with new nights; and over cloud and day and night, did I spread out laughter like a gay-coloured canopy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I taught them all MY poetisation and aspiration: to compose and collect into unity what is fragment in man, and riddle and fearful chance;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As composer, riddle-reader, and redeemer of chance, did I teach them to create the future, and all that HATH BEEN—to redeem by creating.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The past of man to redeem, and every “It was” to transform, until the Will saith: “But so did I will it! So shall I will it—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—This did I call redemption; this alone taught I them to call redemption.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now do I await MY redemption—that I may go unto them for the last time.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For once more will I go unto men: AMONGST them will my sun set; in dying will I give them my choicest gift!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From the sun did I learn this, when it goeth down, the exuberant one: gold doth it then pour into the sea, out of inexhaustible riches,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—So that the poorest fisherman roweth even with GOLDEN oars! For this did I once see, and did not tire of weeping in beholding it.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Like the sun will also Zarathustra go down: now sitteth he here and waiteth, old broken tables around him, and also new tables—half-written.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behold, here is a new table; but where are my brethren who will carry it with me to the valley and into hearts of flesh?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus demandeth my great love to the remotest ones: BE NOT CONSIDERATE OF THY NEIGHBOUR! Man is something that must be surpassed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are many divers ways and modes of surpassing: see THOU thereto! But only a buffoon thinketh: “man can also be OVERLEAPT.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Surpass thyself even in thy neighbour: and a right which thou canst seize upon, shalt thou not allow to be given thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What thou doest can no one do to thee again. Lo, there is no requital.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who cannot command himself shall obey. And many a one CAN command himself, but still sorely lacketh self-obedience!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>5.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus wisheth the type of noble souls: they desire to have nothing GRATUITOUSLY, least of all, life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who is of the populace wisheth to live gratuitously; we others, however, to whom life hath given itself—we are ever considering WHAT we can best give IN RETURN!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, it is a noble dictum which saith: “What life promiseth US, that promise will WE keep—to life!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One should not wish to enjoy where one doth not contribute to the enjoyment. And one should not WISH to enjoy!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For enjoyment and innocence are the most bashful things. Neither like to be sought for. One should HAVE them,—but one should rather SEEK for guilt and pain!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, he who is a firstling is ever sacrificed. Now, however, are we firstlings!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We all bleed on secret sacrificial altars, we all burn and broil in honour of ancient idols.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Our best is still young: this exciteth old palates. Our flesh is tender, our skin is only lambs’ skin:—how could we not excite old idol-priests!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>IN OURSELVES dwelleth he still, the old idol-priest, who broileth our best for his banquet. Ah, my brethren, how could firstlings fail to be sacrifices!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But so wisheth our type; and I love those who do not wish to preserve themselves, the down-going ones do I love with mine entire love: for they go beyond.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>7.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be true—that CAN few be! And he who can, will not! Least of all, however, can the good be true.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, those good ones! GOOD MEN NEVER SPEAK THE TRUTH. For the spirit, thus to be good, is a malady.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They yield, those good ones, they submit themselves; their heart repeateth, their soul obeyeth: HE, however, who obeyeth, DOTH NOT LISTEN TO HIMSELF!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All that is called evil by the good, must come together in order that one truth may be born. O my brethren, are ye also evil enough for THIS truth?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The daring venture, the prolonged distrust, the cruel Nay, the tedium, the cutting-into-the-quick—how seldom do THESE come together! Out of such seed, however—is truth produced!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>BESIDE the bad conscience hath hitherto grown all KNOWLEDGE! Break up, break up, ye discerning ones, the old tables!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>8.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the water hath planks, when gangways and railings o’erspan the stream, verily, he is not believed who then saith: “All is in flux.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But even the simpletons contradict him. “What?” say the simpletons, “all in flux? Planks and railings are still OVER the stream!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“OVER the stream all is stable, all the values of things, the bridges and bearings, all ‘good’ and ‘evil’: these are all STABLE!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Cometh, however, the hard winter, the stream-tamer, then learn even the wittiest distrust, and verily, not only the simpletons then say: “Should not everything—STAND STILL?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Fundamentally standeth everything still”—that is an appropriate winter doctrine, good cheer for an unproductive period, a great comfort for winter-sleepers and fireside-loungers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Fundamentally standeth everything still”—: but CONTRARY thereto, preacheth the thawing wind!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The thawing wind, a bullock, which is no ploughing bullock—a furious bullock, a destroyer, which with angry horns breaketh the ice! The ice however—BREAKETH GANGWAYS!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, is not everything AT PRESENT IN FLUX? Have not all railings and gangways fallen into the water? Who would still HOLD ON to “good” and “evil”?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Woe to us! Hail to us! The thawing wind bloweth!”—Thus preach, my brethren, through all the streets!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>9.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is an old illusion—it is called good and evil. Around soothsayers and astrologers hath hitherto revolved the orbit of this illusion.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Once did one BELIEVE in soothsayers and astrologers; and THEREFORE did one believe, “Everything is fate: thou shalt, for thou must!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then again did one distrust all soothsayers and astrologers; and THEREFORE did one believe, “Everything is freedom: thou canst, for thou willest!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, concerning the stars and the future there hath hitherto been only illusion, and not knowledge; and THEREFORE concerning good and evil there hath hitherto been only illusion and not knowledge!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>10.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou shalt not rob! Thou shalt not slay!”—such precepts were once called holy; before them did one bow the knee and the head, and take off one’s shoes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But I ask you: Where have there ever been better robbers and slayers in the world than such holy precepts?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is there not even in all life—robbing and slaying? And for such precepts to be called holy, was not TRUTH itself thereby—slain?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Or was it a sermon of death that called holy what contradicted and dissuaded from life?—O my brethren, break up, break up for me the old tables!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>11.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is my sympathy with all the past that I see it is abandoned,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Abandoned to the favour, the spirit and the madness of every generation that cometh, and reinterpreteth all that hath been as its bridge!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A great potentate might arise, an artful prodigy, who with approval and disapproval could strain and constrain all the past, until it became for him a bridge, a harbinger, a herald, and a cock-crowing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This however is the other danger, and mine other sympathy:—he who is of the populace, his thoughts go back to his grandfather,—with his grandfather, however, doth time cease.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus is all the past abandoned: for it might some day happen for the populace to become master, and drown all time in shallow waters.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore, O my brethren, a NEW NOBILITY is needed, which shall be the adversary of all populace and potentate rule, and shall inscribe anew the word “noble” on new tables.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For many noble ones are needed, and many kinds of noble ones, FOR A NEW NOBILITY! Or, as I once said in parable: “That is just divinity, that there are Gods, but no God!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>12.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, I consecrate you and point you to a new nobility: ye shall become procreators and cultivators and sowers of the future;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Verily, not to a nobility which ye could purchase like traders with traders’ gold; for little worth is all that hath its price.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let it not be your honour henceforth whence ye come, but whither ye go! Your Will and your feet which seek to surpass you—let these be your new honour!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, not that ye have served a prince—of what account are princes now!—nor that ye have become a bulwark to that which standeth, that it may stand more firmly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not that your family have become courtly at courts, and that ye have learned—gay-coloured, like the flamingo—to stand long hours in shallow pools:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(For ABILITY-to-stand is a merit in courtiers; and all courtiers believe that unto blessedness after death pertaineth—PERMISSION-to-sit!)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nor even that a Spirit called Holy, led your forefathers into promised lands, which I do not praise: for where the worst of all trees grew—the cross,—in that land there is nothing to praise!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And verily, wherever this “Holy Spirit” led its knights, always in such campaigns did—goats and geese, and wryheads and guyheads run FOREMOST!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, not backward shall your nobility gaze, but OUTWARD! Exiles shall ye be from all fatherlands and forefather-lands!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your CHILDREN’S LAND shall ye love: let this love be your new nobility,—the undiscovered in the remotest seas! For it do I bid your sails search and search!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unto your children shall ye MAKE AMENDS for being the children of your fathers: all the past shall ye THUS redeem! This new table do I place over you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>13.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why should one live? All is vain! To live—that is to thrash straw; to live—that is to burn oneself and yet not get warm.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such ancient babbling still passeth for “wisdom”; because it is old, however, and smelleth mustily, THEREFORE is it the more honoured. Even mould ennobleth.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Children might thus speak: they SHUN the fire because it hath burnt them! There is much childishness in the old books of wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he who ever “thrasheth straw,” why should he be allowed to rail at thrashing! Such a fool one would have to muzzle!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such persons sit down to the table and bring nothing with them, not even good hunger:—and then do they rail: “All is vain!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But to eat and drink well, my brethren, is verily no vain art! Break up, break up for me the tables of the never-joyous ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>14.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“To the clean are all things clean”—thus say the people. I, however, say unto you: To the swine all things become swinish!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore preach the visionaries and bowed-heads (whose hearts are also bowed down): “The world itself is a filthy monster.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For these are all unclean spirits; especially those, however, who have no peace or rest, unless they see the world FROM THE BACKSIDE—the backworldsmen!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>TO THOSE do I say it to the face, although it sound unpleasantly: the world resembleth man, in that it hath a backside,—SO MUCH is true!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is in the world much filth: SO MUCH is true! But the world itself is not therefore a filthy monster!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is wisdom in the fact that much in the world smelleth badly: loathing itself createth wings, and fountain-divining powers!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the best there is still something to loathe; and the best is still something that must be surpassed!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, there is much wisdom in the fact that much filth is in the world!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>15.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such sayings did I hear pious backworldsmen speak to their consciences, and verily without wickedness or guile,—although there is nothing more guileful in the world, or more wicked.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Let the world be as it is! Raise not a finger against it!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Let whoever will choke and stab and skin and scrape the people: raise not a finger against it! Thereby will they learn to renounce the world.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“And thine own reason—this shalt thou thyself stifle and choke; for it is a reason of this world,—thereby wilt thou learn thyself to renounce the world.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Shatter, shatter, O my brethren, those old tables of the pious! Tatter the maxims of the world-maligners!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>16.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“He who learneth much unlearneth all violent cravings”—that do people now whisper to one another in all the dark lanes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Wisdom wearieth, nothing is worth while; thou shalt not crave!”—this new table found I hanging even in the public markets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Break up for me, O my brethren, break up also that NEW table! The weary-o’-the-world put it up, and the preachers of death and the jailer: for lo, it is also a sermon for slavery:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Because they learned badly and not the best, and everything too early and everything too fast; because they ATE badly: from thence hath resulted their ruined stomach;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For a ruined stomach, is their spirit: IT persuadeth to death! For verily, my brethren, the spirit IS a stomach!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Life is a well of delight, but to him in whom the ruined stomach speaketh, the father of affliction, all fountains are poisoned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To discern: that is DELIGHT to the lion-willed! But he who hath become weary, is himself merely “willed”; with him play all the waves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And such is always the nature of weak men: they lose themselves on their way. And at last asketh their weariness: “Why did we ever go on the way? All is indifferent!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>TO THEM soundeth it pleasant to have preached in their ears: “Nothing is worth while! Ye shall not will!” That, however, is a sermon for slavery.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, a fresh blustering wind cometh Zarathustra unto all way-weary ones; many noses will he yet make sneeze!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even through walls bloweth my free breath, and in into prisons and imprisoned spirits!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Willing emancipateth: for willing is creating: so do I teach. And ONLY for creating shall ye learn!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And also the learning shall ye LEARN only from me, the learning well!—He who hath ears let him hear!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>17.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There standeth the boat—thither goeth it over, perhaps into vast nothingness—but who willeth to enter into this “Perhaps”?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>None of you want to enter into the death-boat! How should ye then be WORLD-WEARY ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>World-weary ones! And have not even withdrawn from the earth! Eager did I ever find you for the earth, amorous still of your own earth-weariness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not in vain doth your lip hang down:—a small worldly wish still sitteth thereon! And in your eye—floateth there not a cloudlet of unforgotten earthly bliss?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are on the earth many good inventions, some useful, some pleasant: for their sake is the earth to be loved.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And many such good inventions are there, that they are like woman’s breasts: useful at the same time, and pleasant.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye world-weary ones, however! Ye earth-idlers! You, shall one beat with stripes! With stripes shall one again make you sprightly limbs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For if ye be not invalids, or decrepit creatures, of whom the earth is weary, then are ye sly sloths, or dainty, sneaking pleasure-cats. And if ye will not again RUN gaily, then shall ye—pass away!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the incurable shall one not seek to be a physician: thus teacheth Zarathustra:—so shall ye pass away!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But more COURAGE is needed to make an end than to make a new verse: that do all physicians and poets know well.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>18.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, there are tables which weariness framed, and tables which slothfulness framed, corrupt slothfulness: although they speak similarly, they want to be heard differently.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See this languishing one! Only a span-breadth is he from his goal; but from weariness hath he lain down obstinately in the dust, this brave one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From weariness yawneth he at the path, at the earth, at the goal, and at himself: not a step further will he go,—this brave one!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now gloweth the sun upon him, and the dogs lick at his sweat: but he lieth there in his obstinacy and preferreth to languish:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A span-breadth from his goal, to languish! Verily, ye will have to drag him into his heaven by the hair of his head—this hero!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better still that ye let him lie where he hath lain down, that sleep may come unto him, the comforter, with cooling patter-rain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let him lie, until of his own accord he awakeneth,—until of his own accord he repudiateth all weariness, and what weariness hath taught through him!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Only, my brethren, see that ye scare the dogs away from him, the idle skulkers, and all the swarming vermin:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—All the swarming vermin of the “cultured,” that—feast on the sweat of every hero!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>19.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I form circles around me and holy boundaries; ever fewer ascend with me ever higher mountains: I build a mountain-range out of ever holier mountains.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But wherever ye would ascend with me, O my brethren, take care lest a PARASITE ascend with you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A parasite: that is a reptile, a creeping, cringing reptile, that trieth to fatten on your infirm and sore places.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And THIS is its art: it divineth where ascending souls are weary, in your trouble and dejection, in your sensitive modesty, doth it build its loathsome nest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where the strong are weak, where the noble are all-too-gentle—there buildeth it its loathsome nest; the parasite liveth where the great have small sore-places.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What is the highest of all species of being, and what is the lowest? The parasite is the lowest species; he, however, who is of the highest species feedeth most parasites.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the soul which hath the longest ladder, and can go deepest down: how could there fail to be most parasites upon it?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The most comprehensive soul, which can run and stray and rove furthest in itself; the most necessary soul, which out of joy flingeth itself into chance:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The soul in Being, which plungeth into Becoming; the possessing soul, which SEEKETH to attain desire and longing:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The soul fleeing from itself, which overtaketh itself in the widest circuit; the wisest soul, unto which folly speaketh most sweetly:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The soul most self-loving, in which all things have their current and counter-current, their ebb and their flow:—oh, how could THE LOFTIEST SOUL fail to have the worst parasites?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>20.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, am I then cruel? But I say: What falleth, that shall one also push!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything of to-day—it falleth, it decayeth; who would preserve it! But I—I wish also to push it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Know ye the delight which rolleth stones into precipitous depths?—Those men of to-day, see just how they roll into my depths!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A prelude am I to better players, O my brethren! An example! DO according to mine example!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And him whom ye do not teach to fly, teach I pray you—TO FALL FASTER!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>21.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love the brave: but it is not enough to be a swordsman,—one must also know WHEREON to use swordsmanship!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And often is it greater bravery to keep quiet and pass by, that THEREBY one may reserve oneself for a worthier foe!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye shall only have foes to be hated; but not foes to be despised: ye must be proud of your foes. Thus have I already taught.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the worthier foe, O my brethren, shall ye reserve yourselves: therefore must ye pass by many a one,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Especially many of the rabble, who din your ears with noise about people and peoples.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Keep your eye clear of their For and Against! There is there much right, much wrong: he who looketh on becometh wroth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therein viewing, therein hewing—they are the same thing: therefore depart into the forests and lay your sword to sleep!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Go YOUR ways! and let the people and peoples go theirs!—gloomy ways, verily, on which not a single hope glinteth any more!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let there the trader rule, where all that still glittereth is—traders’ gold. It is the time of kings no longer: that which now calleth itself the people is unworthy of kings.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See how these peoples themselves now do just like the traders: they pick up the smallest advantage out of all kinds of rubbish!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They lay lures for one another, they lure things out of one another,—that they call “good neighbourliness.” O blessed remote period when a people said to itself: “I will be—MASTER over peoples!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For, my brethren, the best shall rule, the best also WILLETH to rule! And where the teaching is different, there—the best is LACKING.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>22.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If THEY had—bread for nothing, alas! for what would THEY cry! Their maintainment—that is their true entertainment; and they shall have it hard!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beasts of prey, are they: in their “working”—there is even plundering, in their “earning”—there is even overreaching! Therefore shall they have it hard!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better beasts of prey shall they thus become, subtler, cleverer, MORE MAN-LIKE: for man is the best beast of prey.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All the animals hath man already robbed of their virtues: that is why of all animals it hath been hardest for man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Only the birds are still beyond him. And if man should yet learn to fly, alas! TO WHAT HEIGHT—would his rapacity fly!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>23.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus would I have man and woman: fit for war, the one; fit for maternity, the other; both, however, fit for dancing with head and legs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And lost be the day to us in which a measure hath not been danced. And false be every truth which hath not had laughter along with it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>24.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Your marriage-arranging: see that it be not a bad ARRANGING! Ye have arranged too hastily: so there FOLLOWETH therefrom—marriage-breaking!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And better marriage-breaking than marriage-bending, marriage-lying!—Thus spake a woman unto me: “Indeed, I broke the marriage, but first did the marriage break—me!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The badly paired found I ever the most revengeful: they make every one suffer for it that they no longer run singly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On that account want I the honest ones to say to one another: “We love each other: let us SEE TO IT that we maintain our love! Or shall our pledging be blundering?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Give us a set term and a small marriage, that we may see if we are fit for the great marriage! It is a great matter always to be twain.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus do I counsel all honest ones; and what would be my love to the Superman, and to all that is to come, if I should counsel and speak otherwise!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not only to propagate yourselves onwards but UPWARDS—thereto, O my brethren, may the garden of marriage help you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>25.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who hath grown wise concerning old origins, lo, he will at last seek after the fountains of the future and new origins.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, not long will it be until NEW PEOPLES shall arise and new fountains shall rush down into new depths.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the earthquake—it choketh up many wells, it causeth much languishing: but it bringeth also to light inner powers and secrets.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The earthquake discloseth new fountains. In the earthquake of old peoples new fountains burst forth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whoever calleth out: “Lo, here is a well for many thirsty ones, one heart for many longing ones, one will for many instruments”:—around him collecteth a PEOPLE, that is to say, many attempting ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Who can command, who must obey—THAT IS THERE ATTEMPTED! Ah, with what long seeking and solving and failing and learning and re-attempting!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Human society: it is an attempt—so I teach—a long seeking: it seeketh however the ruler!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—An attempt, my brethren! And NO “contract”! Destroy, I pray you, destroy that word of the soft-hearted and half-and-half!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>26.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren! With whom lieth the greatest danger to the whole human future? Is it not with the good and just?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As those who say and feel in their hearts: “We already know what is good and just, we possess it also; woe to those who still seek thereafter!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whatever harm the wicked may do, the harm of the good is the harmfulest harm!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whatever harm the world-maligners may do, the harm of the good is the harmfulest harm!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, into the hearts of the good and just looked some one once on a time, who said: “They are the Pharisees.” But people did not understand him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The good and just themselves were not free to understand him; their spirit was imprisoned in their good conscience. The stupidity of the good is unfathomably wise.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is the truth, however, that the good MUST be Pharisees—they have no choice!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The good MUST crucify him who deviseth his own virtue! That IS the truth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The second one, however, who discovered their country—the country, heart and soil of the good and just,—it was he who asked: “Whom do they hate most?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The CREATOR, hate they most, him who breaketh the tables and old values, the breaker,—him they call the law-breaker.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the good—they CANNOT create; they are always the beginning of the end:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—They crucify him who writeth new values on new tables, they sacrifice UNTO THEMSELVES the future—they crucify the whole human future!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The good—they have always been the beginning of the end.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>27.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, have ye also understood this word? And what I once said of the “last man”?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With whom lieth the greatest danger to the whole human future? Is it not with the good and just?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>BREAK UP, BREAK UP, I PRAY YOU, THE GOOD AND JUST!—O my brethren, have ye understood also this word?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>28.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye flee from me? Ye are frightened? Ye tremble at this word?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, when I enjoined you to break up the good, and the tables of the good, then only did I embark man on his high seas.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And now only cometh unto him the great terror, the great outlook, the great sickness, the great nausea, the great sea-sickness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>False shores and false securities did the good teach you; in the lies of the good were ye born and bred. Everything hath been radically contorted and distorted by the good.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But he who discovered the country of “man,” discovered also the country of “man’s future.” Now shall ye be sailors for me, brave, patient!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Keep yourselves up betimes, my brethren, learn to keep yourselves up! The sea stormeth: many seek to raise themselves again by you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The sea stormeth: all is in the sea. Well! Cheer up! Ye old seaman-hearts!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What of fatherland! THITHER striveth our helm where our CHILDREN’S LAND is! Thitherwards, stormier than the sea, stormeth our great longing!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>29.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why so hard!”—said to the diamond one day the charcoal; “are we then not near relatives?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why so soft? O my brethren; thus do <i>I</i> ask you: are ye then not—my brethren?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Why so soft, so submissive and yielding? Why is there so much negation and abnegation in your hearts? Why is there so little fate in your looks?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if ye will not be fates and inexorable ones, how can ye one day— conquer with me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if your hardness will not glance and cut and chip to pieces, how can ye one day—create with me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the creators are hard. And blessedness must it seem to you to press your hand upon millenniums as upon wax,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Blessedness to write upon the will of millenniums as upon brass,—harder than brass, nobler than brass. Entirely hard is only the noblest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This new table, O my brethren, put I up over you: BECOME HARD!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>30.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O thou, my Will! Thou change of every need, MY needfulness! Preserve me from all small victories!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou fatedness of my soul, which I call fate! Thou In-me! Over-me! Preserve and spare me for one great fate!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thy last greatness, my Will, spare it for thy last—that thou mayest be inexorable IN thy victory! Ah, who hath not succumbed to his victory!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, whose eye hath not bedimmed in this intoxicated twilight! Ah, whose foot hath not faltered and forgotten in victory—how to stand!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That I may one day be ready and ripe in the great noontide: ready and ripe like the glowing ore, the lightning-bearing cloud, and the swelling milk-udder:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ready for myself and for my most hidden Will: a bow eager for its arrow, an arrow eager for its star:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A star, ready and ripe in its noontide, glowing, pierced, blessed, by annihilating sun-arrows:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A sun itself, and an inexorable sun-will, ready for annihilation in victory!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Will, thou change of every need, MY needfulness! Spare me for one great victory!—-</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LVII. THE CONVALESCENT.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One morning, not long after his return to his cave, Zarathustra sprang up from his couch like a madman, crying with a frightful voice, and acting as if some one still lay on the couch who did not wish to rise. Zarathustra’s voice also resounded in such a manner that his animals came to him frightened, and out of all the neighbouring caves and lurking-places all the creatures slipped away—flying, fluttering, creeping or leaping, according to their variety of foot or wing. Zarathustra, however, spake these words:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Up, abysmal thought out of my depth! I am thy cock and morning dawn, thou overslept reptile: Up! Up! My voice shall soon crow thee awake!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unbind the fetters of thine ears: listen! For I wish to hear thee! Up! Up! There is thunder enough to make the very graves listen!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And rub the sleep and all the dimness and blindness out of thine eyes! Hear me also with thine eyes: my voice is a medicine even for those born blind.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And once thou art awake, then shalt thou ever remain awake. It is not MY custom to awake great-grandmothers out of their sleep that I may bid them—sleep on!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou stirrest, stretchest thyself, wheezest? Up! Up! Not wheeze, shalt thou,—but speak unto me! Zarathustra calleth thee, Zarathustra the godless!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I, Zarathustra, the advocate of living, the advocate of suffering, the advocate of the circuit—thee do I call, my most abysmal thought!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Joy to me! Thou comest,—I hear thee! Mine abyss SPEAKETH, my lowest depth have I turned over into the light!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Joy to me! Come hither! Give me thy hand—ha! let be! aha!—Disgust, disgust, disgust—alas to me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hardly, however, had Zarathustra spoken these words, when he fell down as one dead, and remained long as one dead. When however he again came to himself, then was he pale and trembling, and remained lying; and for long he would neither eat nor drink. This condition continued for seven days; his animals, however, did not leave him day nor night, except that the eagle flew forth to fetch food. And what it fetched and foraged, it laid on Zarathustra’s couch: so that Zarathustra at last lay among yellow and red berries, grapes, rosy apples, sweet-smelling herbage, and pine-cones. At his feet, however, two lambs were stretched, which the eagle had with difficulty carried off from their shepherds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At last, after seven days, Zarathustra raised himself upon his couch, took a rosy apple in his hand, smelt it and found its smell pleasant. Then did his animals think the time had come to speak unto him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” said they, “now hast thou lain thus for seven days with heavy eyes: wilt thou not set thyself again upon thy feet?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Step out of thy cave: the world waiteth for thee as a garden. The wind playeth with heavy fragrance which seeketh for thee; and all brooks would like to run after thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All things long for thee, since thou hast remained alone for seven days—step forth out of thy cave! All things want to be thy physicians!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did perhaps a new knowledge come to thee, a bitter, grievous knowledge? Like leavened dough layest thou, thy soul arose and swelled beyond all its bounds.—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—O mine animals, answered Zarathustra, talk on thus and let me listen! It refresheth me so to hear your talk: where there is talk, there is the world as a garden unto me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How charming it is that there are words and tones; are not words and tones rainbows and seeming bridges ‘twixt the eternally separated?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To each soul belongeth another world; to each soul is every other soul a back-world.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Among the most alike doth semblance deceive most delightfully: for the smallest gap is most difficult to bridge over.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For me—how could there be an outside-of-me? There is no outside! But this we forget on hearing tones; how delightful it is that we forget!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have not names and tones been given unto things that man may refresh himself with them? It is a beautiful folly, speaking; therewith danceth man over everything.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How lovely is all speech and all falsehoods of tones! With tones danceth our love on variegated rainbows.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“O Zarathustra,” said then his animals, “to those who think like us, things all dance themselves: they come and hold out the hand and laugh and flee—and return.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything goeth, everything returneth; eternally rolleth the wheel of existence. Everything dieth, everything blossometh forth again; eternally runneth on the year of existence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Everything breaketh, everything is integrated anew; eternally buildeth itself the same house of existence. All things separate, all things again greet one another; eternally true to itself remaineth the ring of existence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every moment beginneth existence, around every ‘Here’ rolleth the ball ‘There.’ The middle is everywhere. Crooked is the path of eternity.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—O ye wags and barrel-organs! answered Zarathustra, and smiled once more, how well do ye know what had to be fulfilled in seven days:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And how that monster crept into my throat and choked me! But I bit off its head and spat it away from me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ye—ye have made a lyre-lay out of it? Now, however, do I lie here, still exhausted with that biting and spitting-away, still sick with mine own salvation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>AND YE LOOKED ON AT IT ALL? O mine animals, are ye also cruel? Did ye like to look at my great pain as men do? For man is the cruellest animal.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At tragedies, bull-fights, and crucifixions hath he hitherto been happiest on earth; and when he invented his hell, behold, that was his heaven on earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the great man crieth—: immediately runneth the little man thither, and his tongue hangeth out of his mouth for very lusting. He, however, calleth it his “pity.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The little man, especially the poet—how passionately doth he accuse life in words! Hearken to him, but do not fail to hear the delight which is in all accusation!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such accusers of life—them life overcometh with a glance of the eye. “Thou lovest me?” saith the insolent one; “wait a little, as yet have I no time for thee.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Towards himself man is the cruellest animal; and in all who call themselves “sinners” and “bearers of the cross” and “penitents,” do not overlook the voluptuousness in their plaints and accusations!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And I myself—do I thereby want to be man’s accuser? Ah, mine animals, this only have I learned hitherto, that for man his baddest is necessary for his best,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That all that is baddest is the best POWER, and the hardest stone for the highest creator; and that man must become better AND badder:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not to THIS torture-stake was I tied, that I know man is bad,—but I cried, as no one hath yet cried:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ah, that his baddest is so very small! Ah, that his best is so very small!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The great disgust at man—IT strangled me and had crept into my throat: and what the soothsayer had presaged: “All is alike, nothing is worth while, knowledge strangleth.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A long twilight limped on before me, a fatally weary, fatally intoxicated sadness, which spake with yawning mouth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Eternally he returneth, the man of whom thou art weary, the small man”—so yawned my sadness, and dragged its foot and could not go to sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A cavern, became the human earth to me; its breast caved in; everything living became to me human dust and bones and mouldering past.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My sighing sat on all human graves, and could no longer arise: my sighing and questioning croaked and choked, and gnawed and nagged day and night:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Ah, man returneth eternally! The small man returneth eternally!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Naked had I once seen both of them, the greatest man and the smallest man: all too like one another—all too human, even the greatest man!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All too small, even the greatest man!—that was my disgust at man! And the eternal return also of the smallest man!—that was my disgust at all existence!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, Disgust! Disgust! Disgust!—Thus spake Zarathustra, and sighed and shuddered; for he remembered his sickness. Then did his animals prevent him from speaking further.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Do not speak further, thou convalescent!”—so answered his animals, “but go out where the world waiteth for thee like a garden.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Go out unto the roses, the bees, and the flocks of doves! Especially, however, unto the singing-birds, to learn SINGING from them!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For singing is for the convalescent; the sound ones may talk. And when the sound also want songs, then want they other songs than the convalescent.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“O ye wags and barrel-organs, do be silent!” answered Zarathustra, and smiled at his animals. “How well ye know what consolation I devised for myself in seven days!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That I have to sing once more—THAT consolation did I devise for myself, and THIS convalescence: would ye also make another lyre-lay thereof?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Do not talk further,” answered his animals once more; “rather, thou convalescent, prepare for thyself first a lyre, a new lyre!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For behold, O Zarathustra! For thy new lays there are needed new lyres.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sing and bubble over, O Zarathustra, heal thy soul with new lays: that thou mayest bear thy great fate, which hath not yet been any one’s fate!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For thine animals know it well, O Zarathustra, who thou art and must become: behold, THOU ART THE TEACHER OF THE ETERNAL RETURN,—that is now THY fate!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That thou must be the first to teach this teaching—how could this great fate not be thy greatest danger and infirmity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behold, we know what thou teachest: that all things eternally return, and ourselves with them, and that we have already existed times without number, and all things with us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou teachest that there is a great year of Becoming, a prodigy of a great year; it must, like a sand-glass, ever turn up anew, that it may anew run down and run out:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—So that all those years are like one another in the greatest and also in the smallest, so that we ourselves, in every great year, are like ourselves in the greatest and also in the smallest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if thou wouldst now die, O Zarathustra, behold, we know also how thou wouldst then speak to thyself:—but thine animals beseech thee not to die yet!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou wouldst speak, and without trembling, buoyant rather with bliss, for a great weight and worry would be taken from thee, thou patientest one!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Now do I die and disappear,’ wouldst thou say, ‘and in a moment I am nothing. Souls are as mortal as bodies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the plexus of causes returneth in which I am intertwined,—it will again create me! I myself pertain to the causes of the eternal return.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I come again with this sun, with this earth, with this eagle, with this serpent—NOT to a new life, or a better life, or a similar life:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—I come again eternally to this identical and selfsame life, in its greatest and its smallest, to teach again the eternal return of all things,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—To speak again the word of the great noontide of earth and man, to announce again to man the Superman.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I have spoken my word. I break down by my word: so willeth mine eternal fate—as announcer do I succumb!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The hour hath now come for the down-goer to bless himself. Thus—ENDETH Zarathustra’s down-going.’”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the animals had spoken these words they were silent and waited, so that Zarathustra might say something to them: but Zarathustra did not hear that they were silent. On the contrary, he lay quietly with closed eyes like a person sleeping, although he did not sleep; for he communed just then with his soul. The serpent, however, and the eagle, when they found him silent in such wise, respected the great stillness around him, and prudently retired.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LVIII. THE GREAT LONGING.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I have taught thee to say “to-day” as “once on a time” and “formerly,” and to dance thy measure over every Here and There and Yonder.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I delivered thee from all by-places, I brushed down from thee dust and spiders and twilight.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I washed the petty shame and the by-place virtue from thee, and persuaded thee to stand naked before the eyes of the sun.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the storm that is called “spirit” did I blow over thy surging sea; all clouds did I blow away from it; I strangled even the strangler called “sin.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I gave thee the right to say Nay like the storm, and to say Yea as the open heaven saith Yea: calm as the light remainest thou, and now walkest through denying storms.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I restored to thee liberty over the created and the uncreated; and who knoweth, as thou knowest, the voluptuousness of the future?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I taught thee the contempt which doth not come like worm-eating, the great, the loving contempt, which loveth most where it contemneth most.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I taught thee so to persuade that thou persuadest even the grounds themselves to thee: like the sun, which persuadeth even the sea to its height.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I have taken from thee all obeying and knee-bending and homage-paying; I have myself given thee the names, “Change of need” and “Fate.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I have given thee new names and gay-coloured playthings, I have called thee “Fate” and “the Circuit of circuits” and “the Navel-string of time” and “the Azure bell.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, to thy domain gave I all wisdom to drink, all new wines, and also all immemorially old strong wines of wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, every sun shed I upon thee, and every night and every silence and every longing:—then grewest thou up for me as a vine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, exuberant and heavy dost thou now stand forth, a vine with swelling udders and full clusters of brown golden grapes:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Filled and weighted by thy happiness, waiting from superabundance, and yet ashamed of thy waiting.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, there is nowhere a soul which could be more loving and more comprehensive and more extensive! Where could future and past be closer together than with thee?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I have given thee everything, and all my hands have become empty by thee:—and now! Now sayest thou to me, smiling and full of melancholy: “Which of us oweth thanks?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Doth the giver not owe thanks because the receiver received? Is bestowing not a necessity? Is receiving not—pitying?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, I understand the smiling of thy melancholy: thine over-abundance itself now stretcheth out longing hands!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thy fulness looketh forth over raging seas, and seeketh and waiteth: the longing of over-fulness looketh forth from the smiling heaven of thine eyes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, O my soul! Who could see thy smiling and not melt into tears? The angels themselves melt into tears through the over-graciousness of thy smiling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thy graciousness and over-graciousness, is it which will not complain and weep: and yet, O my soul, longeth thy smiling for tears, and thy trembling mouth for sobs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Is not all weeping complaining? And all complaining, accusing?” Thus speakest thou to thyself; and therefore, O my soul, wilt thou rather smile than pour forth thy grief—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Than in gushing tears pour forth all thy grief concerning thy fulness, and concerning the craving of the vine for the vintager and vintage-knife!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But wilt thou not weep, wilt thou not weep forth thy purple melancholy, then wilt thou have to SING, O my soul!—Behold, I smile myself, who foretell thee this:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thou wilt have to sing with passionate song, until all seas turn calm to hearken unto thy longing,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Until over calm longing seas the bark glideth, the golden marvel, around the gold of which all good, bad, and marvellous things frisk:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Also many large and small animals, and everything that hath light marvellous feet, so that it can run on violet-blue paths,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000002999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Towards the golden marvel, the spontaneous bark, and its master: he, however, is the vintager who waiteth with the diamond vintage-knife,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thy great deliverer, O my soul, the nameless one—for whom future songs only will find names! And verily, already hath thy breath the fragrance of future songs,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Already glowest thou and dreamest, already drinkest thou thirstily at all deep echoing wells of consolation, already reposeth thy melancholy in the bliss of future songs!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my soul, now have I given thee all, and even my last possession, and all my hands have become empty by thee:—THAT I BADE THEE SING, behold, that was my last thing to give!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That I bade thee sing,—say now, say: WHICH of us now—oweth thanks?— Better still, however: sing unto me, sing, O my soul! And let me thank thee!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LIX. THE SECOND DANCE-SONG.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Into thine eyes gazed I lately, O Life: gold saw I gleam in thy night-eyes,—my heart stood still with delight:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A golden bark saw I gleam on darkened waters, a sinking, drinking, reblinking, golden swing-bark!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At my dance-frantic foot, dost thou cast a glance, a laughing, questioning, melting, thrown glance:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Twice only movedst thou thy rattle with thy little hands—then did my feet swing with dance-fury.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My heels reared aloft, my toes they hearkened,—thee they would know: hath not the dancer his ear—in his toe!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unto thee did I spring: then fledst thou back from my bound; and towards me waved thy fleeing, flying tresses round!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Away from thee did I spring, and from thy snaky tresses: then stoodst thou there half-turned, and in thine eye caresses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With crooked glances—dost thou teach me crooked courses; on crooked courses learn my feet—crafty fancies!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I fear thee near, I love thee far; thy flight allureth me, thy seeking secureth me:—I suffer, but for thee, what would I not gladly bear!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For thee, whose coldness inflameth, whose hatred misleadeth, whose flight enchaineth, whose mockery—pleadeth:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Who would not hate thee, thou great bindress, inwindress, temptress, seekress, findress! Who would not love thee, thou innocent, impatient, wind-swift, child-eyed sinner!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whither pullest thou me now, thou paragon and tomboy? And now foolest thou me fleeing; thou sweet romp dost annoy!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I dance after thee, I follow even faint traces lonely. Where art thou? Give me thy hand! Or thy finger only!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here are caves and thickets: we shall go astray!—Halt! Stand still! Seest thou not owls and bats in fluttering fray?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou bat! Thou owl! Thou wouldst play me foul? Where are we? From the dogs hast thou learned thus to bark and howl.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou gnashest on me sweetly with little white teeth; thine evil eyes shoot out upon me, thy curly little mane from underneath!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is a dance over stock and stone: I am the hunter,—wilt thou be my hound, or my chamois anon?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now beside me! And quickly, wickedly springing! Now up! And over!—Alas! I have fallen myself overswinging!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, see me lying, thou arrogant one, and imploring grace! Gladly would I walk with thee—in some lovelier place!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—In the paths of love, through bushes variegated, quiet, trim! Or there along the lake, where gold-fishes dance and swim!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou art now a-weary? There above are sheep and sun-set stripes: is it not sweet to sleep—the shepherd pipes?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou art so very weary? I carry thee thither; let just thine arm sink! And art thou thirsty—I should have something; but thy mouth would not like it to drink!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Oh, that cursed, nimble, supple serpent and lurking-witch! Where art thou gone? But in my face do I feel through thy hand, two spots and red blotches itch!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am verily weary of it, ever thy sheepish shepherd to be. Thou witch, if I have hitherto sung unto thee, now shalt THOU—cry unto me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the rhythm of my whip shalt thou dance and cry! I forget not my whip?—Not I!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then did Life answer me thus, and kept thereby her fine ears closed:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra! Crack not so terribly with thy whip! Thou knowest surely that noise killeth thought,—and just now there came to me such delicate thoughts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We are both of us genuine ne’er-do-wells and ne’er-do-ills. Beyond good and evil found we our island and our green meadow—we two alone! Therefore must we be friendly to each other!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And even should we not love each other from the bottom of our hearts,—must we then have a grudge against each other if we do not love each other perfectly?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And that I am friendly to thee, and often too friendly, that knowest thou: and the reason is that I am envious of thy Wisdom. Ah, this mad old fool, Wisdom!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If thy Wisdom should one day run away from thee, ah! then would also my love run away from thee quickly.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereupon did Life look thoughtfully behind and around, and said softly: “O Zarathustra, thou art not faithful enough to me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou lovest me not nearly so much as thou sayest; I know thou thinkest of soon leaving me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is an old heavy, heavy, booming-clock: it boometh by night up to thy cave:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When thou hearest this clock strike the hours at midnight, then thinkest thou between one and twelve thereon—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thou thinkest thereon, O Zarathustra, I know it—of soon leaving me!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Yea,” answered I, hesitatingly, “but thou knowest it also”—And I said something into her ear, in amongst her confused, yellow, foolish tresses.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou KNOWEST that, O Zarathustra? That knoweth no one—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And we gazed at each other, and looked at the green meadow o’er which the cool evening was just passing, and we wept together.—Then, however, was Life dearer unto me than all my Wisdom had ever been.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>One!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O man! Take heed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Two!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What saith deep midnight’s voice indeed?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Three!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I slept my sleep—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Four!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“From deepest dream I’ve woke and plead:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Five!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The world is deep,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Six!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“And deeper than the day could read.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Seven!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Deep is its woe—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Eight!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Joy—deeper still than grief can be:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Nine!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Woe saith: Hence! Go!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Ten!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“But joys all want eternity—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Eleven!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Want deep profound eternity!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><i>Twelve!</i></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LX. THE SEVEN SEALS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>(OR THE YEA AND AMEN LAY.)</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>1.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If I be a diviner and full of the divining spirit which wandereth on high mountain-ridges, ‘twixt two seas,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Wandereth ‘twixt the past and the future as a heavy cloud—hostile to sultry plains, and to all that is weary and can neither die nor live:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ready for lightning in its dark bosom, and for the redeeming flash of light, charged with lightnings which say Yea! which laugh Yea! ready for divining flashes of lightning:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Blessed, however, is he who is thus charged! And verily, long must he hang like a heavy tempest on the mountain, who shall one day kindle the light of the future!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! 2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever my wrath hath burst graves, shifted landmarks, or rolled old shattered tables into precipitous depths:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever my scorn hath scattered mouldered words to the winds, and if I have come like a besom to cross-spiders, and as a cleansing wind to old charnel-houses:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever I have sat rejoicing where old Gods lie buried, world-blessing, world-loving, beside the monuments of old world-maligners:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For even churches and Gods’-graves do I love, if only heaven looketh through their ruined roofs with pure eyes; gladly do I sit like grass and red poppies on ruined churches—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity, and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! 3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever a breath hath come to me of the creative breath, and of the heavenly necessity which compelleth even chances to dance star-dances:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever I have laughed with the laughter of the creative lightning, to which the long thunder of the deed followeth, grumblingly, but obediently:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever I have played dice with the Gods at the divine table of the earth, so that the earth quaked and ruptured, and snorted forth fire-streams:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For a divine table is the earth, and trembling with new creative dictums and dice-casts of the Gods:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity, and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! 4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever I have drunk a full draught of the foaming spice- and confection-bowl in which all things are well mixed:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever my hand hath mingled the furthest with the nearest, fire with spirit, joy with sorrow, and the harshest with the kindest:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If I myself am a grain of the saving salt which maketh everything in the confection-bowl mix well:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For there is a salt which uniteth good with evil; and even the evilest is worthy, as spicing and as final over-foaming:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity, and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! 5.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If I be fond of the sea, and all that is sealike, and fondest of it when it angrily contradicteth me:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If the exploring delight be in me, which impelleth sails to the undiscovered, if the seafarer’s delight be in my delight:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever my rejoicing hath called out: “The shore hath vanished,—now hath fallen from me the last chain—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The boundless roareth around me, far away sparkle for me space and time,—well! cheer up! old heart!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity, and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! 6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If my virtue be a dancer’s virtue, and if I have often sprung with both feet into golden-emerald rapture:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If my wickedness be a laughing wickedness, at home among rose-banks and hedges of lilies:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For in laughter is all evil present, but it is sanctified and absolved by its own bliss:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if it be my Alpha and Omega that everything heavy shall become light, every body a dancer, and every spirit a bird: and verily, that is my Alpha and Omega!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity, and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! 7.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ever I have spread out a tranquil heaven above me, and have flown into mine own heaven with mine own pinions:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If I have swum playfully in profound luminous distances, and if my freedom’s avian wisdom hath come to me:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thus however speaketh avian wisdom:—“Lo, there is no above and no below! Throw thyself about,—outward, backward, thou light one! Sing! speak no more!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Are not all words made for the heavy? Do not all words lie to the light ones? Sing! speak no more!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Oh, how could I not be ardent for Eternity, and for the marriage-ring of rings—the ring of the return?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Never yet have I found the woman by whom I should like to have children, unless it be this woman whom I love: for I love thee, O Eternity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>FOR I LOVE THEE, O ETERNITY! <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>FOURTH AND LAST PART.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, where in the world have there been greater follies than with the pitiful? And what in the world hath caused more suffering than the follies of the pitiful?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Woe unto all loving ones who have not an elevation which is above their pity!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the devil unto me, once on a time: “Even God hath his hell: it is his love for man.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And lately did I hear him say these words: “God is dead: of his pity for man hath God died.”—ZARATHUSTRA, II., “The Pitiful.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXI. THE HONEY SACRIFICE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And again passed moons and years over Zarathustra’s soul, and he heeded it not; his hair, however, became white. One day when he sat on a stone in front of his cave, and gazed calmly into the distance—one there gazeth out on the sea, and away beyond sinuous abysses,—then went his animals thoughtfully round about him, and at last set themselves in front of him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” said they, “gazest thou out perhaps for thy happiness?”—“Of what account is my happiness!” answered he, “I have long ceased to strive any more for happiness, I strive for my work.”—“O Zarathustra,” said the animals once more, “that sayest thou as one who hath overmuch of good things. Liest thou not in a sky-blue lake of happiness?”—“Ye wags,” answered Zarathustra, and smiled, “how well did ye choose the simile! But ye know also that my happiness is heavy, and not like a fluid wave of water: it presseth me and will not leave me, and is like molten pitch.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then went his animals again thoughtfully around him, and placed themselves once more in front of him. “O Zarathustra,” said they, “it is consequently FOR THAT REASON that thou thyself always becometh yellower and darker, although thy hair looketh white and flaxen? Lo, thou sittest in thy pitch!”—“What do ye say, mine animals?” said Zarathustra, laughing; “verily I reviled when I spake of pitch. As it happeneth with me, so is it with all fruits that turn ripe. It is the HONEY in my veins that maketh my blood thicker, and also my soul stiller.”—“So will it be, O Zarathustra,” answered his animals, and pressed up to him; “but wilt thou not to-day ascend a high mountain? The air is pure, and to-day one seeth more of the world than ever.”—“Yea, mine animals,” answered he, “ye counsel admirably and according to my heart: I will to-day ascend a high mountain! But see that honey is there ready to hand, yellow, white, good, ice-cool, golden-comb-honey. For know that when aloft I will make the honey-sacrifice.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra, however, was aloft on the summit, he sent his animals home that had accompanied him, and found that he was now alone:—then he laughed from the bottom of his heart, looked around him, and spake thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That I spake of sacrifices and honey-sacrifices, it was merely a ruse in talking and verily, a useful folly! Here aloft can I now speak freer than in front of mountain-caves and anchorites’ domestic animals.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What to sacrifice! I squander what is given me, a squanderer with a thousand hands: how could I call that—sacrificing?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I desired honey I only desired bait, and sweet mucus and mucilage, for which even the mouths of growling bears, and strange, sulky, evil birds, water:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The best bait, as huntsmen and fishermen require it. For if the world be as a gloomy forest of animals, and a pleasure-ground for all wild huntsmen, it seemeth to me rather—and preferably—a fathomless, rich sea;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A sea full of many-hued fishes and crabs, for which even the Gods might long, and might be tempted to become fishers in it, and casters of nets,—so rich is the world in wonderful things, great and small!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Especially the human world, the human sea:—towards IT do I now throw out my golden angle-rod and say: Open up, thou human abyss!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Open up, and throw unto me thy fish and shining crabs! With my best bait shall I allure to myself to-day the strangest human fish!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—My happiness itself do I throw out into all places far and wide ‘twixt orient, noontide, and occident, to see if many human fish will not learn to hug and tug at my happiness;—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Until, biting at my sharp hidden hooks, they have to come up unto MY height, the motleyest abyss-groundlings, to the wickedest of all fishers of men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For THIS am I from the heart and from the beginning—drawing, hither-drawing, upward-drawing, upbringing; a drawer, a trainer, a training-master, who not in vain counselled himself once on a time: “Become what thou art!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus may men now come UP to me; for as yet do I await the signs that it is time for my down-going; as yet do I not myself go down, as I must do, amongst men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore do I here wait, crafty and scornful upon high mountains, no impatient one, no patient one; rather one who hath even unlearnt patience,—because he no longer “suffereth.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For my fate giveth me time: it hath forgotten me perhaps? Or doth it sit behind a big stone and catch flies?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, I am well-disposed to mine eternal fate, because it doth not hound and hurry me, but leaveth me time for merriment and mischief; so that I have to-day ascended this high mountain to catch fish.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did ever any one catch fish upon high mountains? And though it be a folly what I here seek and do, it is better so than that down below I should become solemn with waiting, and green and yellow—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A posturing wrath-snorter with waiting, a holy howl-storm from the mountains, an impatient one that shouteth down into the valleys: “Hearken, else I will scourge you with the scourge of God!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not that I would have a grudge against such wrathful ones on that account: they are well enough for laughter to me! Impatient must they now be, those big alarm-drums, which find a voice now or never!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Myself, however, and my fate—we do not talk to the Present, neither do we talk to the Never: for talking we have patience and time and more than time. For one day must it yet come, and may not pass by.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What must one day come and may not pass by? Our great Hazar, that is to say, our great, remote human-kingdom, the Zarathustra-kingdom of a thousand years—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How remote may such “remoteness” be? What doth it concern me? But on that account it is none the less sure unto me—, with both feet stand I secure on this ground;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—On an eternal ground, on hard primary rock, on this highest, hardest, primary mountain-ridge, unto which all winds come, as unto the storm-parting, asking Where? and Whence? and Whither?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here laugh, laugh, my hearty, healthy wickedness! From high mountains cast down thy glittering scorn-laughter! Allure for me with thy glittering the finest human fish!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whatever belongeth unto ME in all seas, my in-and-for-me in all things—fish THAT out for me, bring THAT up to me: for that do I wait, the wickedest of all fish-catchers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Out! out! my fishing-hook! In and down, thou bait of my happiness! Drip thy sweetest dew, thou honey of my heart! Bite, my fishing-hook, into the belly of all black affliction!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Look out, look out, mine eye! Oh, how many seas round about me, what dawning human futures! And above me—what rosy red stillness! What unclouded silence!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXII. THE CRY OF DISTRESS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The next day sat Zarathustra again on the stone in front of his cave, whilst his animals roved about in the world outside to bring home new food,—also new honey: for Zarathustra had spent and wasted the old honey to the very last particle. When he thus sat, however, with a stick in his hand, tracing the shadow of his figure on the earth, and reflecting—verily! not upon himself and his shadow,—all at once he startled and shrank back: for he saw another shadow beside his own. And when he hastily looked around and stood up, behold, there stood the soothsayer beside him, the same whom he had once given to eat and drink at his table, the proclaimer of the great weariness, who taught: “All is alike, nothing is worth while, the world is without meaning, knowledge strangleth.” But his face had changed since then; and when Zarathustra looked into his eyes, his heart was startled once more: so much evil announcement and ashy-grey lightnings passed over that countenance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The soothsayer, who had perceived what went on in Zarathustra’s soul, wiped his face with his hand, as if he would wipe out the impression; the same did also Zarathustra. And when both of them had thus silently composed and strengthened themselves, they gave each other the hand, as a token that they wanted once more to recognise each other.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Welcome hither,” said Zarathustra, “thou soothsayer of the great weariness, not in vain shalt thou once have been my messmate and guest. Eat and drink also with me to-day, and forgive it that a cheerful old man sitteth with thee at table!”—“A cheerful old man?” answered the soothsayer, shaking his head, “but whoever thou art, or wouldst be, O Zarathustra, thou hast been here aloft the longest time,—in a little while thy bark shall no longer rest on dry land!”—“Do I then rest on dry land?”—asked Zarathustra, laughing.—“The waves around thy mountain,” answered the soothsayer, “rise and rise, the waves of great distress and affliction: they will soon raise thy bark also and carry thee away.”—Thereupon was Zarathustra silent and wondered.—“Dost thou still hear nothing?” continued the soothsayer: “doth it not rush and roar out of the depth?”—Zarathustra was silent once more and listened: then heard he a long, long cry, which the abysses threw to one another and passed on; for none of them wished to retain it: so evil did it sound.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou ill announcer,” said Zarathustra at last, “that is a cry of distress, and the cry of a man; it may come perhaps out of a black sea. But what doth human distress matter to me! My last sin which hath been reserved for me,—knowest thou what it is called?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“PITY!” answered the soothsayer from an overflowing heart, and raised both his hands aloft—“O Zarathustra, I have come that I may seduce thee to thy last sin!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And hardly had those words been uttered when there sounded the cry once more, and longer and more alarming than before—also much nearer. “Hearest thou? Hearest thou, O Zarathustra?” called out the soothsayer, “the cry concerneth thee, it calleth thee: Come, come, come; it is time, it is the highest time!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra was silent thereupon, confused and staggered; at last he asked, like one who hesitateth in himself: “And who is it that there calleth me?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“But thou knowest it, certainly,” answered the soothsayer warmly, “why dost thou conceal thyself? It is THE HIGHER MAN that crieth for thee!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The higher man?” cried Zarathustra, horror-stricken: “what wanteth HE? What wanteth HE? The higher man! What wanteth he here?”—and his skin covered with perspiration.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The soothsayer, however, did not heed Zarathustra’s alarm, but listened and listened in the downward direction. When, however, it had been still there for a long while, he looked behind, and saw Zarathustra standing trembling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” he began, with sorrowful voice, “thou dost not stand there like one whose happiness maketh him giddy: thou wilt have to dance lest thou tumble down!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But although thou shouldst dance before me, and leap all thy side-leaps, no one may say unto me: ‘Behold, here danceth the last joyous man!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In vain would any one come to this height who sought HIM here: caves would he find, indeed, and back-caves, hiding-places for hidden ones; but not lucky mines, nor treasure-chambers, nor new gold-veins of happiness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Happiness—how indeed could one find happiness among such buried-alive and solitary ones! Must I yet seek the last happiness on the Happy Isles, and far away among forgotten seas?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But all is alike, nothing is worth while, no seeking is of service, there are no longer any Happy Isles!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sighed the soothsayer; with his last sigh, however, Zarathustra again became serene and assured, like one who hath come out of a deep chasm into the light. “Nay! Nay! Three times Nay!” exclaimed he with a strong voice, and stroked his beard—“THAT do I know better! There are still Happy Isles! Silence THEREON, thou sighing sorrow-sack!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Cease to splash THEREON, thou rain-cloud of the forenoon! Do I not already stand here wet with thy misery, and drenched like a dog?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now do I shake myself and run away from thee, that I may again become dry: thereat mayest thou not wonder! Do I seem to thee discourteous? Here however is MY court.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But as regards the higher man: well! I shall seek him at once in those forests: FROM THENCE came his cry. Perhaps he is there hard beset by an evil beast.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He is in MY domain: therein shall he receive no scath! And verily, there are many evil beasts about me.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With those words Zarathustra turned around to depart. Then said the soothsayer: “O Zarathustra, thou art a rogue!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I know it well: thou wouldst fain be rid of me! Rather wouldst thou run into the forest and lay snares for evil beasts!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But what good will it do thee? In the evening wilt thou have me again: in thine own cave will I sit, patient and heavy like a block—and wait for thee!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“So be it!” shouted back Zarathustra, as he went away: “and what is mine in my cave belongeth also unto thee, my guest!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Shouldst thou however find honey therein, well! just lick it up, thou growling bear, and sweeten thy soul! For in the evening we want both to be in good spirits;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—In good spirits and joyful, because this day hath come to an end! And thou thyself shalt dance to my lays, as my dancing-bear.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou dost not believe this? Thou shakest thy head? Well! Cheer up, old bear! But I also—am a soothsayer.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXIII. TALK WITH THE KINGS.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ere Zarathustra had been an hour on his way in the mountains and forests, he saw all at once a strange procession. Right on the path which he was about to descend came two kings walking, bedecked with crowns and purple girdles, and variegated like flamingoes: they drove before them a laden ass. “What do these kings want in my domain?” said Zarathustra in astonishment to his heart, and hid himself hastily behind a thicket. When however the kings approached to him, he said half-aloud, like one speaking only to himself: “Strange! Strange! How doth this harmonise? Two kings do I see—and only one ass!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereupon the two kings made a halt; they smiled and looked towards the spot whence the voice proceeded, and afterwards looked into each other’s faces. “Such things do we also think among ourselves,” said the king on the right, “but we do not utter them.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The king on the left, however, shrugged his shoulders and answered: “That may perhaps be a goat-herd. Or an anchorite who hath lived too long among rocks and trees. For no society at all spoileth also good manners.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Good manners?” replied angrily and bitterly the other king: “what then do we run out of the way of? Is it not ‘good manners’? Our ‘good society’?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better, verily, to live among anchorites and goat-herds, than with our gilded, false, over-rouged populace—though it call itself ‘good society.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Though it call itself ‘nobility.’ But there all is false and foul, above all the blood—thanks to old evil diseases and worse curers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The best and dearest to me at present is still a sound peasant, coarse, artful, obstinate and enduring: that is at present the noblest type.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The peasant is at present the best; and the peasant type should be master! But it is the kingdom of the populace—I no longer allow anything to be imposed upon me. The populace, however—that meaneth, hodgepodge.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Populace-hodgepodge: therein is everything mixed with everything, saint and swindler, gentleman and Jew, and every beast out of Noah’s ark.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Good manners! Everything is false and foul with us. No one knoweth any longer how to reverence: it is THAT precisely that we run away from. They are fulsome obtrusive dogs; they gild palm-leaves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This loathing choketh me, that we kings ourselves have become false, draped and disguised with the old faded pomp of our ancestors, show-pieces for the stupidest, the craftiest, and whosoever at present trafficketh for power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We ARE NOT the first men—and have nevertheless to STAND FOR them: of this imposture have we at last become weary and disgusted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>From the rabble have we gone out of the way, from all those bawlers and scribe-blowflies, from the trader-stench, the ambition-fidgeting, the bad breath—: fie, to live among the rabble;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Fie, to stand for the first men among the rabble! Ah, loathing! Loathing! Loathing! What doth it now matter about us kings!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thine old sickness seizeth thee,” said here the king on the left, “thy loathing seizeth thee, my poor brother. Thou knowest, however, that some one heareth us.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Immediately thereupon, Zarathustra, who had opened ears and eyes to this talk, rose from his hiding-place, advanced towards the kings, and thus began:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“He who hearkeneth unto you, he who gladly hearkeneth unto you, is called Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am Zarathustra who once said: ‘What doth it now matter about kings!’ Forgive me; I rejoiced when ye said to each other: ‘What doth it matter about us kings!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here, however, is MY domain and jurisdiction: what may ye be seeking in my domain? Perhaps, however, ye have FOUND on your way what <i>I</i> seek: namely, the higher man.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the kings heard this, they beat upon their breasts and said with one voice: “We are recognised!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the sword of thine utterance severest thou the thickest darkness of our hearts. Thou hast discovered our distress; for lo! we are on our way to find the higher man—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The man that is higher than we, although we are kings. To him do we convey this ass. For the highest man shall also be the highest lord on earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is no sorer misfortune in all human destiny, than when the mighty of the earth are not also the first men. Then everything becometh false and distorted and monstrous.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when they are even the last men, and more beast than man, then riseth and riseth the populace in honour, and at last saith even the populace-virtue: ‘Lo, I alone am virtue!’”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What have I just heard? answered Zarathustra. What wisdom in kings! I am enchanted, and verily, I have already promptings to make a rhyme thereon:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Even if it should happen to be a rhyme not suited for every one’s ears. I unlearned long ago to have consideration for long ears. Well then! Well now!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(Here, however, it happened that the ass also found utterance: it said distinctly and with malevolence, Y-E-A.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Twas once—methinks year one of our blessed Lord,—Drunk without wine, the Sybil thus deplored:—“How ill things go! Decline! Decline! Ne’er sank the world so low! Rome now hath turned harlot and harlot-stew, Rome’s Caesar a beast, and God—hath turned Jew!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With those rhymes of Zarathustra the kings were delighted; the king on the right, however, said: “O Zarathustra, how well it was that we set out to see thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For thine enemies showed us thy likeness in their mirror: there lookedst thou with the grimace of a devil, and sneeringly: so that we were afraid of thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But what good did it do! Always didst thou prick us anew in heart and ear with thy sayings. Then did we say at last: What doth it matter how he look!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We must HEAR him; him who teacheth: ‘Ye shall love peace as a means to new wars, and the short peace more than the long!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No one ever spake such warlike words: ‘What is good? To be brave is good. It is the good war that halloweth every cause.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, our fathers’ blood stirred in our veins at such words: it was like the voice of spring to old wine-casks.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the swords ran among one another like red-spotted serpents, then did our fathers become fond of life; the sun of every peace seemed to them languid and lukewarm, the long peace, however, made them ashamed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How they sighed, our fathers, when they saw on the wall brightly furbished, dried-up swords! Like those they thirsted for war. For a sword thirsteth to drink blood, and sparkleth with desire.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When the kings thus discoursed and talked eagerly of the happiness of their fathers, there came upon Zarathustra no little desire to mock at their eagerness: for evidently they were very peaceable kings whom he saw before him, kings with old and refined features. But he restrained himself. “Well!” said he, “thither leadeth the way, there lieth the cave of Zarathustra; and this day is to have a long evening! At present, however, a cry of distress calleth me hastily away from you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It will honour my cave if kings want to sit and wait in it: but, to be sure, ye will have to wait long!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! What of that! Where doth one at present learn better to wait than at courts? And the whole virtue of kings that hath remained unto them—is it not called to-day: ABILITY to wait?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXIV. THE LEECH.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And Zarathustra went thoughtfully on, further and lower down, through forests and past moory bottoms; as it happeneth, however, to every one who meditateth upon hard matters, he trod thereby unawares upon a man. And lo, there spurted into his face all at once a cry of pain, and two curses and twenty bad invectives, so that in his fright he raised his stick and also struck the trodden one. Immediately afterwards, however, he regained his composure, and his heart laughed at the folly he had just committed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Pardon me,” said he to the trodden one, who had got up enraged, and had seated himself, “pardon me, and hear first of all a parable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As a wanderer who dreameth of remote things on a lonesome highway, runneth unawares against a sleeping dog, a dog which lieth in the sun:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As both of them then start up and snap at each other, like deadly enemies, those two beings mortally frightened—so did it happen unto us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And yet! And yet—how little was lacking for them to caress each other, that dog and that lonesome one! Are they not both—lonesome ones!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Whoever thou art,” said the trodden one, still enraged, “thou treadest also too nigh me with thy parable, and not only with thy foot!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo! am I then a dog?”—And thereupon the sitting one got up, and pulled his naked arm out of the swamp. For at first he had lain outstretched on the ground, hidden and indiscernible, like those who lie in wait for swamp-game.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“But whatever art thou about!” called out Zarathustra in alarm, for he saw a deal of blood streaming over the naked arm,—“what hath hurt thee? Hath an evil beast bit thee, thou unfortunate one?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The bleeding one laughed, still angry, “What matter is it to thee!” said he, and was about to go on. “Here am I at home and in my province. Let him question me whoever will: to a dolt, however, I shall hardly answer.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou art mistaken,” said Zarathustra sympathetically, and held him fast; “thou art mistaken. Here thou art not at home, but in my domain, and therein shall no one receive any hurt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Call me however what thou wilt—I am who I must be. I call myself Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! Up thither is the way to Zarathustra’s cave: it is not far,—wilt thou not attend to thy wounds at my home?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It hath gone badly with thee, thou unfortunate one, in this life: first a beast bit thee, and then—a man trod upon thee!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When however the trodden one had heard the name of Zarathustra he was transformed. “What happeneth unto me!” he exclaimed, “WHO preoccupieth me so much in this life as this one man, namely Zarathustra, and that one animal that liveth on blood, the leech?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the sake of the leech did I lie here by this swamp, like a fisher, and already had mine outstretched arm been bitten ten times, when there biteth a still finer leech at my blood, Zarathustra himself!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O happiness! O miracle! Praised be this day which enticed me into the swamp! Praised be the best, the livest cupping-glass, that at present liveth; praised be the great conscience-leech Zarathustra!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the trodden one, and Zarathustra rejoiced at his words and their refined reverential style. “Who art thou?” asked he, and gave him his hand, “there is much to clear up and elucidate between us, but already methinketh pure clear day is dawning.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I am THE SPIRITUALLY CONSCIENTIOUS ONE,” answered he who was asked, “and in matters of the spirit it is difficult for any one to take it more rigorously, more restrictedly, and more severely than I, except him from whom I learnt it, Zarathustra himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better know nothing than half-know many things! Better be a fool on one’s own account, than a sage on other people’s approbation! I—go to the basis:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—What matter if it be great or small? If it be called swamp or sky? A handbreadth of basis is enough for me, if it be actually basis and ground!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A handbreadth of basis: thereon can one stand. In the true knowing-knowledge there is nothing great and nothing small.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Then thou art perhaps an expert on the leech?” asked Zarathustra; “and thou investigatest the leech to its ultimate basis, thou conscientious one?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” answered the trodden one, “that would be something immense; how could I presume to do so!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That, however, of which I am master and knower, is the BRAIN of the leech:—that is MY world!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And it is also a world! Forgive it, however, that my pride here findeth expression, for here I have not mine equal. Therefore said I: ‘here am I at home.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How long have I investigated this one thing, the brain of the leech, so that here the slippery truth might no longer slip from me! Here is MY domain!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For the sake of this did I cast everything else aside, for the sake of this did everything else become indifferent to me; and close beside my knowledge lieth my black ignorance.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My spiritual conscience requireth from me that it should be so—that I should know one thing, and not know all else: they are a loathing unto me, all the semi-spiritual, all the hazy, hovering, and visionary.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where mine honesty ceaseth, there am I blind, and want also to be blind. Where I want to know, however, there want I also to be honest—namely, severe, rigorous, restricted, cruel and inexorable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Because THOU once saidest, O Zarathustra: ‘Spirit is life which itself cutteth into life’;—that led and allured me to thy doctrine. And verily, with mine own blood have I increased mine own knowledge!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“As the evidence indicateth,” broke in Zarathustra; for still was the blood flowing down on the naked arm of the conscientious one. For there had ten leeches bitten into it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O thou strange fellow, how much doth this very evidence teach me—namely, thou thyself! And not all, perhaps, might I pour into thy rigorous ear!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well then! We part here! But I would fain find thee again. Up thither is the way to my cave: to-night shalt thou there be my welcome guest!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Fain would I also make amends to thy body for Zarathustra treading upon thee with his feet: I think about that. Just now, however, a cry of distress calleth me hastily away from thee.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXV. THE MAGICIAN.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When however Zarathustra had gone round a rock, then saw he on the same path, not far below him, a man who threw his limbs about like a maniac, and at last tumbled to the ground on his belly. “Halt!” said then Zarathustra to his heart, “he there must surely be the higher man, from him came that dreadful cry of distress,—I will see if I can help him.” When, however, he ran to the spot where the man lay on the ground, he found a trembling old man, with fixed eyes; and in spite of all Zarathustra’s efforts to lift him and set him again on his feet, it was all in vain. The unfortunate one, also, did not seem to notice that some one was beside him; on the contrary, he continually looked around with moving gestures, like one forsaken and isolated from all the world. At last, however, after much trembling, and convulsion, and curling-himself-up, he began to lament thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">     Who warm’th me, who lov’th me still?\n<br>     Give ardent fingers!\n<br>     Give heartening charcoal-warmers!\n<br>     Prone, outstretched, trembling,\n<br>     Like him, half dead and cold, whose feet one warm’th—\n<br>     And shaken, ah! by unfamiliar fevers,\n<br>     Shivering with sharpened, icy-cold frost-arrows,\n<br>     By thee pursued, my fancy!\n<br>     Ineffable!  Recondite!  Sore-frightening!\n<br>     Thou huntsman ’hind the cloud-banks!\n<br>     Now lightning-struck by thee,\n<br>     Thou mocking eye that me in darkness watcheth:\n<br>     —Thus do I lie,\n<br>     Bend myself, twist myself, convulsed\n<br>     With all eternal torture,\n<br>     And smitten\n<br>     By thee, cruellest huntsman,\n<br>     Thou unfamiliar—GOD...\n<br>\n<br>     Smite deeper!\n<br>     Smite yet once more!\n<br>     Pierce through and rend my heart!\n<br>     What mean’th this torture\n<br>     With dull, indented arrows?\n<br>     Why look’st thou hither,\n<br>     Of human pain not weary,\n<br>     With mischief-loving, godly flash-glances?\n<br>     Not murder wilt thou,\n<br>     But torture, torture?\n<br>     For why—ME torture,\n<br>     Thou mischief-loving, unfamiliar God?—\n<br>\n<br>     Ha!  Ha!\n<br>     Thou stealest nigh\n<br>     In midnight’s gloomy hour?...\n<br>     What wilt thou?\n<br>     Speak!\n<br>     Thou crowdst me, pressest—\n<br>     Ha! now far too closely!\n<br>     Thou hearst me breathing,\n<br>     Thou o’erhearst my heart,\n<br>     Thou ever jealous one!\n<br>     —Of what, pray, ever jealous?\n<br>     Off!  Off!\n<br>     For why the ladder?\n<br>     Wouldst thou GET IN?\n<br>     To heart in-clamber?\n<br>     To mine own secretest\n<br>     Conceptions in-clamber?\n<br>     Shameless one!  Thou unknown one!—Thief!\n<br>     What seekst thou by thy stealing?\n<br>     What seekst thou by thy hearkening?\n<br>     What seekst thou by thy torturing?\n<br>     Thou torturer!\n<br>     Thou—hangman-God!\n<br>     Or shall I, as the mastiffs do,\n<br>     Roll me before thee?\n<br>     And cringing, enraptured, frantical,\n<br>     My tail friendly—waggle!\n<br>\n<br>     In vain!\n<br>     Goad further!\n<br>     Cruellest goader!\n<br>     No dog—thy game just am I,\n<br>     Cruellest huntsman!\n<br>     Thy proudest of captives,\n<br>     Thou robber ’hind the cloud-banks...\n<br>     Speak finally!\n<br>     Thou lightning-veiled one!  Thou unknown one!  Speak!\n<br>     What wilt thou, highway-ambusher, from—ME?\n<br>     What WILT thou, unfamiliar—God?\n<br>     What?\n<br>     Ransom-gold?\n<br>     How much of ransom-gold?\n<br>     Solicit much—that bid’th my pride!\n<br>     And be concise—that bid’th mine other pride!\n<br>\n<br>     Ha!  Ha!\n<br>     ME—wantst thou?  me?\n<br>     —Entire?...\n<br>\n<br>     Ha!  Ha!\n<br>     And torturest me, fool that thou art,\n<br>     Dead-torturest quite my pride?\n<br>     Give LOVE to me—who warm’th me still?\n<br>     Who lov’th me still?—\n<br>     Give ardent fingers,\n<br>     Give heartening charcoal-warmers,\n<br>     Give me, the lonesomest,\n<br>     The ice (ah! seven-fold frozen ice,\n<br>     For very enemies,\n<br>     For foes, doth make one thirst),\n<br>     Give, yield to me,\n<br>     Cruellest foe,\n<br>     —THYSELF!—\n<br>\n<br>     Away!\n<br>     There fled he surely,\n<br>     My final, only comrade,\n<br>     My greatest foe,\n<br>     Mine unfamiliar—\n<br>     My hangman-God!...\n<br>\n<br>     —Nay!\n<br>     Come thou back!\n<br>     WITH all of thy great tortures!\n<br>     To me the last of lonesome ones,\n<br>     Oh, come thou back!\n<br>     All my hot tears in streamlets trickle\n<br>     Their course to thee!\n<br>     And all my final hearty fervour—\n<br>     Up-glow’th to THEE!\n<br>     Oh, come thou back,\n<br>     Mine unfamiliar God! my PAIN!\n<br>     My final bliss!\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Here, however, Zarathustra could no longer restrain himself; he took his staff and struck the wailer with all his might. “Stop this,” cried he to him with wrathful laughter, “stop this, thou stage-player! Thou false coiner! Thou liar from the very heart! I know thee well!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I will soon make warm legs to thee, thou evil magician: I know well how—to make it hot for such as thou!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Leave off,” said the old man, and sprang up from the ground, “strike me no more, O Zarathustra! I did it only for amusement!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That kind of thing belongeth to mine art. Thee thyself, I wanted to put to the proof when I gave this performance. And verily, thou hast well detected me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But thou thyself—hast given me no small proof of thyself: thou art HARD, thou wise Zarathustra! Hard strikest thou with thy ‘truths,’ thy cudgel forceth from me—THIS truth!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Flatter not,” answered Zarathustra, still excited and frowning, “thou stage-player from the heart! Thou art false: why speakest thou—of truth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou peacock of peacocks, thou sea of vanity; WHAT didst thou represent before me, thou evil magician; WHOM was I meant to believe in when thou wailedst in such wise?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“THE PENITENT IN SPIRIT,” said the old man, “it was him—I represented; thou thyself once devisedst this expression—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The poet and magician who at last turneth his spirit against himself, the transformed one who freezeth to death by his bad science and conscience.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And just acknowledge it: it was long, O Zarathustra, before thou discoveredst my trick and lie! Thou BELIEVEDST in my distress when thou heldest my head with both thy hands,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—I heard thee lament ‘we have loved him too little, loved him too little!’ Because I so far deceived thee, my wickedness rejoiced in me.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou mayest have deceived subtler ones than I,” said Zarathustra sternly. “I am not on my guard against deceivers; I HAVE TO BE without precaution: so willeth my lot.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou, however,—MUST deceive: so far do I know thee! Thou must ever be equivocal, trivocal, quadrivocal, and quinquivocal! Even what thou hast now confessed, is not nearly true enough nor false enough for me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou bad false coiner, how couldst thou do otherwise! Thy very malady wouldst thou whitewash if thou showed thyself naked to thy physician.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus didst thou whitewash thy lie before me when thou saidst: ‘I did so ONLY for amusement!’ There was also SERIOUSNESS therein, thou ART something of a penitent-in-spirit!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I divine thee well: thou hast become the enchanter of all the world; but for thyself thou hast no lie or artifice left,—thou art disenchanted to thyself!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou hast reaped disgust as thy one truth. No word in thee is any longer genuine, but thy mouth is so: that is to say, the disgust that cleaveth unto thy mouth.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Who art thou at all!” cried here the old magician with defiant voice, “who dareth to speak thus unto ME, the greatest man now living?”—and a green flash shot from his eye at Zarathustra. But immediately after he changed, and said sadly:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra, I am weary of it, I am disgusted with mine arts, I am not GREAT, why do I dissemble! But thou knowest it well—I sought for greatness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A great man I wanted to appear, and persuaded many; but the lie hath been beyond my power. On it do I collapse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, everything is a lie in me; but that I collapse—this my collapsing is GENUINE!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“It honoureth thee,” said Zarathustra gloomily, looking down with sidelong glance, “it honoureth thee that thou soughtest for greatness, but it betrayeth thee also. Thou art not great.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou bad old magician, THAT is the best and the honestest thing I honour in thee, that thou hast become weary of thyself, and hast expressed it: ‘I am not great.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THEREIN do I honour thee as a penitent-in-spirit, and although only for the twinkling of an eye, in that one moment wast thou—genuine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But tell me, what seekest thou here in MY forests and rocks? And if thou hast put thyself in MY way, what proof of me wouldst thou have?—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Wherein didst thou put ME to the test?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and his eyes sparkled. But the old magician kept silence for a while; then said he: “Did I put thee to the test? I—seek only.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O Zarathustra, I seek a genuine one, a right one, a simple one, an unequivocal one, a man of perfect honesty, a vessel of wisdom, a saint of knowledge, a great man!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Knowest thou it not, O Zarathustra? I SEEK ZARATHUSTRA.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And here there arose a long silence between them: Zarathustra, however, became profoundly absorbed in thought, so that he shut his eyes. But afterwards coming back to the situation, he grasped the hand of the magician, and said, full of politeness and policy:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Well! Up thither leadeth the way, there is the cave of Zarathustra. In it mayest thou seek him whom thou wouldst fain find.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ask counsel of mine animals, mine eagle and my serpent: they shall help thee to seek. My cave however is large.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I myself, to be sure—I have as yet seen no great man. That which is great, the acutest eye is at present insensible to it. It is the kingdom of the populace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many a one have I found who stretched and inflated himself, and the people cried: ‘Behold; a great man!’ But what good do all bellows do! The wind cometh out at last.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At last bursteth the frog which hath inflated itself too long: then cometh out the wind. To prick a swollen one in the belly, I call good pastime. Hear that, ye boys!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Our to-day is of the populace: who still KNOWETH what is great and what is small! Who could there seek successfully for greatness! A fool only: it succeedeth with fools.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou seekest for great men, thou strange fool? Who TAUGHT that to thee? Is to-day the time for it? Oh, thou bad seeker, why dost thou—tempt me?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, comforted in his heart, and went laughing on his way.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXVI. OUT OF SERVICE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not long, however, after Zarathustra had freed himself from the magician, he again saw a person sitting beside the path which he followed, namely a tall, black man, with a haggard, pale countenance: THIS MAN grieved him exceedingly. “Alas,” said he to his heart, “there sitteth disguised affliction; methinketh he is of the type of the priests: what do THEY want in my domain?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What! Hardly have I escaped from that magician, and must another necromancer again run across my path,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Some sorcerer with laying-on-of-hands, some sombre wonder-worker by the grace of God, some anointed world-maligner, whom, may the devil take!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But the devil is never at the place which would be his right place: he always cometh too late, that cursed dwarf and club-foot!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus cursed Zarathustra impatiently in his heart, and considered how with averted look he might slip past the black man. But behold, it came about otherwise. For at the same moment had the sitting one already perceived him; and not unlike one whom an unexpected happiness overtaketh, he sprang to his feet, and went straight towards Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Whoever thou art, thou traveller,” said he, “help a strayed one, a seeker, an old man, who may here easily come to grief!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The world here is strange to me, and remote; wild beasts also did I hear howling; and he who could have given me protection—he is himself no more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I was seeking the pious man, a saint and an anchorite, who, alone in his forest, had not yet heard of what all the world knoweth at present.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“WHAT doth all the world know at present?” asked Zarathustra. “Perhaps that the old God no longer liveth, in whom all the world once believed?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou sayest it,” answered the old man sorrowfully. “And I served that old God until his last hour.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, however, am I out of service, without master, and yet not free; likewise am I no longer merry even for an hour, except it be in recollections.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Therefore did I ascend into these mountains, that I might finally have a festival for myself once more, as becometh an old pope and church-father: for know it, that I am the last pope!—a festival of pious recollections and divine services.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, however, is he himself dead, the most pious of men, the saint in the forest, who praised his God constantly with singing and mumbling.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He himself found I no longer when I found his cot—but two wolves found I therein, which howled on account of his death,—for all animals loved him. Then did I haste away.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Had I thus come in vain into these forests and mountains? Then did my heart determine that I should seek another, the most pious of all those who believe not in God—, my heart determined that I should seek Zarathustra!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the hoary man, and gazed with keen eyes at him who stood before him. Zarathustra however seized the hand of the old pope and regarded it a long while with admiration.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Lo! thou venerable one,” said he then, “what a fine and long hand! That is the hand of one who hath ever dispensed blessings. Now, however, doth it hold fast him whom thou seekest, me, Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is I, the ungodly Zarathustra, who saith: ‘Who is ungodlier than I, that I may enjoy his teaching?’”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and penetrated with his glances the thoughts and arrear-thoughts of the old pope. At last the latter began:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“He who most loved and possessed him hath now also lost him most—:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Lo, I myself am surely the most godless of us at present? But who could rejoice at that!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Thou servedst him to the last?” asked Zarathustra thoughtfully, after a deep silence, “thou knowest HOW he died? Is it true what they say, that sympathy choked him;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—That he saw how MAN hung on the cross, and could not endure it;—that his love to man became his hell, and at last his death?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The old pope however did not answer, but looked aside timidly, with a painful and gloomy expression.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Let him go,” said Zarathustra, after prolonged meditation, still looking the old man straight in the eye.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Let him go, he is gone. And though it honoureth thee that thou speakest only in praise of this dead one, yet thou knowest as well as I WHO he was, and that he went curious ways.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“To speak before three eyes,” said the old pope cheerfully (he was blind of one eye), “in divine matters I am more enlightened than Zarathustra himself—and may well be so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My love served him long years, my will followed all his will. A good servant, however, knoweth everything, and many a thing even which a master hideth from himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He was a hidden God, full of secrecy. Verily, he did not come by his son otherwise than by secret ways. At the door of his faith standeth adultery.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whoever extolleth him as a God of love, doth not think highly enough of love itself. Did not that God want also to be judge? But the loving one loveth irrespective of reward and requital.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When he was young, that God out of the Orient, then was he harsh and revengeful, and built himself a hell for the delight of his favourites.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At last, however, he became old and soft and mellow and pitiful, more like a grandfather than a father, but most like a tottering old grandmother.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There did he sit shrivelled in his chimney-corner, fretting on account of his weak legs, world-weary, will-weary, and one day he suffocated of his all-too-great pity.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou old pope,” said here Zarathustra interposing, “hast thou seen THAT with thine eyes? It could well have happened in that way: in that way, AND also otherwise. When Gods die they always die many kinds of death.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! At all events, one way or other—he is gone! He was counter to the taste of mine ears and eyes; worse than that I should not like to say against him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love everything that looketh bright and speaketh honestly. But he—thou knowest it, forsooth, thou old priest, there was something of thy type in him, the priest-type—he was equivocal.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He was also indistinct. How he raged at us, this wrath-snorter, because we understood him badly! But why did he not speak more clearly?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if the fault lay in our ears, why did he give us ears that heard him badly? If there was dirt in our ears, well! who put it in them?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too much miscarried with him, this potter who had not learned thoroughly! That he took revenge on his pots and creations, however, because they turned out badly—that was a sin against GOOD TASTE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is also good taste in piety: THIS at last said: ‘Away with SUCH a God! Better to have no God, better to set up destiny on one’s own account, better to be a fool, better to be God oneself!’”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“What do I hear!” said then the old pope, with intent ears; “O Zarathustra, thou art more pious than thou believest, with such an unbelief! Some God in thee hath converted thee to thine ungodliness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is it not thy piety itself which no longer letteth thee believe in a God? And thine over-great honesty will yet lead thee even beyond good and evil!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behold, what hath been reserved for thee? Thou hast eyes and hands and mouth, which have been predestined for blessing from eternity. One doth not bless with the hand alone.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nigh unto thee, though thou professest to be the ungodliest one, I feel a hale and holy odour of long benedictions: I feel glad and grieved thereby.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Let me be thy guest, O Zarathustra, for a single night! Nowhere on earth shall I now feel better than with thee!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Amen! So shall it be!” said Zarathustra, with great astonishment; “up thither leadeth the way, there lieth the cave of Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gladly, forsooth, would I conduct thee thither myself, thou venerable one; for I love all pious men. But now a cry of distress calleth me hastily away from thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In my domain shall no one come to grief; my cave is a good haven. And best of all would I like to put every sorrowful one again on firm land and firm legs.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Who, however, could take THY melancholy off thy shoulders? For that I am too weak. Long, verily, should we have to wait until some one re-awoke thy God for thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For that old God liveth no more: he is indeed dead.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXVII. THE UGLIEST MAN.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And again did Zarathustra’s feet run through mountains and forests, and his eyes sought and sought, but nowhere was he to be seen whom they wanted to see—the sorely distressed sufferer and crier. On the whole way, however, he rejoiced in his heart and was full of gratitude. “What good things,” said he, “hath this day given me, as amends for its bad beginning! What strange interlocutors have I found!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At their words will I now chew a long while as at good corn; small shall my teeth grind and crush them, until they flow like milk into my soul!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When, however, the path again curved round a rock, all at once the landscape changed, and Zarathustra entered into a realm of death. Here bristled aloft black and red cliffs, without any grass, tree, or bird’s voice. For it was a valley which all animals avoided, even the beasts of prey, except that a species of ugly, thick, green serpent came here to die when they became old. Therefore the shepherds called this valley: “Serpent-death.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra, however, became absorbed in dark recollections, for it seemed to him as if he had once before stood in this valley. And much heaviness settled on his mind, so that he walked slowly and always more slowly, and at last stood still. Then, however, when he opened his eyes, he saw something sitting by the wayside shaped like a man, and hardly like a man, something nondescript. And all at once there came over Zarathustra a great shame, because he had gazed on such a thing. Blushing up to the very roots of his white hair, he turned aside his glance, and raised his foot that he might leave this ill-starred place. Then, however, became the dead wilderness vocal: for from the ground a noise welled up, gurgling and rattling, as water gurgleth and rattleth at night through stopped-up water-pipes; and at last it turned into human voice and human speech:—it sounded thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Zarathustra! Zarathustra! Read my riddle! Say, say! WHAT IS THE REVENGE ON THE WITNESS?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I entice thee back; here is smooth ice! See to it, see to it, that thy pride doth not here break its legs!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003388",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou thinkest thyself wise, thou proud Zarathustra! Read then the riddle, thou hard nut-cracker,—the riddle that I am! Say then: who am <i>I</i>!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003389": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003389",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When however Zarathustra had heard these words,—what think ye then took place in his soul? PITY OVERCAME HIM; and he sank down all at once, like an oak that hath long withstood many tree-fellers,—heavily, suddenly, to the terror even of those who meant to fell it. But immediately he got up again from the ground, and his countenance became stern.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003390": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003390",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I know thee well,” said he, with a brazen voice, “THOU ART THE MURDERER OF GOD! Let me go.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003391": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003391",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou couldst not ENDURE him who beheld THEE,—who ever beheld thee through and through, thou ugliest man. Thou tookest revenge on this witness!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003392": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003392",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra and was about to go; but the nondescript grasped at a corner of his garment and began anew to gurgle and seek for words. “Stay,” said he at last—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003393": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003393",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Stay! Do not pass by! I have divined what axe it was that struck thee to the ground: hail to thee, O Zarathustra, that thou art again upon thy feet!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003394": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003394",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou hast divined, I know it well, how the man feeleth who killed him,—the murderer of God. Stay! Sit down here beside me; it is not to no purpose.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003395": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003395",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To whom would I go but unto thee? Stay, sit down! Do not however look at me! Honour thus—mine ugliness!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003396": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003396",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They persecute me: now art THOU my last refuge. NOT with their hatred, NOT with their bailiffs;—Oh, such persecution would I mock at, and be proud and cheerful!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003397": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003397",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hath not all success hitherto been with the well-persecuted ones? And he who persecuteth well learneth readily to be OBSEQUENT—when once he is—put behind! But it is their PITY—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003398": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003398",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Their pity is it from which I flee away and flee to thee. O Zarathustra, protect me, thou, my last refuge, thou sole one who divinedst me:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003399": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003399",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thou hast divined how the man feeleth who killed HIM. Stay! And if thou wilt go, thou impatient one, go not the way that I came. THAT way is bad.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003400": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003400",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Art thou angry with me because I have already racked language too long? Because I have already counselled thee? But know that it is I, the ugliest man,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003401": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003401",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Who have also the largest, heaviest feet. Where <i>I</i> have gone, the way is bad. I tread all paths to death and destruction.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003402": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003402",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But that thou passedst me by in silence, that thou blushedst—I saw it well: thereby did I know thee as Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003403": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003403",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every one else would have thrown to me his alms, his pity, in look and speech. But for that—I am not beggar enough: that didst thou divine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003404": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003404",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For that I am too RICH, rich in what is great, frightful, ugliest, most unutterable! Thy shame, O Zarathustra, HONOURED me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003405": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003405",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With difficulty did I get out of the crowd of the pitiful,—that I might find the only one who at present teacheth that ‘pity is obtrusive’— thyself, O Zarathustra!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003406": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003406",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Whether it be the pity of a God, or whether it be human pity, it is offensive to modesty. And unwillingness to help may be nobler than the virtue that rusheth to do so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003407": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003407",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THAT however—namely, pity—is called virtue itself at present by all petty people:—they have no reverence for great misfortune, great ugliness, great failure.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003408": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003408",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beyond all these do I look, as a dog looketh over the backs of thronging flocks of sheep. They are petty, good-wooled, good-willed, grey people.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003409": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003409",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As the heron looketh contemptuously at shallow pools, with backward-bent head, so do I look at the throng of grey little waves and wills and souls.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003410": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003410",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too long have we acknowledged them to be right, those petty people: SO we have at last given them power as well;—and now do they teach that ‘good is only what petty people call good.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003411": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003411",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And ‘truth’ is at present what the preacher spake who himself sprang from them, that singular saint and advocate of the petty people, who testified of himself: ‘I—am the truth.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003412": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003412",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That immodest one hath long made the petty people greatly puffed up,—he who taught no small error when he taught: ‘I—am the truth.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003413": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003413",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hath an immodest one ever been answered more courteously?—Thou, however, O Zarathustra, passedst him by, and saidst: ‘Nay! Nay! Three times Nay!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003414": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003414",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou warnedst against his error; thou warnedst—the first to do so—against pity:—not every one, not none, but thyself and thy type.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003415": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003415",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou art ashamed of the shame of the great sufferer; and verily when thou sayest: ‘From pity there cometh a heavy cloud; take heed, ye men!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003416": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003416",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When thou teachest: ‘All creators are hard, all great love is beyond their pity:’ O Zarathustra, how well versed dost thou seem to me in weather-signs!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003417": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003417",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou thyself, however,—warn thyself also against THY pity! For many are on their way to thee, many suffering, doubting, despairing, drowning, freezing ones—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003418": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003418",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I warn thee also against myself. Thou hast read my best, my worst riddle, myself, and what I have done. I know the axe that felleth thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003419": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003419",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But he—HAD TO die: he looked with eyes which beheld EVERYTHING,—he beheld men’s depths and dregs, all his hidden ignominy and ugliness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003420": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003420",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His pity knew no modesty: he crept into my dirtiest corners. This most prying, over-intrusive, over-pitiful one had to die.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003421": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003421",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He ever beheld ME: on such a witness I would have revenge—or not live myself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003422": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003422",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The God who beheld everything, AND ALSO MAN: that God had to die! Man cannot ENDURE it that such a witness should live.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003423": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003423",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the ugliest man. Zarathustra however got up, and prepared to go on: for he felt frozen to the very bowels.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003424": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003424",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou nondescript,” said he, “thou warnedst me against thy path. As thanks for it I praise mine to thee. Behold, up thither is the cave of Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003425": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003425",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My cave is large and deep and hath many corners; there findeth he that is most hidden his hiding-place. And close beside it, there are a hundred lurking-places and by-places for creeping, fluttering, and hopping creatures.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003426": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003426",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou outcast, who hast cast thyself out, thou wilt not live amongst men and men’s pity? Well then, do like me! Thus wilt thou learn also from me; only the doer learneth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003427": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003427",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And talk first and foremost to mine animals! The proudest animal and the wisest animal—they might well be the right counsellors for us both!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003428": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003428",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra and went his way, more thoughtfully and slowly even than before: for he asked himself many things, and hardly knew what to answer.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003429": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003429",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“How poor indeed is man,” thought he in his heart, “how ugly, how wheezy, how full of hidden shame!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003430": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003430",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They tell me that man loveth himself. Ah, how great must that self-love be! How much contempt is opposed to it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003431": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003431",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Even this man hath loved himself, as he hath despised himself,—a great lover methinketh he is, and a great despiser.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003432": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003432",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No one have I yet found who more thoroughly despised himself: even THAT is elevation. Alas, was THIS perhaps the higher man whose cry I heard?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003433": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003433",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I love the great despisers. Man is something that hath to be surpassed.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003434": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003434",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003435": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003435",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003436": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003436",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXVIII. THE VOLUNTARY BEGGAR.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003437": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003437",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra had left the ugliest man, he was chilled and felt lonesome: for much coldness and lonesomeness came over his spirit, so that even his limbs became colder thereby. When, however, he wandered on and on, uphill and down, at times past green meadows, though also sometimes over wild stony couches where formerly perhaps an impatient brook had made its bed, then he turned all at once warmer and heartier again.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003438": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003438",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What hath happened unto me?” he asked himself, “something warm and living quickeneth me; it must be in the neighbourhood.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003439": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003439",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Already am I less alone; unconscious companions and brethren rove around me; their warm breath toucheth my soul.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003440": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003440",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When, however, he spied about and sought for the comforters of his lonesomeness, behold, there were kine there standing together on an eminence, whose proximity and smell had warmed his heart. The kine, however, seemed to listen eagerly to a speaker, and took no heed of him who approached. When, however, Zarathustra was quite nigh unto them, then did he hear plainly that a human voice spake in the midst of the kine, and apparently all of them had turned their heads towards the speaker.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003441": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003441",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then ran Zarathustra up speedily and drove the animals aside; for he feared that some one had here met with harm, which the pity of the kine would hardly be able to relieve. But in this he was deceived; for behold, there sat a man on the ground who seemed to be persuading the animals to have no fear of him, a peaceable man and Preacher-on-the-Mount, out of whose eyes kindness itself preached. “What dost thou seek here?” called out Zarathustra in astonishment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003442": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003442",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What do I here seek?” answered he: “the same that thou seekest, thou mischief-maker; that is to say, happiness upon earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003443": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003443",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To that end, however, I would fain learn of these kine. For I tell thee that I have already talked half a morning unto them, and just now were they about to give me their answer. Why dost thou disturb them?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003444": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003444",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Except we be converted and become as kine, we shall in no wise enter into the kingdom of heaven. For we ought to learn from them one thing: ruminating.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003445": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003445",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, although a man should gain the whole world, and yet not learn one thing, ruminating, what would it profit him! He would not be rid of his affliction,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003446": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003446",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—His great affliction: that, however, is at present called DISGUST. Who hath not at present his heart, his mouth and his eyes full of disgust? Thou also! Thou also! But behold these kine!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003447": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003447",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the Preacher-on-the-Mount, and turned then his own look towards Zarathustra—for hitherto it had rested lovingly on the kine—: then, however, he put on a different expression. “Who is this with whom I talk?” he exclaimed frightened, and sprang up from the ground.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003448": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003448",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“This is the man without disgust, this is Zarathustra himself, the surmounter of the great disgust, this is the eye, this is the mouth, this is the heart of Zarathustra himself.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003449": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003449",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And whilst he thus spake he kissed with o’erflowing eyes the hands of him with whom he spake, and behaved altogether like one to whom a precious gift and jewel hath fallen unawares from heaven. The kine, however, gazed at it all and wondered.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003450": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003450",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Speak not of me, thou strange one; thou amiable one!” said Zarathustra, and restrained his affection, “speak to me firstly of thyself! Art thou not the voluntary beggar who once cast away great riches,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003451": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003451",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Who was ashamed of his riches and of the rich, and fled to the poorest to bestow upon them his abundance and his heart? But they received him not.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003452": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003452",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“But they received me not,” said the voluntary beggar, “thou knowest it, forsooth. So I went at last to the animals and to those kine.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003453": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003453",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Then learnedst thou,” interrupted Zarathustra, “how much harder it is to give properly than to take properly, and that bestowing well is an ART—the last, subtlest master-art of kindness.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003454": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003454",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Especially nowadays,” answered the voluntary beggar: “at present, that is to say, when everything low hath become rebellious and exclusive and haughty in its manner—in the manner of the populace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003455": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003455",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For the hour hath come, thou knowest it forsooth, for the great, evil, long, slow mob-and-slave-insurrection: it extendeth and extendeth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003456": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003456",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now doth it provoke the lower classes, all benevolence and petty giving; and the overrich may be on their guard!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003457": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003457",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whoever at present drip, like bulgy bottles out of all-too-small necks:—of such bottles at present one willingly breaketh the necks.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003458": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003458",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Wanton avidity, bilious envy, careworn revenge, populace-pride: all these struck mine eye. It is no longer true that the poor are blessed. The kingdom of heaven, however, is with the kine.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003459": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003459",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“And why is it not with the rich?” asked Zarathustra temptingly, while he kept back the kine which sniffed familiarly at the peaceful one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003460": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003460",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Why dost thou tempt me?” answered the other. “Thou knowest it thyself better even than I. What was it drove me to the poorest, O Zarathustra? Was it not my disgust at the richest?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003461": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003461",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—At the culprits of riches, with cold eyes and rank thoughts, who pick up profit out of all kinds of rubbish—at this rabble that stinketh to heaven,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003462": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003462",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—At this gilded, falsified populace, whose fathers were pickpockets, or carrion-crows, or rag-pickers, with wives compliant, lewd and forgetful:—for they are all of them not far different from harlots—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003463": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003463",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Populace above, populace below! What are ‘poor’ and ‘rich’ at present! That distinction did I unlearn,—then did I flee away further and ever further, until I came to those kine.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003464": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003464",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the peaceful one, and puffed himself and perspired with his words: so that the kine wondered anew. Zarathustra, however, kept looking into his face with a smile, all the time the man talked so severely—and shook silently his head.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003465": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003465",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou doest violence to thyself, thou Preacher-on-the-Mount, when thou usest such severe words. For such severity neither thy mouth nor thine eye have been given thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003466": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003466",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nor, methinketh, hath thy stomach either: unto IT all such rage and hatred and foaming-over is repugnant. Thy stomach wanteth softer things: thou art not a butcher.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003467": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003467",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Rather seemest thou to me a plant-eater and a root-man. Perhaps thou grindest corn. Certainly, however, thou art averse to fleshly joys, and thou lovest honey.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003468": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003468",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou hast divined me well,” answered the voluntary beggar, with lightened heart. “I love honey, I also grind corn; for I have sought out what tasteth sweetly and maketh pure breath:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003469": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003469",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Also what requireth a long time, a day’s-work and a mouth’s-work for gentle idlers and sluggards.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003470": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003470",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Furthest, to be sure, have those kine carried it: they have devised ruminating and lying in the sun. They also abstain from all heavy thoughts which inflate the heart.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003471": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003471",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“Well!” said Zarathustra, “thou shouldst also see MINE animals, mine eagle and my serpent,—their like do not at present exist on earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003472": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003472",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Behold, thither leadeth the way to my cave: be to-night its guest. And talk to mine animals of the happiness of animals,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003473": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003473",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Until I myself come home. For now a cry of distress calleth me hastily away from thee. Also, shouldst thou find new honey with me, ice-cold, golden-comb-honey, eat it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003474": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003474",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, however, take leave at once of thy kine, thou strange one! thou amiable one! though it be hard for thee. For they are thy warmest friends and preceptors!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003475": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003475",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“One excepted, whom I hold still dearer,” answered the voluntary beggar. “Thou thyself art good, O Zarathustra, and better even than a cow!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003476": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003476",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Away, away with thee! thou evil flatterer!” cried Zarathustra mischievously, “why dost thou spoil me with such praise and flattery-honey?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003477": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003477",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Away, away from me!” cried he once more, and heaved his stick at the fond beggar, who, however, ran nimbly away.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003478": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003478",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003479": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003479",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003480": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003480",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXIX. THE SHADOW.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003481": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003481",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Scarcely however was the voluntary beggar gone in haste, and Zarathustra again alone, when he heard behind him a new voice which called out: “Stay! Zarathustra! Do wait! It is myself, forsooth, O Zarathustra, myself, thy shadow!” But Zarathustra did not wait; for a sudden irritation came over him on account of the crowd and the crowding in his mountains. “Whither hath my lonesomeness gone?” spake he.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003482": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003482",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“It is verily becoming too much for me; these mountains swarm; my kingdom is no longer of THIS world; I require new mountains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003483": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003483",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My shadow calleth me? What matter about my shadow! Let it run after me! I—run away from it.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003484": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003484",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra to his heart and ran away. But the one behind followed after him, so that immediately there were three runners, one after the other—namely, foremost the voluntary beggar, then Zarathustra, and thirdly, and hindmost, his shadow. But not long had they run thus when Zarathustra became conscious of his folly, and shook off with one jerk all his irritation and detestation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003485": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003485",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What!” said he, “have not the most ludicrous things always happened to us old anchorites and saints?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003486": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003486",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Verily, my folly hath grown big in the mountains! Now do I hear six old fools’ legs rattling behind one another!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003487": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003487",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But doth Zarathustra need to be frightened by his shadow? Also, methinketh that after all it hath longer legs than mine.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003488": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003488",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and, laughing with eyes and entrails, he stood still and turned round quickly—and behold, he almost thereby threw his shadow and follower to the ground, so closely had the latter followed at his heels, and so weak was he. For when Zarathustra scrutinised him with his glance he was frightened as by a sudden apparition, so slender, swarthy, hollow and worn-out did this follower appear.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003489": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003489",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Who art thou?” asked Zarathustra vehemently, “what doest thou here? And why callest thou thyself my shadow? Thou art not pleasing unto me.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003490": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003490",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Forgive me,” answered the shadow, “that it is I; and if I please thee not—well, O Zarathustra! therein do I admire thee and thy good taste.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003491": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003491",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A wanderer am I, who have walked long at thy heels; always on the way, but without a goal, also without a home: so that verily, I lack little of being the eternally Wandering Jew, except that I am not eternal and not a Jew.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003492": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003492",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What? Must I ever be on the way? Whirled by every wind, unsettled, driven about? O earth, thou hast become too round for me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003493": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003493",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On every surface have I already sat, like tired dust have I fallen asleep on mirrors and window-panes: everything taketh from me, nothing giveth; I become thin—I am almost equal to a shadow.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003494": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003494",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>After thee, however, O Zarathustra, did I fly and hie longest; and though I hid myself from thee, I was nevertheless thy best shadow: wherever thou hast sat, there sat I also.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003495": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003495",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thee have I wandered about in the remotest, coldest worlds, like a phantom that voluntarily haunteth winter roofs and snows.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003496": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003496",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thee have I pushed into all the forbidden, all the worst and the furthest: and if there be anything of virtue in me, it is that I have had no fear of any prohibition.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003497": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003497",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thee have I broken up whatever my heart revered; all boundary-stones and statues have I o’erthrown; the most dangerous wishes did I pursue,—verily, beyond every crime did I once go.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003498": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003498",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With thee did I unlearn the belief in words and worths and in great names. When the devil casteth his skin, doth not his name also fall away? It is also skin. The devil himself is perhaps—skin.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003499": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003499",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Nothing is true, all is permitted’: so said I to myself. Into the coldest water did I plunge with head and heart. Ah, how oft did I stand there naked on that account, like a red crab!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003500": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003500",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah, where have gone all my goodness and all my shame and all my belief in the good! Ah, where is the lying innocence which I once possessed, the innocence of the good and of their noble lies!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003501": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003501",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too oft, verily, did I follow close to the heels of truth: then did it kick me on the face. Sometimes I meant to lie, and behold! then only did I hit—the truth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003502": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003502",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Too much hath become clear unto me: now it doth not concern me any more. Nothing liveth any longer that I love,—how should I still love myself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003503": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003503",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘To live as I incline, or not to live at all’: so do I wish; so wisheth also the holiest. But alas! how have <i>I</i> still—inclination?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003504": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003504",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have <i>I</i>—still a goal? A haven towards which MY sail is set?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003505": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003505",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A good wind? Ah, he only who knoweth WHITHER he saileth, knoweth what wind is good, and a fair wind for him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003506": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003506",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What still remaineth to me? A heart weary and flippant; an unstable will; fluttering wings; a broken backbone.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003507": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003507",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This seeking for MY home: O Zarathustra, dost thou know that this seeking hath been MY home-sickening; it eateth me up.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003508": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003508",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘WHERE is—MY home?’ For it do I ask and seek, and have sought, but have not found it. O eternal everywhere, O eternal nowhere, O eternal—in-vain!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003509": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003509",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the shadow, and Zarathustra’s countenance lengthened at his words. “Thou art my shadow!” said he at last sadly.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003510": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003510",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thy danger is not small, thou free spirit and wanderer! Thou hast had a bad day: see that a still worse evening doth not overtake thee!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003511": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003511",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To such unsettled ones as thou, seemeth at last even a prisoner blessed. Didst thou ever see how captured criminals sleep? They sleep quietly, they enjoy their new security.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003512": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003512",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Beware lest in the end a narrow faith capture thee, a hard, rigorous delusion! For now everything that is narrow and fixed seduceth and tempteth thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003513": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003513",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou hast lost thy goal. Alas, how wilt thou forego and forget that loss? Thereby—hast thou also lost thy way!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003514": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003514",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou poor rover and rambler, thou tired butterfly! wilt thou have a rest and a home this evening? Then go up to my cave!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003515": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003515",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thither leadeth the way to my cave. And now will I run quickly away from thee again. Already lieth as it were a shadow upon me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003516": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003516",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I will run alone, so that it may again become bright around me. Therefore must I still be a long time merrily upon my legs. In the evening, however, there will be—dancing with me!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003517": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003517",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003518": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003518",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003519": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003519",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003520": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003520",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXX. NOONTIDE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003521": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003521",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And Zarathustra ran and ran, but he found no one else, and was alone and ever found himself again; he enjoyed and quaffed his solitude, and thought of good things—for hours. About the hour of noontide, however, when the sun stood exactly over Zarathustra’s head, he passed an old, bent and gnarled tree, which was encircled round by the ardent love of a vine, and hidden from itself; from this there hung yellow grapes in abundance, confronting the wanderer. Then he felt inclined to quench a little thirst, and to break off for himself a cluster of grapes. When, however, he had already his arm out-stretched for that purpose, he felt still more inclined for something else—namely, to lie down beside the tree at the hour of perfect noontide and sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003522": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003522",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This Zarathustra did; and no sooner had he laid himself on the ground in the stillness and secrecy of the variegated grass, than he had forgotten his little thirst, and fell asleep. For as the proverb of Zarathustra saith: “One thing is more necessary than the other.” Only that his eyes remained open:—for they never grew weary of viewing and admiring the tree and the love of the vine. In falling asleep, however, Zarathustra spake thus to his heart:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003523": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003523",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Hush! Hush! Hath not the world now become perfect? What hath happened unto me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003524": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003524",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As a delicate wind danceth invisibly upon parqueted seas, light, feather-light, so—danceth sleep upon me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003525": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003525",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>No eye doth it close to me, it leaveth my soul awake. Light is it, verily, feather-light.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003526": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003526",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It persuadeth me, I know not how, it toucheth me inwardly with a caressing hand, it constraineth me. Yea, it constraineth me, so that my soul stretcheth itself out:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003527": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003527",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—How long and weary it becometh, my strange soul! Hath a seventh-day evening come to it precisely at noontide? Hath it already wandered too long, blissfully, among good and ripe things?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003528": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003528",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It stretcheth itself out, long—longer! it lieth still, my strange soul. Too many good things hath it already tasted; this golden sadness oppresseth it, it distorteth its mouth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003529": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003529",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As a ship that putteth into the calmest cove:—it now draweth up to the land, weary of long voyages and uncertain seas. Is not the land more faithful?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003530": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003530",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As such a ship huggeth the shore, tuggeth the shore:—then it sufficeth for a spider to spin its thread from the ship to the land. No stronger ropes are required there.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003531": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003531",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As such a weary ship in the calmest cove, so do I also now repose, nigh to the earth, faithful, trusting, waiting, bound to it with the lightest threads.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003532": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003532",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O happiness! O happiness! Wilt thou perhaps sing, O my soul? Thou liest in the grass. But this is the secret, solemn hour, when no shepherd playeth his pipe.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003533": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003533",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Take care! Hot noontide sleepeth on the fields. Do not sing! Hush! The world is perfect.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003534": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003534",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do not sing, thou prairie-bird, my soul! Do not even whisper! Lo—hush! The old noontide sleepeth, it moveth its mouth: doth it not just now drink a drop of happiness—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003535": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003535",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—An old brown drop of golden happiness, golden wine? Something whisketh over it, its happiness laugheth. Thus—laugheth a God. Hush!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003536": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003536",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—‘For happiness, how little sufficeth for happiness!’ Thus spake I once and thought myself wise. But it was a blasphemy: THAT have I now learned. Wise fools speak better.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003537": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003537",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The least thing precisely, the gentlest thing, the lightest thing, a lizard’s rustling, a breath, a whisk, an eye-glance—LITTLE maketh up the BEST happiness. Hush!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003538": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003538",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—What hath befallen me: Hark! Hath time flown away? Do I not fall? Have I not fallen—hark! into the well of eternity?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003539": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003539",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—What happeneth to me? Hush! It stingeth me—alas—to the heart? To the heart! Oh, break up, break up, my heart, after such happiness, after such a sting!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003540": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003540",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—What? Hath not the world just now become perfect? Round and ripe? Oh, for the golden round ring—whither doth it fly? Let me run after it! Quick!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003541": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003541",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hush—” (and here Zarathustra stretched himself, and felt that he was asleep.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003542": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003542",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Up!” said he to himself, “thou sleeper! Thou noontide sleeper! Well then, up, ye old legs! It is time and more than time; many a good stretch of road is still awaiting you—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003543": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003543",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now have ye slept your fill; for how long a time? A half-eternity! Well then, up now, mine old heart! For how long after such a sleep mayest thou—remain awake?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003544": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003544",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(But then did he fall asleep anew, and his soul spake against him and defended itself, and lay down again)—“Leave me alone! Hush! Hath not the world just now become perfect? Oh, for the golden round ball!—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003545": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003545",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Get up,” said Zarathustra, “thou little thief, thou sluggard! What! Still stretching thyself, yawning, sighing, falling into deep wells?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003546": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003546",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Who art thou then, O my soul!” (and here he became frightened, for a sunbeam shot down from heaven upon his face.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003547": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003547",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O heaven above me,” said he sighing, and sat upright, “thou gazest at me? Thou hearkenest unto my strange soul?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003548": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003548",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When wilt thou drink this drop of dew that fell down upon all earthly things,—when wilt thou drink this strange soul—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003549": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003549",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—When, thou well of eternity! thou joyous, awful, noontide abyss! when wilt thou drink my soul back into thee?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003550": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003550",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and rose from his couch beside the tree, as if awakening from a strange drunkenness: and behold! there stood the sun still exactly above his head. One might, however, rightly infer therefrom that Zarathustra had not then slept long.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003551": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003551",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003552": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003552",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003553": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003553",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXI. THE GREETING.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003554": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003554",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It was late in the afternoon only when Zarathustra, after long useless searching and strolling about, again came home to his cave. When, however, he stood over against it, not more than twenty paces therefrom, the thing happened which he now least of all expected: he heard anew the great CRY OF DISTRESS. And extraordinary! this time the cry came out of his own cave. It was a long, manifold, peculiar cry, and Zarathustra plainly distinguished that it was composed of many voices: although heard at a distance it might sound like the cry out of a single mouth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003555": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003555",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thereupon Zarathustra rushed forward to his cave, and behold! what a spectacle awaited him after that concert! For there did they all sit together whom he had passed during the day: the king on the right and the king on the left, the old magician, the pope, the voluntary beggar, the shadow, the intellectually conscientious one, the sorrowful soothsayer, and the ass; the ugliest man, however, had set a crown on his head, and had put round him two purple girdles,—for he liked, like all ugly ones, to disguise himself and play the handsome person. In the midst, however, of that sorrowful company stood Zarathustra’s eagle, ruffled and disquieted, for it had been called upon to answer too much for which its pride had not any answer; the wise serpent however hung round its neck.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003556": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003556",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All this did Zarathustra behold with great astonishment; then however he scrutinised each individual guest with courteous curiosity, read their souls and wondered anew. In the meantime the assembled ones had risen from their seats, and waited with reverence for Zarathustra to speak. Zarathustra however spake thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003557": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003557",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ye despairing ones! Ye strange ones! So it was YOUR cry of distress that I heard? And now do I know also where he is to be sought, whom I have sought for in vain to-day: THE HIGHER MAN—:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003558": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003558",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—In mine own cave sitteth he, the higher man! But why do I wonder! Have not I myself allured him to me by honey-offerings and artful lure-calls of my happiness?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003559": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003559",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But it seemeth to me that ye are badly adapted for company: ye make one another’s hearts fretful, ye that cry for help, when ye sit here together? There is one that must first come,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003560": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003560",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—One who will make you laugh once more, a good jovial buffoon, a dancer, a wind, a wild romp, some old fool:—what think ye?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003561": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003561",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Forgive me, however, ye despairing ones, for speaking such trivial words before you, unworthy, verily, of such guests! But ye do not divine WHAT maketh my heart wanton:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003562": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003562",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ye yourselves do it, and your aspect, forgive it me! For every one becometh courageous who beholdeth a despairing one. To encourage a despairing one—every one thinketh himself strong enough to do so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003563": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003563",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To myself have ye given this power,—a good gift, mine honourable guests! An excellent guest’s-present! Well, do not then upbraid when I also offer you something of mine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003564": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003564",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is mine empire and my dominion: that which is mine, however, shall this evening and tonight be yours. Mine animals shall serve you: let my cave be your resting-place!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003565": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003565",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At house and home with me shall no one despair: in my purlieus do I protect every one from his wild beasts. And that is the first thing which I offer you: security!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003566": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003566",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The second thing, however, is my little finger. And when ye have THAT, then take the whole hand also, yea, and the heart with it! Welcome here, welcome to you, my guests!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003567": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003567",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and laughed with love and mischief. After this greeting his guests bowed once more and were reverentially silent; the king on the right, however, answered him in their name.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003568": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003568",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra, by the way in which thou hast given us thy hand and thy greeting, we recognise thee as Zarathustra. Thou hast humbled thyself before us; almost hast thou hurt our reverence—:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003569": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003569",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Who however could have humbled himself as thou hast done, with such pride? THAT uplifteth us ourselves; a refreshment is it, to our eyes and hearts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003570": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003570",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To behold this, merely, gladly would we ascend higher mountains than this. For as eager beholders have we come; we wanted to see what brighteneth dim eyes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003571": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003571",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And lo! now is it all over with our cries of distress. Now are our minds and hearts open and enraptured. Little is lacking for our spirits to become wanton.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003572": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003572",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There is nothing, O Zarathustra, that groweth more pleasingly on earth than a lofty, strong will: it is the finest growth. An entire landscape refresheth itself at one such tree.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003573": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003573",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To the pine do I compare him, O Zarathustra, which groweth up like thee—tall, silent, hardy, solitary, of the best, supplest wood, stately,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003574": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003574",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—In the end, however, grasping out for ITS dominion with strong, green branches, asking weighty questions of the wind, the storm, and whatever is at home on high places;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003575": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003575",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Answering more weightily, a commander, a victor! Oh! who should not ascend high mountains to behold such growths?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003576": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003576",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At thy tree, O Zarathustra, the gloomy and ill-constituted also refresh themselves; at thy look even the wavering become steady and heal their hearts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003577": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003577",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, towards thy mountain and thy tree do many eyes turn to-day; a great longing hath arisen, and many have learned to ask: ‘Who is Zarathustra?’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003578": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003578",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And those into whose ears thou hast at any time dripped thy song and thy honey: all the hidden ones, the lone-dwellers and the twain-dwellers, have simultaneously said to their hearts:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003579": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003579",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Doth Zarathustra still live? It is no longer worth while to live, everything is indifferent, everything is useless: or else—we must live with Zarathustra!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003580": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003580",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Why doth he not come who hath so long announced himself?’ thus do many people ask; ‘hath solitude swallowed him up? Or should we perhaps go to him?’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003581": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003581",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now doth it come to pass that solitude itself becometh fragile and breaketh open, like a grave that breaketh open and can no longer hold its dead. Everywhere one seeth resurrected ones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003582": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003582",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now do the waves rise and rise around thy mountain, O Zarathustra. And however high be thy height, many of them must rise up to thee: thy boat shall not rest much longer on dry ground.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003583": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003583",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And that we despairing ones have now come into thy cave, and already no longer despair:—it is but a prognostic and a presage that better ones are on the way to thee,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003584": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003584",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For they themselves are on the way to thee, the last remnant of God among men—that is to say, all the men of great longing, of great loathing, of great satiety,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003585": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003585",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—All who do not want to live unless they learn again to HOPE—unless they learn from thee, O Zarathustra, the GREAT hope!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003586": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003586",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the king on the right, and seized the hand of Zarathustra in order to kiss it; but Zarathustra checked his veneration, and stepped back frightened, fleeing as it were, silently and suddenly into the far distance. After a little while, however, he was again at home with his guests, looked at them with clear scrutinising eyes, and said:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003587": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003587",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“My guests, ye higher men, I will speak plain language and plainly with you. It is not for YOU that I have waited here in these mountains.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003588": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003588",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(“‘Plain language and plainly?’ Good God!” said here the king on the left to himself; “one seeth he doth not know the good Occidentals, this sage out of the Orient!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003589": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003589",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But he meaneth ‘blunt language and bluntly’—well! That is not the worst taste in these days!”)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003590": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003590",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ye may, verily, all of you be higher men,” continued Zarathustra; “but for me—ye are neither high enough, nor strong enough.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003591": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003591",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For me, that is to say, for the inexorable which is now silent in me, but will not always be silent. And if ye appertain to me, still it is not as my right arm.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003592": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003592",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For he who himself standeth, like you, on sickly and tender legs, wisheth above all to be TREATED INDULGENTLY, whether he be conscious of it or hide it from himself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003593": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003593",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My arms and my legs, however, I do not treat indulgently, I DO NOT TREAT MY WARRIORS INDULGENTLY: how then could ye be fit for MY warfare?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003594": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003594",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With you I should spoil all my victories. And many of you would tumble over if ye but heard the loud beating of my drums.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003595": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003595",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Moreover, ye are not sufficiently beautiful and well-born for me. I require pure, smooth mirrors for my doctrines; on your surface even mine own likeness is distorted.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003596": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003596",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On your shoulders presseth many a burden, many a recollection; many a mischievous dwarf squatteth in your corners. There is concealed populace also in you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003597": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003597",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And though ye be high and of a higher type, much in you is crooked and misshapen. There is no smith in the world that could hammer you right and straight for me.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003598": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003598",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye are only bridges: may higher ones pass over upon you! Ye signify steps: so do not upbraid him who ascendeth beyond you into HIS height!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003599": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003599",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Out of your seed there may one day arise for me a genuine son and perfect heir: but that time is distant. Ye yourselves are not those unto whom my heritage and name belong.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003600": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003600",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not for you do I wait here in these mountains; not with you may I descend for the last time. Ye have come unto me only as a presage that higher ones are on the way to me,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003601": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003601",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—NOT the men of great longing, of great loathing, of great satiety, and that which ye call the remnant of God;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003602": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003602",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Nay! Nay! Three times Nay! For OTHERS do I wait here in these mountains, and will not lift my foot from thence without them;</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003603": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003603",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—For higher ones, stronger ones, triumphanter ones, merrier ones, for such as are built squarely in body and soul: LAUGHING LIONS must come!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003604": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003604",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my guests, ye strange ones—have ye yet heard nothing of my children? And that they are on the way to me?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003605": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003605",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do speak unto me of my gardens, of my Happy Isles, of my new beautiful race—why do ye not speak unto me thereof?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003606": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003606",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This guests’-present do I solicit of your love, that ye speak unto me of my children. For them am I rich, for them I became poor: what have I not surrendered,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003607": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003607",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—What would I not surrender that I might have one thing: THESE children, THIS living plantation, THESE life-trees of my will and of my highest hope!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003608": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003608",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra, and stopped suddenly in his discourse: for his longing came over him, and he closed his eyes and his mouth, because of the agitation of his heart. And all his guests also were silent, and stood still and confounded: except only that the old soothsayer made signs with his hands and his gestures.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003609": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003609",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003610": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003610",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003611": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003611",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXII. THE SUPPER.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003612": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003612",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For at this point the soothsayer interrupted the greeting of Zarathustra and his guests: he pressed forward as one who had no time to lose, seized Zarathustra’s hand and exclaimed: “But Zarathustra!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003613": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003613",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One thing is more necessary than the other, so sayest thou thyself: well, one thing is now more necessary UNTO ME than all others.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003614": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003614",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A word at the right time: didst thou not invite me to TABLE? And here are many who have made long journeys. Thou dost not mean to feed us merely with discourses?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003615": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003615",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Besides, all of you have thought too much about freezing, drowning, suffocating, and other bodily dangers: none of you, however, have thought of MY danger, namely, perishing of hunger—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003616": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003616",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(Thus spake the soothsayer. When Zarathustra’s animals, however, heard these words, they ran away in terror. For they saw that all they had brought home during the day would not be enough to fill the one soothsayer.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003617": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003617",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Likewise perishing of thirst,” continued the soothsayer. “And although I hear water splashing here like words of wisdom—that is to say, plenteously and unweariedly, I—want WINE!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003618": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003618",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Not every one is a born water-drinker like Zarathustra. Neither doth water suit weary and withered ones: WE deserve wine—IT alone giveth immediate vigour and improvised health!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003619": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003619",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On this occasion, when the soothsayer was longing for wine, it happened that the king on the left, the silent one, also found expression for once. “WE took care,” said he, “about wine, I, along with my brother the king on the right: we have enough of wine,—a whole ass-load of it. So there is nothing lacking but bread.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003620": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003620",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Bread,” replied Zarathustra, laughing when he spake, “it is precisely bread that anchorites have not. But man doth not live by bread alone, but also by the flesh of good lambs, of which I have two:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003621": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003621",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—THESE shall we slaughter quickly, and cook spicily with sage: it is so that I like them. And there is also no lack of roots and fruits, good enough even for the fastidious and dainty,—nor of nuts and other riddles for cracking.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003622": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003622",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus will we have a good repast in a little while. But whoever wish to eat with us must also give a hand to the work, even the kings. For with Zarathustra even a king may be a cook.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003623": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003623",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This proposal appealed to the hearts of all of them, save that the voluntary beggar objected to the flesh and wine and spices.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003624": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003624",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Just hear this glutton Zarathustra!” said he jokingly: “doth one go into caves and high mountains to make such repasts?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003625": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003625",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now indeed do I understand what he once taught us: Blessed be moderate poverty!’ And why he wisheth to do away with beggars.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003626": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003626",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Be of good cheer,” replied Zarathustra, “as I am. Abide by thy customs, thou excellent one: grind thy corn, drink thy water, praise thy cooking,—if only it make thee glad!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003627": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003627",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I am a law only for mine own; I am not a law for all. He, however, who belongeth unto me must be strong of bone and light of foot,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003628": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003628",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Joyous in fight and feast, no sulker, no John o’ Dreams, ready for the hardest task as for the feast, healthy and hale.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003629": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003629",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The best belongeth unto mine and me; and if it be not given us, then do we take it:—the best food, the purest sky, the strongest thoughts, the fairest women!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003630": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003630",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra; the king on the right however answered and said: “Strange! Did one ever hear such sensible things out of the mouth of a wise man?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003631": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003631",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, it is the strangest thing in a wise man, if over and above, he be still sensible, and not an ass.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003632": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003632",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the king on the right and wondered; the ass however, with ill-will, said YE-A to his remark. This however was the beginning of that long repast which is called “The Supper” in the history-books. At this there was nothing else spoken of but THE HIGHER MAN.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003633": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003633",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003634": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003634",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003635": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003635",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXIII. THE HIGHER MAN.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003636": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003636",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003637": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003637",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When I came unto men for the first time, then did I commit the anchorite folly, the great folly: I appeared on the market-place.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003638": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003638",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when I spake unto all, I spake unto none. In the evening, however, rope-dancers were my companions, and corpses; and I myself almost a corpse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003639": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003639",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the new morning, however, there came unto me a new truth: then did I learn to say: “Of what account to me are market-place and populace and populace-noise and long populace-ears!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003640": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003640",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, learn THIS from me: On the market-place no one believeth in higher men. But if ye will speak there, very well! The populace, however, blinketh: “We are all equal.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003641": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003641",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ye higher men,”—so blinketh the populace—“there are no higher men, we are all equal; man is man, before God—we are all equal!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003642": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003642",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Before God!—Now, however, this God hath died. Before the populace, however, we will not be equal. Ye higher men, away from the market-place!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003643": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003643",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003644": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003644",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Before God!—Now however this God hath died! Ye higher men, this God was your greatest danger.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003645": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003645",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Only since he lay in the grave have ye again arisen. Now only cometh the great noontide, now only doth the higher man become—master!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003646": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003646",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have ye understood this word, O my brethren? Ye are frightened: do your hearts turn giddy? Doth the abyss here yawn for you? Doth the hell-hound here yelp at you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003647": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003647",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! Take heart! ye higher men! Now only travaileth the mountain of the human future. God hath died: now do WE desire—the Superman to live.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003648": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003648",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003649": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003649",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The most careful ask to-day: “How is man to be maintained?” Zarathustra however asketh, as the first and only one: “How is man to be SURPASSED?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003650": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003650",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The Superman, I have at heart; THAT is the first and only thing to me—and NOT man: not the neighbour, not the poorest, not the sorriest, not the best.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003651": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003651",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O my brethren, what I can love in man is that he is an over-going and a down-going. And also in you there is much that maketh me love and hope.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003652": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003652",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In that ye have despised, ye higher men, that maketh me hope. For the great despisers are the great reverers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003653": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003653",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In that ye have despaired, there is much to honour. For ye have not learned to submit yourselves, ye have not learned petty policy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003654": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003654",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For to-day have the petty people become master: they all preach submission and humility and policy and diligence and consideration and the long et cetera of petty virtues.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003655": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003655",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whatever is of the effeminate type, whatever originateth from the servile type, and especially the populace-mishmash:—THAT wisheth now to be master of all human destiny—O disgust! Disgust! Disgust!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003656": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003656",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THAT asketh and asketh and never tireth: “How is man to maintain himself best, longest, most pleasantly?” Thereby—are they the masters of to-day.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003657": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003657",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These masters of to-day—surpass them, O my brethren—these petty people: THEY are the Superman’s greatest danger!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003658": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003658",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Surpass, ye higher men, the petty virtues, the petty policy, the sand-grain considerateness, the ant-hill trumpery, the pitiable comfortableness, the “happiness of the greatest number”—!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003659": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003659",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And rather despair than submit yourselves. And verily, I love you, because ye know not to-day how to live, ye higher men! For thus do YE live—best!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003660": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003660",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003661": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003661",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have ye courage, O my brethren? Are ye stout-hearted? NOT the courage before witnesses, but anchorite and eagle courage, which not even a God any longer beholdeth?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003662": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003662",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Cold souls, mules, the blind and the drunken, I do not call stout-hearted. He hath heart who knoweth fear, but VANQUISHETH it; who seeth the abyss, but with PRIDE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003663": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003663",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who seeth the abyss, but with eagle’s eyes,—he who with eagle’s talons GRASPETH the abyss: he hath courage.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003664": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003664",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>5.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003665": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003665",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Man is evil”—so said to me for consolation, all the wisest ones. Ah, if only it be still true to-day! For the evil is man’s best force.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003666": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003666",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Man must become better and eviler”—so do <i>I</i> teach. The evilest is necessary for the Superman’s best.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003667": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003667",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It may have been well for the preacher of the petty people to suffer and be burdened by men’s sin. I, however, rejoice in great sin as my great CONSOLATION.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003668": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003668",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such things, however, are not said for long ears. Every word, also, is not suited for every mouth. These are fine far-away things: at them sheep’s claws shall not grasp!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003669": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003669",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003670": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003670",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, think ye that I am here to put right what ye have put wrong?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003671": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003671",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or that I wished henceforth to make snugger couches for you sufferers? Or show you restless, miswandering, misclimbing ones, new and easier footpaths?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003672": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003672",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nay! Nay! Three times Nay! Always more, always better ones of your type shall succumb,—for ye shall always have it worse and harder. Thus only—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003673": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003673",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thus only groweth man aloft to the height where the lightning striketh and shattereth him: high enough for the lightning!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003674": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003674",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Towards the few, the long, the remote go forth my soul and my seeking: of what account to me are your many little, short miseries!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003675": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003675",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye do not yet suffer enough for me! For ye suffer from yourselves, ye have not yet suffered FROM MAN. Ye would lie if ye spake otherwise! None of you suffereth from what <i>I</i> have suffered.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003676": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003676",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>7.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003677": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003677",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is not enough for me that the lightning no longer doeth harm. I do not wish to conduct it away: it shall learn—to work for ME.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003678": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003678",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My wisdom hath accumulated long like a cloud, it becometh stiller and darker. So doeth all wisdom which shall one day bear LIGHTNINGS.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003679": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003679",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unto these men of to-day will I not be LIGHT, nor be called light. THEM—will I blind: lightning of my wisdom! put out their eyes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003680": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003680",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>8.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003681": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003681",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do not will anything beyond your power: there is a bad falseness in those who will beyond their power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003682": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003682",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Especially when they will great things! For they awaken distrust in great things, these subtle false-coiners and stage-players:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003683": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003683",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Until at last they are false towards themselves, squint-eyed, whited cankers, glossed over with strong words, parade virtues and brilliant false deeds.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003684": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003684",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Take good care there, ye higher men! For nothing is more precious to me, and rarer, than honesty.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003685": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003685",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is this to-day not that of the populace? The populace however knoweth not what is great and what is small, what is straight and what is honest: it is innocently crooked, it ever lieth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003686": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003686",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>9.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003687": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003687",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have a good distrust to-day ye, higher men, ye enheartened ones! Ye open-hearted ones! And keep your reasons secret! For this to-day is that of the populace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003688": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003688",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What the populace once learned to believe without reasons, who could— refute it to them by means of reasons?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003689": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003689",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And on the market-place one convinceth with gestures. But reasons make the populace distrustful.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003690": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003690",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And when truth hath once triumphed there, then ask yourselves with good distrust: “What strong error hath fought for it?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003691": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003691",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Be on your guard also against the learned! They hate you, because they are unproductive! They have cold, withered eyes before which every bird is unplumed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003692": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003692",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such persons vaunt about not lying: but inability to lie is still far from being love to truth. Be on your guard!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003693": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003693",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Freedom from fever is still far from being knowledge! Refrigerated spirits I do not believe in. He who cannot lie, doth not know what truth is.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003694": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003694",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>10.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003695": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003695",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If ye would go up high, then use your own legs! Do not get yourselves CARRIED aloft; do not seat yourselves on other people’s backs and heads!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003696": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003696",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou hast mounted, however, on horseback? Thou now ridest briskly up to thy goal? Well, my friend! But thy lame foot is also with thee on horseback!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003697": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003697",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When thou reachest thy goal, when thou alightest from thy horse: precisely on thy HEIGHT, thou higher man,—then wilt thou stumble!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003698": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003698",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>11.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003699": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003699",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye creating ones, ye higher men! One is only pregnant with one’s own child.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003700": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003700",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do not let yourselves be imposed upon or put upon! Who then is YOUR neighbour? Even if ye act “for your neighbour”—ye still do not create for him!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003701": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003701",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unlearn, I pray you, this “for,” ye creating ones: your very virtue wisheth you to have naught to do with “for” and “on account of” and “because.” Against these false little words shall ye stop your ears.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003702": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003702",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“For one’s neighbour,” is the virtue only of the petty people: there it is said “like and like,” and “hand washeth hand”:—they have neither the right nor the power for YOUR self-seeking!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003703": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003703",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In your self-seeking, ye creating ones, there is the foresight and foreseeing of the pregnant! What no one’s eye hath yet seen, namely, the fruit—this, sheltereth and saveth and nourisheth your entire love.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003704": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003704",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where your entire love is, namely, with your child, there is also your entire virtue! Your work, your will is YOUR “neighbour”: let no false values impose upon you!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003705": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003705",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>12.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003706": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003706",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye creating ones, ye higher men! Whoever hath to give birth is sick; whoever hath given birth, however, is unclean.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003707": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003707",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ask women: one giveth birth, not because it giveth pleasure. The pain maketh hens and poets cackle.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003708": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003708",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye creating ones, in you there is much uncleanliness. That is because ye have had to be mothers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003709": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003709",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A new child: oh, how much new filth hath also come into the world! Go apart! He who hath given birth shall wash his soul!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003710": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003710",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>13.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003711": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003711",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Be not virtuous beyond your powers! And seek nothing from yourselves opposed to probability!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003712": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003712",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Walk in the footsteps in which your fathers’ virtue hath already walked! How would ye rise high, if your fathers’ will should not rise with you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003713": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003713",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He, however, who would be a firstling, let him take care lest he also become a lastling! And where the vices of your fathers are, there should ye not set up as saints!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003714": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003714",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He whose fathers were inclined for women, and for strong wine and flesh of wildboar swine; what would it be if he demanded chastity of himself?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003715": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003715",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A folly would it be! Much, verily, doth it seem to me for such a one, if he should be the husband of one or of two or of three women.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003716": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003716",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if he founded monasteries, and inscribed over their portals: “The way to holiness,”—I should still say: What good is it! it is a new folly!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003717": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003717",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He hath founded for himself a penance-house and refuge-house: much good may it do! But I do not believe in it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003718": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003718",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In solitude there groweth what any one bringeth into it—also the brute in one’s nature. Thus is solitude inadvisable unto many.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003719": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003719",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hath there ever been anything filthier on earth than the saints of the wilderness? AROUND THEM was not only the devil loose—but also the swine.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003720": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003720",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>14.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003721": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003721",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Shy, ashamed, awkward, like the tiger whose spring hath failed—thus, ye higher men, have I often seen you slink aside. A CAST which ye made had failed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003722": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003722",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But what doth it matter, ye dice-players! Ye had not learned to play and mock, as one must play and mock! Do we not ever sit at a great table of mocking and playing?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003723": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003723",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if great things have been a failure with you, have ye yourselves therefore—been a failure? And if ye yourselves have been a failure, hath man therefore—been a failure? If man, however, hath been a failure: well then! never mind!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003724": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003724",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>15.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003725": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003725",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The higher its type, always the seldomer doth a thing succeed. Ye higher men here, have ye not all—been failures?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003726": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003726",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Be of good cheer; what doth it matter? How much is still possible! Learn to laugh at yourselves, as ye ought to laugh!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003727": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003727",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What wonder even that ye have failed and only half-succeeded, ye half-shattered ones! Doth not—man’s FUTURE strive and struggle in you?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003728": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003728",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Man’s furthest, profoundest, star-highest issues, his prodigious powers—do not all these foam through one another in your vessel?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003729": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003729",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What wonder that many a vessel shattereth! Learn to laugh at yourselves, as ye ought to laugh! Ye higher men, O, how much is still possible!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003730": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003730",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, how much hath already succeeded! How rich is this earth in small, good, perfect things, in well-constituted things!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003731": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003731",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Set around you small, good, perfect things, ye higher men. Their golden maturity healeth the heart. The perfect teacheth one to hope.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003732": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003732",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>16.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003733": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003733",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What hath hitherto been the greatest sin here on earth? Was it not the word of him who said: “Woe unto them that laugh now!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003734": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003734",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Did he himself find no cause for laughter on the earth? Then he sought badly. A child even findeth cause for it.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003735": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003735",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He—did not love sufficiently: otherwise would he also have loved us, the laughing ones! But he hated and hooted us; wailing and teeth-gnashing did he promise us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003736": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003736",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Must one then curse immediately, when one doth not love? That—seemeth to me bad taste. Thus did he, however, this absolute one. He sprang from the populace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003737": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003737",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he himself just did not love sufficiently; otherwise would he have raged less because people did not love him. All great love doth not SEEK love:—it seeketh more.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003738": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003738",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Go out of the way of all such absolute ones! They are a poor sickly type, a populace-type: they look at this life with ill-will, they have an evil eye for this earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003739": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003739",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Go out of the way of all such absolute ones! They have heavy feet and sultry hearts:—they do not know how to dance. How could the earth be light to such ones!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003740": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003740",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>17.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003741": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003741",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Tortuously do all good things come nigh to their goal. Like cats they curve their backs, they purr inwardly with their approaching happiness,—all good things laugh.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003742": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003742",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>His step betrayeth whether a person already walketh on HIS OWN path: just see me walk! He, however, who cometh nigh to his goal, danceth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003743": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003743",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, a statue have I not become, not yet do I stand there stiff, stupid and stony, like a pillar; I love fast racing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003744": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003744",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And though there be on earth fens and dense afflictions, he who hath light feet runneth even across the mud, and danceth, as upon well-swept ice.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003745": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003745",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lift up your hearts, my brethren, high, higher! And do not forget your legs! Lift up also your legs, ye good dancers, and better still, if ye stand upon your heads!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003746": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003746",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>18.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003747": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003747",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This crown of the laughter, this rose-garland crown: I myself have put on this crown, I myself have consecrated my laughter. No one else have I found to-day potent enough for this.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003748": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003748",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra the dancer, Zarathustra the light one, who beckoneth with his pinions, one ready for flight, beckoning unto all birds, ready and prepared, a blissfully light-spirited one:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003749": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003749",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra the soothsayer, Zarathustra the sooth-laugher, no impatient one, no absolute one, one who loveth leaps and side-leaps; I myself have put on this crown!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003750": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003750",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>19.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003751": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003751",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lift up your hearts, my brethren, high, higher! And do not forget your legs! Lift up also your legs, ye good dancers, and better still if ye stand upon your heads!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003752": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003752",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>There are also heavy animals in a state of happiness, there are club-footed ones from the beginning. Curiously do they exert themselves, like an elephant which endeavoureth to stand upon its head.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003753": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003753",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better, however, to be foolish with happiness than foolish with misfortune, better to dance awkwardly than walk lamely. So learn, I pray you, my wisdom, ye higher men: even the worst thing hath two good reverse sides,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003754": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003754",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Even the worst thing hath good dancing-legs: so learn, I pray you, ye higher men, to put yourselves on your proper legs!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003755": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003755",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So unlearn, I pray you, the sorrow-sighing, and all the populace-sadness! Oh, how sad the buffoons of the populace seem to me to-day! This to-day, however, is that of the populace.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003756": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003756",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>20.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003757": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003757",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Do like unto the wind when it rusheth forth from its mountain-caves: unto its own piping will it dance; the seas tremble and leap under its footsteps.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003758": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003758",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That which giveth wings to asses, that which milketh the lionesses:— praised be that good, unruly spirit, which cometh like a hurricane unto all the present and unto all the populace,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003759": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003759",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Which is hostile to thistle-heads and puzzle-heads, and to all withered leaves and weeds:—praised be this wild, good, free spirit of the storm, which danceth upon fens and afflictions, as upon meadows!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003760": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003760",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Which hateth the consumptive populace-dogs, and all the ill-constituted, sullen brood:—praised be this spirit of all free spirits, the laughing storm, which bloweth dust into the eyes of all the melanopic and melancholic!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003761": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003761",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, the worst thing in you is that ye have none of you learned to dance as ye ought to dance—to dance beyond yourselves! What doth it matter that ye have failed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003762": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003762",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How many things are still possible! So LEARN to laugh beyond yourselves! Lift up your hearts, ye good dancers, high! higher! And do not forget the good laughter!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003763": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003763",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This crown of the laughter, this rose-garland crown: to you my brethren do I cast this crown! Laughing have I consecrated; ye higher men, LEARN, I pray you—to laugh!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003764": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003764",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003765": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003765",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003766": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003766",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXIV. THE SONG OF MELANCHOLY.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003767": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003767",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003768": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003768",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When Zarathustra spake these sayings, he stood nigh to the entrance of his cave; with the last words, however, he slipped away from his guests, and fled for a little while into the open air.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003769": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003769",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O pure odours around me,” cried he, “O blessed stillness around me! But where are mine animals? Hither, hither, mine eagle and my serpent!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003770": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003770",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Tell me, mine animals: these higher men, all of them—do they perhaps not SMELL well? O pure odours around me! Now only do I know and feel how I love you, mine animals.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003771": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003771",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And Zarathustra said once more: “I love you, mine animals!” The eagle, however, and the serpent pressed close to him when he spake these words, and looked up to him. In this attitude were they all three silent together, and sniffed and sipped the good air with one another. For the air here outside was better than with the higher men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003772": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003772",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003773": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003773",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hardly, however, had Zarathustra left the cave when the old magician got up, looked cunningly about him, and said: “He is gone!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003774": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003774",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And already, ye higher men—let me tickle you with this complimentary and flattering name, as he himself doeth—already doth mine evil spirit of deceit and magic attack me, my melancholy devil,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003775": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003775",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Which is an adversary to this Zarathustra from the very heart: forgive it for this! Now doth it wish to conjure before you, it hath just ITS hour; in vain do I struggle with this evil spirit.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003776": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003776",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unto all of you, whatever honours ye like to assume in your names, whether ye call yourselves ‘the free spirits’ or ‘the conscientious,’ or ‘the penitents of the spirit,’ or ‘the unfettered,’ or ‘the great longers,’—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003777": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003777",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Unto all of you, who like me suffer FROM THE GREAT LOATHING, to whom the old God hath died, and as yet no new God lieth in cradles and swaddling clothes—unto all of you is mine evil spirit and magic-devil favourable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003778": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003778",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I know you, ye higher men, I know him,—I know also this fiend whom I love in spite of me, this Zarathustra: he himself often seemeth to me like the beautiful mask of a saint,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003779": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003779",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Like a new strange mummery in which mine evil spirit, the melancholy devil, delighteth:—I love Zarathustra, so doth it often seem to me, for the sake of mine evil spirit.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003780": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003780",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But already doth IT attack me and constrain me, this spirit of melancholy, this evening-twilight devil: and verily, ye higher men, it hath a longing—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003781": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003781",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Open your eyes!—it hath a longing to come NAKED, whether male or female, I do not yet know: but it cometh, it constraineth me, alas! open your wits!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003782": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003782",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The day dieth out, unto all things cometh now the evening, also unto the best things; hear now, and see, ye higher men, what devil—man or woman—this spirit of evening-melancholy is!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003783": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003783",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the old magician, looked cunningly about him, and then seized his harp.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003784": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003784",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003785": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003785",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">     In evening’s limpid air,\n<br>     What time the dew’s soothings\n<br>     Unto the earth downpour,\n<br>     Invisibly and unheard—\n<br>     For tender shoe-gear wear\n<br>     The soothing dews, like all that’s kind-gentle—:\n<br>     Bethinkst thou then, bethinkst thou, burning heart,\n<br>     How once thou thirstedest\n<br>     For heaven’s kindly teardrops and dew’s down-droppings,\n<br>     All singed and weary thirstedest,\n<br>     What time on yellow grass-pathways\n<br>     Wicked, occidental sunny glances\n<br>     Through sombre trees about thee sported,\n<br>     Blindingly sunny glow-glances, gladly-hurting?\n<br>\n<br>     “Of TRUTH the wooer?  Thou?”—so taunted they—\n<br>     “Nay!  Merely poet!\n<br>     A brute insidious, plundering, grovelling,\n<br>     That aye must lie,\n<br>     That wittingly, wilfully, aye must lie:\n<br>     For booty lusting,\n<br>     Motley masked,\n<br>     Self-hidden, shrouded,\n<br>     Himself his booty—\n<br>     HE—of truth the wooer?\n<br>     Nay!  Mere fool!  Mere poet!\n<br>     Just motley speaking,\n<br>     From mask of fool confusedly shouting,\n<br>     Circumambling on fabricated word-bridges,\n<br>     On motley rainbow-arches,\n<br>     ‘Twixt the spurious heavenly,\n<br>     And spurious earthly,\n<br>     Round us roving, round us soaring,—\n<br>     MERE FOOL!  MERE POET!\n<br>\n<br>     HE—of truth the wooer?\n<br>     Not still, stiff, smooth and cold,\n<br>     Become an image,\n<br>     A godlike statue,\n<br>     Set up in front of temples,\n<br>     As a God’s own door-guard:\n<br>     Nay! hostile to all such truthfulness-statues,\n<br>     In every desert homelier than at temples,\n<br>     With cattish wantonness,\n<br>     Through every window leaping\n<br>     Quickly into chances,\n<br>     Every wild forest a-sniffing,\n<br>     Greedily-longingly, sniffing,\n<br>     That thou, in wild forests,\n<br>     ’Mong the motley-speckled fierce creatures,\n<br>     Shouldest rove, sinful-sound and fine-coloured,\n<br>     With longing lips smacking,\n<br>     Blessedly mocking, blessedly hellish, blessedly bloodthirsty,\n<br>     Robbing, skulking, lying—roving:—\n<br>\n<br>     Or unto eagles like which fixedly,\n<br>     Long adown the precipice look,\n<br>     Adown THEIR precipice:—\n<br>     Oh, how they whirl down now,\n<br>     Thereunder, therein,\n<br>     To ever deeper profoundness whirling!—\n<br>     Then,\n<br>     Sudden,\n<br>     With aim aright,\n<br>     With quivering flight,\n<br>     On LAMBKINS pouncing,\n<br>     Headlong down, sore-hungry,\n<br>     For lambkins longing,\n<br>     Fierce ’gainst all lamb-spirits,\n<br>     Furious-fierce ’gainst all that look\n<br>     Sheeplike, or lambeyed, or crisp-woolly,\n<br>     —Grey, with lambsheep kindliness!\n<br>\n<br>     Even thus,\n<br>     Eaglelike, pantherlike,\n<br>     Are the poet’s desires,\n<br>     Are THINE OWN desires ‘neath a thousand guises,\n<br>     Thou fool!  Thou poet!\n<br>     Thou who all mankind viewedst—\n<br>     So God, as sheep—:\n<br>     The God TO REND within mankind,\n<br>     As the sheep in mankind,\n<br>     And in rending LAUGHING—\n<br>\n<br>     THAT, THAT is thine own blessedness!\n<br>     Of a panther and eagle—blessedness!\n<br>     Of a poet and fool—the blessedness!—\n<br>\n<br>     In evening’s limpid air,\n<br>     What time the moon’s sickle,\n<br>     Green, ‘twixt the purple-glowings,\n<br>     And jealous, steal’th forth:\n<br>     —Of day the foe,\n<br>     With every step in secret,\n<br>     The rosy garland-hammocks\n<br>     Downsickling, till they’ve sunken\n<br>     Down nightwards, faded, downsunken:—\n<br>\n<br>     Thus had I sunken one day\n<br>     From mine own truth-insanity,\n<br>     From mine own fervid day-longings,\n<br>     Of day aweary, sick of sunshine,\n<br>     —Sunk downwards, evenwards, shadowwards:\n<br>     By one sole trueness\n<br>     All scorched and thirsty:\n<br>     —Bethinkst thou still, bethinkst thou, burning heart,\n<br>     How then thou thirstedest?—\n<br>     THAT I SHOULD BANNED BE\n<br>     FROM ALL THE TRUENESS!\n<br>     MERE FOOL!  MERE POET!\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003786": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003786",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003787": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003787",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003788": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003788",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXV. SCIENCE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003789": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003789",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus sang the magician; and all who were present went like birds unawares into the net of his artful and melancholy voluptuousness. Only the spiritually conscientious one had not been caught: he at once snatched the harp from the magician and called out: “Air! Let in good air! Let in Zarathustra! Thou makest this cave sultry and poisonous, thou bad old magician!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003790": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003790",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou seducest, thou false one, thou subtle one, to unknown desires and deserts. And alas, that such as thou should talk and make ado about the TRUTH!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003791": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003791",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Alas, to all free spirits who are not on their guard against SUCH magicians! It is all over with their freedom: thou teachest and temptest back into prisons,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003792": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003792",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Thou old melancholy devil, out of thy lament soundeth a lurement: thou resemblest those who with their praise of chastity secretly invite to voluptuousness!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003793": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003793",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the conscientious one; the old magician, however, looked about him, enjoying his triumph, and on that account put up with the annoyance which the conscientious one caused him. “Be still!” said he with modest voice, “good songs want to re-echo well; after good songs one should be long silent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003794": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003794",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus do all those present, the higher men. Thou, however, hast perhaps understood but little of my song? In thee there is little of the magic spirit.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003795": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003795",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou praisest me,” replied the conscientious one, “in that thou separatest me from thyself; very well! But, ye others, what do I see? Ye still sit there, all of you, with lusting eyes—:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003796": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003796",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye free spirits, whither hath your freedom gone! Ye almost seem to me to resemble those who have long looked at bad girls dancing naked: your souls themselves dance!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003797": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003797",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In you, ye higher men, there must be more of that which the magician calleth his evil spirit of magic and deceit:—we must indeed be different.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003798": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003798",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And verily, we spake and thought long enough together ere Zarathustra came home to his cave, for me not to be unaware that we ARE different.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003799": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003799",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We SEEK different things even here aloft, ye and I. For I seek more SECURITY; on that account have I come to Zarathustra. For he is still the most steadfast tower and will—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003800": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003800",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—To-day, when everything tottereth, when all the earth quaketh. Ye, however, when I see what eyes ye make, it almost seemeth to me that ye seek MORE INSECURITY,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003801": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003801",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—More horror, more danger, more earthquake. Ye long (it almost seemeth so to me—forgive my presumption, ye higher men)—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003802": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003802",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ye long for the worst and dangerousest life, which frighteneth ME most,—for the life of wild beasts, for forests, caves, steep mountains and labyrinthine gorges.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003803": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003803",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And it is not those who lead OUT OF danger that please you best, but those who lead you away from all paths, the misleaders. But if such longing in you be ACTUAL, it seemeth to me nevertheless to be IMPOSSIBLE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003804": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003804",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For fear—that is man’s original and fundamental feeling; through fear everything is explained, original sin and original virtue. Through fear there grew also MY virtue, that is to say: Science.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003805": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003805",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For fear of wild animals—that hath been longest fostered in man, inclusive of the animal which he concealeth and feareth in himself:—Zarathustra calleth it ‘the beast inside.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003806": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003806",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such prolonged ancient fear, at last become subtle, spiritual and intellectual—at present, me thinketh, it is called SCIENCE.”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003807": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003807",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the conscientious one; but Zarathustra, who had just come back into his cave and had heard and divined the last discourse, threw a handful of roses to the conscientious one, and laughed on account of his “truths.” “Why!” he exclaimed, “what did I hear just now? Verily, it seemeth to me, thou art a fool, or else I myself am one: and quietly and quickly will I put thy ‘truth’ upside down.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003808": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003808",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For FEAR—is an exception with us. Courage, however, and adventure, and delight in the uncertain, in the unattempted—COURAGE seemeth to me the entire primitive history of man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003809": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003809",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The wildest and most courageous animals hath he envied and robbed of all their virtues: thus only did he become—man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003810": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003810",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THIS courage, at last become subtle, spiritual and intellectual, this human courage, with eagle’s pinions and serpent’s wisdom: THIS, it seemeth to me, is called at present—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003811": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003811",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“ZARATHUSTRA!” cried all of them there assembled, as if with one voice, and burst out at the same time into a great laughter; there arose, however, from them as it were a heavy cloud. Even the magician laughed, and said wisely: “Well! It is gone, mine evil spirit!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003812": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003812",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And did I not myself warn you against it when I said that it was a deceiver, a lying and deceiving spirit?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003813": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003813",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Especially when it showeth itself naked. But what can <i>I</i> do with regard to its tricks! Have <i>I</i> created it and the world?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003814": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003814",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! Let us be good again, and of good cheer! And although Zarathustra looketh with evil eye—just see him! he disliketh me—:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003815": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003815",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ere night cometh will he again learn to love and laud me; he cannot live long without committing such follies.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003816": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003816",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>HE—loveth his enemies: this art knoweth he better than any one I have seen. But he taketh revenge for it—on his friends!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003817": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003817",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the old magician, and the higher men applauded him; so that Zarathustra went round, and mischievously and lovingly shook hands with his friends,—like one who hath to make amends and apologise to every one for something. When however he had thereby come to the door of his cave, lo, then had he again a longing for the good air outside, and for his animals,—and wished to steal out.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003818": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003818",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003819": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003819",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003820": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003820",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXVI. AMONG DAUGHTERS OF THE DESERT.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003821": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003821",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003822": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003822",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Go not away!” said then the wanderer who called himself Zarathustra’s shadow, “abide with us—otherwise the old gloomy affliction might again fall upon us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003823": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003823",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now hath that old magician given us of his worst for our good, and lo! the good, pious pope there hath tears in his eyes, and hath quite embarked again upon the sea of melancholy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003824": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003824",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Those kings may well put on a good air before us still: for that have THEY learned best of us all at present! Had they however no one to see them, I wager that with them also the bad game would again commence,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003825": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003825",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The bad game of drifting clouds, of damp melancholy, of curtained heavens, of stolen suns, of howling autumn-winds,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003826": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003826",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The bad game of our howling and crying for help! Abide with us, O Zarathustra! Here there is much concealed misery that wisheth to speak, much evening, much cloud, much damp air!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003827": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003827",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou hast nourished us with strong food for men, and powerful proverbs: do not let the weakly, womanly spirits attack us anew at dessert!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003828": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003828",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou alone makest the air around thee strong and clear! Did I ever find anywhere on earth such good air as with thee in thy cave?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003829": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003829",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many lands have I seen, my nose hath learned to test and estimate many kinds of air: but with thee do my nostrils taste their greatest delight!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003830": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003830",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Unless it be,—unless it be—, do forgive an old recollection! Forgive me an old after-dinner song, which I once composed amongst daughters of the desert:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003831": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003831",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For with them was there equally good, clear, Oriental air; there was I furthest from cloudy, damp, melancholy Old-Europe!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003832": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003832",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then did I love such Oriental maidens and other blue kingdoms of heaven, over which hang no clouds and no thoughts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003833": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003833",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye would not believe how charmingly they sat there, when they did not dance, profound, but without thoughts, like little secrets, like beribboned riddles, like dessert-nuts—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003834": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003834",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many-hued and foreign, forsooth! but without clouds: riddles which can be guessed: to please such maidens I then composed an after-dinner psalm.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003835": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003835",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the wanderer who called himself Zarathustra’s shadow; and before any one answered him, he had seized the harp of the old magician, crossed his legs, and looked calmly and sagely around him:—with his nostrils, however, he inhaled the air slowly and questioningly, like one who in new countries tasteth new foreign air. Afterward he began to sing with a kind of roaring.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003836": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003836",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2. THE DESERTS GROW: WOE HIM WHO DOTH THEM HIDE!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003837": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003837",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">     —Ha!\n<br>     Solemnly!\n<br>     In effect solemnly!\n<br>     A worthy beginning!\n<br>     Afric manner, solemnly!\n<br>     Of a lion worthy,\n<br>     Or perhaps of a virtuous howl-monkey—\n<br>     —But it’s naught to you,\n<br>     Ye friendly damsels dearly loved,\n<br>     At whose own feet to me,\n<br>     The first occasion,\n<br>     To a European under palm-trees,\n<br>     A seat is now granted.  Selah.\n<br>\n<br>     Wonderful, truly!\n<br>     Here do I sit now,\n<br>     The desert nigh, and yet I am\n<br>     So far still from the desert,\n<br>     Even in naught yet deserted:\n<br>     That is, I’m swallowed down\n<br>     By this the smallest oasis—:\n<br>     —It opened up just yawning,\n<br>     Its loveliest mouth agape,\n<br>     Most sweet-odoured of all mouthlets:\n<br>     Then fell I right in,\n<br>     Right down, right through—in ’mong you,\n<br>     Ye friendly damsels dearly loved!  Selah.\n<br>\n<br>     Hail! hail! to that whale, fishlike,\n<br>     If it thus for its guest’s convenience\n<br>     Made things nice!—(ye well know,\n<br>     Surely, my learned allusion?)\n<br>     Hail to its belly,\n<br>     If it had e’er\n<br>     A such loveliest oasis-belly\n<br>     As this is:  though however I doubt about it,\n<br>     —With this come I out of Old-Europe,\n<br>     That doubt’th more eagerly than doth any\n<br>     Elderly married woman.\n<br>     May the Lord improve it!\n<br>     Amen!\n<br>\n<br>     Here do I sit now,\n<br>     In this the smallest oasis,\n<br>     Like a date indeed,\n<br>     Brown, quite sweet, gold-suppurating,\n<br>     For rounded mouth of maiden longing,\n<br>     But yet still more for youthful, maidlike,\n<br>     Ice-cold and snow-white and incisory\n<br>     Front teeth:  and for such assuredly,\n<br>     Pine the hearts all of ardent date-fruits.  Selah.\n<br>\n<br>     To the there-named south-fruits now,\n<br>     Similar, all-too-similar,\n<br>     Do I lie here; by little\n<br>     Flying insects\n<br>     Round-sniffled and round-played,\n<br>     And also by yet littler,\n<br>     Foolisher, and peccabler\n<br>     Wishes and phantasies,—\n<br>     Environed by you,\n<br>     Ye silent, presentientest\n<br>     Maiden-kittens,\n<br>     Dudu and Suleika,\n<br>     —ROUNDSPHINXED, that into one word\n<br>     I may crowd much feeling:\n<br>     (Forgive me, O God,\n<br>     All such speech-sinning!)\n<br>     —Sit I here the best of air sniffling,\n<br>     Paradisal air, truly,\n<br>     Bright and buoyant air, golden-mottled,\n<br>     As goodly air as ever\n<br>     From lunar orb downfell—\n<br>     Be it by hazard,\n<br>     Or supervened it by arrogancy?\n<br>     As the ancient poets relate it.\n<br>     But doubter, I’m now calling it\n<br>     In question:  with this do I come indeed\n<br>     Out of Europe,\n<br>     That doubt’th more eagerly than doth any\n<br>     Elderly married woman.\n<br>     May the Lord improve it!\n<br>     Amen.\n<br>\n<br>     This the finest air drinking,\n<br>     With nostrils out-swelled like goblets,\n<br>     Lacking future, lacking remembrances\n<br>     Thus do I sit here, ye\n<br>     Friendly damsels dearly loved,\n<br>     And look at the palm-tree there,\n<br>     How it, to a dance-girl, like,\n<br>     Doth bow and bend and on its haunches bob,\n<br>     —One doth it too, when one view’th it long!—\n<br>     To a dance-girl like, who as it seem’th to me,\n<br>     Too long, and dangerously persistent,\n<br>     Always, always, just on SINGLE leg hath stood?\n<br>     —Then forgot she thereby, as it seem’th to me,\n<br>     The OTHER leg?\n<br>     For vainly I, at least,\n<br>     Did search for the amissing\n<br>     Fellow-jewel\n<br>     —Namely, the other leg—\n<br>     In the sanctified precincts,\n<br>     Nigh her very dearest, very tenderest,\n<br>     Flapping and fluttering and flickering skirting.\n<br>     Yea, if ye should, ye beauteous friendly ones,\n<br>     Quite take my word:\n<br>     She hath, alas! LOST it!\n<br>     Hu!  Hu!  Hu!  Hu!  Hu!\n<br>     It is away!\n<br>     For ever away!\n<br>     The other leg!\n<br>     Oh, pity for that loveliest other leg!\n<br>     Where may it now tarry, all-forsaken weeping?\n<br>     The lonesomest leg?\n<br>     In fear perhaps before a\n<br>     Furious, yellow, blond and curled\n<br>     Leonine monster?  Or perhaps even\n<br>     Gnawed away, nibbled badly—\n<br>     Most wretched, woeful! woeful! nibbled badly!  Selah.\n<br>\n<br>     Oh, weep ye not,\n<br>     Gentle spirits!\n<br>     Weep ye not, ye\n<br>     Date-fruit spirits!  Milk-bosoms!\n<br>     Ye sweetwood-heart\n<br>     Purselets!\n<br>     Weep ye no more,\n<br>     Pallid Dudu!\n<br>     Be a man, Suleika!  Bold!  Bold!\n<br>     —Or else should there perhaps\n<br>     Something strengthening, heart-strengthening,\n<br>     Here most proper be?\n<br>     Some inspiring text?\n<br>     Some solemn exhortation?—\n<br>     Ha!  Up now! honour!\n<br>     Moral honour!  European honour!\n<br>     Blow again, continue,\n<br>     Bellows-box of virtue!\n<br>     Ha!\n<br>     Once more thy roaring,\n<br>     Thy moral roaring!\n<br>     As a virtuous lion\n<br>     Nigh the daughters of deserts roaring!\n<br>     —For virtue’s out-howl,\n<br>     Ye very dearest maidens,\n<br>     Is more than every\n<br>     European fervour, European hot-hunger!\n<br>     And now do I stand here,\n<br>     As European,\n<br>     I can’t be different, God’s help to me!\n<br>     Amen!\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003838": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003838",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THE DESERTS GROW: WOE HIM WHO DOTH THEM HIDE! <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003839": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003839",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003840": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003840",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXVII. THE AWAKENING.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003841": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003841",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003842": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003842",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>After the song of the wanderer and shadow, the cave became all at once full of noise and laughter: and since the assembled guests all spake simultaneously, and even the ass, encouraged thereby, no longer remained silent, a little aversion and scorn for his visitors came over Zarathustra, although he rejoiced at their gladness. For it seemed to him a sign of convalescence. So he slipped out into the open air and spake to his animals.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003843": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003843",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Whither hath their distress now gone?” said he, and already did he himself feel relieved of his petty disgust—“with me, it seemeth that they have unlearned their cries of distress!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003844": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003844",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Though, alas! not yet their crying.” And Zarathustra stopped his ears, for just then did the YE-A of the ass mix strangely with the noisy jubilation of those higher men.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003845": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003845",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“They are merry,” he began again, “and who knoweth? perhaps at their host’s expense; and if they have learned of me to laugh, still it is not MY laughter they have learned.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003846": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003846",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But what matter about that! They are old people: they recover in their own way, they laugh in their own way; mine ears have already endured worse and have not become peevish.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003847": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003847",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This day is a victory: he already yieldeth, he fleeth, THE SPIRIT OF GRAVITY, mine old arch-enemy! How well this day is about to end, which began so badly and gloomily!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003848": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003848",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And it is ABOUT TO end. Already cometh the evening: over the sea rideth it hither, the good rider! How it bobbeth, the blessed one, the home-returning one, in its purple saddles!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003849": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003849",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The sky gazeth brightly thereon, the world lieth deep. Oh, all ye strange ones who have come to me, it is already worth while to have lived with me!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003850": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003850",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra. And again came the cries and laughter of the higher men out of the cave: then began he anew:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003851": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003851",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“They bite at it, my bait taketh, there departeth also from them their enemy, the spirit of gravity. Now do they learn to laugh at themselves: do I hear rightly?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003852": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003852",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My virile food taketh effect, my strong and savoury sayings: and verily, I did not nourish them with flatulent vegetables! But with warrior-food, with conqueror-food: new desires did I awaken.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003853": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003853",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>New hopes are in their arms and legs, their hearts expand. They find new words, soon will their spirits breathe wantonness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003854": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003854",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Such food may sure enough not be proper for children, nor even for longing girls old and young. One persuadeth their bowels otherwise; I am not their physician and teacher.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003855": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003855",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The DISGUST departeth from these higher men; well! that is my victory. In my domain they become assured; all stupid shame fleeth away; they empty themselves.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003856": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003856",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They empty their hearts, good times return unto them, they keep holiday and ruminate,—they become THANKFUL.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003857": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003857",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>THAT do I take as the best sign: they become thankful. Not long will it be ere they devise festivals, and put up memorials to their old joys.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003858": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003858",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They are CONVALESCENTS!” Thus spake Zarathustra joyfully to his heart and gazed outward; his animals, however, pressed up to him, and honoured his happiness and his silence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003859": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003859",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003860": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003860",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All on a sudden however, Zarathustra’s ear was frightened: for the cave which had hitherto been full of noise and laughter, became all at once still as death;—his nose, however, smelt a sweet-scented vapour and incense-odour, as if from burning pine-cones.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003861": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003861",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What happeneth? What are they about?” he asked himself, and stole up to the entrance, that he might be able unobserved to see his guests. But wonder upon wonder! what was he then obliged to behold with his own eyes!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003862": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003862",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“They have all of them become PIOUS again, they PRAY, they are mad!”—said he, and was astonished beyond measure. And forsooth! all these higher men, the two kings, the pope out of service, the evil magician, the voluntary beggar, the wanderer and shadow, the old soothsayer, the spiritually conscientious one, and the ugliest man—they all lay on their knees like children and credulous old women, and worshipped the ass. And just then began the ugliest man to gurgle and snort, as if something unutterable in him tried to find expression; when, however, he had actually found words, behold! it was a pious, strange litany in praise of the adored and censed ass. And the litany sounded thus:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003863": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003863",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Amen! And glory and honour and wisdom and thanks and praise and strength be to our God, from everlasting to everlasting!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003864": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003864",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003865": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003865",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He carrieth our burdens, he hath taken upon him the form of a servant, he is patient of heart and never saith Nay; and he who loveth his God chastiseth him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003866": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003866",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003867": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003867",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He speaketh not: except that he ever saith Yea to the world which he created: thus doth he extol his world. It is his artfulness that speaketh not: thus is he rarely found wrong.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003868": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003868",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003869": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003869",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Uncomely goeth he through the world. Grey is the favourite colour in which he wrappeth his virtue. Hath he spirit, then doth he conceal it; every one, however, believeth in his long ears.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003870": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003870",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003871": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003871",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What hidden wisdom it is to wear long ears, and only to say Yea and never Nay! Hath he not created the world in his own image, namely, as stupid as possible?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003872": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003872",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003873": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003873",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou goest straight and crooked ways; it concerneth thee little what seemeth straight or crooked unto us men. Beyond good and evil is thy domain. It is thine innocence not to know what innocence is.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003874": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003874",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003875": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003875",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Lo! how thou spurnest none from thee, neither beggars nor kings. Thou sufferest little children to come unto thee, and when the bad boys decoy thee, then sayest thou simply, YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003876": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003876",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003877": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003877",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou lovest she-asses and fresh figs, thou art no food-despiser. A thistle tickleth thy heart when thou chancest to be hungry. There is the wisdom of a God therein.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003878": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003878",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The ass, however, here brayed YE-A.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003879": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003879",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003880": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003880",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003881": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003881",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXVIII. THE ASS-FESTIVAL.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003882": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003882",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003883": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003883",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At this place in the litany, however, Zarathustra could no longer control himself; he himself cried out YE-A, louder even than the ass, and sprang into the midst of his maddened guests. “Whatever are you about, ye grown-up children?” he exclaimed, pulling up the praying ones from the ground. “Alas, if any one else, except Zarathustra, had seen you:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003884": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003884",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Every one would think you the worst blasphemers, or the very foolishest old women, with your new belief!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003885": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003885",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And thou thyself, thou old pope, how is it in accordance with thee, to adore an ass in such a manner as God?”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003886": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003886",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” answered the pope, “forgive me, but in divine matters I am more enlightened even than thou. And it is right that it should be so.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003887": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003887",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Better to adore God so, in this form, than in no form at all! Think over this saying, mine exalted friend: thou wilt readily divine that in such a saying there is wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003888": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003888",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He who said ‘God is a Spirit’—made the greatest stride and slide hitherto made on earth towards unbelief: such a dictum is not easily amended again on earth!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003889": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003889",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mine old heart leapeth and boundeth because there is still something to adore on earth. Forgive it, O Zarathustra, to an old, pious pontiff-heart!—”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003890": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003890",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“And thou,” said Zarathustra to the wanderer and shadow, “thou callest and thinkest thyself a free spirit? And thou here practisest such idolatry and hierolatry?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003891": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003891",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Worse verily, doest thou here than with thy bad brown girls, thou bad, new believer!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003892": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003892",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“It is sad enough,” answered the wanderer and shadow, “thou art right: but how can I help it! The old God liveth again, O Zarathustra, thou mayst say what thou wilt.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003893": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003893",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The ugliest man is to blame for it all: he hath reawakened him. And if he say that he once killed him, with Gods DEATH is always just a prejudice.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003894": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003894",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“And thou,” said Zarathustra, “thou bad old magician, what didst thou do! Who ought to believe any longer in thee in this free age, when THOU believest in such divine donkeyism?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003895": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003895",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It was a stupid thing that thou didst; how couldst thou, a shrewd man, do such a stupid thing!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003896": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003896",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” answered the shrewd magician, “thou art right, it was a stupid thing,—it was also repugnant to me.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003897": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003897",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“And thou even,” said Zarathustra to the spiritually conscientious one, “consider, and put thy finger to thy nose! Doth nothing go against thy conscience here? Is thy spirit not too cleanly for this praying and the fumes of those devotees?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003898": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003898",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“There is something therein,” said the spiritually conscientious one, and put his finger to his nose, “there is something in this spectacle which even doeth good to my conscience.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003899": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003899",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Perhaps I dare not believe in God: certain it is however, that God seemeth to me most worthy of belief in this form.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003900": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003900",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God is said to be eternal, according to the testimony of the most pious: he who hath so much time taketh his time. As slow and as stupid as possible: THEREBY can such a one nevertheless go very far.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003901": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003901",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And he who hath too much spirit might well become infatuated with stupidity and folly. Think of thyself, O Zarathustra!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003902": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003902",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou thyself—verily! even thou couldst well become an ass through superabundance of wisdom.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003903": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003903",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Doth not the true sage willingly walk on the crookedest paths? The evidence teacheth it, O Zarathustra,—THINE OWN evidence!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003904": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003904",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—“And thou thyself, finally,” said Zarathustra, and turned towards the ugliest man, who still lay on the ground stretching up his arm to the ass (for he gave it wine to drink). “Say, thou nondescript, what hast thou been about!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003905": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003905",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou seemest to me transformed, thine eyes glow, the mantle of the sublime covereth thine ugliness: WHAT didst thou do?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003906": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003906",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Is it then true what they say, that thou hast again awakened him? And why? Was he not for good reasons killed and made away with?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003907": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003907",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou thyself seemest to me awakened: what didst thou do? why didst THOU turn round? Why didst THOU get converted? Speak, thou nondescript!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003908": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003908",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O Zarathustra,” answered the ugliest man, “thou art a rogue!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003909": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003909",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Whether HE yet liveth, or again liveth, or is thoroughly dead—which of us both knoweth that best? I ask thee.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003910": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003910",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>One thing however do I know,—from thyself did I learn it once, O Zarathustra: he who wanteth to kill most thoroughly, LAUGHETH.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003911": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003911",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Not by wrath but by laughter doth one kill’—thus spakest thou once, O Zarathustra, thou hidden one, thou destroyer without wrath, thou dangerous saint,—thou art a rogue!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003912": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003912",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003913": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003913",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then, however, did it come to pass that Zarathustra, astonished at such merely roguish answers, jumped back to the door of his cave, and turning towards all his guests, cried out with a strong voice:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003914": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003914",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“O ye wags, all of you, ye buffoons! Why do ye dissemble and disguise yourselves before me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003915": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003915",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How the hearts of all of you convulsed with delight and wickedness, because ye had at last become again like little children—namely, pious,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003916": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003916",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Because ye at last did again as children do—namely, prayed, folded your hands and said ‘good God’!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003917": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003917",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But now leave, I pray you, THIS nursery, mine own cave, where to-day all childishness is carried on. Cool down, here outside, your hot child-wantonness and heart-tumult!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003918": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003918",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To be sure: except ye become as little children ye shall not enter into THAT kingdom of heaven.” (And Zarathustra pointed aloft with his hands.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003919": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003919",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“But we do not at all want to enter into the kingdom of heaven: we have become men,—SO WE WANT THE KINGDOM OF EARTH.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003920": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003920",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003921": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003921",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And once more began Zarathustra to speak. “O my new friends,” said he,— “ye strange ones, ye higher men, how well do ye now please me,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003922": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003922",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Since ye have again become joyful! Ye have, verily, all blossomed forth: it seemeth to me that for such flowers as you, NEW FESTIVALS are required.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003923": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003923",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A little valiant nonsense, some divine service and ass-festival, some old joyful Zarathustra fool, some blusterer to blow your souls bright.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003924": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003924",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Forget not this night and this ass-festival, ye higher men! THAT did ye devise when with me, that do I take as a good omen,—such things only the convalescents devise!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003925": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003925",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And should ye celebrate it again, this ass-festival, do it from love to yourselves, do it also from love to me! And in remembrance of me!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003926": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003926",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003927": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003927",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003928": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003928",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003929": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003929",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXIX. THE DRUNKEN SONG.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003930": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003930",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>1.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003931": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003931",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Meanwhile one after another had gone out into the open air, and into the cool, thoughtful night; Zarathustra himself, however, led the ugliest man by the hand, that he might show him his night-world, and the great round moon, and the silvery water-falls near his cave. There they at last stood still beside one another; all of them old people, but with comforted, brave hearts, and astonished in themselves that it was so well with them on earth; the mystery of the night, however, came nigher and nigher to their hearts. And anew Zarathustra thought to himself: “Oh, how well do they now please me, these higher men!”—but he did not say it aloud, for he respected their happiness and their silence.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003932": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003932",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Then, however, there happened that which in this astonishing long day was most astonishing: the ugliest man began once more and for the last time to gurgle and snort, and when he had at length found expression, behold! there sprang a question plump and plain out of his mouth, a good, deep, clear question, which moved the hearts of all who listened to him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003933": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003933",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“My friends, all of you,” said the ugliest man, “what think ye? For the sake of this day—<i>I</i> am for the first time content to have lived mine entire life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003934": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003934",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And that I testify so much is still not enough for me. It is worth while living on the earth: one day, one festival with Zarathustra, hath taught me to love the earth.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003935": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003935",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>‘Was THAT—life?’ will I say unto death. ‘Well! Once more!’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003936": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003936",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My friends, what think ye? Will ye not, like me, say unto death: ‘Was THAT—life? For the sake of Zarathustra, well! Once more!’”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003937": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003937",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake the ugliest man; it was not, however, far from midnight. And what took place then, think ye? As soon as the higher men heard his question, they became all at once conscious of their transformation and convalescence, and of him who was the cause thereof: then did they rush up to Zarathustra, thanking, honouring, caressing him, and kissing his hands, each in his own peculiar way; so that some laughed and some wept. The old soothsayer, however, danced with delight; and though he was then, as some narrators suppose, full of sweet wine, he was certainly still fuller of sweet life, and had renounced all weariness. There are even those who narrate that the ass then danced: for not in vain had the ugliest man previously given it wine to drink. That may be the case, or it may be otherwise; and if in truth the ass did not dance that evening, there nevertheless happened then greater and rarer wonders than the dancing of an ass would have been. In short, as the proverb of Zarathustra saith: “What doth it matter!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003938": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003938",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003939": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003939",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When, however, this took place with the ugliest man, Zarathustra stood there like one drunken: his glance dulled, his tongue faltered and his feet staggered. And who could divine what thoughts then passed through Zarathustra’s soul? Apparently, however, his spirit retreated and fled in advance and was in remote distances, and as it were “wandering on high mountain-ridges,” as it standeth written, “‘twixt two seas,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003940": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003940",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Wandering ‘twixt the past and the future as a heavy cloud.” Gradually, however, while the higher men held him in their arms, he came back to himself a little, and resisted with his hands the crowd of the honouring and caring ones; but he did not speak. All at once, however, he turned his head quickly, for he seemed to hear something: then laid he his finger on his mouth and said: “COME!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003941": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003941",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And immediately it became still and mysterious round about; from the depth however there came up slowly the sound of a clock-bell. Zarathustra listened thereto, like the higher men; then, however, laid he his finger on his mouth the second time, and said again: “COME! COME! IT IS GETTING ON TO MIDNIGHT!”—and his voice had changed. But still he had not moved from the spot. Then it became yet stiller and more mysterious, and everything hearkened, even the ass, and Zarathustra’s noble animals, the eagle and the serpent,—likewise the cave of Zarathustra and the big cool moon, and the night itself. Zarathustra, however, laid his hand upon his mouth for the third time, and said:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003942": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003942",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>COME! COME! COME! LET US NOW WANDER! IT IS THE HOUR: LET US WANDER INTO THE NIGHT!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003943": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003943",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003944": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003944",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, it is getting on to midnight: then will I say something into your ears, as that old clock-bell saith it into mine ear,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003945": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003945",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—As mysteriously, as frightfully, and as cordially as that midnight clock-bell speaketh it to me, which hath experienced more than one man:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003946": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003946",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Which hath already counted the smarting throbbings of your fathers’ hearts—ah! ah! how it sigheth! how it laugheth in its dream! the old, deep, deep midnight!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003947": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003947",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Hush! Hush! Then is there many a thing heard which may not be heard by day; now however, in the cool air, when even all the tumult of your hearts hath become still,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003948": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003948",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Now doth it speak, now is it heard, now doth it steal into overwakeful, nocturnal souls: ah! ah! how the midnight sigheth! how it laugheth in its dream!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003949": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003949",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Hearest thou not how it mysteriously, frightfully, and cordially speaketh unto THEE, the old deep, deep midnight?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003950": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003950",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O MAN, TAKE HEED! 4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003951": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003951",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Woe to me! Whither hath time gone? Have I not sunk into deep wells? The world sleepeth—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003952": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003952",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ah! Ah! The dog howleth, the moon shineth. Rather will I die, rather will I die, than say unto you what my midnight-heart now thinketh.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003953": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003953",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Already have I died. It is all over. Spider, why spinnest thou around me? Wilt thou have blood? Ah! Ah! The dew falleth, the hour cometh—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003954": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003954",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The hour in which I frost and freeze, which asketh and asketh and asketh: “Who hath sufficient courage for it?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003955": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003955",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Who is to be master of the world? Who is going to say: THUS shall ye flow, ye great and small streams!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003956": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003956",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—The hour approacheth: O man, thou higher man, take heed! this talk is for fine ears, for thine ears—WHAT SAITH DEEP MIDNIGHT’S VOICE INDEED?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003957": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003957",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>5.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003958": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003958",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It carrieth me away, my soul danceth. Day’s-work! Day’s-work! Who is to be master of the world?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003959": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003959",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The moon is cool, the wind is still. Ah! Ah! Have ye already flown high enough? Ye have danced: a leg, nevertheless, is not a wing.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003960": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003960",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye good dancers, now is all delight over: wine hath become lees, every cup hath become brittle, the sepulchres mutter.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003961": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003961",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye have not flown high enough: now do the sepulchres mutter: “Free the dead! Why is it so long night? Doth not the moon make us drunken?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003962": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003962",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, free the sepulchres, awaken the corpses! Ah, why doth the worm still burrow? There approacheth, there approacheth, the hour,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003963": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003963",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—There boometh the clock-bell, there thrilleth still the heart, there burroweth still the wood-worm, the heart-worm. Ah! Ah! THE WORLD IS DEEP!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003964": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003964",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003965": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003965",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sweet lyre! Sweet lyre! I love thy tone, thy drunken, ranunculine tone!—how long, how far hath come unto me thy tone, from the distance, from the ponds of love!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003966": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003966",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou old clock-bell, thou sweet lyre! Every pain hath torn thy heart, father-pain, fathers’-pain, forefathers’-pain; thy speech hath become ripe,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003967": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003967",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ripe like the golden autumn and the afternoon, like mine anchorite heart—now sayest thou: The world itself hath become ripe, the grape turneth brown,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003968": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003968",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Now doth it wish to die, to die of happiness. Ye higher men, do ye not feel it? There welleth up mysteriously an odour,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003969": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003969",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A perfume and odour of eternity, a rosy-blessed, brown, gold-wine-odour of old happiness,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003970": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003970",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Of drunken midnight-death happiness, which singeth: the world is deep, AND DEEPER THAN THE DAY COULD READ!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003971": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003971",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>7.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003972": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003972",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Leave me alone! Leave me alone! I am too pure for thee. Touch me not! Hath not my world just now become perfect?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003973": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003973",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My skin is too pure for thy hands. Leave me alone, thou dull, doltish, stupid day! Is not the midnight brighter?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003974": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003974",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The purest are to be masters of the world, the least known, the strongest, the midnight-souls, who are brighter and deeper than any day.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003975": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003975",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O day, thou gropest for me? Thou feelest for my happiness? For thee am I rich, lonesome, a treasure-pit, a gold chamber?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003976": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003976",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O world, thou wantest ME? Am I worldly for thee? Am I spiritual for thee? Am I divine for thee? But day and world, ye are too coarse,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003977": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003977",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Have cleverer hands, grasp after deeper happiness, after deeper unhappiness, grasp after some God; grasp not after me:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003978": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003978",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Mine unhappiness, my happiness is deep, thou strange day, but yet am I no God, no God’s-hell: DEEP IS ITS WOE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003979": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003979",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>8.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003980": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003980",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>God’s woe is deeper, thou strange world! Grasp at God’s woe, not at me! What am I! A drunken sweet lyre,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003981": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003981",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—A midnight-lyre, a bell-frog, which no one understandeth, but which MUST speak before deaf ones, ye higher men! For ye do not understand me!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003982": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003982",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Gone! Gone! O youth! O noontide! O afternoon! Now have come evening and night and midnight,—the dog howleth, the wind:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003983": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003983",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Is the wind not a dog? It whineth, it barketh, it howleth. Ah! Ah! how she sigheth! how she laugheth, how she wheezeth and panteth, the midnight!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003984": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003984",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>How she just now speaketh soberly, this drunken poetess! hath she perhaps overdrunk her drunkenness? hath she become overawake? doth she ruminate?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003985": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003985",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Her woe doth she ruminate over, in a dream, the old, deep midnight—and still more her joy. For joy, although woe be deep, JOY IS DEEPER STILL THAN GRIEF CAN BE.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003986": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003986",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>9.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003987": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003987",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thou grape-vine! Why dost thou praise me? Have I not cut thee! I am cruel, thou bleedest—: what meaneth thy praise of my drunken cruelty?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003988": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003988",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Whatever hath become perfect, everything mature—wanteth to die!” so sayest thou. Blessed, blessed be the vintner’s knife! But everything immature wanteth to live: alas!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003989": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003989",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Woe saith: “Hence! Go! Away, thou woe!” But everything that suffereth wanteth to live, that it may become mature and lively and longing,</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003990": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003990",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Longing for the further, the higher, the brighter. “I want heirs,” so saith everything that suffereth, “I want children, I do not want MYSELF,”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003991": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003991",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Joy, however, doth not want heirs, it doth not want children,—joy wanteth itself, it wanteth eternity, it wanteth recurrence, it wanteth everything eternally-like-itself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003992": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003992",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Woe saith: “Break, bleed, thou heart! Wander, thou leg! Thou wing, fly! Onward! upward! thou pain!” Well! Cheer up! O mine old heart: WOE SAITH: “HENCE! GO!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003993": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003993",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>10.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003994": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003994",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, what think ye? Am I a soothsayer? Or a dreamer? Or a drunkard? Or a dream-reader? Or a midnight-bell?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003995": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003995",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Or a drop of dew? Or a fume and fragrance of eternity? Hear ye it not? Smell ye it not? Just now hath my world become perfect, midnight is also mid-day,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003996": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003996",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pain is also a joy, curse is also a blessing, night is also a sun,—go away! or ye will learn that a sage is also a fool.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003997": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003997",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Said ye ever Yea to one joy? O my friends, then said ye Yea also unto ALL woe. All things are enlinked, enlaced and enamoured,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003998": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003998",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Wanted ye ever once to come twice; said ye ever: “Thou pleasest me, happiness! Instant! Moment!” then wanted ye ALL to come back again!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003999": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000003999",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—All anew, all eternal, all enlinked, enlaced and enamoured, Oh, then did ye LOVE the world,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004000": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004000",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Ye eternal ones, ye love it eternally and for all time: and also unto woe do ye say: Hence! Go! but come back! FOR JOYS ALL WANT—ETERNITY!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004001": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004001",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>11.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004002": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004002",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All joy wanteth the eternity of all things, it wanteth honey, it wanteth lees, it wanteth drunken midnight, it wanteth graves, it wanteth grave-tears’ consolation, it wanteth gilded evening-red—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004003": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004003",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—WHAT doth not joy want! it is thirstier, heartier, hungrier, more frightful, more mysterious, than all woe: it wanteth ITSELF, it biteth into ITSELF, the ring’s will writheth in it,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004004": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004004",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—It wanteth love, it wanteth hate, it is over-rich, it bestoweth, it throweth away, it beggeth for some one to take from it, it thanketh the taker, it would fain be hated,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004005": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004005",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—So rich is joy that it thirsteth for woe, for hell, for hate, for shame, for the lame, for the WORLD,—for this world, Oh, ye know it indeed!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004006": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004006",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Ye higher men, for you doth it long, this joy, this irrepressible, blessed joy—for your woe, ye failures! For failures, longeth all eternal joy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004007": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004007",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>For joys all want themselves, therefore do they also want grief! O happiness, O pain! Oh break, thou heart! Ye higher men, do learn it, that joys want eternity.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004008": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004008",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Joys want the eternity of ALL things, they WANT DEEP, PROFOUND ETERNITY!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004009": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004009",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>12.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004010": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004010",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Have ye now learned my song? Have ye divined what it would say? Well! Cheer up! Ye higher men, sing now my roundelay!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004011": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004011",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Sing now yourselves the song, the name of which is “Once more,” the signification of which is “Unto all eternity!”—sing, ye higher men, Zarathustra’s roundelay!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004012": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004012",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"pgmonospaced\">     O man!  Take heed!\n<br>     What saith deep midnight’s voice indeed?\n<br>     “I slept my sleep—,\n<br>     “From deepest dream I’ve woke, and plead:—\n<br>     “The world is deep,\n<br>     “And deeper than the day could read.\n<br>     “Deep is its woe—,\n<br>     “Joy—deeper still than grief can be:\n<br>     “Woe saith:  Hence!  Go!\n<br>     “But joys all want eternity-,\n<br>     “-Want deep, profound eternity!”\n<br> </div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004013": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004013",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004014": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004014",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004015": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004015",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>LXXX. THE SIGN.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004016": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004016",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the morning, however, after this night, Zarathustra jumped up from his couch, and, having girded his loins, he came out of his cave glowing and strong, like a morning sun coming out of gloomy mountains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004017": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004017",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thou great star,” spake he, as he had spoken once before, “thou deep eye of happiness, what would be all thy happiness if thou hadst not THOSE for whom thou shinest!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004018": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004018",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>And if they remained in their chambers whilst thou art already awake, and comest and bestowest and distributest, how would thy proud modesty upbraid for it!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004019": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004019",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! they still sleep, these higher men, whilst <i>I</i> am awake: THEY are not my proper companions! Not for them do I wait here in my mountains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004020": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004020",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At my work I want to be, at my day: but they understand not what are the signs of my morning, my step—is not for them the awakening-call.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004021": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004021",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>They still sleep in my cave; their dream still drinketh at my drunken songs. The audient ear for ME—the OBEDIENT ear, is yet lacking in their limbs.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004022": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004022",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—This had Zarathustra spoken to his heart when the sun arose: then looked he inquiringly aloft, for he heard above him the sharp call of his eagle. “Well!” called he upwards, “thus is it pleasing and proper to me. Mine animals are awake, for I am awake.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004023": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004023",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Mine eagle is awake, and like me honoureth the sun. With eagle-talons doth it grasp at the new light. Ye are my proper animals; I love you.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004024": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004024",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But still do I lack my proper men!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004025": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004025",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra; then, however, it happened that all on a sudden he became aware that he was flocked around and fluttered around, as if by innumerable birds,—the whizzing of so many wings, however, and the crowding around his head was so great that he shut his eyes. And verily, there came down upon him as it were a cloud, like a cloud of arrows which poureth upon a new enemy. But behold, here it was a cloud of love, and showered upon a new friend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004026": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004026",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What happeneth unto me?” thought Zarathustra in his astonished heart, and slowly seated himself on the big stone which lay close to the exit from his cave. But while he grasped about with his hands, around him, above him and below him, and repelled the tender birds, behold, there then happened to him something still stranger: for he grasped thereby unawares into a mass of thick, warm, shaggy hair; at the same time, however, there sounded before him a roar,—a long, soft lion-roar.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004027": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004027",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“THE SIGN COMETH,” said Zarathustra, and a change came over his heart. And in truth, when it turned clear before him, there lay a yellow, powerful animal at his feet, resting its head on his knee,—unwilling to leave him out of love, and doing like a dog which again findeth its old master. The doves, however, were no less eager with their love than the lion; and whenever a dove whisked over its nose, the lion shook its head and wondered and laughed.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004028": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004028",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When all this went on Zarathustra spake only a word: “MY CHILDREN ARE NIGH, MY CHILDREN”—, then he became quite mute. His heart, however, was loosed, and from his eyes there dropped down tears and fell upon his hands. And he took no further notice of anything, but sat there motionless, without repelling the animals further. Then flew the doves to and fro, and perched on his shoulder, and caressed his white hair, and did not tire of their tenderness and joyousness. The strong lion, however, licked always the tears that fell on Zarathustra’s hands, and roared and growled shyly. Thus did these animals do.—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004029": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004029",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>All this went on for a long time, or a short time: for properly speaking, there is NO time on earth for such things—. Meanwhile, however, the higher men had awakened in Zarathustra’s cave, and marshalled themselves for a procession to go to meet Zarathustra, and give him their morning greeting: for they had found when they awakened that he no longer tarried with them. When, however, they reached the door of the cave and the noise of their steps had preceded them, the lion started violently; it turned away all at once from Zarathustra, and roaring wildly, sprang towards the cave. The higher men, however, when they heard the lion roaring, cried all aloud as with one voice, fled back and vanished in an instant.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004030": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004030",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra himself, however, stunned and strange, rose from his seat, looked around him, stood there astonished, inquired of his heart, bethought himself, and remained alone. “What did I hear?” said he at last, slowly, “what happened unto me just now?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004031": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004031",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>But soon there came to him his recollection, and he took in at a glance all that had taken place between yesterday and to-day. “Here is indeed the stone,” said he, and stroked his beard, “on IT sat I yester-morn; and here came the soothsayer unto me, and here heard I first the cry which I heard just now, the great cry of distress.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004032": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004032",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>O ye higher men, YOUR distress was it that the old soothsayer foretold to me yester-morn,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004033": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004033",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—Unto your distress did he want to seduce and tempt me: ‘O Zarathustra,’ said he to me, ‘I come to seduce thee to thy last sin.’</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004034": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004034",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>To my last sin?” cried Zarathustra, and laughed angrily at his own words: “WHAT hath been reserved for me as my last sin?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004035": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004035",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>—And once more Zarathustra became absorbed in himself, and sat down again on the big stone and meditated. Suddenly he sprang up,—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004036": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004036",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“FELLOW-SUFFERING! FELLOW-SUFFERING WITH THE HIGHER MEN!” he cried out, and his countenance changed into brass. “Well! THAT—hath had its time!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004037": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004037",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>My suffering and my fellow-suffering—what matter about them! Do I then strive after HAPPINESS? I strive after my WORK!</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004038": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004038",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Well! The lion hath come, my children are nigh, Zarathustra hath grown ripe, mine hour hath come:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004039": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004039",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is MY morning, MY day beginneth: ARISE NOW, ARISE, THOU GREAT NOONTIDE!”—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004040": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004040",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Thus spake Zarathustra and left his cave, glowing and strong, like a morning sun coming out of gloomy mountains.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004041": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004041",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><br>\n<br></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004042": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004042",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\">\n\n</div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004043": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004043",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><br>\n<br>\n<a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004044": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004044",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004045": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004045",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>APPENDIX.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004046": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004046",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004047": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004047",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004048": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004048",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>NOTES ON “THUS SPAKE ZARATHUSTRA” BY ANTHONY M. LUDOVICI.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004049": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004049",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I have had some opportunities of studying the conditions under which Nietzsche is read in Germany, France, and England, and I have found that, in each of these countries, students of his philosophy, as if actuated by precisely similar motives and desires, and misled by the same mistaken tactics on the part of most publishers, all proceed in the same happy-go-lucky style when “taking him up.” They have had it said to them that he wrote without any system, and they very naturally conclude that it does not matter in the least whether they begin with his first, third, or last book, provided they can obtain a few vague ideas as to what his leading and most sensational principles were.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004050": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004050",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, it is clear that the book with the most mysterious, startling, or suggestive title, will always stand the best chance of being purchased by those who have no other criteria to guide them in their choice than the aspect of a title-page; and this explains why “Thus Spake Zarathustra” is almost always the first and often the only one of Nietzsche’s books that falls into the hands of the uninitiated.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004051": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004051",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The title suggests all kinds of mysteries; a glance at the chapter-headings quickly confirms the suspicions already aroused, and the sub-title: “A Book for All and None”, generally succeeds in dissipating the last doubts the prospective purchaser may entertain concerning his fitness for the book or its fitness for him. And what happens?</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004052": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004052",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Thus Spake Zarathustra” is taken home; the reader, who perchance may know no more concerning Nietzsche than a magazine article has told him, tries to read it and, understanding less than half he reads, probably never gets further than the second or third part,—and then only to feel convinced that Nietzsche himself was “rather hazy” as to what he was talking about. Such chapters as “The Child with the Mirror”, “In the Happy Isles”, “The Grave-Song,” “Immaculate Perception,” “The Stillest Hour”, “The Seven Seals”, and many others, are almost utterly devoid of meaning to all those who do not know something of Nietzsche’s life, his aims and his friendships.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004053": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004053",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>As a matter of fact, “Thus Spake Zarathustra”, though it is unquestionably Nietzsche’s opus magnum, is by no means the first of Nietzsche’s works that the beginner ought to undertake to read. The author himself refers to it as the deepest work ever offered to the German public, and elsewhere speaks of his other writings as being necessary for the understanding of it. But when it is remembered that in Zarathustra we not only have the history of his most intimate experiences, friendships, feuds, disappointments, triumphs and the like, but that the very form in which they are narrated is one which tends rather to obscure than to throw light upon them, the difficulties which meet the reader who starts quite unprepared will be seen to be really formidable.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004054": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004054",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra, then,—this shadowy, allegorical personality, speaking in allegories and parables, and at times not even refraining from relating his own dreams—is a figure we can understand but very imperfectly if we have no knowledge of his creator and counterpart, Friedrich Nietzsche; and it were therefore well, previous to our study of the more abstruse parts of this book, if we were to turn to some authoritative book on Nietzsche’s life and works and to read all that is there said on the subject. Those who can read German will find an excellent guide, in this respect, in Frau Foerster-Nietzsche’s exhaustive and highly interesting biography of her brother: “Das Leben Friedrich Nietzsche’s” (published by Naumann); while the works of Deussen, Raoul Richter, and Baroness Isabelle von Unger-Sternberg, will be found to throw useful and necessary light upon many questions which it would be difficult for a sister to touch upon.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004055": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004055",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In regard to the actual philosophical views expounded in this work, there is an excellent way of clearing up any difficulties they may present, and that is by an appeal to Nietzsche’s other works. Again and again, of course, he will be found to express himself so clearly that all reference to his other writings may be dispensed with; but where this is not the case, the advice he himself gives is after all the best to be followed here, viz.:—to regard such works as: “Joyful Science”, “Beyond Good and Evil”, “The Genealogy of Morals”, “The Twilight of the Idols”, “The Antichrist”, “The Will to Power”, etc., etc., as the necessary preparation for “Thus Spake Zarathustra”.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004056": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004056",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These directions, though they are by no means simple to carry out, seem at least to possess the quality of definiteness and straightforwardness. “Follow them and all will be clear,” I seem to imply. But I regret to say that this is not really the case. For my experience tells me that even after the above directions have been followed with the greatest possible zeal, the student will still halt in perplexity before certain passages in the book before us, and wonder what they mean. Now, it is with the view of giving a little additional help to all those who find themselves in this position that I proceed to put forth my own personal interpretation of the more abstruse passages in this work.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004057": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004057",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In offering this little commentary to the Nietzsche student, I should like it to be understood that I make no claim as to its infallibility or indispensability. It represents but an attempt on my part—a very feeble one perhaps—to give the reader what little help I can in surmounting difficulties which a long study of Nietzsche’s life and works has enabled me, partially I hope, to overcome.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004058": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004058",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>...</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004059": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004059",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Perhaps it would be as well to start out with a broad and rapid sketch of Nietzsche as a writer on Morals, Evolution, and Sociology, so that the reader may be prepared to pick out for himself, so to speak, all passages in this work bearing in any way upon Nietzsche’s views in those three important branches of knowledge.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004060": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004060",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(A.) Nietzsche and Morality.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004061": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004061",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In morality, Nietzsche starts out by adopting the position of the relativist. He says there are no absolute values “good” and “evil”; these are mere means adopted by all in order to acquire power to maintain their place in the world, or to become supreme. It is the lion’s good to devour an antelope. It is the dead-leaf butterfly’s good to tell a foe a falsehood. For when the dead-leaf butterfly is in danger, it clings to the side of a twig, and what it says to its foe is practically this: “I am not a butterfly, I am a dead leaf, and can be of no use to thee.” This is a lie which is good to the butterfly, for it preserves it. In nature every species of organic being instinctively adopts and practises those acts which most conduce to the prevalence or supremacy of its kind. Once the most favourable order of conduct is found, proved efficient and established, it becomes the ruling morality of the species that adopts it and bears them along to victory. All species must not and cannot value alike, for what is the lion’s good is the antelope’s evil and vice versa.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004062": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004062",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Concepts of good and evil are therefore, in their origin, merely a means to an end, they are expedients for acquiring power.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004063": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004063",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Applying this principle to mankind, Nietzsche attacked Christian moral values. He declared them to be, like all other morals, merely an expedient for protecting a certain type of man. In the case of Christianity this type was, according to Nietzsche, a low one.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004064": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004064",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Conflicting moral codes have been no more than the conflicting weapons of different classes of men; for in mankind there is a continual war between the powerful, the noble, the strong, and the well-constituted on the one side, and the impotent, the mean, the weak, and the ill-constituted on the other. The war is a war of moral principles. The morality of the powerful class, Nietzsche calls NOBLE- or MASTER-MORALITY; that of the weak and subordinate class he calls SLAVE-MORALITY. In the first morality it is the eagle which, looking down upon a browsing lamb, contends that “eating lamb is good.” In the second, the slave-morality, it is the lamb which, looking up from the sward, bleats dissentingly: “Eating lamb is evil.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004065": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004065",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(B.) The Master- and Slave-Morality Compared.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004066": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004066",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The first morality is active, creative, Dionysian. The second is passive, defensive,—to it belongs the “struggle for existence.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004067": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004067",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Where attempts have not been made to reconcile the two moralities, they may be described as follows:—All is GOOD in the noble morality which proceeds from strength, power, health, well-constitutedness, happiness, and awfulness; for, the motive force behind the people practising it is “the struggle for power.” The antithesis “good and bad” to this first class means the same as “noble” and “despicable.” “Bad” in the master-morality must be applied to the coward, to all acts that spring from weakness, to the man with “an eye to the main chance,” who would forsake everything in order to live.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004068": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004068",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>With the second, the slave-morality, the case is different. There, inasmuch as the community is an oppressed, suffering, unemancipated, and weary one, all THAT will be held to be good which alleviates the state of suffering. Pity, the obliging hand, the warm heart, patience, industry, and humility—these are unquestionably the qualities we shall here find flooded with the light of approval and admiration; because they are the most USEFUL qualities—; they make life endurable, they are of assistance in the “struggle for existence” which is the motive force behind the people practising this morality. To this class, all that is AWFUL is bad, in fact it is THE evil par excellence. Strength, health, superabundance of animal spirits and power, are regarded with hate, suspicion, and fear by the subordinate class.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004069": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004069",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now Nietzsche believed that the first or the noble-morality conduced to an ascent in the line of life; because it was creative and active. On the other hand, he believed that the second or slave-morality, where it became paramount, led to degeneration, because it was passive and defensive, wanting merely to keep those who practised it alive. Hence his earnest advocacy of noble-morality.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004070": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004070",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(C.) Nietzsche and Evolution.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004071": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004071",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche as an evolutionist I shall have occasion to define and discuss in the course of these notes (see Notes on Chapter LVI., par.10, and on Chapter LVII.). For the present let it suffice for us to know that he accepted the “Development Hypothesis” as an explanation of the origin of species: but he did not halt where most naturalists have halted. He by no means regarded man as the highest possible being which evolution could arrive at; for though his physical development may have reached its limit, this is not the case with his mental or spiritual attributes. If the process be a fact; if things have BECOME what they are, then, he contends, we may describe no limit to man’s aspirations. If he struggled up from barbarism, and still more remotely from the lower Primates, his ideal should be to surpass man himself and reach Superman (see especially the Prologue).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004072": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004072",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(D.) Nietzsche and Sociology.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004073": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004073",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche as a sociologist aims at an aristocratic arrangement of society. He would have us rear an ideal race. Honest and truthful in intellectual matters, he could not even think that men are equal. “With these preachers of equality will I not be mixed up and confounded. For thus speaketh justice unto ME: ‘Men are not equal.’” He sees precisely in this inequality a purpose to be served, a condition to be exploited. “Every elevation of the type ‘man,’” he writes in “Beyond Good and Evil”, “has hitherto been the work of an aristocratic society—and so will it always be—a society believing in a long scale of gradations of rank and differences of worth among human beings.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004074": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004074",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Those who are sufficiently interested to desire to read his own detailed account of the society he would fain establish, will find an excellent passage in Aphorism 57 of “The Antichrist”.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004075": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004075",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>... <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004076": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004076",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004077": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004077",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>PART I. THE PROLOGUE.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004078": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004078",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In Part I. including the Prologue, no very great difficulties will appear. Zarathustra’s habit of designating a whole class of men or a whole school of thought by a single fitting nickname may perhaps lead to a little confusion at first; but, as a rule, when the general drift of his arguments is grasped, it requires but a slight effort of the imagination to discover whom he is referring to. In the ninth paragraph of the Prologue, for instance, it is quite obvious that “Herdsmen” in the verse “Herdsmen, I say, etc., etc.,” stands for all those to-day who are the advocates of gregariousness—of the ant-hill. And when our author says: “A robber shall Zarathustra be called by the herdsmen,” it is clear that these words may be taken almost literally from one whose ideal was the rearing of a higher aristocracy. Again, “the good and just,” throughout the book, is the expression used in referring to the self-righteous of modern times,—those who are quite sure that they know all that is to be known concerning good and evil, and are satisfied that the values their little world of tradition has handed down to them, are destined to rule mankind as long as it lasts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004079": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004079",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the last paragraph of the Prologue, verse 7, Zarathustra gives us a foretaste of his teaching concerning the big and the little sagacities, expounded subsequently. He says he would he were as wise as his serpent; this desire will be found explained in the discourse entitled “The Despisers of the Body”, which I shall have occasion to refer to later.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004080": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004080",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>... THE DISCOURSES. <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004081": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004081",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004082": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004082",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter I. The Three Metamorphoses.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004083": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004083",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This opening discourse is a parable in which Zarathustra discloses the mental development of all creators of new values. It is the story of a life which reaches its consummation in attaining to a second ingenuousness or in returning to childhood. Nietzsche, the supposed anarchist, here plainly disclaims all relationship whatever to anarchy, for he shows us that only by bearing the burdens of the existing law and submitting to it patiently, as the camel submits to being laden, does the free spirit acquire that ascendancy over tradition which enables him to meet and master the dragon “Thou shalt,”—the dragon with the values of a thousand years glittering on its scales. There are two lessons in this discourse: first, that in order to create one must be as a little child; secondly, that it is only through existing law and order that one attains to that height from which new law and new order may be promulgated.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004084": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004084",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004085": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004085",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004086": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004086",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter II. The Academic Chairs of Virtue.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004087": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004087",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Almost the whole of this is quite comprehensible. It is a discourse against all those who confound virtue with tameness and smug ease, and who regard as virtuous only that which promotes security and tends to deepen sleep.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004088": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004088",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004089": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004089",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004090": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004090",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter IV. The Despisers of the Body.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004091": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004091",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here Zarathustra gives names to the intellect and the instincts; he calls the one “the little sagacity” and the latter “the big sagacity.” Schopenhauer’s teaching concerning the intellect is fully endorsed here. “An instrument of thy body is also thy little sagacity, my brother, which thou callest ‘spirit,’” says Zarathustra. From beginning to end it is a warning to those who would think too lightly of the instincts and unduly exalt the intellect and its derivatives: Reason and Understanding.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004092": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004092",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004093": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004093",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004094": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004094",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter IX. The Preachers of Death.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004095": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004095",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is an analysis of the psychology of all those who have the “evil eye” and are pessimists by virtue of their constitutions.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004096": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004096",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004097": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004097",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004098": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004098",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XV. The Thousand and One Goals.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004099": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004099",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In this discourse Zarathustra opens his exposition of the doctrine of relativity in morality, and declares all morality to be a mere means to power. Needless to say that verses 9, 10, 11, and 12 refer to the Greeks, the Persians, the Jews, and the Germans respectively. In the penultimate verse he makes known his discovery concerning the root of modern Nihilism and indifference,—i.e., that modern man has no goal, no aim, no ideals (see Note A).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004100": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004100",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004101": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004101",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004102": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004102",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XVIII. Old and Young Women.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004103": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004103",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche’s views on women have either to be loved at first sight or they become perhaps the greatest obstacle in the way of those who otherwise would be inclined to accept his philosophy. Women especially, of course, have been taught to dislike them, because it has been rumoured that his views are unfriendly to themselves. Now, to my mind, all this is pure misunderstanding and error.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004104": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004104",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>German philosophers, thanks to Schopenhauer, have earned rather a bad name for their views on women. It is almost impossible for one of them to write a line on the subject, however kindly he may do so, without being suspected of wishing to open a crusade against the fair sex. Despite the fact, therefore, that all Nietzsche’s views in this respect were dictated to him by the profoundest love; despite Zarathustra’s reservation in this discourse, that “with women nothing (that can be said) is impossible,” and in the face of other overwhelming evidence to the contrary, Nietzsche is universally reported to have mis son pied dans le plat, where the female sex is concerned. And what is the fundamental doctrine which has given rise to so much bitterness and aversion?—Merely this: that the sexes are at bottom ANTAGONISTIC—that is to say, as different as blue is from yellow, and that the best possible means of rearing anything approaching a desirable race is to preserve and to foster this profound hostility. What Nietzsche strives to combat and to overthrow is the modern democratic tendency which is slowly labouring to level all things—even the sexes. His quarrel is not with women—what indeed could be more undignified?—it is with those who would destroy the natural relationship between the sexes, by modifying either the one or the other with a view to making them more alike. The human world is just as dependent upon women’s powers as upon men’s. It is women’s strongest and most valuable instincts which help to determine who are to be the fathers of the next generation. By destroying these particular instincts, that is to say by attempting to masculinise woman, and to feminise men, we jeopardise the future of our people. The general democratic movement of modern times, in its frantic struggle to mitigate all differences, is now invading even the world of sex. It is against this movement that Nietzsche raises his voice; he would have woman become ever more woman and man become ever more man. Only thus, and he is undoubtedly right, can their combined instincts lead to the excellence of humanity. Regarded in this light, all his views on woman appear not only necessary but just (see Note on Chapter LVI., par. 21.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004105": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004105",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is interesting to observe that the last line of the discourse, which has so frequently been used by women as a weapon against Nietzsche’s views concerning them, was suggested to Nietzsche by a woman (see “Das Leben F. Nietzsche’s”).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004106": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004106",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004107": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004107",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004108": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004108",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXI. Voluntary Death.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004109": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004109",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In regard to this discourse, I should only like to point out that Nietzsche had a particular aversion to the word “suicide”—self-murder. He disliked the evil it suggested, and in rechristening the act Voluntary Death, i.e., the death that comes from no other hand than one’s own, he was desirous of elevating it to the position it held in classical antiquity (see Aphorism 36 in “The Twilight of the Idols”).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004110": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004110",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004111": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004111",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004112": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004112",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXII. The Bestowing Virtue.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004113": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004113",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An important aspect of Nietzsche’s philosophy is brought to light in this discourse. His teaching, as is well known, places the Aristotelian man of spirit, above all others in the natural divisions of man. The man with overflowing strength, both of mind and body, who must discharge this strength or perish, is the Nietzschean ideal. To such a man, giving from his overflow becomes a necessity; bestowing develops into a means of existence, and this is the only giving, the only charity, that Nietzsche recognises. In paragraph 3 of the discourse, we read Zarathustra’s healthy exhortation to his disciples to become independent thinkers and to find themselves before they learn any more from him (see Notes on Chapters LVI., par. 5, and LXXIII., pars. 10, 11).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004114": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004114",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>... <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004115": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004115",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004116": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004116",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>PART II.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004117": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004117",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004118": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004118",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004119": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004119",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXIII. The Child with the Mirror.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004120": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004120",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche tells us here, in a poetical form, how deeply grieved he was by the manifold misinterpretations and misunderstandings which were becoming rife concerning his publications. He does not recognise himself in the mirror of public opinion, and recoils terrified from the distorted reflection of his features. In verse 20 he gives us a hint which it were well not to pass over too lightly; for, in the introduction to “The Genealogy of Morals” (written in 1887) he finds it necessary to refer to the matter again and with greater precision. The point is this, that a creator of new values meets with his surest and strongest obstacles in the very spirit of the language which is at his disposal. Words, like all other manifestations of an evolving race, are stamped with the values that have long been paramount in that race. Now, the original thinker who finds himself compelled to use the current speech of his country in order to impart new and hitherto untried views to his fellows, imposes a task upon the natural means of communication which it is totally unfitted to perform,—hence the obscurities and prolixities which are so frequently met with in the writings of original thinkers. In the “Dawn of Day”, Nietzsche actually cautions young writers against THE DANGER OF ALLOWING THEIR THOUGHTS TO BE MOULDED BY THE WORDS AT THEIR DISPOSAL.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004121": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004121",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004122": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004122",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004123": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004123",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXIV. In the Happy Isles.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004124": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004124",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>While writing this, Nietzsche is supposed to have been thinking of the island of Ischia which was ultimately destroyed by an earthquake. His teaching here is quite clear. He was among the first thinkers of Europe to overcome the pessimism which godlessness generally brings in its wake. He points to creating as the surest salvation from the suffering which is a concomitant of all higher life. “What would there be to create,” he asks, “if there were—Gods?” His ideal, the Superman, lends him the cheerfulness necessary to the overcoming of that despair usually attendant upon godlessness and upon the apparent aimlessness of a world without a god.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004125": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004125",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004126": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004126",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004127": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004127",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXIX. The Tarantulas.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004128": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004128",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The tarantulas are the Socialists and Democrats. This discourse offers us an analysis of their mental attitude. Nietzsche refuses to be confounded with those resentful and revengeful ones who condemn society FROM BELOW, and whose criticism is only suppressed envy. “There are those who preach my doctrine of life,” he says of the Nietzschean Socialists, “and are at the same time preachers of equality and tarantulas” (see Notes on Chapter XL. and Chapter LI.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004129": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004129",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004130": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004130",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004131": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004131",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXX. The Famous Wise Ones.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004132": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004132",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This refers to all those philosophers hitherto, who have run in the harness of established values and have not risked their reputation with the people in pursuit of truth. The philosopher, however, as Nietzsche understood him, is a man who creates new values, and thus leads mankind in a new direction.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004133": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004133",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004134": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004134",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004135": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004135",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXIII. The Grave-Song.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004136": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004136",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here Zarathustra sings about the ideals and friendships of his youth. Verses 27 to 31 undoubtedly refer to Richard Wagner (see Note on Chapter LXV.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004137": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004137",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004138": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004138",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004139": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004139",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXIV. Self-Surpassing.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004140": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004140",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In this discourse we get the best exposition in the whole book of Nietzsche’s doctrine of the Will to Power. I go into this question thoroughly in the Note on Chapter LVII.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004141": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004141",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche was not an iconoclast from choice. Those who hastily class him with the anarchists (or the Progressivists of the last century) fail to understand the high esteem in which he always held both law and discipline. In verse 41 of this most decisive discourse he truly explains his position when he says: “...he who hath to be a creator in good and evil—verily he hath first to be a destroyer, and break values in pieces.” This teaching in regard to self-control is evidence enough of his reverence for law.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004142": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004142",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004143": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004143",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004144": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004144",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXV. The Sublime Ones.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004145": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004145",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These belong to a type which Nietzsche did not altogether dislike, but which he would fain have rendered more subtle and plastic. It is the type that takes life and itself too seriously, that never surmounts the camel-stage mentioned in the first discourse, and that is obdurately sublime and earnest. To be able to smile while speaking of lofty things and NOT TO BE OPPRESSED by them, is the secret of real greatness. He whose hand trembles when it lays hold of a beautiful thing, has the quality of reverence, without the artist’s unembarrassed friendship with the beautiful. Hence the mistakes which have arisen in regard to confounding Nietzsche with his extreme opposites the anarchists and agitators. For what they dare to touch and break with the impudence and irreverence of the unappreciative, he seems likewise to touch and break,—but with other fingers—with the fingers of the loving and unembarrassed artist who is on good terms with the beautiful and who feels able to create it and to enhance it with his touch. The question of taste plays an important part in Nietzsche’s philosophy, and verses 9, 10 of this discourse exactly state Nietzsche’s ultimate views on the subject. In the “Spirit of Gravity”, he actually cries:—“Neither a good nor a bad taste, but MY taste, of which I have no longer either shame or secrecy.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004146": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004146",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004147": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004147",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004148": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004148",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXVI. The Land of Culture.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004149": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004149",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is a poetical epitome of some of the scathing criticism of scholars which appears in the first of the “Thoughts out of Season”—the polemical pamphlet (written in 1873) against David Strauss and his school. He reproaches his former colleagues with being sterile and shows them that their sterility is the result of their not believing in anything. “He who had to create, had always his presaging dreams and astral premonitions—and believed in believing!” (See Note on Chapter LXXVII.) In the last two verses he reveals the nature of his altruism. How far it differs from that of Christianity we have already read in the discourse “Neighbour-Love”, but here he tells us definitely the nature of his love to mankind; he explains why he was compelled to assail the Christian values of pity and excessive love of the neighbour, not only because they are slave-values and therefore tend to promote degeneration (see Note B.), but because he could only love his children’s land, the undiscovered land in a remote sea; because he would fain retrieve the errors of his fathers in his children.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004150": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004150",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004151": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004151",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004152": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004152",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXVII. Immaculate Perception.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004153": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004153",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>An important feature of Nietzsche’s interpretation of Life is disclosed in this discourse. As Buckle suggests in his “Influence of Women on the Progress of Knowledge”, the scientific spirit of the investigator is both helped and supplemented by the latter’s emotions and personality, and the divorce of all emotionalism and individual temperament from science is a fatal step towards sterility. Zarathustra abjures all those who would fain turn an IMPERSONAL eye upon nature and contemplate her phenomena with that pure objectivity to which the scientific idealists of to-day would so much like to attain. He accuses such idealists of hypocrisy and guile; he says they lack innocence in their desires and therefore slander all desiring.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004154": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004154",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004155": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004155",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004156": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004156",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXVIII. Scholars.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004157": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004157",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is a record of Nietzsche’s final breach with his former colleagues—the scholars of Germany. Already after the publication of the “Birth of Tragedy”, numbers of German philologists and professional philosophers had denounced him as one who had strayed too far from their flock, and his lectures at the University of Bale were deserted in consequence; but it was not until 1879, when he finally severed all connection with University work, that he may be said to have attained to the freedom and independence which stamp this discourse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004158": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004158",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004159": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004159",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004160": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004160",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XXXIX. Poets.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004161": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004161",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>People have sometimes said that Nietzsche had no sense of humour. I have no intention of defending him here against such foolish critics; I should only like to point out to the reader that we have him here at his best, poking fun at himself, and at his fellow-poets (see Note on Chapter LXIII., pars. 16, 17, 18, 19, 20).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004162": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004162",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004163": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004163",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004164": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004164",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XL. Great Events.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004165": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004165",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here we seem to have a puzzle. Zarathustra himself, while relating his experience with the fire-dog to his disciples, fails to get them interested in his narrative, and we also may be only too ready to turn over these pages under the impression that they are little more than a mere phantasy or poetical flight. Zarathustra’s interview with the fire-dog is, however, of great importance. In it we find Nietzsche face to face with the creature he most sincerely loathes—the spirit of revolution, and we obtain fresh hints concerning his hatred of the anarchist and rebel. “‘Freedom’ ye all roar most eagerly,” he says to the fire-dog, “but I have unlearned the belief in ‘Great Events’ when there is much roaring and smoke about them. Not around the inventors of new noise, but around the inventors of new values, doth the world revolve; INAUDIBLY it revolveth.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004166": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004166",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004167": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004167",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004168": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004168",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLI. The Soothsayer.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004169": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004169",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This refers, of course, to Schopenhauer. Nietzsche, as is well known, was at one time an ardent follower of Schopenhauer. He overcame Pessimism by discovering an object in existence; he saw the possibility of raising society to a higher level and preached the profoundest Optimism in consequence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004170": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004170",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004171": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004171",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004172": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004172",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLII. Redemption.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004173": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004173",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra here addresses cripples. He tells them of other cripples—the GREAT MEN in this world who have one organ or faculty inordinately developed at the cost of their other faculties. This is doubtless a reference to a fact which is too often noticeable in the case of so many of the world’s giants in art, science, or religion. In verse 19 we are told what Nietzsche called Redemption—that is to say, the ability to say of all that is past: “Thus would I have it.” The in ability to say this, and the resentment which results therefrom, he regards as the source of all our feelings of revenge, and all our desires to punish—punishment meaning to him merely a euphemism for the word revenge, invented in order to still our consciences. He who can be proud of his enemies, who can be grateful to them for the obstacles they have put in his way; he who can regard his worst calamity as but the extra strain on the bow of his life, which is to send the arrow of his longing even further than he could have hoped;—this man knows no revenge, neither does he know despair, he truly has found redemption and can turn on the worst in his life and even in himself, and call it his best (see Notes on Chapter LVII.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004174": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004174",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004175": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004175",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004176": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004176",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLIII. Manly Prudence.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004177": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004177",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This discourse is very important. In “Beyond Good and Evil” we hear often enough that the select and superior man must wear a mask, and here we find this injunction explained. “And he who would not languish amongst men, must learn to drink out of all glasses: and he who would keep clean amongst men, must know how to wash himself even with dirty water.” This, I venture to suggest, requires some explanation. At a time when individuality is supposed to be shown most tellingly by putting boots on one’s hands and gloves on one’s feet, it is somewhat refreshing to come across a true individualist who feels the chasm between himself and others so deeply, that he must perforce adapt himself to them outwardly, at least, in all respects, so that the inner difference should be overlooked. Nietzsche practically tells us here that it is not he who intentionally wears eccentric clothes or does eccentric things who is truly the individualist. The profound man, who is by nature differentiated from his fellows, feels this difference too keenly to call attention to it by any outward show. He is shamefast and bashful with those who surround him and wishes not to be discovered by them, just as one instinctively avoids all lavish display of comfort or wealth in the presence of a poor friend.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004178": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004178",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004179": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004179",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004180": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004180",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLIV. The Stillest Hour.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004181": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004181",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This seems to me to give an account of the great struggle which must have taken place in Nietzsche’s soul before he finally resolved to make known the more esoteric portions of his teaching. Our deepest feelings crave silence. There is a certain self-respect in the serious man which makes him hold his profoundest feelings sacred. Before they are uttered they are full of the modesty of a virgin, and often the oldest sage will blush like a girl when this virginity is violated by an indiscretion which forces him to reveal his deepest thoughts.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004182": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004182",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>... <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004183": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004183",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004184": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004184",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>PART III.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004185": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004185",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is perhaps the most important of all the four parts. If it contained only “The Vision and the Enigma” and “The Old and New Tables” I should still be of this opinion; for in the former of these discourses we meet with what Nietzsche regarded as the crowning doctrine of his philosophy and in “The Old and New Tables” we have a valuable epitome of practically all his leading principles.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004186": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004186",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004187": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004187",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004188": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004188",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLVI. The Vision and the Enigma.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004189": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004189",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“The Vision and the Enigma” is perhaps an example of Nietzsche in his most obscure vein. We must know how persistently he inveighed against the oppressing and depressing influence of man’s sense of guilt and consciousness of sin in order fully to grasp the significance of this discourse. Slowly but surely, he thought the values of Christianity and Judaic traditions had done their work in the minds of men. What were once but expedients devised for the discipline of a certain portion of humanity, had now passed into man’s blood and had become instincts. This oppressive and paralysing sense of guilt and of sin is what Nietzsche refers to when he speaks of “the spirit of gravity.” This creature half-dwarf, half-mole, whom he bears with him a certain distance on his climb and finally defies, and whom he calls his devil and arch-enemy, is nothing more than the heavy millstone “guilty conscience,” together with the concept of sin which at present hangs round the neck of men. To rise above it—to soar—is the most difficult of all things to-day. Nietzsche is able to think cheerfully and optimistically of the possibility of life in this world recurring again and again, when he has once cast the dwarf from his shoulders, and he announces his doctrine of the Eternal Recurrence of all things great and small to his arch-enemy and in defiance of him.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004190": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004190",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>That there is much to be said for Nietzsche’s hypothesis of the Eternal Recurrence of all things great and small, nobody who has read the literature on the subject will doubt for an instant; but it remains a very daring conjecture notwithstanding and even in its ultimate effect, as a dogma, on the minds of men, I venture to doubt whether Nietzsche ever properly estimated its worth (see Note on Chapter LVII.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004191": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004191",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>What follows is clear enough. Zarathustra sees a young shepherd struggling on the ground with a snake holding fast to the back of his throat. The sage, assuming that the snake must have crawled into the young man’s mouth while he lay sleeping, runs to his help and pulls at the loathsome reptile with all his might, but in vain. At last, in despair, Zarathustra appeals to the young man’s will. Knowing full well what a ghastly operation he is recommending, he nevertheless cries, “Bite! Bite! Its head off! Bite!” as the only possible solution of the difficulty. The young shepherd bites, and far away he spits the snake’s head, whereupon he rises, “No longer shepherd, no longer man—a transfigured being, a light-surrounded being, that LAUGHED! Never on earth laughed a man as he laughed!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004192": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004192",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In this parable the young shepherd is obviously the man of to-day; the snake that chokes him represents the stultifying and paralysing social values that threaten to shatter humanity, and the advice “Bite! Bite!” is but Nietzsche’s exasperated cry to mankind to alter their values before it is too late.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004193": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004193",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004194": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004194",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004195": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004195",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLVII. Involuntary Bliss.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004196": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004196",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, like “The Wanderer”, is one of the many introspective passages in the work, and is full of innuendos and hints as to the Nietzschean outlook on life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004197": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004197",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004198": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004198",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004199": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004199",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLVIII. Before Sunrise.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004200": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004200",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here we have a record of Zarathustra’s avowal of optimism, as also the important statement concerning “Chance” or “Accident” (verse 27). Those who are familiar with Nietzsche’s philosophy will not require to be told what an important role his doctrine of chance plays in his teaching. The Giant Chance has hitherto played with the puppet “man,”—this is the fact he cannot contemplate with equanimity. Man shall now exploit chance, he says again and again, and make it fall on its knees before him! (See verse 33 in “On the Olive Mount”, and verses 9-10 in “The Bedwarfing Virtue”).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004201": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004201",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004202": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004202",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004203": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004203",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter XLIX. The Bedwarfing Virtue.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004204": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004204",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This requires scarcely any comment. It is a satire on modern man and his belittling virtues. In verses 23 and 24 of the second part of the discourse we are reminded of Nietzsche’s powerful indictment of the great of to-day, in the Antichrist (Aphorism 43):—“At present nobody has any longer the courage for separate rights, for rights of domination, for a feeling of reverence for himself and his equals,—FOR PATHOS OF DISTANCE...Our politics are MORBID from this want of courage!—The aristocracy of character has been undermined most craftily by the lie of the equality of souls; and if the belief in the ‘privilege of the many,’ makes revolutions and WILL CONTINUE TO MAKE them, it is Christianity, let us not doubt it, it is CHRISTIAN valuations, which translate every revolution merely into blood and crime!” (see also “Beyond Good and Evil”, pages 120, 121). Nietzsche thought it was a bad sign of the times that even rulers have lost the courage of their positions, and that a man of Frederick the Great’s power and distinguished gifts should have been able to say: “Ich bin der erste Diener des Staates” (I am the first servant of the State.) To this utterance of the great sovereign, verse 24 undoubtedly refers. “Cowardice” and “Mediocrity,” are the names with which he labels modern notions of virtue and moderation.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004205": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004205",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In Part III., we get the sentiments of the discourse “In the Happy Isles”, but perhaps in stronger terms. Once again we find Nietzsche thoroughly at ease, if not cheerful, as an atheist, and speaking with vertiginous daring of making chance go on its knees to him. In verse 20, Zarathustra makes yet another attempt at defining his entirely anti-anarchical attitude, and unless such passages have been completely overlooked or deliberately ignored hitherto by those who will persist in laying anarchy at his door, it is impossible to understand how he ever became associated with that foul political party.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004206": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004206",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The last verse introduces the expression, “THE GREAT NOONTIDE!” In the poem to be found at the end of “Beyond Good and Evil”, we meet with the expression again, and we shall find it occurring time and again in Nietzsche’s works. It will be found fully elucidated in the fifth part of “The Twilight of the Idols”; but for those who cannot refer to this book, it were well to point out that Nietzsche called the present period—our period—the noon of man’s history. Dawn is behind us. The childhood of mankind is over. Now we KNOW; there is now no longer any excuse for mistakes which will tend to botch and disfigure the type man. “With respect to what is past,” he says, “I have, like all discerning ones, great toleration, that is to say, GENEROUS self-control...But my feeling changes suddenly, and breaks out as soon as I enter the modern period, OUR period. Our age KNOWS...” (See Note on Chapter LXX.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004207": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004207",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004208": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004208",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004209": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004209",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LI. On Passing-by.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004210": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004210",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here we find Nietzsche confronted with his extreme opposite, with him therefore for whom he is most frequently mistaken by the unwary. “Zarathustra’s ape” he is called in the discourse. He is one of those at whose hands Nietzsche had to suffer most during his life-time, and at whose hands his philosophy has suffered most since his death. In this respect it may seem a little trivial to speak of extremes meeting; but it is wonderfully apt. Many have adopted Nietzsche’s mannerisms and word-coinages, who had nothing in common with him beyond the ideas and “business” they plagiarised; but the superficial observer and a large portion of the public, not knowing of these things,—not knowing perhaps that there are iconoclasts who destroy out of love and are therefore creators, and that there are others who destroy out of resentment and revengefulness and who are therefore revolutionists and anarchists,—are prone to confound the two, to the detriment of the nobler type.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004211": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004211",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>If we now read what the fool says to Zarathustra, and note the tricks of speech he has borrowed from him: if we carefully follow the attitude he assumes, we shall understand why Zarathustra finally interrupts him. “Stop this at once,” Zarathustra cries, “long have thy speech and thy species disgusted me...Out of love alone shall my contempt and my warning bird take wing; BUT NOT OUT OF THE SWAMP!” It were well if this discourse were taken to heart by all those who are too ready to associate Nietzsche with lesser and noiser men,—with mountebanks and mummers.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004212": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004212",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004213": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004213",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004214": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004214",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LII. The Apostates.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004215": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004215",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It is clear that this applies to all those breathless and hasty “tasters of everything,” who plunge too rashly into the sea of independent thought and “heresy,” and who, having miscalculated their strength, find it impossible to keep their head above water. “A little older, a little colder,” says Nietzsche. They soon clamber back to the conventions of the age they intended reforming. The French then say “le diable se fait hermite,” but these men, as a rule, have never been devils, neither do they become angels; for, in order to be really good or evil, some strength and deep breathing is required. Those who are more interested in supporting orthodoxy than in being over nice concerning the kind of support they give it, often refer to these people as evidence in favour of the true faith.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004216": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004216",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004217": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004217",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004218": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004218",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LIII. The Return Home.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004219": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004219",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is an example of a class of writing which may be passed over too lightly by those whom poetasters have made distrustful of poetry. From first to last it is extremely valuable as an autobiographical note. The inevitable superficiality of the rabble is contrasted with the peaceful and profound depths of the anchorite. Here we first get a direct hint concerning Nietzsche’s fundamental passion—the main force behind all his new values and scathing criticism of existing values. In verse 30 we are told that pity was his greatest danger. The broad altruism of the law-giver, thinking over vast eras of time, was continually being pitted by Nietzsche, in himself, against that transient and meaner sympathy for the neighbour which he more perhaps than any of his contemporaries had suffered from, but which he was certain involved enormous dangers not only for himself but also to the next and subsequent generations (see Note B., where “pity” is mentioned among the degenerate virtues). Later in the book we shall see how his profound compassion leads him into temptation, and how frantically he struggles against it. In verses 31 and 32, he tells us to what extent he had to modify himself in order to be endured by his fellows whom he loved (see also verse 12 in “Manly Prudence”). Nietzsche’s great love for his fellows, which he confesses in the Prologue, and which is at the root of all his teaching, seems rather to elude the discerning powers of the average philanthropist and modern man. He cannot see the wood for the trees. A philanthropy that sacrifices the minority of the present-day for the majority constituting posterity, completely evades his mental grasp, and Nietzsche’s philosophy, because it declares Christian values to be a danger to the future of our kind, is therefore shelved as brutal, cold, and hard (see Note on Chapter XXXVI.). Nietzsche tried to be all things to all men; he was sufficiently fond of his fellows for that: in the Return Home he describes how he ultimately returns to loneliness in order to recover from the effects of his experiment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004220": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004220",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004221": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004221",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004222": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004222",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LIV. The Three Evil Things.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004223": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004223",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche is here completely in his element. Three things hitherto best-cursed and most calumniated on earth, are brought forward to be weighed. Voluptuousness, thirst of power, and selfishness,—the three forces in humanity which Christianity has done most to garble and besmirch,—Nietzsche endeavours to reinstate in their former places of honour. Voluptuousness, or sensual pleasure, is a dangerous thing to discuss nowadays. If we mention it with favour we may be regarded, however unjustly, as the advocate of savages, satyrs, and pure sensuality. If we condemn it, we either go over to the Puritans or we join those who are wont to come to table with no edge to their appetites and who therefore grumble at all good fare. There can be no doubt that the value of healthy innocent voluptuousness, like the value of health itself, must have been greatly discounted by all those who, resenting their inability to partake of this world’s goods, cried like St Paul: “I would that all men were even as I myself.” Now Nietzsche’s philosophy might be called an attempt at giving back to healthy and normal men innocence and a clean conscience in their desires—NOT to applaud the vulgar sensualists who respond to every stimulus and whose passions are out of hand; not to tell the mean, selfish individual, whose selfishness is a pollution (see Aphorism 33, “Twilight of the Idols”), that he is right, nor to assure the weak, the sick, and the crippled, that the thirst of power, which they gratify by exploiting the happier and healthier individuals, is justified;—but to save the clean healthy man from the values of those around him, who look at everything through the mud that is in their own bodies,—to give him, and him alone, a clean conscience in his manhood and the desires of his manhood. “Do I counsel you to slay your instincts? I counsel to innocence in your instincts.” In verse 7 of the second paragraph (as in verse I of paragraph 19 in “The Old and New Tables”) Nietzsche gives us a reason for his occasional obscurity (see also verses 3 to 7 of “Poets”). As I have already pointed out, his philosophy is quite esoteric. It can serve no purpose with the ordinary, mediocre type of man. I, personally, can no longer have any doubt that Nietzsche’s only object, in that part of his philosophy where he bids his friends stand “Beyond Good and Evil” with him, was to save higher men, whose growth and scope might be limited by the too strict observance of modern values from foundering on the rocks of a “Compromise” between their own genius and traditional conventions. The only possible way in which the great man can achieve greatness is by means of exceptional freedom—the freedom which assists him in experiencing HIMSELF. Verses 20 to 30 afford an excellent supplement to Nietzsche’s description of the attitude of the noble type towards the slaves in Aphorism 260 of the work “Beyond Good and Evil” (see also Note B.)</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004224": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004224",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004225": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004225",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004226": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004226",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LV. The Spirit of Gravity.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004227": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004227",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>(See Note on Chapter XLVI.) In Part II. of this discourse we meet with a doctrine not touched upon hitherto, save indirectly;—I refer to the doctrine of self-love. We should try to understand this perfectly before proceeding; for it is precisely views of this sort which, after having been cut out of the original context, are repeated far and wide as internal evidence proving the general unsoundness of Nietzsche’s philosophy. Already in the last of the “Thoughts out of Season” Nietzsche speaks as follows about modern men: “...these modern creatures wish rather to be hunted down, wounded and torn to shreds, than to live alone with themselves in solitary calm. Alone with oneself!—this thought terrifies the modern soul; it is his one anxiety, his one ghastly fear” (English Edition, page 141). In his feverish scurry to find entertainment and diversion, whether in a novel, a newspaper, or a play, the modern man condemns his own age utterly; for he shows that in his heart of hearts he despises himself. One cannot change a condition of this sort in a day; to become endurable to oneself an inner transformation is necessary. Too long have we lost ourselves in our friends and entertainments to be able to find ourselves so soon at another’s bidding. “And verily, it is no commandment for to-day and to-morrow to LEARN to love oneself. Rather is it of all arts the finest, subtlest, last, and patientest.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004228": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004228",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the last verse Nietzsche challenges us to show that our way is the right way. In his teaching he does not coerce us, nor does he overpersuade; he simply says: “I am a law only for mine own, I am not a law for all. This—is now MY way,—where is yours?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004229": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004229",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004230": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004230",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004231": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004231",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LVI. Old and New Tables. Par. 2.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004232": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004232",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche himself declares this to be the most decisive portion of the whole of “Thus Spake Zarathustra”. It is a sort of epitome of his leading doctrines. In verse 12 of the second paragraph, we learn how he himself would fain have abandoned the poetical method of expression had he not known only too well that the only chance a new doctrine has of surviving, nowadays, depends upon its being given to the world in some kind of art-form. Just as prophets, centuries ago, often had to have recourse to the mask of madness in order to mitigate the hatred of those who did not and could not see as they did; so, to-day, the struggle for existence among opinions and values is so great, that an art-form is practically the only garb in which a new philosophy can dare to introduce itself to us.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004233": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004233",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 3 and 4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004234": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004234",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Many of the paragraphs will be found to be merely reminiscent of former discourses. For instance, par. 3 recalls “Redemption”. The last verse of par. 4 is important. Freedom which, as I have pointed out before, Nietzsche considered a dangerous acquisition in inexperienced or unworthy hands, here receives its death-blow as a general desideratum. In the first Part we read under “The Way of the Creating One”, that freedom as an end in itself does not concern Zarathustra at all. He says there: “Free from what? What doth that matter to Zarathustra? Clearly, however, shall thine eye answer me: free FOR WHAT?” And in “The Bedwarfing Virtue”: “Ah that ye understood my word: ‘Do ever what ye will—but first be such as CAN WILL.’”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004235": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004235",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 5.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004236": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004236",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here we have a description of the kind of altruism Nietzsche exacted from higher men. It is really a comment upon “The Bestowing Virtue” (see Note on Chapter XXII.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004237": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004237",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004238": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004238",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This refers, of course, to the reception pioneers of Nietzsche’s stamp meet with at the hands of their contemporaries.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004239": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004239",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 8.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004240": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004240",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche teaches that nothing is stable,—not even values,—not even the concepts good and evil. He likens life unto a stream. But foot-bridges and railings span the stream, and they seem to stand firm. Many will be reminded of good and evil when they look upon these structures; for thus these same values stand over the stream of life, and life flows on beneath them and leaves them standing. When, however, winter comes and the stream gets frozen, many inquire: “Should not everything—STAND STILL? Fundamentally everything standeth still.” But soon the spring cometh and with it the thaw-wind. It breaks the ice, and the ice breaks down the foot-bridges and railings, whereupon everything is swept away. This state of affairs, according to Nietzsche, has now been reached. “Oh, my brethren, is not everything AT PRESENT IN FLUX? Have not all railings and foot-bridges fallen into the water? Who would still HOLD ON to ‘good’ and ‘evil’?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004241": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004241",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 9.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004242": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004242",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is complementary to the first three verses of par. 2.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004243": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004243",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 10.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004244": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004244",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>So far, this is perhaps the most important paragraph. It is a protest against reading a moral order of things in life. “Life is something essentially immoral!” Nietzsche tells us in the introduction to the “Birth of Tragedy”. Even to call life “activity,” or to define it further as “the continuous adjustment of internal relations to external relations,” as Spencer has it, Nietzsche characterises as a “democratic idiosyncracy.” He says to define it in this way, “is to mistake the true nature and function of life, which is Will to Power...Life is ESSENTIALLY appropriation, injury, conquest of the strange and weak, suppression, severity, obtrusion of its own forms, incorporation and at least, putting it mildest, exploitation.” Adaptation is merely a secondary activity, a mere re-activity (see Note on Chapter LVII.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004245": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004245",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 11, 12.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004246": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004246",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These deal with Nietzsche’s principle of the desirability of rearing a select race. The biological and historical grounds for his insistence upon this principle are, of course, manifold. Gobineau in his great work, “L’Inegalite des Races Humaines”, lays strong emphasis upon the evils which arise from promiscuous and inter-social marriages. He alone would suffice to carry Nietzsche’s point against all those who are opposed to the other conditions, to the conditions which would have saved Rome, which have maintained the strength of the Jewish race, and which are strictly maintained by every breeder of animals throughout the world. Darwin in his remarks relative to the degeneration of CULTIVATED types of animals through the action of promiscuous breeding, brings Gobineau support from the realm of biology.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004247": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004247",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The last two verses of par. 12 were discussed in the Notes on Chapters XXXVI. and LIII.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004248": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004248",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 13.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004249": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004249",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This, like the first part of “The Soothsayer”, is obviously a reference to the Schopenhauerian Pessimism.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004250": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004250",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 14, 15, 16, 17.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004251": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004251",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These are supplementary to the discourse “Backworld’s-men”.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004252": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004252",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 18.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004253": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004253",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We must be careful to separate this paragraph, in sense, from the previous four paragraphs. Nietzsche is still dealing with Pessimism here; but it is the pessimism of the hero—the man most susceptible of all to desperate views of life, owing to the obstacles that are arrayed against him in a world where men of his kind are very rare and are continually being sacrificed. It was to save this man that Nietzsche wrote. Heroism foiled, thwarted, and wrecked, hoping and fighting until the last, is at length overtaken by despair, and renounces all struggle for sleep. This is not the natural or constitutional pessimism which proceeds from an unhealthy body—the dyspeptic’s lack of appetite; it is rather the desperation of the netted lion that ultimately stops all movement, because the more it moves the more involved it becomes.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004254": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004254",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 20.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004255": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004255",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“All that increases power is good, all that springs from weakness is bad. The weak and ill-constituted shall perish: first principle of our charity. And one shall also help them thereto.” Nietzsche partly divined the kind of reception moral values of this stamp would meet with at the hands of the effeminate manhood of Europe. Here we see that he had anticipated the most likely form their criticism would take (see also the last two verses of par. 17).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004256": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004256",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 21.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004257": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004257",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The first ten verses, here, are reminiscent of “War and Warriors” and of “The Flies in the Market-place.” Verses 11 and 12, however, are particularly important. There is a strong argument in favour of the sharp differentiation of castes and of races (and even of sexes; see Note on Chapter XVIII.) running all through Nietzsche’s writings. But sharp differentiation also implies antagonism in some form or other—hence Nietzsche’s fears for modern men. What modern men desire above all, is peace and the cessation of pain. But neither great races nor great castes have ever been built up in this way. “Who still wanteth to rule?” Zarathustra asks in the “Prologue”. “Who still wanteth to obey? Both are too burdensome.” This is rapidly becoming everybody’s attitude to-day. The tame moral reading of the face of nature, together with such democratic interpretations of life as those suggested by Herbert Spencer, are signs of a physiological condition which is the reverse of that bounding and irresponsible healthiness in which harder and more tragic values rule.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004258": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004258",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 24.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004259": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004259",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This should be read in conjunction with “Child and Marriage”. In the fifth verse we shall recognise our old friend “Marriage on the ten-years system,” which George Meredith suggested some years ago. This, however, must not be taken too literally. I do not think Nietzsche’s profoundest views on marriage were ever intended to be given over to the public at all, at least not for the present. They appear in the biography by his sister, and although their wisdom is unquestionable, the nature of the reforms he suggests render it impossible for them to become popular just now.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004260": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004260",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 26, 27.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004261": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004261",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>See Note on “The Prologue”.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004262": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004262",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 28.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004263": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004263",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche was not an iconoclast from predilection. No bitterness or empty hate dictated his vituperations against existing values and against the dogmas of his parents and forefathers. He knew too well what these things meant to the millions who profess them, to approach the task of uprooting them with levity or even with haste. He saw what modern anarchists and revolutionists do NOT see—namely, that man is in danger of actual destruction when his customs and values are broken. I need hardly point out, therefore, how deeply he was conscious of the responsibility he threw upon our shoulders when he invited us to reconsider our position. The lines in this paragraph are evidence enough of his earnestness.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004264": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004264",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004265": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004265",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004266": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004266",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LVII. The Convalescent.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004267": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004267",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We meet with several puzzles here. Zarathustra calls himself the advocate of the circle (the Eternal Recurrence of all things), and he calls this doctrine his abysmal thought. In the last verse of the first paragraph, however, after hailing his deepest thought, he cries: “Disgust, disgust, disgust!” We know Nietzsche’s ideal man was that “world-approving, exuberant, and vivacious creature, who has not only learnt to compromise and arrange with that which was and is, but wishes to have it again, AS IT WAS AND IS, for all eternity insatiably calling out da capo, not only to himself, but to the whole piece and play” (see Note on Chapter XLII.). But if one ask oneself what the conditions to such an attitude are, one will realise immediately how utterly different Nietzsche was from his ideal. The man who insatiably cries da capo to himself and to the whole of his mise-en-scene, must be in a position to desire every incident in his life to be repeated, not once, but again and again eternally. Now, Nietzsche’s life had been too full of disappointments, illness, unsuccessful struggles, and snubs, to allow of his thinking of the Eternal Recurrence without loathing—hence probably the words of the last verse.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004268": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004268",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In verses 15 and 16, we have Nietzsche declaring himself an evolutionist in the broadest sense—that is to say, that he believes in the Development Hypothesis as the description of the process by which species have originated. Now, to understand his position correctly we must show his relationship to the two greatest of modern evolutionists—Darwin and Spencer. As a philosopher, however, Nietzsche does not stand or fall by his objections to the Darwinian or Spencerian cosmogony. He never laid claim to a very profound knowledge of biology, and his criticism is far more valuable as the attitude of a fresh mind than as that of a specialist towards the question. Moreover, in his objections many difficulties are raised which are not settled by an appeal to either of the men above mentioned. We have given Nietzsche’s definition of life in the Note on Chapter LVI., par. 10. Still, there remains a hope that Darwin and Nietzsche may some day become reconciled by a new description of the processes by which varieties occur. The appearance of varieties among animals and of “sporting plants” in the vegetable kingdom, is still shrouded in mystery, and the question whether this is not precisely the ground on which Darwin and Nietzsche will meet, is an interesting one. The former says in his “Origin of Species”, concerning the causes of variability: “...there are two factors, namely, the nature of the organism, and the nature of the conditions. THE FORMER SEEMS TO BE MUCH THE MORE IMPORTANT (The italics are mine.), for nearly similar variations sometimes arise under, as far as we can judge, dissimilar conditions; and on the other hand, dissimilar variations arise under conditions which appear to be nearly uniform.” Nietzsche, recognising this same truth, would ascribe practically all the importance to the “highest functionaries in the organism, in which the life-will appears as an active and formative principle,” and except in certain cases (where passive organisms alone are concerned) would not give such a prominent place to the influence of environment. Adaptation, according to him, is merely a secondary activity, a mere re-activity, and he is therefore quite opposed to Spencer’s definition: “Life is the continuous adjustment of internal relations to external relations.” Again in the motive force behind animal and plant life, Nietzsche disagrees with Darwin. He transforms the “Struggle for Existence”—the passive and involuntary condition—into the “Struggle for Power,” which is active and creative, and much more in harmony with Darwin’s own view, given above, concerning the importance of the organism itself. The change is one of such far-reaching importance that we cannot dispose of it in a breath, as a mere play upon words. “Much is reckoned higher than life itself by the living one.” Nietzsche says that to speak of the activity of life as a “struggle for existence,” is to state the case inadequately. He warns us not to confound Malthus with nature. There is something more than this struggle between the organic beings on this earth; want, which is supposed to bring this struggle about, is not so common as is supposed; some other force must be operative. The Will to Power is this force, “the instinct of self-preservation is only one of the indirect and most frequent results thereof.” A certain lack of acumen in psychological questions and the condition of affairs in England at the time Darwin wrote, may both, according to Nietzsche, have induced the renowned naturalist to describe the forces of nature as he did in his “Origin of Species”.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004269": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004269",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In verses 28, 29, and 30 of the second portion of this discourse we meet with a doctrine which, at first sight, seems to be merely “le manoir a l’envers,” indeed one English critic has actually said of Nietzsche, that “Thus Spake Zarathustra” is no more than a compendium of modern views and maxims turned upside down. Examining these heterodox pronouncements a little more closely, however, we may possibly perceive their truth. Regarding good and evil as purely relative values, it stands to reason that what may be bad or evil in a given man, relative to a certain environment, may actually be good if not highly virtuous in him relative to a certain other environment. If this hypothetical man represent the ascending line of life—that is to say, if he promise all that which is highest in a Graeco-Roman sense, then it is likely that he will be condemned as wicked if introduced into the society of men representing the opposite and descending line of life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004270": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004270",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>By depriving a man of his wickedness—more particularly nowadays— therefore, one may unwittingly be doing violence to the greatest in him. It may be an outrage against his wholeness, just as the lopping-off of a leg would be. Fortunately, the natural so-called “wickedness” of higher men has in a certain measure been able to resist this lopping process which successive slave-moralities have practised; but signs are not wanting which show that the noblest wickedness is fast vanishing from society—the wickedness of courage and determination—and that Nietzsche had good reasons for crying: “Ah, that (man’s) baddest is so very small! Ah, that his best is so very small. What is good? To be brave is good! It is the good war which halloweth every cause!” (see also par. 5, “Higher Man”).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004271": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004271",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004272": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004272",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004273": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004273",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LX. The Seven Seals.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004274": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004274",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This is a final paean which Zarathustra sings to Eternity and the marriage-ring of rings, the ring of the Eternal Recurrence.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004275": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004275",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>... <a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004276": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004276",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004277": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004277",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>PART IV.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004278": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004278",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In my opinion this part is Nietzsche’s open avowal that all his philosophy, together with all his hopes, enthusiastic outbursts, blasphemies, prolixities, and obscurities, were merely so many gifts laid at the feet of higher men. He had no desire to save the world. What he wished to determine was: Who is to be master of the world? This is a very different thing. He came to save higher men;—to give them that freedom by which, alone, they can develop and reach their zenith (see Note on Chapter LIV., end). It has been argued, and with considerable force, that no such philosophy is required by higher men, that, as a matter of fact, higher men, by virtue of their constitutions always, do stand Beyond Good and Evil, and never allow anything to stand in the way of their complete growth. Nietzsche, however, was evidently not so confident about this. He would probably have argued that we only see the successful cases. Being a great man himself, he was well aware of the dangers threatening greatness in our age. In “Beyond Good and Evil” he writes: “There are few pains so grievous as to have seen, divined, or experienced how an exceptional man has missed his way and deteriorated...” He knew “from his painfullest recollections on what wretched obstacles promising developments of the highest rank have hitherto usually gone to pieces, broken down, sunk, and become contemptible.” Now in Part IV. we shall find that his strongest temptation to descend to the feeling of “pity” for his contemporaries, is the “cry for help” which he hears from the lips of the higher men exposed to the dreadful danger of their modern environment.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004279": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004279",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004280": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004280",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004281": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004281",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXI. The Honey Sacrifice.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004282": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004282",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the fourteenth verse of this discourse Nietzsche defines the solemn duty he imposed upon himself: “Become what thou art.” Surely the criticism which has been directed against this maxim must all fall to the ground when it is remembered, once and for all, that Nietzsche’s teaching was never intended to be other than an esoteric one. “I am a law only for mine own,” he says emphatically, “I am not a law for all.” It is of the greatest importance to humanity that its highest individuals should be allowed to attain to their full development; for, only by means of its heroes can the human race be led forward step by step to higher and yet higher levels. “Become what thou art” applied to all, of course, becomes a vicious maxim; it is to be hoped, however, that we may learn in time that the same action performed by a given number of men, loses its identity precisely that same number of times.—“Quod licet Jovi, non licet bovi.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At the last eight verses many readers may be tempted to laugh. In England we almost always laugh when a man takes himself seriously at anything save sport. And there is of course no reason why the reader should not be hilarious.—A certain greatness is requisite, both in order to be sublime and to have reverence for the sublime. Nietzsche earnestly believed that the Zarathustra-kingdom—his dynasty of a thousand years—would one day come; if he had not believed it so earnestly, if every artist in fact had not believed so earnestly in his Hazar, whether of ten, fifteen, a hundred, or a thousand years, we should have lost all our higher men; they would have become pessimists, suicides, or merchants. If the minor poet and philosopher has made us shy of the prophetic seriousness which characterized an Isaiah or a Jeremiah, it is surely our loss and the minor poet’s gain.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXII. The Cry of Distress.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>We now meet with Zarathustra in extraordinary circumstances. He is confronted with Schopenhauer and tempted by the old Soothsayer to commit the sin of pity. “I have come that I may seduce thee to thy last sin!” says the Soothsayer to Zarathustra. It will be remembered that in Schopenhauer’s ethics, pity is elevated to the highest place among the virtues, and very consistently too, seeing that the Weltanschauung is a pessimistic one. Schopenhauer appeals to Nietzsche’s deepest and strongest sentiment—his sympathy for higher men. “Why dost thou conceal thyself?” he cries. “It is THE HIGHER MAN that calleth for thee!” Zarathustra is almost overcome by the Soothsayer’s pleading, as he had been once already in the past, but he resists him step by step. At length he can withstand him no longer, and, on the plea that the higher man is on his ground and therefore under his protection, Zarathustra departs in search of him, leaving Schopenhauer—a higher man in Nietzsche’s opinion—in the cave as a guest.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004289": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004289",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004290": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004290",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXIII. Talk with the Kings.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004291": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004291",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>On his way Zarathustra meets two more higher men of his time; two kings cross his path. They are above the average modern type; for their instincts tell them what real ruling is, and they despise the mockery which they have been taught to call “Reigning.” “We ARE NOT the first men,” they say, “and have nevertheless to STAND FOR them: of this imposture have we at last become weary and disgusted.” It is the kings who tell Zarathustra: “There is no sorer misfortune in all human destiny than when the mighty of the earth are not also the first men. There everything becometh false and distorted and monstrous.” The kings are also asked by Zarathustra to accept the shelter of his cave, whereupon he proceeds on his way.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004292": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004292",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004293": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004293",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004294": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004294",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXIV. The Leech.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004295": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004295",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Among the higher men whom Zarathustra wishes to save, is also the scientific specialist—the man who honestly and scrupulously pursues his investigations, as Darwin did, in one department of knowledge. “I love him who liveth in order to know, and seeketh to know in order that the Superman may hereafter live. Thus seeketh he his own down-going.” “The spiritually conscientious one,” he is called in this discourse. Zarathustra steps on him unawares, and the slave of science, bleeding from the violence he has done to himself by his self-imposed task, speaks proudly of his little sphere of knowledge—his little hand’s breadth of ground on Zarathustra’s territory, philosophy. “Where mine honesty ceaseth,” says the true scientific specialist, “there am I blind and want also to be blind. Where I want to know, however, there want I also to be honest—namely, severe, rigorous, restricted, cruel, and inexorable.” Zarathustra greatly respecting this man, invites him too to the cave, and then vanishes in answer to another cry for help.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004296": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004296",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004297": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004297",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004298": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004298",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXV. The Magician.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004299": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004299",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The Magician is of course an artist, and Nietzsche’s intimate knowledge of perhaps the greatest artist of his age rendered the selection of Wagner, as the type in this discourse, almost inevitable. Most readers will be acquainted with the facts relating to Nietzsche’s and Wagner’s friendship and ultimate separation. As a boy and a youth Nietzsche had shown such a remarkable gift for music that it had been a question at one time whether he should not perhaps give up everything else in order to develop this gift, but he became a scholar notwithstanding, although he never entirely gave up composing, and playing the piano. While still in his teens, he became acquainted with Wagner’s music and grew passionately fond of it. Long before he met Wagner he must have idealised him in his mind to an extent which only a profoundly artistic nature could have been capable of. Nietzsche always had high ideals for humanity. If one were asked whether, throughout his many changes, there was yet one aim, one direction, and one hope to which he held fast, one would be forced to reply in the affirmative and declare that aim, direction, and hope to have been “the elevation of the type man.” Now, when Nietzsche met Wagner he was actually casting about for an incarnation of his dreams for the German people, and we have only to remember his youth (he was twenty-one when he was introduced to Wagner), his love of Wagner’s music, and the undoubted power of the great musician’s personality, in order to realise how very uncritical his attitude must have been in the first flood of his enthusiasm. Again, when the friendship ripened, we cannot well imagine Nietzsche, the younger man, being anything less than intoxicated by his senior’s attention and love, and we are therefore not surprised to find him pressing Wagner forward as the great Reformer and Saviour of mankind. “Wagner in Bayreuth” (English Edition, 1909) gives us the best proof of Nietzsche’s infatuation, and although signs are not wanting in this essay which show how clearly and even cruelly he was sub-consciously “taking stock” of his friend—even then, the work is a record of what great love and admiration can do in the way of endowing the object of one’s affection with all the qualities and ideals that a fertile imagination can conceive.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004300": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004300",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When the blow came it was therefore all the more severe. Nietzsche at length realised that the friend of his fancy and the real Richard Wagner—the composer of Parsifal—were not one; the fact dawned upon him slowly; disappointment upon disappointment, revelation after revelation, ultimately brought it home to him, and though his best instincts were naturally opposed to it at first, the revulsion of feeling at last became too strong to be ignored, and Nietzsche was plunged into the blackest despair. Years after his break with Wagner, he wrote “The Case of Wagner”, and “Nietzsche contra Wagner”, and these works are with us to prove the sincerity and depth of his views on the man who was the greatest event of his life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004301": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004301",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The poem in this discourse is, of course, reminiscent of Wagner’s own poetical manner, and it must be remembered that the whole was written subsequent to Nietzsche’s final break with his friend. The dialogue between Zarathustra and the Magician reveals pretty fully what it was that Nietzsche grew to loathe so intensely in Wagner,—viz., his pronounced histrionic tendencies, his dissembling powers, his inordinate vanity, his equivocalness, his falseness. “It honoureth thee,” says Zarathustra, “that thou soughtest for greatness, but it betrayeth thee also. Thou art not great.” The Magician is nevertheless sent as a guest to Zarathustra’s cave; for, in his heart, Zarathustra believed until the end that the Magician was a higher man broken by modern values.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004302": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004302",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004303": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004303",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004304": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004304",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXVI. Out of Service.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004305": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004305",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra now meets the last pope, and, in a poetical form, we get Nietzsche’s description of the course Judaism and Christianity pursued before they reached their final break-up in Atheism, Agnosticism, and the like. The God of a strong, warlike race—the God of Israel—is a jealous, revengeful God. He is a power that can be pictured and endured only by a hardy and courageous race, a race rich enough to sacrifice and to lose in sacrifice. The image of this God degenerates with the people that appropriate it, and gradually He becomes a God of love—“soft and mellow,” a lower middle-class deity, who is “pitiful.” He can no longer be a God who requires sacrifice, for we ourselves are no longer rich enough for that. The tables are therefore turned upon Him; HE must sacrifice to us. His pity becomes so great that he actually does sacrifice something to us—His only begotten Son. Such a process carried to its logical conclusions must ultimately end in His own destruction, and thus we find the pope declaring that God was one day suffocated by His all-too-great pity. What follows is clear enough. Zarathustra recognises another higher man in the ex-pope and sends him too as a guest to the cave.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004306": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004306",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004307": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004307",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004308": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004308",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXVII. The Ugliest Man.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004309": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004309",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>This discourse contains perhaps the boldest of Nietzsche’s suggestions concerning Atheism, as well as some extremely penetrating remarks upon the sentiment of pity. Zarathustra comes across the repulsive creature sitting on the wayside, and what does he do? He manifests the only correct feelings that can be manifested in the presence of any great misery—that is to say, shame, reverence, embarrassment. Nietzsche detested the obtrusive and gushing pity that goes up to misery without a blush either on its cheek or in its heart—the pity which is only another form of self-glorification. “Thank God that I am not like thee!”—only this self-glorifying sentiment can lend a well-constituted man the impudence to SHOW his pity for the cripple and the ill-constituted. In the presence of the ugliest man Nietzsche blushes,—he blushes for his race; his own particular kind of altruism—the altruism that might have prevented the existence of this man—strikes him with all its force. He will have the world otherwise. He will have a world where one need not blush for one’s fellows—hence his appeal to us to love only our children’s land, the land undiscovered in the remotest sea.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004310": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004310",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Zarathustra calls the ugliest man the murderer of God! Certainly, this is one aspect of a certain kind of Atheism—the Atheism of the man who reveres beauty to such an extent that his own ugliness, which outrages him, must be concealed from every eye lest it should not be respected as Zarathustra respected it. If there be a God, He too must be evaded. His pity must be foiled. But God is ubiquitous and omniscient. Therefore, for the really GREAT ugly man, He must not exist. “Their pity IS it from which I flee away,” he says—that is to say: “It is from their want of reverence and lack of shame in presence of my great misery!” The ugliest man despises himself; but Zarathustra said in his Prologue: “I love the great despisers because they are the great adorers, and arrows of longing for the other shore.” He therefore honours the ugliest man: sees height in his self-contempt, and invites him to join the other higher men in the cave.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004311": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004311",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004312": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004312",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004313": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004313",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXVIII. The Voluntary Beggar.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004314": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004314",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In this discourse, we undoubtedly have the ideal Buddhist, if not Gautama Buddha himself. Nietzsche had the greatest respect for Buddhism, and almost wherever he refers to it in his works, it is in terms of praise. He recognised that though Buddhism is undoubtedly a religion for decadents, its decadent values emanate from the higher and not, as in Christianity, from the lower grades of society. In Aphorism 20 of “The Antichrist”, he compares it exhaustively with Christianity, and the result of his investigation is very much in favour of the older religion. Still, he recognised a most decided Buddhistic influence in Christ’s teaching, and the words in verses 29, 30, and 31 are very reminiscent of his views in regard to the Christian Savior.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004315": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004315",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The figure of Christ has been introduced often enough into fiction, and many scholars have undertaken to write His life according to their own lights, but few perhaps have ever attempted to present Him to us bereft of all those characteristics which a lack of the sense of harmony has attached to His person through the ages in which His doctrines have been taught. Now Nietzsche disagreed entirely with Renan’s view, that Christ was “le grand maitre en ironie”; in Aphorism 31 of “The Antichrist”, he says that he (Nietzsche) always purged his picture of the Humble Nazarene of all those bitter and spiteful outbursts which, in view of the struggle the first Christians went through, may very well have been added to the original character by Apologists and Sectarians who, at that time, could ill afford to consider nice psychological points, seeing that what they needed, above all, was a wrangling and abusive deity. These two conflicting halves in the character of the Christ of the Gospels, which no sound psychology can ever reconcile, Nietzsche always kept distinct in his own mind; he could not credit the same man with sentiments sometimes so noble and at other times so vulgar, and in presenting us with this new portrait of the Saviour, purged of all impurities, Nietzsche rendered military honours to a foe, which far exceed in worth all that His most ardent disciples have ever claimed for Him. In verse 26 we are vividly reminded of Herbert Spencer’s words “‘Le mariage de convenance’ is legalised prostitution.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004316": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004316",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004317": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004317",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004318": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004318",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXIX. The Shadow.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004319": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004319",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here we have a description of that courageous and wayward spirit that literally haunts the footsteps of every great thinker and every great leader; sometimes with the result that it loses all aims, all hopes, and all trust in a definite goal. It is the case of the bravest and most broad-minded men of to-day. These literally shadow the most daring movements in the science and art of their generation; they completely lose their bearings and actually find themselves, in the end, without a way, a goal, or a home. “On every surface have I already sat!...I become thin, I am almost equal to a shadow!” At last, in despair, such men do indeed cry out: “Nothing is true; all is permitted,” and then they become mere wreckage. “Too much hath become clear unto me: now nothing mattereth to me any more. Nothing liveth any longer that I love,—how should I still love myself! Have I still a goal? Where is MY home?” Zarathustra realises the danger threatening such a man. “Thy danger is not small, thou free spirit and wanderer,” he says. “Thou hast had a bad day. See that a still worse evening doth not overtake thee!” The danger Zarathustra refers to is precisely this, that even a prison may seem a blessing to such a man. At least the bars keep him in a place of rest; a place of confinement, at its worst, is real. “Beware lest in the end a narrow faith capture thee,” says Zarathustra, “for now everything that is narrow and fixed seduceth and tempteth thee.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004320": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004320",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004321": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004321",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004322": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004322",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXX. Noontide.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004323": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004323",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At the noon of life Nietzsche said he entered the world; with him man came of age. We are now held responsible for our actions; our old guardians, the gods and demi-gods of our youth, the superstitions and fears of our childhood, withdraw; the field lies open before us; we lived through our morning with but one master—chance—; let us see to it that we MAKE our afternoon our own (see Note XLIX., Part III.).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004324": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004324",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004325": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004325",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004326": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004326",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXI. The Greeting.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004327": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004327",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here I think I may claim that my contention in regard to the purpose and aim of the whole of Nietzsche’s philosophy (as stated at the beginning of my Notes on Part IV.) is completely upheld. He fought for “all who do not want to live, unless they learn again to HOPE—unless THEY learn (from him) the GREAT hope!” Zarathustra’s address to his guests shows clearly enough how he wished to help them: “I DO NOT TREAT MY WARRIORS INDULGENTLY,” he says: “how then could ye be fit for MY warfare?” He rebukes and spurns them, no word of love comes from his lips. Elsewhere he says a man should be a hard bed to his friend, thus alone can he be of use to him. Nietzsche would be a hard bed to higher men. He would make them harder; for, in order to be a law unto himself, man must possess the requisite hardness. “I wait for higher ones, stronger ones, more triumphant ones, merrier ones, for such as are built squarely in body and soul.” He says in par. 6 of “Higher Man”:—</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004328": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004328",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Ye higher men, think ye that I am here to put right what ye have put wrong? Or that I wished henceforth to make snugger couches for you sufferers? Or show you restless, miswandering, misclimbing ones new and easier footpaths?”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004329": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004329",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“Nay! Nay! Three times nay! Always more, always better ones of your type shall succumb—for ye shall always have it worse and harder.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004330": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004330",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004331": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004331",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004332": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004332",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXII. The Supper.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004333": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004333",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the first seven verses of this discourse, I cannot help seeing a gentle allusion to Schopenhauer’s habits as a bon-vivant. For a pessimist, be it remembered, Schopenhauer led quite an extraordinary life. He ate well, loved well, played the flute well, and I believe he smoked the best cigars. What follows is clear enough.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004334": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004334",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004335": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004335",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004336": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004336",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXIII. The Higher Man. Par. 1.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004337": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004337",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Nietzsche admits, here, that at one time he had thought of appealing to the people, to the crowd in the market-place, but that he had ultimately to abandon the task. He bids higher men depart from the market-place.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004338": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004338",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 3.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004339": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004339",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here we are told quite plainly what class of men actually owe all their impulses and desires to the instinct of self-preservation. The struggle for existence is indeed the only spur in the case of such people. To them it matters not in what shape or condition man be preserved, provided only he survive. The transcendental maxim that “Life per se is precious” is the ruling maxim here.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004340": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004340",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 4.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004341": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004341",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the Note on Chapter LVII. (end) I speak of Nietzsche’s elevation of the virtue, Courage, to the highest place among the virtues. Here he tells higher men the class of courage he expects from them.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004342": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004342",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 5, 6.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004343": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004343",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These have already been referred to in the Notes on Chapters LVII. (end) and LXXI.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004344": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004344",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 7.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004345": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004345",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>I suggest that the last verse in this paragraph strongly confirms the view that Nietzsche’s teaching was always meant by him to be esoteric and for higher man alone.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004346": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004346",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 9.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004347": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004347",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In the last verse, here, another shaft of light is thrown upon the Immaculate Perception or so-called “pure objectivity” of the scientific mind. “Freedom from fever is still far from being knowledge.” Where a man’s emotions cease to accompany him in his investigations, he is not necessarily nearer the truth. Says Spencer, in the Preface to his Autobiography:—“In the genesis of a system of thought, the emotional nature is a large factor: perhaps as large a factor as the intellectual nature” (see pages 134, 141 of Vol. I., “Thoughts out of Season”).</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004348": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004348",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 10, 11.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004349": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004349",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>When we approach Nietzsche’s philosophy we must be prepared to be independent thinkers; in fact, the greatest virtue of his works is perhaps the subtlety with which they impose the obligation upon one of thinking alone, of scoring off one’s own bat, and of shifting intellectually for oneself.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004350": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004350",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 13.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004351": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004351",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“I am a railing alongside the torrent; whoever is able to grasp me, may grasp me! Your crutch, however, I am not.” These two paragraphs are an exhortation to higher men to become independent.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004352": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004352",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Par. 15.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004353": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004353",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Here Nietzsche perhaps exaggerates the importance of heredity. As, however, the question is by no means one on which we are all agreed, what he says is not without value.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004354": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004354",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>A very important principle in Nietzsche’s philosophy is enunciated in the first verse of this paragraph. “The higher its type, always the seldomer doth a thing succeed” (see page 82 of “Beyond Good and Evil”). Those who, like some political economists, talk in a business-like way about the terrific waste of human life and energy, deliberately overlook the fact that the waste most to be deplored usually occurs among higher individuals. Economy was never precisely one of nature’s leading principles. All this sentimental wailing over the larger proportion of failures than successes in human life, does not seem to take into account the fact that it is the rarest thing on earth for a highly organised being to attain to the fullest development and activity of all its functions, simply because it is so highly organised. The blind Will to Power in nature therefore stands in urgent need of direction by man.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004355": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004355",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Pars. 16, 17, 18, 19, 20.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004356": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004356",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>These paragraphs deal with Nietzsche’s protest against the democratic seriousness (Pobelernst) of modern times. “All good things laugh,” he says, and his final command to the higher men is, “LEARN, I pray you—to laugh.” All that is GOOD, in Nietzsche’s sense, is cheerful. To be able to crack a joke about one’s deepest feelings is the greatest test of their value. The man who does not laugh, like the man who does not make faces, is already a buffoon at heart.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004357": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004357",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>“What hath hitherto been the greatest sin here on earth? Was it not the word of him who said: ‘Woe unto them that laugh now!’ Did he himself find no cause for laughter on the earth? Then he sought badly. A child even findeth cause for it.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004358": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004358",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004359": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004359",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004360": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004360",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXIV. The Song of Melancholy.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004361": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004361",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>After his address to the higher men, Zarathustra goes out into the open to recover himself. Meanwhile the magician (Wagner), seizing the opportunity in order to draw them all into his net once more, sings the Song of Melancholy.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004362": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004362",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004363": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004363",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004364": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004364",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXV. Science.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004365": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004365",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>The only one to resist the “melancholy voluptuousness” of his art, is the spiritually conscientious one—the scientific specialist of whom we read in the discourse entitled “The Leech”. He takes the harp from the magician and cries for air, while reproving the musician in the style of “The Case of Wagner”. When the magician retaliates by saying that the spiritually conscientious one could have understood little of his song, the latter replies: “Thou praisest me in that thou separatest me from thyself.” The speech of the scientific man to his fellow higher men is well worth studying. By means of it, Nietzsche pays a high tribute to the honesty of the true specialist, while, in representing him as the only one who can resist the demoniacal influence of the magician’s music, he elevates him at a stroke, above all those present. Zarathustra and the spiritually conscientious one join issue at the end on the question of the proper place of “fear” in man’s history, and Nietzsche avails himself of the opportunity in order to restate his views concerning the relation of courage to humanity. It is precisely because courage has played the most important part in our development that he would not see it vanish from among our virtues to-day. “...courage seemeth to me the entire primitive history of man.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004366": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004366",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004367": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004367",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004368": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004368",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXVI. Among the Daughters of the Desert.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004369": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004369",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h3>This tells its own tale.</h3></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004370": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004370",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004371": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004371",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004372": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004372",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXVII. The Awakening.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004373": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004373",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In this discourse, Nietzsche wishes to give his followers a warning. He thinks he has so far helped them that they have become convalescent, that new desires are awakened in them and that new hopes are in their arms and legs. But he mistakes the nature of the change. True, he has helped them, he has given them back what they most need, i.e., belief in believing—the confidence in having confidence in something, but how do they use it? This belief in faith, if one can so express it without seeming tautological, has certainly been restored to them, and in the first flood of their enthusiasm they use it by bowing down and worshipping an ass! When writing this passage, Nietzsche was obviously thinking of the accusations which were levelled at the early Christians by their pagan contemporaries. It is well known that they were supposed not only to be eaters of human flesh but also ass-worshippers, and among the Roman graffiti, the most famous is the one found on the Palatino, showing a man worshipping a cross on which is suspended a figure with the head of an ass (see Minucius Felix, “Octavius” IX.; Tacitus, “Historiae” v. 3; Tertullian, “Apologia”, etc.). Nietzsche’s obvious moral, however, is that great scientists and thinkers, once they have reached the wall encircling scepticism and have thereby learned to recover their confidence in the act of believing, as such, usually manifest the change in their outlook by falling victims to the narrowest and most superstitious of creeds. So much for the introduction of the ass as an object of worship.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004374": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004374",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>Now, with regard to the actual service and Ass-Festival, no reader who happens to be acquainted with the religious history of the Middle Ages will fail to see the allusion here to the asinaria festa which were by no means uncommon in France, Germany, and elsewhere in Europe during the thirteenth, fourteenth, and fifteenth centuries.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004375": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004375",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004376": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004376",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004377": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004377",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXVIII. The Ass-Festival.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004378": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004378",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>At length, in the middle of their feast, Zarathustra bursts in upon them and rebukes them soundly. But he does not do so long; in the Ass-Festival, it suddenly occurs to him, that he is concerned with a ceremony that may not be without its purpose, as something foolish but necessary—a recreation for wise men. He is therefore highly pleased that the higher men have all blossomed forth; they therefore require new festivals,—“A little valiant nonsense, some divine service and ass-festival, some old joyful Zarathustra fool, some blusterer to blow their souls bright.”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004379": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004379",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>He tells them not to forget that night and the ass-festival, for “such things only the convalescent devise! And should ye celebrate it again,” he concludes, “do it from love to yourselves, do it also from love to me! And in remembrance of ME!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004380": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004380",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004381": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004381",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004382": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004382",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXIX. The Drunken Song.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004383": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004383",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>It were the height of presumption to attempt to fix any particular interpretation of my own to the words of this song. With what has gone before, the reader, while reading it as poetry, should be able to seek and find his own meaning in it. The doctrine of the Eternal Recurrence appears for the last time here, in an art-form. Nietzsche lays stress upon the fact that all happiness, all delight, longs for repetitions, and just as a child cries “Again! Again!” to the adult who happens to be amusing him; so the man who sees a meaning, and a joyful meaning, in existence must also cry “Again!” and yet “Again!” to all his life.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004384": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004384",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p><a></a></p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004385": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004385",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><div class=\"c8\"><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br></div></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004386": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004386",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><h2>Chapter LXXX. The Sign.</h2></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004387": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004387",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-9b89d6 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-054be7 twpub-9f0a66bf42729524-6b4cd0\"><p>In this discourse, Nietzsche disassociates himself finally from the higher men, and by the symbol of the lion, wishes to convey to us that he has won over and mastered the best and the most terrible in nature. That great power and tenderness are kin, was already his belief in 1875—eight years before he wrote this speech, and when the birds and the lion come to him, it is because he is the embodiment of the two qualities. All that is terrible and great in nature, the higher men are not yet prepared for; for they retreat horror-stricken into the cave when the lion springs at them; but Zarathustra makes not a move towards them. He was tempted to them on the previous day, he says, but “That hath had its time! My suffering and my fellow suffering,—what matter about them! Do I then strive after HAPPINESS? I strive after my work! Well! the lion hath come, my children are nigh. Zarathustra hath grown ripe. MY day beginneth: ARISE NOW, ARISE, THOU GREAT NOONDAY!”</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004388": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/9f0a66bf42729524/text/000004388",
